        "name" => "The Empress",
        "upright_keyword" => "Sacred Feminine, Sensuality, Fertility, Nurturing, Creativity, Beauty, Abundance, Nature",
        "reversed_keyword" => "Insecurity, Domination, Neglect, Suffocation, Lack of Growth, Lack of Progress",
        "astrology" => "Venus",
        "element" => "Earth Element",
        "image_key" => "03_Empress",
        "content" => "The Empress depicts a woman seated on a throne. From the lush nature surrounding her, we can assume this woman represents the archetype of Mother Earth, a fertility goddess. Her world is ruled by Venus, suggesting complete love, harmony, fertility, and luxury under the grace of this goddess. The woman herself has golden hair adorned with stars, symbolizing her sacred connection to the mystical realms. She wears a pomegranate-patterned robe symbolizing fertility and sits on a cushion embroidered with the symbol of Venus. Surrounding her is a captivating green forest, with rivers flowing through. The Empress brings richness and blessings in readings for those she encounters.",
        "upright_content" => "The Empress shows us our deep connection to the feminine qualities. Feminine qualities may relate to fertility, expression, creativity, and nurturing, among many others. Therefore, it calls upon you to connect with beauty, bringing happiness to your life. Understand yourself and tap into your sensuality so you can attract environments of happiness and joy into your life. She is a signal to treat yourself well and take care of yourself.
The Empress is also a strong sign of pregnancy and motherhood. You may look to other cards to confirm whether this is a literal pregnancy or, more accurately, an attitude of motherhood, nurturing, and care. The Empress card can also signify the birth of new ideas, businesses, or projects in your life. With the good fortune surrounding this card, you can be confident that such situations and endeavors will end successfully in your life. Identify and pursue those ideas that have been persistent in your mind and ensure you dedicate yourself to bringing them to fruition. This card is a sign that they will succeed and will be well nurtured. As an archetype of Mother Earth, the Empress also encourages you to spend time interacting with nature, the mother of us all.",
        "reversed_content" => "Reversed Empress indicates that you have lost too much willpower and strength as you began to put too much effort and care into the affairs of others. While the nature of the Empress is caring and nurturing towards her loved ones, it can sometimes be excessive. You may neglect your own needs, even suffocating those you love with well-intentioned actions.
In a shift of roles, perhaps a reversed Empress is entering your life; this could also represent you relying on others to take care of you and make decisions for you. You need to work on removing this influence on your life and build confidence in your own actions. Always strive as much as possible to ensure you are the one solving problems for yourself.",
        "upright_love" => "The love symbolism of the Empress Tarot comes from the Earth element. The person represented by this card can be loving, nurturing, and affectionate, appreciating economic security or the beauty and comforting aspects of life. Sometimes, the Empress can indicate love blending with work, either with colleagues or in new business ventures.
When it comes to relationships, this card also suggests a stable, serious, and loyal connection. Because this card also represents motherhood, sometimes it can also signify marriage or pregnancy, or at least a new family, whatever that means for you.",
        "reversed_love" => "The reversed Empress in love Tarot can indicate a partner being overly possessive, domineering, unable to express their feelings. This card can also suggest a need for someone to boost their self-worth. If you feel unworthy of love, you may struggle to maintain such a relationship, no matter who you're with.
If you're in a romantic relationship, the Empress of Love Tarot can encourage spending quality time together, caring for each other. Enjoy yourselves by going out on dates or taking walks holding hands. These moments will bring you closer together.",
        "upright_career" => "Your career path may be experiencing an uplift at the moment. You might be feeling more creative and passionate than usual, channeling all your ideas into your projects. As the Empress is associated with nurturing and caretaking, it may also indicate that you're feeling particularly nurturing and generous in the workplace. You might be striving to create a more harmonious, welcoming office environment, whether that means supporting colleagues or giving your home office a fresh coat of paint. Having an environment where you can thrive can certainly provide you with more motivation. Sometimes, this card can also point to another person in your workplace who embodies these qualities.",
        "reversed_career" => "Your career may feel stagnant, dull, and lacking in fulfillment at the moment. You may feel like you're not making much progress in developing your skills and abilities. The work may feel monotonous, or perhaps you've mastered what this position has to offer. You might feel unappreciated by others for the work you're doing, further adding to your sense of frustration. Sometimes, this card may also indicate a lack of security in your career, which may lead to other issues you encounter. Take some time now to figure out which issues need external changes, like changing jobs, and which require internal changes, like cultivating better confidence and communication skills; this is crucial.",
        "upright_finances" => "The Empress is abundant both in creativity and material wealth, so this card can indicate a comfortable financial situation. You might also feel very generous with your money right now, wanting to share your wealth and good fortune with your friends and family. It's certainly a time to share what you have.",
        "reversed_finances" => "Since the Empress is usually a positive card in terms of finances, even in the reversed position, she still signifies financial stability. However, reversed, she might suggest that despite having enough, you may still feel insecure. Sometimes, this may stem from growing up in poverty, or simply the nature of being self-employed. You may need to do some internal work to understand why this is and what you can do to change it. Keep being responsible with your finances, and you're likely to be just fine.",
        "yes_no" => "The Empress represents all things motherly. She's a nurturing, loving problem solver, indicating that successful business ventures or other positive, productive opportunities are on the horizon. She suggests moving forward to unlock your full potential, and the answer you seek is a definite yes.",
        "past" => "The last opportunity you had is proving its influence now. New partnerships, whether in business, personal, or artistic pursuits, require your continued effort to succeed. Remember your most cunning actions, especially your discipline.",
        "present" => "There might be a new beginning unfolding before you, and you get to decide its quality. Stay understanding and particularly sensitive to the emotional aspects of life. Loved ones may need a helping hand or a light in the darkness. Whatever your choices, the role is yours to play.",
        "future" => "Opportunities for healing and respite from emotional and physical traumas will come in the future. It's more beneficial to spend time walking new paths than mending bridges. Your investments will pay off if you tend to them carefully.",

