    4 =>
    [
        "id" => 5,
        "type_id" => 1,
        "number" => 4,
        "name" => "The Emperor",
        "upright_keyword" => "Stability, Structure, Protection, Authority, Control, Practicality, Focus, Discipline",
        "reversed_keyword" => "Tyranny, Domination, Inflexibility, Stubbornness, Lack of Discipline, Rashness",
        "astrology" => "Aries",
        "element" => "Fire Element",
        "image_key" => "04_Emperor",
        "content" => "In the tarot, the Emperor is depicted as a steadfast ruler seated on his throne, adorned with four ram heads representing his astrological sign, Aries. On one hand, he holds a scepter, symbolizing his authority and rule, and on the other, he holds a globe, symbolizing the kingdom he protects. The Emperor's long beard represents his rich experience; over time, he has learned much about ruling, establishing power, authority, and maintaining order for the benefit of his people.

  The Emperor card represents moral laws and regulations, leaning towards order, norms, and stable situations, possessing supreme authority. However, precisely because of these rationality and authority, personal emotions must be suppressed, and there is a metaphor of 'loneliness at the top'.",
        "upright_content" => "For the Emperor, everything revolves around control, as this card signifies authority, supervision, organization, and fatherly love. The Emperor represents a strategic thinker who devises plans he must see through. He is a symbol of the masculine principle in life, embodying structure, rule-making, and systematization, while imparting knowledge. While the Empress desires to create happiness in her kingdom, the Emperor desires to cultivate honor and discipline. He guides with a firm hand, following the call of the crown above all else. Though he is a ruler, he understands that rulership is also service, thus his actions are rational and for the greater good of the kingdom.

  Seeing him in the tarot offers an opportunity for growth in setting goals for yourself. As long as you pursue goals with the same methodical, strategic approach as the Emperor, a successful future will manifest.

  When you see him in the tarot, a possible interpretation is that you may take charge of something significant. It could be a position in work or any organization or institution in urgent need of order and decisive thinking. You may be called upon to take action in place of the Emperor, using his wisdom to clarify projects.",
        "reversed_content" => "The reversed Emperor is a sign of abusing authority. In your social life, it might manifest as a father figure or a domineering partner's excessive expansion of power. In the workplace, it could come from a superior. It presents a man who wants to control your actions and make you feel powerless. It may also be you playing the role of a weak ruler, devising a plan to avoid the tasks of responsibility. Perhaps you long for a more flexible profession than one constrained by strict rules.

  On a personal level, the Emperor can represent a lack of self-discipline and an inability to handle situations. When he is reversed, the structures, rules, and systems he creates no longer work. His desire to spark higher desires for principles in his kingdom has turned into heartlessness, tyranny, and rigidity. He seeks to rule, forgetting the call of the throne to do the best for his people, only concerned with losing control and causing suffering.",
        "upright_love" => "Although the Emperor is a serious figure with no hint of romance, appearing in love tarot still has its benefits. The Emperor tarot card in love demands that we bring common sense, structure, discipline, and logic into relationships and romance. Relationships surrounding this tarot card may be quite traditional and, if mishandled, could be suffocating.

  As a person, the Emperor represents an elder and respected figure who may find it difficult to express their feelings. But sometimes, this card can also symbolize a self-driven individual, domineering and unable to sympathize with others.",
        "reversed_love" => "When it comes to love and relationships, the reversed Emperor tarot card may indicate some power struggles or a fight for dominance. There may be competitiveness and a desire for correctness rather than bringing your different ideas together.

  This card can also suggest a domineering partner, whether it's you or your significant other. Be cautious not to relinquish too much personal power or suppress yourself to become a reality in this relationship. Alternatively, this card may also indicate difficulty in emotional connection in your relationship or potential relationship.",
        "upright_career" => "Due to your hard work, focus, and organized approach, your career may thrive. The Emperor urges you to be disciplined, efficient, and persistent in getting what you want from work or job-seeking. If your office or your workflow is a bit chaotic or frustrating right now, you can step in to introduce new methods or structures to help you and your team collaborate more effectively. This card may also indicate a more senior colleague or boss who can provide support and advice for your career.",
        "reversed_career" => "Without focus or discipline, your work may start to falter. If you've been lacking these qualities in the workplace, you may notice it affecting your projects. Sometimes, this card may also suggest stagnation and bureaucracy in your work environment. This could stifle your creativity and motivation as processes required for anything become dull and frustrating. In the worst case, the reversed Emperor can point to senior employees or bosses ruling the workplace like tyrants. If this is your situation, it's best to start looking for work elsewhere.",
        "upright_finances" => "When it comes to your finances, the Emperor indicates the need for control, discipline, and responsibility with your money. Ensure you have a clear understanding of where your funds are going; establish a budget, make sure to stick to it, and review it every month or so. With perseverance, you may be in good financial shape.",
        "reversed_finances" => "You may feel like your finances are out of control right now. The reversed Emperor can suggest an inability to handle one's finances properly. Sometimes, it may also indicate a lack of discipline in spending. If you fall into the former category, you may need to find a professional who can help you. If the latter applies, you really need to take a close look at your income and expenses and learn to cut back.",
        "yes_no" => "As the counterpart to the Empress, the Emperor represents paternal love over all things. He is the structure, order, and authority in your life. As you move forward, this card indicates decisiveness and rationality will take you far. With that, your answer is affirmative.",
        "past" => "Authority has played a significant role in shaping your life. Your good standing may be due to government or influential individuals. Recent conflicts are likely to be resolved soon.",
        "present" => "At times, someone influential may offer to help you. However, the person coming to your aid may be more capable than you. Protecting those you love is important, but those in leadership positions must know how to compromise. Beware of excessive reliance.",
        "future" => "Taking initiative may bring you closer to your goals, but only if you can be accountable for all your actions. You'll have the opportunity to play one of many roles in life. Remember those who follow in your footsteps.",
    ],
