        "element" => "Earth Element",
        "image_key" => "05_Hierophant",
        "content" => "This card depicts a religious figure seated in a rather formal setting with features reminiscent of a church. He wears three elaborately designed robes, each representing three different worlds. His right hand is raised in a blessing gesture, the same as the one the Magician raises. On the other hand, he carries a triple cross traditionally associated with the Hierophant. Each horizontal bar on the cross is believed to represent the Father, the Son, and the Holy Spirit. Below him, sit two acolytes representing the transfer of sacred knowledge within the institution. Through these followers, this card also represents the path of seeking knowledge and education.

  This card is also known as the High Priest in some decks — as well as the Hierophant. He plays the male counterpart to another card named the 'High Priestess.' This card is ruled by Taurus.",
        "upright_content" => "The Hierophant upright represents support, self-realization, and growth expansion. Whether emotionally or spiritually, now is a good time to develop interpersonal emotional relationships and contemplate philosophical questions, making yourself a more spiritually awakened person. The appearance of the Hierophant card indicates that you have the opportunity to integrate the mind and spirit, elevating your awareness to higher levels. In other words, you can cultivate your talents through continuous learning and heeding good advice.

  The Hierophant card suggests that you would do well to follow established and traditional social structures of your own. For example, you may engage in certain rituals, ceremonies, or other religious rites. In terms of tarot cards, this special card most commonly represents institutions and their core values. It is a sign that you need to adhere to existing rules and situations.",
        "reversed_content" => "When you see the Hierophant reversed, it may indicate that you feel particularly restricted, even by too much structure and rules. As a result, you've lost a lot of control and flexibility in life. You have a strong will and desire to move forward, regain control, and break free from traditional constraints. You're eager to try unconventional methods or operate in a way that goes against social norms and conventions.

  The reversed Hierophant mainly signifies questioning certain traditions and ensuring that what you're doing is right for this particular moment.",
        "upright_love" => "When it comes to interpreting relationship tarot cards, the upright meaning of the Hierophant can point to the influence of traditional religion on love and partner selection. You may be attracted to a partner who is safe, traditional, and respected by the community, avoiding couples seen as 'taboo.' The sacred love in tarot can also represent more spiritual aspects of love, reminding us to treat our partners with morality and compassion. Sometimes, this card can also symbolize marriage.

  Relationships influenced by the Hierophant card are typically traditional, conventional, and socially accepted. Couples may share a belief system.",
        "reversed_love" => "The reversed Hierophant may indicate that your relationship may become rather stale or dull. You may have entered into this relationship, but without injecting some extra excitement, it can feel mundane. When it comes to shared values and creating a future together, the reversed Hierophant may suggest that your views may not quite align with your own. This isn't necessarily a bad thing, but it may require some compromise.

  Generally, this card also indicates that not all advice you receive about your romantic relationship at this time may be helpful to you. It's best to think for yourself what works best for your love life rather than relying on others to tell you what's right for you.",
        "upright_career" => "With the Hierophant, you may find success in your career through collaboration with others. This sometimes means making choices that are not wavering and staying on established, proven paths. With so many variables in work, it's best to stay secure for now. This card can also indicate that cohesion within the team is more important than individuality at this time. Sometimes the Hierophant can also signify a more senior mentor who can help you progress in your career. This card is also representative of education, suggesting that a period of learning, whether through school or vocational training, will be beneficial for you.",
        "reversed_career" => "Your creativity, achievements, or autonomy in the workplace may now be stifled by bureaucracy, processes, or rules. You may feel restricted and constrained. If you have ideas, you may have been able to solve many of the problems in your organization, but they may insist on doing things 'their way'. Sometimes this may mean having to toe the line with colleagues or even bosses in order to get tasks done. Even if you have differing opinions, there may be significant pressure to follow the organization's decisions. Weigh the risks of going your own way; can you stay true to where you are currently?",
        "upright_finances" => "When it comes to your finances, the Hierophant advises you to keep your funds in traditional, established institutions. Novel ways of making money, whether it's a side hustle you're not quite familiar with or new financial products, could spell trouble for you; avoid gambling with your money.",
        "reversed_finances" => "At this time, financial advice from your peers may feel suffocating. You may be eager to take risks and try new ways of making money, whether that means engaging in a side hustle in your spare time or learning about cryptocurrency. Remain responsible and rational about what risks you're willing to take and what you're willing to lose.",
        "yes_no" => "The Hierophant is a symbol of education and tradition. This card suggests seeking spiritual guidance or advice in your life. It also indicates conformity and religious approval, with neither a positive nor negative implication. The only answer is maybe.",
        "past" => "Your past aspirations have been valuable. Look for a strength you may have overlooked.",
        "present" => "Opportunities to work under or learn from authority figures are imminent. If those around you have the capacity to make mistakes, so do you.",
        "future" => "Seek support from stable organizations or structured principles to succeed. Your actions should be motivated by self-interest, or they will yield little reward.",
    ],
    6 =>
    [
        "id" => 7,
        "type_id" => 1,
        "number" => 6,
        "name" => "The Lovers",
        "upright_keyword" => "Love, Union, Partnership, Relationships, Choices, Romance, Balance, Unity",
        "reversed_keyword" => "Disunity, Imbalance, Conflict, Detachment, Poor choices, Indecision",
        "astrology" => "Gemini",
        "element" => "Air Element",
        "image_key" => "06_Lovers",
        "content" => "In the Lovers card, the figures of a man and a woman are protected and blessed by an angel above. The couple appears secure and happy in their home, reminiscent of Eden. The tree with the serpent behind the woman is a reference to that story, depicting humanity's fall into temptation and carnality. The angel depicted here is the Air angel Raphael - who shares the same element as the constellation ruling this card: Gemini. Air is associated with mental activity, particularly communication, which is foundational to healthy relationships. His blessing seems to impart a sense of balance and harmony to this card, symbolizing the union of two opposing forces on a grand and cosmic scale.",
        "upright_content" => "The primary significance of the Lovers is harmony, attraction, and perfection in relationships. The trust and unity between lovers give each of them confidence and strength, empowering one another. The bond they've formed is so strong, indicating that they are married and involved in other intimate and close relationships. Another meaning behind the Lovers is the concept of choice - choosing between opposites and exclusives. It could be a dilemma where you need to carefully consider and make the best decision for your situation. The more personalized meaning applicable to individuals involves developing your own belief system, regardless of societal norms. We see it as the development of a sacred doctrine, where one formulates laws and passes on their knowledge through standardized systems. It's a time when you're figuring out what you stand for and what your life philosophy will be. You must start deciding what you deem important and what isn't. You should be as truthful to yourself as possible, so you can be genuine and authentic to those around you.",
        "reversed_content" => "The reversed Lovers can indicate internal and external conflicts you're dealing with. Disunity can make daily life challenging and may put strain on your relationships. You should take time to think about what you're punishing yourself for, so you can either address or let go of them. At this time, you should also consider your personal values and belief systems to ensure they align with the life you want. Communication breakdown could be another possible interpretation. The foundation of your interpersonal relationships may be severed, causing imbalance between you and your partner or loved ones. The unity often present in the card has become imbalanced. The reversed Lovers can also suggest that you've been avoiding taking responsibility for your actions. You could have made decisions based on your desires at the moment, but now you're attributing the consequences catching up to you to others. So, you need to make amends or let go of the past and make better decisions for the future.",
        "upright_love" => "When it comes to love and relationships, the Lovers card is a welcomed sight for any seeker. The tarot card symbolizes wonderful cohesion and strength balance, indicating complementary energies. It represents a pair that can work well together. On the other hand, because the card also symbolizes choices and commitment, it raises questions about your level of commitment to love. This doesn't have to specifically point to another person, but can also indicate choosing between love and work, love and family, love and friendships, or sometimes love and your entire lifestyle. The idea here is that to have this kind of love, you might have to make sacrifices. In some ways, all commitments are a form of sacrifice, but commitments made for the right person can help you grow as an individual.",
        "reversed_love" => "The reversed Lovers in a love relationship or romance tarot card can suggest indifference in your relationship. What used to work in balance no longer does. Some issues may be hindering your relationship and need to be addressed to rebuild a closer connection. Sometimes, it may also show a fear of commitment. It could be when you have many suitors, or your dating life may be very active. While initially this might be fun, you might feel there are too many choices, or you have to give up too many possibilities to develop a romantic relationship. This might require some introspection; make sure you're honest with yourself about your fears and desires.",
        "upright_career" => "Sometimes, the Lovers can indicate business partnerships or establishing harmonious and mutually beneficial relationships with colleagues. The Lovers card can also symbolize platonic friendships, although sometimes, it can also indicate romantic relationships that can blossom. If indeed the latter is the case, make sure you understand the types of risks you're facing and make decisions with both your head and heart. The Lovers tarot card can also suggest significant decisions you'll need to make in your future career. You might be at a crossroads, or transitioning from one path to another, or you might need to make choices between work and other aspects of life.",
        "reversed_career" => "When the Lovers are reversed, conflicts may arise among your colleagues or business partners. Lengthy discussions may be needed to reach a decision acceptable to everyone. Or it could be one person doing all the work, or having to carry teammates who've lost all motivation. Both colleagues could be hindered because of one person's inability to fairly distribute the workload. Sometimes, this card does indeed indicate the start of a romantic relationship in your workplace, but in reverse, this could spell trouble for you. If you continue down this path, consequences you hadn't foreseen might arise.",
        "upright_finances" => "Financially, the Lovers card can indicate the need to make significant financial decisions. You might have to choose between one significant expenditure and another; the crucial point to remember is that you seem unable to have both at the same time. Your choices may have larger implications in the future.",
        "reversed_finances" => "Your current financial choices might be quite impulsive, meaning your long-term financial security could be threatened. Are you making responsible choices, or seeking immediate gratification? Make sure you understand what you truly can afford financially.",
        "yes_no" => "The Lovers reveal you're at a crossroads in life. While this card is highly symbolic of interpersonal relationships, love, and unity, it could also indicate positive business partnerships or collaborations moving forward. The answer to your question is affirmative.",
        "past" => "You've been more capable of connecting with others. Emotional burdens from recent conflicts will soon be relieved and successfully resolved.",
        "present" => "An upcoming conflict will test your values. To move forward, you'll have to make decisions between love and career. Neither will disappear forever, but the choice will determine your priorities.",
        "future" => "In the future, both of you will have separate lives, with new choices to be made.",
    ],
    7 =>
    [
        "id" => 8,
        "type_id" => 1,
        "number" => 7,
        "name" => "The Chariot",
        "upright_keyword" => "Efficiency, Seizing Opportunities, Success, Ambition, Determination, Willpower, Control, Self-discipline, Focus",
        "reversed_keyword" => "Loss of Control, Accidents, Failure, Lack of Direction, Lack of Control, Stubbornness, Aggression, Obstacles",
        "astrology" => "Cancer",
        "element" => "Water Element",
        "image_key" => "07_Chariot",
        "content" => "The Chariot tarot card depicts a figure seated inside a chariot driven by two sphinxes, one black and one white. The figure sits under a canopy adorned with white stars. On his shoulder, he carries the symbol of the crescent moon, representing the spiritual influences he's under. Crowned, symbolizing enlightenment, purity of will. A square on his chest represents the elements of earth and the material world, the foundation of him and his actions.
    The sphinxes are painted black and white, symbolizing the opposing forces the charioteer must learn to control. Here, they are calm, but often at odds due to their apparent desire to move in different directions, leading to a struggle. His task is to guide these sphinxes toward a destination, one marked by the universal forces he represents. The Chariot is associated with the Cancer zodiac sign.",
        "upright_content" => "The Chariot tarot card signifies overcoming challenges and achieving victory by maintaining control over one's surroundings. This perfect control and confidence enable the charioteer to triumph in any situation. The use of strength and willpower is crucial to ensure you overcome obstacles on the road. The message conveyed by the Chariot will make you stronger as you strive to achieve your goals.
    He brings you the key message that you must remain focused, confident, and determined amid twists and turns. If you have a seemingly uncertain plan or project, the Chariot suggests that you execute it in a structured and orderly manner. Your boldness will ensure you achieve everything expected of you in this endeavor.
    In the pursuit of goals with the Chariot, he may exhibit behaviors he has never seen in himself before—competition and a desire for success may make his character more aggressive. Aggression is a natural part of human nature, and the Chariot reminds you that it can also be used to help you control your situation, but it must also be controlled to avoid hindering your path forward.",
        "reversed_content" => "The appearance of the reversed Chariot can help you realize a lack of aggression and willpower. This may indicate a lack of focus, motivation, or direction, or you may be distorted by your obsession with your goals. In the former case, let the Chariot remind you that you can achieve victory as long as you have the courage. In the latter, your impulsiveness may be another factor you need to control. Seeing the reversed Chariot may indicate that you need to accept the fact that you cannot always be in control.
    The reversed meaning of the Chariot may also suggest a lack of control and direction in life. You are at the mercy of opposing forces and obstacles, seemingly unable to muster the strength to take charge. You are letting go of everything, and life is moving in any direction it pleases. It should serve as a wake-up call, reminding you to tighten some loose ends and take control of your destiny.",
        "upright_love" => "Now is the time to start and ensure you clearly understand what you are looking for in love and romance. Once you know your destination, the meaning of the Chariot tarot card in love will urge you to take action. When you take control of your love life, you are likely to see rewards. Confidence, courage, and motivation will lead to success.
    As you move towards your goals, the Chariot tarot card in love may also indicate the need to balance two impulses, represented by the two horses in the card. They may pull you in different directions, but a clear path ahead means controlling everyone to keep you on the right track. This card sometimes brings up questions about whether your choices so far have been balanced; is your relationship affected by too much work time? Have you focused so much on your relationship that you've sacrificed too much of your individuality? The Chariot demands that we once again take life into our own hands and steer firmly.",
        "reversed_love" => "When reversed, the meaning of the Chariot tarot card in love may suggest an overwhelming drive to find love, to the extent that other goals and desires may have been forgotten. Sometimes, it's important to remember that in life, we can't control everything around us, and no matter what we do, we can't make the perfect person appear before us. Showing up every day with hope and enthusiasm is important, but patience is also important. Let love find you.
    The reversed Chariot in love may also indicate that things may be out of balance, and you may need to make efforts again to correct them. Ensure that your work, love, family, and friendships are not affected by your overextension in one area or another. This may be the root of disagreements with your partner.",
        "upright_career" => "When you have the Chariot inquiring about your career tarot, your ambition will take you further. With a clear understanding of your career goals, you'll know your objectives and can be extremely focused on achieving them. You may feel very driven in your work, which will bring you the discipline, motivation, and self-control needed for success. If you're looking to change roles or secure a higher position in your current workplace, this card indicates that all you need to do is go for it. When it comes to your work environment, don't get distracted; this may include office politics or competitors; ensure you stay focused on what needs to be done.",
        "reversed_career" => "The reversed Chariot may indicate a lack of ambition, focus, or motivation, or being too ambitious. Ultimately, this card raises questions about how aggressive or radical you are in pursuing goals. Are you the passive type waiting for things to happen as you hope they fall into your lap? Or are you too forceful to the point of disregarding others in the pursuit of success? Both approaches can get you into trouble. Being pushy to the point of hostility may backfire, while being overly passive will never bring you the happiness you desire. Are you satisfied with either of these options? What does a healthy middle ground look like?",
        "upright_finances" => "If any financial obstacles are hindering your material stability, now is the time to address them. The Chariot provides you with the drive, focus, and determination to overcome these challenges. With enough self-discipline, you'll be able to feel satisfied with your financial situation.",
        "reversed_finances" => "Be careful not to rush into purchases without careful consideration. You may lack all the knowledge needed to make wise decisions. Or if that doesn't describe you, then you may be hesitant about money matters. You may have the opportunity to invest your money in something, but you've been hesitating to take any action.",
        "yes_no" => "The Chariot reveals some sort of journey. With its positive connotations, this journey is likely some form of progression. It may also be the ultimate success you've been striving for. The confidence, direction, and victory indicated by this card suggest the answer is yes.",
        "past" => "The struggles have strengthened your resolve, and recent events have given you the opportunity to achieve victory.",
        "present" => "Good news is coming; you will overcome adversaries in decisive victory.",
        "future" => "Keep up your efforts, and the goals you seek will be realized. If you don't give up, honor, praise, and recognition are all possible outcomes for you.",
    ],
    8 =>
    [
        "id" => 9,
        "type_id" => 1,
        "number" => 8,
        "name" => "Strength",
        "upright_keyword" => "Courage, Bravery, Confidence, Compassion, Self-assurance, Inner strength",
        "reversed_keyword" => "Self-doubt, Weakness, Low confidence, Inadequacy, Timidity, Stubbornness",
        "astrology" => "Leo",
        "element" => "Fire element",
        "image_key" => "08_Strength",
        "content" => "In this tarot card, you will see a woman calmly holding the chin of a fully grown lion. Despite the lion appearing fierce and strong, the woman seems to have dominion over it. Fascinating is how she gracefully controls the lion. She is calm and composed, representing control and discipline, especially in adversity.

  She also holds the lion's chin, which also signifies her courage. Her control over the lion is not overly forceful, showing love and compassion. The blue background of the mountains depicts stability and the tranquility brought by stability.

  The lion symbolizes courage, passion, and desire, important components of human survival. However, if these emotions are not controlled, they can lead to our ultimate downfall.",
        "upright_content" => "When you receive the Strength card upright in a tarot reading, it indicates that you have inner strength and resilience during times of danger and distress. It suggests that even when your life is undergoing tremendous struggles, you have the ability to remain calm and strong. It also indicates that you are a compassionate person, always finding time to serve others even if it requires sacrifice.

  Getting the Strength card means you are a very patient person, likely to accomplish whatever you set your mind to. Your resilience will greatly assist you, and your fearlessness means you should have no trouble speaking your mind. This card also foretells that this compassion will be repaid, either now or in the near future, and your life will be very stable.",
        "reversed_content" => "A reversed Strength card may indicate that you are experiencing (or are about to experience) intense anger or fear in your life. You seem to lack the inner strength typically represented by this card, which suggests you may be experiencing fear and lack belief and confidence in your abilities. This could mean you've forgotten your passion and the happiness, joy, and fulfillment that comes from doing what you love.

  Reversed Strength card may also indicate someone is experiencing depression for various reasons, thus draining all joy from their life.

  Ultimately, a person may withdraw from society due to unhappiness or feeling miserable because people seem to be the reason for their sadness. It could also be a manifestation of jealousy, especially when everyone seems to be happy or excelling in various aspects of life while you're stagnant. This card suggests you need to learn to gain confidence to harness your inner strength.",
        "upright_love" => "When you draw the Strength card in a love tarot reading, you may find yourself in the midst of passionate and fiery romance. The strong emotions implied by this card can signify either solid relationships or relationships prone to anger, jealousy, or other emotional outbursts. This type of relationship has both advantages and disadvantages. Alternatively, the love meaning of the Strength tarot card is one of compassion, empathy, and inner strength; you may find these qualities attracting the partner you need or making you closer than ever with an existing partner. Empathy allows you to understand your and your partner's needs and insecurities more deeply. If you find yourself in arguments or intense moments, it's best to treat each other with patience and gentleness.",
        "reversed_love" => "In love tarot readings, when Strength is reversed, this card may indicate that your relationship is somewhat codependent. This may stem from some form of insecurity that makes it difficult for you and your partner to be more independent and pursue your own interests. Again, you yourself lack confidence in this relationship, you lack confidence in walking steadily with him, and your heart is also erratic, so naturally, the difficulty of stabilizing your relationship is also greater. The reversed Strength tarot card love meaning may also suggest that strength and power become more apparent in your relationship. One partner may become increasingly domineering rather than sympathetic and understanding. You may have to ensure one partner's needs aren't trampled upon to support the needs of the other partner.",
        "upright_career" => "If you can harness your animal instincts—your anger, your drive, and your passion—you can take a significant step forward in your career. This doesn't mean letting these instincts take over but rather working with them or channeling them productively. Here, you will be able to find your strength; this card suggests you likely already possess the talent and ability; you just need to muster the courage to make a big move. If you're seeking opportunities for advancement, do something to get noticed. If you want to change your entire career trajectory, boldly go for it. If you dream of starting your own business, push yourself to take the next steps, and then start.",
        "reversed_career" => "Is your fear hindering your career aspirations? The reversed Strength card suggests you may have everything it takes to succeed, except for healthy confidence and belief in yourself. You may continuously self-doubt, allowing your anxiety and self-doubt to dominate and prevent you from making choices that could propel your career forward. If you truly examine yourself, you'll find you're more capable than you imagine. Believe in your abilities, and others will believe in you.",
        "upright_finances" => "If you've been doing well in controlling impulsive spending, you're likely to find yourself in a comfortable position now. As long as you keep control, you should be fine. You may also be ready to make bold moves in purchasing; perhaps putting your finances into something you've always dreamed of.",
        "reversed_finances" => "Avoid compulsive spending now, as it could do more damage to your financial situation than usual. Alternatively, this card can also suggest hesitancy in spending money on things that would benefit you now, even if you may have enough funds. There will be a sense of financial insecurity regardless of your actual situation.",
        "yes_no" => "The Strength card shows facing life's challenges with confidence and self-assurance. It indicates a person in power but with the ability to exercise strong self-control in all matters. Your pursuits may require patience and strength, and the answer you seek is likely affirmative.",
        "past" => "Your strength has been balanced, both physically and mentally. This inner strength may have guided you to explore other potentialities of your abilities.",
        "present" => "Do not refuse any propositions that could alter your future. Have faith in your beliefs and have enough strength to believe where you will land.",
        "future" => "There's a powerful, vibrant release in your future that will lead you to significant life changes. By understanding your true value, you will seize this excellent opportunity to improve your life.",
    ],
    9 =>
    [
        "id" => 10,
        "type_id" => 1,
        "number" => 9,
        "name" => "The Hermit",
        "upright_keyword" => "Self-reflection, Introspection, Contemplation, Withdrawal, Solitude, Self-discovery",
        "reversed_keyword" => "Loneliness, Isolation, Seclusion, Antisocial behavior, Rejection, Reintegration into society",
        "astrology" => "Virgo",
        "element" => "Earth Element",
        "image_key" => "09_Hermit",
        "content" => "The Hermit depicts an elderly man standing alone on a mountaintop, holding a lantern in one hand and a staff in the other. The mountain represents achievement, development, and success. The Hermit tarot card refers to the level of spiritual knowledge he has attained, and he is prepared to impart this knowledge to everyone. He also has a firm commitment to his goals and a profound understanding of the path he is walking. Inside the lantern, you will notice a six-pointed star, also known as the Seal of Solomon. This symbol represents wisdom. The staff he holds symbolizes authority and power.",
        "upright_content" => "The Hermit is a seeker of inner knowledge. A solitary wanderer on the dark paths of the night, he seeks something that can only be gained through prolonged solitude—the voice of the inner self. To hear it, he must disconnect from the crowd of voices and desires threatening to overwhelm him. He traverses the unconscious dark night with only the faint light of the North Star to guide him, his destination being his home, his self.

  You are currently contemplating the need for solitude. Never be afraid to seize this opportunity for reflection, as it can help clear away all the clutter of daily life. The Hermit may also indicate your efforts to take authentic action and stay true to your true self. You may be seeking inner guidance to find the right direction and goals for the next step.

  The appearance of the Hermit in the tarot cards may also indicate the arrival of someone in your life who will become your mentor.",
        "reversed_content" => "When reversed, you may find yourself in a situation where you want to be alone, and that's okay. However, your seclusion may be detrimental to both yourself and others. While the Hermit sets out with lofty aspirations to seek the truth within, the path to his inner self may also be fraught with great danger. Going inward can lead to madness and abyss, as the unconscious is filled with images he may not yet understand, lurking to tempt him in. Like one lost in their own dreams, the Hermit may find himself trapped in his own world, lonely, trapped, unreal. You must learn to balance your need for truth with connections to your fellow human beings.

  In terms of work, the reversed Hermit suggests that you are ready to delve deeper into something that has been troubling you for a long time. Searches need to be conducted, and you have a responsibility to ask questions and make others aware of the situation.",
        "upright_love" => "Love, as one of life's greatest mysteries, can be a great teacher. It requires all of us to truly understand ourselves, our needs, our fears, and our insecurities. The love meaning of the Hermit tarot card suggests that before establishing a solid romantic relationship with another person, we may need some time alone to gain some understanding of ourselves. This period may feel a bit lonely, but it will set you on the right path to find the love you desire. If you are already in a romantic relationship, this introspection is something both of you might want to do together. You both may want to consider what you expect from a relationship and what will make you happier. The initial conversations may be uncomfortable, but they will lay a solid foundation for addressing future issues.",
        "reversed_love" => "The reversed Hermit tarot card love meaning can indicate a period of loneliness, one that is imposed upon you rather than initiated by yourself. While this time may be challenging, making the most of it can help you focus on your goals and clarify what you want from a partner and life. These will be the cornerstones of building a strong future relationship. If you are already in a romantic relationship, you may find that one of you feels distant and is gradually withdrawing. Despite efforts from both parties, someone may feel lonely in the partnership. Now is the time to examine these dynamics and see if there are ways you can reach out. It may require attention, care, and a strong sense of self-awareness to feel connected again.",
        "upright_career" => "You may be spending some much-needed time contemplating what you truly want from your career right now. You may feel that the path you are currently on is not truly fulfilling for you, and there may be a sense of dissatisfaction. Now, you are trying to understand what kind of work would bring you happiness on various levels. If you are purely in it for money or financial stability, then those qualifications may no longer be enough for you. You may be seeking a purpose, or at least something that brings you closer to the person you want to become.",
        "reversed_career" => "Sometimes, the reversed Hermit can signal the end of a period of contemplation. You may be ready to reintegrate into society, this time with a clearer understanding of what you want from your career. Adjustments may now be needed, whether it's searching for a new job, networking to find mentors and allies, or developing other social aspects of your career. On the other hand, it could also mean that your period of solitude could be further extended; you may choose to avoid collaboration with others altogether. Initially, the feeling of being alone may be much less; but make sure you continue to receive social support. Sometimes, this card may also indicate being forced to work alone, leading to feelings of loneliness, or being abandoned by colleagues.",
        "upright_finances" => "You may now realize that money cannot bring you happiness. This may be a time of less focus on material things and more on trying to understand where you can truly find fulfillment.",
        "reversed_finances" => "When it comes to financial decisions, you may be ready to seek advice from external sources. Ideally, you have finished contemplating what material security and money mean to you, and you may be putting these insights into practice. Hopefully, this can establish a better relationship with your material circumstances.",
        "yes_no" => "The Hermit is a card symbolizing seeking some form of spiritual enlightenment. Solitary introspection and contemplation are also associated with the Hermit. Perhaps you need to do some introspection and reflection. Therefore, the answer to your question is possible.",
        "past" => "Your past strides have slowed down, and it's time to accept that. Continue to seek your future goals and consider the insights you've gained recently.",
        "present" => "Someone may be able to help you solve all your problems, and their insights may surprise you. That person is yourself. Understand yourself to better understand others.",
        "future" => "When you realize your true essence, nothing can stop your path. Life has challenged you, but you are ready to face the future.",
    ],
    10 =>
    [
        "id" => 11,
        "type_id" => 1,
        "number" => 10,
        "name" => "Wheel of Fortune",
        "upright_keyword" => "Change, Cycles, Destiny, Pivotal moments, Luck, Fortune, Unexpected events",
        "reversed_keyword" => "Bad luck, Lack of control, Fixating on control, uUnwelcome changes, Delays",
        "astrology" => "Jupiter",
        "element" => "Fire Element",
        "image_key" => "10_Wheel_of_Fortune",
        "content" => "The Wheel of Fortune is one of the most symbolically rich cards in the deck, filled with meanings for each of its components. In the center of the card, there is a large wheel covered with intricate symbols. Surrounding the wheel are various creatures: an angel, an eagle, a bull, and a lion. These are associated with the four fixed signs of the Zodiac – Leo, Taurus, Scorpio, and Aquarius. These four animals also represent the four Gospel writers in Christian tradition, perhaps explaining their adorned wings.

    Each creature holds a book, representing the Torah that communicates wisdom and self-understanding. The serpent signifies the descent into the material world. Riding atop the wheel itself is a sphinx-like figure seated at the top, while what appears to be a devil, or perhaps Anubis himself, appears at the bottom. These two Egyptian figures represent the wisdom of the gods and kings (in the case of the sphinx) and the underworld (Anubis). They forever revolve in a cycle, indicating that as one rises, another falls.",
        "upright_content" => "The Wheel of Fortune keeps turning, seeming to convey that life consists of both good and bad, and cycles are beyond our control. It's something that both kings and laborers are subject to, and no one on Earth can avoid what is destined to happen. When you encounter moments of joy in life, make sure to savor them fully, as what goes up must come down. Similarly, when you find yourself in dire straits, things will eventually turn for the better.

    There's a powerful force at play here that humans cannot control. The same force that governs the changing of the seasons or the rising and setting of the sun also governs luck and individual destiny. Its landing is as random as chance – you might find yourself at the top or the bottom, but remember, whatever the outcome, it may not last long, as the wheel is always turning.",
        "reversed_content" => "When the Wheel of Fortune is reversed, it signifies that luck isn't on your side, and misfortune is following you. When associated with this card, you must understand that these are due to external influences beyond your control. Like the wheel, our luck and destiny are always in motion, and sometimes we find ourselves at the bottom. Rest assured, the wheel will turn again, and you'll soon be back on top.

    However, what you shouldn't do is cling to the illusion of control. Perhaps the lesson in this cycle is to learn to let go and surrender. Some things cannot be propelled by human will and action alone. When we fail to let go, it only brings more suffering, as you may blame yourself for actions that couldn't change the circumstances. When we learn to accept, we also learn to forgive ourselves. We learn to move forward and continue – ultimately, understanding that this acceptance can once again propel the wheel forward and into a new cycle.",
        "upright_love" => "Life is full of unexpected changes, and love is no exception. The Wheel of Fortune tarot card in love can indicate significant changes in your relationship, perhaps changes you didn't foresee. These need not necessarily be bad things but may require adjustments. Commitment to your partner might be tested now, and both of you may need to put in some effort or sacrifice to stay together. If you choose to make the effort, your partnership might become closer than ever, as both of you learn to navigate life's ups and downs as a team. It's important to understand whether these changes are positive or negative; they're not permanent, as the wheel is always turning.",
        "reversed_love" => "Sometimes, no matter how hard we try, the world won't bend to one's will. Life may throw unexpected wrenches into your plans, and besides remembering that this too shall pass, you're powerless. It's likely that some external factors are now affecting your interpersonal relationships, and you may have to adapt to them, patiently accepting them rather than attempting to control the situation. Other aspects of your life might demand high stakes now, as your romantic life may need to take a back seat for a while. If you're partners, try to address these issues as a team and communicate openly.",
        "upright_career" => "Major changes may be happening in your career. If you're considering changing career paths or positions, now might be a good time to make those moves. Try to explore and understand more about the opportunities in your current environment and seize them when they arise. Sometimes, upcoming changes may be difficult and challenging, but these can actually prepare you for future growth by developing skills. Embrace these changes and adapt yourself. Going with the flow of these changes might lead you to success.",
        "reversed_career" => "Is your work life changing rapidly? You might find it challenging to keep up with things currently. All these surprises could be disrupting your plans. You might continue trying to make past solutions work rather than keeping pace with what's happening now. It's important not to cling to the past or your expectations but to remain flexible and ready to change your plans. Are your responsibilities at work changing? Are the demands of your projects constantly evolving? This could be very frustrating, but instead of resisting, try to find your way through. It's important to ensure you find your center.",
        "upright_finances" => "When it comes to your finances, the Wheel of Fortune also suggests changes, so be prepared to adapt to whatever happens. If you've been financially comfortable, make sure you continue to set aside a certain amount of money for rainy days. If you've been dealing with material difficulties, rest assured, this won't last forever. Keep your eyes open for any opportunities that come your way.",
        "reversed_finances" => "Be cautious with risks when it comes to your finances, as this card may indicate unexpected and unwelcome events. It might be wise to establish a small emergency fund now; even if nothing happens, having something tucked away can help alleviate anxiety about what might come next. The world is constantly changing, so make sure you're prepared.",
        "yes_no" => "The Wheel of Fortune represents luck, change, and new directions in life. While it also shows ups and downs, the overall feeling of this card is positive, indicating changes in luck and fortune. The answer you're seeking is affirmative.",
        "past" => "Your past actions are the seeds of your future success. To make progress, you must accept the changes that are coming.",
        "present" => "A beneficial change is on the horizon, but remember, luck is beyond control.",
        "future" => "Opportunities for change towards personal growth and happiness are ahead in the future. You must be prepared to change your mindset as your actions, whether successful or not, represent beneficial changes.",
    ],
    11 =>
    [
        "id" => 12,
        "type_id" => 1,
        "number" => 11,
        "name" => "Justice",
        "upright_keyword" => "Justice, Fairness, Consequences, Responsibility, Law, Truth, Honesty, Integrity, cause and effect",
        "reversed_keyword" => "Injustice, Retaliation, Dishonesty, Corruption, Insincerity, Unfairness, Evasion of responsibility",
        "astrology" => "Libra",
        "element" => "Air Element",
        "image_key" => "11_Justice",
        "content" => "The Justice tarot card symbolizes truth, fairness, and the law. When she sits on her throne, the scales in her left hand represent how intuition should balance logic. She wields a double-edged sword in her right hand, symbolizing justice. The square on her crown symbolizes the clear thinking needed to administer justice. Behind her, there's a purple cloak and a standing gray pillar. Beneath her red cloak fastened with buttons, she reveals a white shoe tip. This is a spiritual reminder that she offers the consequences of their actions.",
        "upright_content" => "The decisions you make now have long-term effects on both yourself and others. There will always be a time for judgment. The presence of the Justice tarot card in a reading indicates making judgments with fairness and corresponding consequences. Your past decisions will be carefully weighed with fairness. Depending on your circumstances, your interpretation of this card may vary.

        If you've been wronged, the appearance of this card might bring you relief. On the other hand, if your actions have caused pain to others, this card serves as a warning. Her appearance represents an opportunity for you to change your behavior now for a better future. When the Justice card appears in a tarot reading, it's time to account for your actions.

        Another meaning of the Justice card is truth. Truth must prevail, not from gossip but from facts. Understand the truth of others and yourself, speak it out before making judgments, and understand the truth. When you see the Justice tarot card, you need to treat all your actions fairly. By following the correct procedures to understand the truth, you will understand what your task is.

        Another interpretation of interpreting the Justice tarot card is a symbol of attention. It may be related to your life, career, or just important decisions you need to make. If you're unsure about something, now is the time to find a solution once and for all.",
        "reversed_content" => "The reversed Justice tarot card can indicate various things. One meaning of a reversed Justice is that it suggests you're living in denial. You're unwilling to accept your actions or the consequences of others. You're avoiding your guilt. However, you must realize that these are all past behaviors. Your future depends on your actions today - and how you'll rebalance the scales. How will you make up for your mistakes? Take action to give yourself the chance to change and stop judging yourself. In legal matters, this could represent the unfair outcome of a case that you won't accept.",
        "upright_love" => "Justice is about karma; if you've been putting in effort, love and romance will come as promised. If you've been kind, loving, and supportive, your relationships will mirror back what you give to others. If you've been single, your loving and positive nature will make you particularly attractive to new potential romances.

        Because this card is about the law of cause and effect, make sure you always treat your partner fairly. Beware of resentment and defensiveness, and make sure to handle conflicts in relationships with respect and trust. Compromise and understanding are needed now. Sometimes, this card is also about wit, expressing your frustrations in a way that considers your partner's feelings. As long as you handle issues honestly and kindly, your relationship will thrive.",
        "reversed_love" => "Sometimes, love and romance can be unfair. You may be exerting your share of effort to push yourself into the world, but luck isn't on your side. Whatever the situation, sometimes you must grit your teeth and keep moving forward. Now might also be a good time to examine if your expectations of love are fair. Are you looking for a perfect person but unwilling or unable to compensate for your own shortcomings? Be honest about your demands and your baggage. If you're in a relationship, this might be a challenging period, requiring more than ever fairness and compromise. Don't blame others or your partner for your responsibilities.",
        "upright_career" => "If you're involved in any workplace disputes, the Justice card can indicate that as long as you conduct yourself with honesty, integrity, and fairness, everything will work in your favor. If this doesn't apply to you, this card can simply serve as a reminder to always act with integrity and ensure you're accountable for your actions, even if you make mistakes. While it can be daunting at times, others will trust and respect you for your honesty and commitment to the truth. Through fair and balanced dealings, your career can thrive.",
        "reversed_career" => "You may be dealing with some unfair situations in your career right now. This could mean taking responsibility for others or for those trying to undermine the quality of your work. While fighting fire with fire may be tempting, it will only escalate the problem. Keep reasonable, logical, and straightforward in how you handle the situation. With Justice reversed, you may find that intense confrontation may mean the responsibility falls on you. Sometimes, this card may also indicate that you haven't been honest enough in your career. This could get you into trouble; or even if it doesn't, it can lead to ongoing anxiety as you wonder when the other shoe will drop. If you still have time, now is the time to make amends and change your habits. If you've been avoiding taking responsibility for mistakes and hoping to blame others, ",
        "upright_finances" => "This card reminds you to maintain honesty, fairness, and equity in financial transactions. Ensure you strike a balance between the needs of others and what you receive versus what you give. Keep balance going, and your finances should be fine.",
        "reversed_finances" => "When the Justice card appears reversed in your tarot spread, there's some dishonesty in your financial situation. Be cautious about sharing your financial information with others and ensure they can be trusted before proceeding. If your financial situation has been consistently difficult, the reversed Justice card may also indicate that you haven't been accountable for your own circumstances. Taking responsibility for difficult situations may sound unpleasant, but it can also empower you.",
        "yes_no" => "The Justice card is about karma, fairness, and balance in various aspects of your life. It doesn't signify a favorable or unfavorable outcome for you, but responsibility, dignity, and integrity all appreciate its presence. Your question doesn't have a straightforward answer.",
        "past" => "Balancing your emotions brings rewards, making you more harmonious in relationships. If you find inner balance, the confusion in your life can be overcome.",
        "present" => "You will receive some advice or settle debts.",
        "future" => "When all is said and done, you will get what you truly deserve. Your moral qualities will be rewarded, so stay honest and strive to balance yourself.",
    ],
    12 =>
    [
        "id" => 13,
        "type_id" => 1,
        "number" => 12,
        "name" => "The Hanged Man",
        "upright_keyword" => "Sacrifice, Waiting, Uncertainty, Lack of direction, Perspective, Contemplation",
        "reversed_keyword" => "Procrastination, Apathy, Stagnation, Avoidance of sacrifice, Indecision, Indifference",
        "astrology" => "Neptune",
        "element" => "Water Element",
        "image_key" => "12_Hanged_Man",
        "content" => "In this card, it depicts a man hanging upside down, his foot suspended from the living world tree. This tree is deeply rooted in the underworld and is known to support the heavens. It is believed that the Hanged Man is actually positioned there by his own free will. We believe this because of the serene expression on his face. His right foot is tied to the branch, but his left foot remains completely free. Meanwhile, his hands are behind his back, forming an inverted triangle. The red pants he wears represent the physical and human passion, while the blue he wears on his shirt represents calm emotions, a common color combination for saints. The yellow of his shoes, hair, and halo symbolizes his wisdom.",
        "upright_content" => "The Hanged Man understands that his position is a sacrifice he needs to make to move forward—whether it is to repent for past mistakes or to take a planned step back to recalculate his forward path. The time he spends here will not be wasted, as it is part of his progress. His inverted state can also symbolize the feelings of those who walk a spiritual path, as they view the world differently. If others do not understand the necessity of the sacrifice, you will see it differently. Walking this path alone is a natural course of action for you.

The Hanged Man card reflects the specific need to pause certain actions. Thus, it can indicate a period of indecision. This means that even if there is an urgent need to take action at this particular moment, certain actions or decisions that need to be implemented correctly may be delayed. In fact, if you can delay certain actions to ensure you have more time to think about making key decisions, it will ultimately be for the best.

This is a card primarily about waiting and pausing. It suggests that this might be something you need to do to achieve success or wait for the right opportunity. Remember, taking action is not always the best solution, and in some cases, not doing so can bring you just as many, if not more, benefits.",
        "reversed_content" => "The reversed meaning of the Hanged Man card represents a very specific period in which you feel as though you have sacrificed a lot of time and gotten nothing in return. You may feel that certain things seem to be in absolute stasis, with no particular solution or way forward. It’s as if you have put all your energy and attention into something, but nothing seems to come out of it as it should.",
        "upright_love" => "Overall, the Hanged Man is about sacrifice, new perspectives, and waiting for the right timing. For singles, the Hanged Man tarot love meaning is about not rushing things. No matter how much effort you put into romantic pursuits or sending all the right signals to your date, if the other person isn't ready, it might not depend on you. Don't try to force or pressure a relationship to blossom; instead, use this time to see how your perspective changes when you are alone. This applies equally to relationships. Timing may be an issue when having important discussions or taking your relationship to the next level.

Alternatively, the concept of sacrifice may play a role in your relationship or potential relationship now. Help might be needed, and this can be a time that tests your commitment but also brings you closer together.",
        "reversed_love" => "Now is the time to take action. The reversed Hanged Man tarot love meaning indicates that the period of waiting is over. Your love life may have slowed down recently, forcing you to take time to consider different perspectives on romance and love. Ideally, you have emerged with a clearer understanding of your relationship expectations. This may be a time when an old, long-held belief is being discarded. With this new perspective, you can now take action or change your romantic life with new energy. This card can also caution against making unnecessary sacrifices for love. Ensure that your needs and your partner's needs are balanced.",
        "upright_career" => "When it comes to work, the Hanged Man can indicate a feeling of waiting or being unsure of what you should do. Your projects may be on hold, forcing you to take a break, or you may be waiting and considering your next move. The lesson of this card is that sometimes, no matter what, you cannot force decisions or make changes when the time is not right. Sometimes, you just have to wait, and the things you’ve been pushing for, whether it's a response from business partners or colleagues, a decision from clients, or a decision about changing careers, will come in due time. Relax, and just let it be. Alternatively, you may be making significant changes to your career.",
        "reversed_career" => "When the Hanged Man is reversed, you may feel that the sacrifices you have made in your career are not really paying off. If you’ve recently changed career paths, taken time off to retrain, or devoted your family time to work projects, things may not be going as planned. It can seem like making those changes wasn’t worth it. Sometimes, this card can also indicate procrastination. Instead of waiting for the right timing, you may be feeling so overwhelmed by what to do next that you’ve been delaying making the decisions that would push you to the next step, leading to a sense of powerlessness or stagnation. Don’t wallow; learn to take an active part in your life.",
        "upright_finances" => "The Hanged Man indicates the need for a change in perspective. If there is some pressure regarding financial matters, you may find that pausing at this moment can actually give you a new way of looking at things. Can you turn a bad situation into an opportunity? Do things look worse than they actually are?",
        "reversed_finances" => "If you’ve been considering making a major purchase or investment with your resources recently, your indecision and hesitation may mean that you never take the next step. Sometimes, this card can also indicate that your investments have not yielded any returns; this doesn’t have to be in traditional financial institutions. Perhaps you lent money to a family member for education, only to have them drop out. Maybe you’ve put some of your finances into a side business, only to see it fail. This card has a feeling of sacrifice for nothing; let these be lessons for how to handle such situations in the future.",
        "yes_no" => "The Hanged Man suggests a form of transformation through breaking patterns, letting go, or undergoing a period of transition. While it can indicate having to give up something to gain a new perspective, it carries neither a positive nor a negative meaning. The answer is maybe.",
        "past" => "Letting go of some past things has brought new value to your spiritual life. You must look at what you have sacrificed in a new way.",
        "present" => "If something is rushed, it could indicate that it will be paused. Remember, the act of helping is not more important than the person being helped.",
        "future" => "Many things are unknown to you right now, so you must set new goals and plan carefully. Acting at the right time will put you ahead.",
    ],
    13 =>
    [
        "id" => 14,
        "type_id" => 1,
        "number" => 13,
        "name" => "Death",
        "upright_keyword" => "Transformation, Endings, Change, Transition, Letting Go, Release",
        "reversed_keyword" => "Fear of Change, Repeating Negative Patterns, Resisting Change, Stagnation, Decay",
        "astrology" => "Scorpio",
        "element" => "Water Element",
        "image_key" => "13_Death",
        "content" => "Here, we see Death riding a beautiful white horse, holding a black flag with a white pattern. He is depicted as a living skeleton, with bones being the only part of the human body that exists after death. He wears armor, making him invincible - signifying that no one can destroy death. The white horse he rides represents purity, as death purifies everyone. Beneath him, all classes of humanity lie in the dirt - kings and beggars, reminding us that death does not distinguish between class, race, or gender.",
        "upright_content" => "Death is one of the most feared cards in the tarot deck and is deeply misunderstood. Many avoid mentioning this card because it holds such power. Most often, people understand the card's name literally. However, the true meaning of the Death card is one of the most positive in the entire deck.

The Death card signifies that a major phase in your life is coming to an end, and a new one is about to begin. You need to close one door for another to open. The past needs to be placed behind you so you can focus your energy on what is ahead.

Another meaning is that you are about to go through a major change, transition, or transformation. The old version of you needs to 'die' to create the new you. This may be a scary time for you as you may be unsure of what will happen in the future. Even if you are afraid, you should welcome this change because you are opening the door to new life events.

Death may also signify that you need to let go of any unhealthy attachments in your life. This is an important part of life, and learning to move on is one of the lessons Death teaches us.",
        "reversed_content" => "The reversed meaning of the Death card is still about change, but you have been resisting it. You may be afraid of letting go of the past, or you may be unsure of what changes need to be made to move forward. Resisting change and clinging to the past will limit your future, leaving you feeling stuck. You should take some time to evaluate how you have been approaching life's changes. You may find that you have been stalling the necessary changes due to fear of the unknown. While you may still feel afraid, you should trust that you are taking the right steps and continue to move forward. Life continues, so fighting against time will only leave you with regrets. Death does not necessarily have to be a card of regret, especially if you heed its warnings.",
        "upright_love" => "When it comes to love and relationships, the Death tarot card love meaning can indicate being stuck in emotional dynamics that are no longer working. If you are in a relationship, for it to continue, you must learn to embrace change. Sometimes, this card may also suggest that you may want to end the relationship, especially if it has not been going well. It is important to remember that every door closed by the Death tarot card opens another. While Death in a love tarot reading can be hard to accept, the transformation for one or both partners may be what is needed to help both individuals grow. Equally important is to remember that the card is a suggestion; you can choose to embrace and welcome the transformation in your relationship or let go.

While initially frightening, the transformation that the Death tarot card brings to love can also be positive. In less drastic terms, it can signify the start of a new era, such as an engagement.

If you are single, the Death tarot card love meaning can point to the beliefs, attitudes, or behaviors you are currently shedding that can help you develop healthier, stronger relationships.",
        "reversed_love" => "The reversed meaning of the Death tarot card in love can signify strong resistance to change when it comes to your attitudes and approaches to relationships and romance. This can manifest in a stagnant relationship that no longer helps you grow as an individual. There may be dependency on the relationship, or you may stay together out of comfort, obligation, or fear of being alone.

On the other hand, old relationships can be revived. If you are single, the reversed Death tarot card in love suggests that you must avoid negative patterns and dynamics to truly engage in a loving relationship. You may have self-esteem issues, a savior complex, or wounds that need healing to find a partner who will love and respect you, and whom you can love and respect in return.",
        "upright_career" => "If you have been considering changing your career, the upright Death card can be a signal that you should act and take steps immediately. You may have experienced a period of apathy, disinterest, and frustration in your current job, and if you do not take decisive action, life events may force you to make a change. You may be holding onto your current path because it provides stability, certainty, and security, but if you are unhappy or feel unchallenged in other aspects, you will lose more than just comfort. Often when one door closes, another opens; embrace the changes happening now and immerse yourself in them.",
        "reversed_career" => "You are also being forced to make changes in your work or career path. However, in reverse, you may be going to great lengths to resist this transformation. Despite unhealthy environments, reduced pay, or monotonous projects, you may be holding on. Change is inevitable; this applies to our careers as well as other aspects of our lives. We must learn to welcome it rather than push it away. When we hold onto a cycle that is no longer meant to stay in our lives, we watch it decay slowly and drain our energy. Sometimes, this card can also represent negative patterns repeating in your workplace. Are you self-sabotaging? Is your defensiveness causing trouble when you make mistakes? Does your imposter syndrome affect how you interact with colleagues? Consider what must be let go to release these unhealthy patterns.",
        "upright_finances" => "The Death tarot card heralds loss, which means you may unfortunately be dealing with the loss of financial resources. This period can also initiate a transformation in your relationship with money and your values. The lessons you learn from this time can bring practical changes in managing your resources and spiritual changes in understanding what truly matters to you.",
        "reversed_finances" => "The loss of financial resources may be inevitable, but it may be hard for you to accept and adapt. To get through this temporary period, you may need to make some adjustments in your expenses, but you may find it difficult to let go of things you deem necessary. Instead of letting this time transform your relationship with resources and your values, you may not be learning the lessons. Learning to stop resisting these changes can make coping easier.",
        "yes_no" => "The Death card indicates some dramatic change so that there can be a new beginning. It is often associated with some kind of loss, failure, or destruction. The overall tone of this card is rather dark and not very promising. Therefore, your answer is no.",
        "past" => "You have entered a new phase of life. Everything changes with time, and the path you walk through this world is no exception.",
        "present" => "Something major is approaching, and it will come suddenly. You will lose something valuable.",
        "future" => "Move forward and look at the world with a fresh perspective. The past is behind you, and the rest of your life lies ahead, so continue your journey with all your heart.",
    ],
    14 =>
    [
        "id" => 15,
        "type_id" => 1,
        "number" => 14,
        "name" => "Temperance",
        "upright_keyword" => "Balance, Peace, Patience, Moderation, Calmness, Serenity, Harmony, Tranquility",
        "reversed_keyword" => "Imbalance, Excess, Extremes, Discord, Recklessness, Haste",
        "astrology" => "Sagittarius",
        "element" => "Fire Element",
        "image_key" => "14_Temperance",
        "content" => "On the Temperance card, there is an angel with wings whose gender is not apparent, suggesting a balance between the sexes. One foot of the angel is in the water, representing the subconscious, while the other foot is on dry land, representing the material world. On her robe, there is a square with a triangle inside it, another echo of the combination of the material earth and the Holy Trinity. She holds two cups in a manner that can mix water, representing the superconscious and the subconscious. The water flows between them, hinting at unity and infinity.

Everything about this card represents balance, the perfect harmony that comes from the union of dualities. Her advice is to test any new waters before jumping into the abyss.",
        "upright_content" => "In times of anxiety or great stress, you have been able to remain calm. You are someone who has mastered the art of not letting things affect you, which has allowed you to make great progress in all the areas you seek to explore. The Temperance tarot card advises moderation and balance, coupled with great patience. Wherever this card appears, it suggests that extremes should be avoided in any situation.

The Temperance card means that you have a clear vision and know what you want to achieve. It is a sign of higher education and a key attribute in your life journey. It reflects that you have found peace in what you are doing, and everything is unfolding as it should. Compared to others, the Temperance card indicates that you can adapt and harmonize with your community, colleagues, and loved ones. Your calmness in all matters brings comfort and reassurance to them.

With the ability to reconcile opposing thoughts and conflicting outcomes, your inner self remains serene and peaceful; you have learned to moderate justice and compassion, success and failure, joy and sorrow, balancing the various demands of life. You accommodate voices that differ from your own but do not fully yield to them; you reconcile conflicting thoughts within yourself, thereby achieving true tolerance.",
        "reversed_content" => "Reversed Temperance reflects that some things have fallen out of balance, which can cause stress and anxiety. Other cards can be used to interpret the true meaning of the Temperance card to identify the areas causing this imbalance. Reversed Temperance can also serve as a warning; if you take a certain path, it will lead to turmoil and excess.

A lack of long-term planning or vision can also be the meaning of reversed Temperance. This leaves you without a goal, and you feel unbalanced as you look around for what you should be doing. You need to reflect and carefully consider what needs to be changed. Temperance reminds us that everything is only good in moderation, and we must examine where we have broken the balance in our lives.",
        "upright_love" => "In romance, the upright Temperance tarot card love meaning suggests patience, moderation, understanding, and taking the middle path. This card advises avoiding extremes and acting cautiously. When it comes to love, consider your behavior; in what ways might your attitudes, beliefs, or thoughts be excessive? Are you too aggressive with potential partners? Or conversely, are you too conservative? Do you also give? Or do you give too little? How can you balance these traits? Additionally, your relationship or potential relationship may now require some patience and an effort to work together to seek compromise and harmony.",
        "reversed_love" => "In love, do you tend to consider everything or nothing at all? Love, like many things in life, is full of gray areas. When reversed Temperance appears in a love tarot reading, your current intensity may be surprising. Sometimes, no matter how hard we try, we cannot force love to happen. A bit more patience may benefit you, while also ensuring that your emotions or desires do not become extreme. When your date does something displeasing, do you tend to reject them immediately? Are your expectations of your potential partners so high that no one can meet them? It is important to remember that humans can never be perfect; make sure your desires are reasonable.",
        "upright_career" => "Patience and moderation can be useful tools for achieving your career goals. When it comes to your work, you are likely to find what you want, but it may come slowly and quietly as you put in the effort every day. Your dedication and ability to handle emotional situations calmly at work can help you get noticed by colleagues and superiors. When it comes to changing your career path, the Temperance card can remind you to stay patient, steady, and focused; all good things take time. Temperance can also indicate that you are doing well in balancing different aspects of your career and life; it's neither about all-encompassing ambition nor just about the paycheck for you.",
        "reversed_career" => "Something at work may now be lacking balance. Do you tend to go all out in your job to the point where other aspects of your life suffer? Are you always working late, hoping it will all pay off? Or, do you find yourself slacking off, causing resentment among your colleagues? While the former may bring you success, it can be harmful in the long run. If this applies to you, seek to correct this imbalance. Make sure that when you complete projects, you don't rush or make reckless choices; the quality of your work may suffer.",
        "upright_finances" => "The Temperance card can ensure that your financial approach is moderate and balanced. This may mean that you have been working hard to save while also being able to occasionally reward yourself with something you can afford. Over time, you may build your resources through steady and diligent saving.",
        "reversed_finances" => "Are you someone who always needs to buy yourself that nice luxury item? Or, are you too frugal, never rewarding your hard work with any small gift? Both of these attitudes may need adjustment, as they are unsustainable in the long run. The first always puts immediate gratification above your future comfort, and vice versa. Consider your financial goals and make sure you also take your happiness into account; both your future happiness and your current happiness need to find a comfortable middle ground.",
        "yes_no" => "Temperance signifies divine intervention and harmony. Its appearance in your tarot reading suggests that you are very confident and in control of your destiny. The answer to your question is 'most likely yes.'",
        "past" => "You lived a harmonious life in the past; this taught you how to cooperate well with others, and this harmony is destined to repeat in the future. You have been greatly influenced by a balanced life, which has made you better.",
        "present" => "The desires you hope for will finally become yours; you have been working hard to achieve your dreams. Expect an increase in wealth, academic or career advancement, healthy relationships, and even marriage to appear in your life. This joy may spread to your loved ones.",
        "future" => "Do not indulge in excess. If you keep a calm mind and think accordingly, future conflicts will be resolved, and a new chapter in your life will begin.",
    ],
    15 =>
    [
        "id" => 16,
        "type_id" => 1,
        "number" => 15,
        "name" => "The Devil",
        "upright_keyword" => "Oppression, Addiction, Obsession, Dependency, Excess, Powerlessness, Limitation",
        "reversed_keyword" => "Independence, Freedom, Revelation, Release, Regaining Power, Regaining Control",
        "astrology" => "Capricorn",
        "element" => "Earth Element",
        "image_key" => "15_Devil",
        "content" => "This card depicts the most famous representation of the Devil, commonly known as Baphomet. Besides being half-goat and half-human, the Devil has bat wings and an inverted pentagram on his forehead. He stands on a pedestal with a naked man and woman chained to it, suggesting his dominion over them.

The man and woman have horns, indicating that the longer they stay with the Devil, the less human they become. The chains make it appear as if they are captured by the Devil. The man has flames on his tail, and the woman has a bowl of grapes, symbolizing their obsession with power and the pleasures of life, respectively.

Upon closer inspection, the man and woman are not happy. Their personal power has been stripped away, leaving them exposed and ashamed of their nakedness.",
        "upright_content" => "Drawing the Devil card in your tarot reading indicates that you are experiencing life's traps, emptiness, and a lack of fulfillment. It could also mean you are a slave to materialism and wealth, and no matter how hard you try, you can't seem to shake off the feeling of wanting to indulge in a luxurious lifestyle.

You may be aware that this way of life is leading you down a rabbit hole, but you feel powerless to control your actions or impulses.

Addiction to material things or sensory pleasures could also be the reason you feel helpless and trapped. In such a case, you may feel like a slave, unable to control your impulses or willpower to guide yourself toward anything beyond these desires.",
        "reversed_content" => "The reversed Devil card can signify a moment when a person becomes self-aware and breaks free from all the chains created by addictions and bad habits. It could be because they are tired of the cycle and need a change.

However, one thing is usually clear—breaking these chains, especially those of addiction, is never easy. Therefore, one must be prepared to make the necessary changes, which may initially feel painful, and then adjust, ultimately being rewarded by finding their true self again.

In this scenario, self-assessment is needed, and the individual must take some time to list all the things they need to break free from. Once done, they should embark on the difficult journey of self-improvement.",
        "upright_love" => "In love tarot readings, the Devil symbolizes desire and temptation. This card can bring hedonism and selfish gratification. In less serious contexts, it may simply mean the pursuit of all earthly pleasures in life. There's nothing wrong with enjoying a little fun, but make sure you do so without hurting others or giving them the wrong impression. If you are just looking for a fling, it's up to you to communicate that to your dates. If they feel your lifestyle isn't suitable for them, ensure you avoid pressuring them. Communication will be more important than ever.

Alternatively, the Devil card in love can also signify addiction, in the context of love and relationships, as codependency. Over time, this can erode both parties' personalities and sense of self. Be careful and ensure that both of you remain strong in your relationship.",
        "reversed_love" => "The reversed Devil card in love tarot readings may indicate that you are breaking free from some negative emotional patterns or addictions that have been hindering your ability to form solid relationships. You may be feeling more in control of your love life than ever before. In some cases, this card can also indicate the end of a relationship with a controlling partner or a codependent relationship that does not allow you to express your true self. You may have recognized that the ties binding you to your partner are unhealthy or unsupportive. Continue fostering your independence and be proud of your progress.",
        "upright_career" => "When it comes to your current career, you may feel trapped or stuck, as if you have no choice but to stay in a place you dislike. In this state, it may be easier to blame the environment, bad luck, or many external factors. You may feel dependent on this job and unable to make changes that would bring you happiness. Sometimes, this card can signal self-sabotage and playing the victim in work relationships with colleagues. Regardless of how it feels, the appearance of the Devil suggests that you have more choices than you think, and you just need to reclaim your power. Taking responsibility for the situation you dislike can be terrifying, but it can also be empowering.",
        "reversed_career" => "In terms of work, you are taking back responsibility for your career choices and making much-needed changes to avoid future problems. If you have been in a stifling situation, you might be taking action; this could mean leaving an unfulfilling job, an unhealthy environment, or addressing tensions with colleagues. You might no longer feel dependent on your job for stability, understanding that you can find it within yourself. Note the changes occurring as you rediscover your independence.",
        "upright_finances" => "Difficult financial situations may be exacerbated by bad habits associated with the Devil in tarot. This might indicate that you usually have more steps to take to get out of this state, but you might not see the solutions or be unable to change how you handle your finances. You could be compulsively spending, gambling, or unable to control your material resources. Ensure you are doing everything you can.",
        "reversed_finances" => "If you have a history of bad financial habits, you may be working to make the necessary changes to regain control. If your material resources have been dependent on others, such as a partner or family, you might be enjoying a new sense of independence.",
        "yes_no" => "The Devil carries a negative connotation towards everything. Anger, violence, temptation, fear, and doubt are just some of the terrors associated with this card. It suggests being trapped in unhealthy relationships, addictions, or lies. Without a doubt, this card tells you no.",
        "past" => "One of the choices you made was the wrong one for you. Negative forces are slowing your progress.",
        "present" => "An event beyond your influence will change your life. Whether it's good or bad is uncertain, but avoid indulgent behaviors and be true to yourself.",
        "future" => "The time is near for you to discover your inner beauty and stop relying on the world. Find the courage to change your life. Your life will surpass your understanding.",
    ],
    16 =>
    [
        "id" => 17,
        "type_id" => 1,
        "number" => 16,
        "name" => "The Tower",
        "upright_keyword" => "Disaster, Destruction, Upheaval, Trauma, Sudden Change, Chaos",
        "reversed_keyword" => "Avoiding Disaster, Narrow Escape, Averted Disaster, Calm Before the Storm",
        "astrology" => "Mars",
        "element" => "Fire Element",
        "image_key" => "16_Tower",
        "content" => "The Tower card depicts a tall spire perched on a mountaintop. A lightning bolt strikes the tower, setting it ablaze. Flames burst from the windows, and people leap from the windows in desperation. They may signify the same figures seen in The Devil card. They are trying to escape the turmoil and destruction within. The tower represents ambitions built on flawed premises. The destruction of the tower must occur to clear the way for new things. Its revelations can come as a flash of truth or inspiration.",
        "upright_content" => "The Tower represents the most radical and necessary changes. It is for this reason that the card itself visually appears so unsettling. But it doesn't necessarily have to be truly terrifying or ominous. Because at the core of this card, its message is foundational, groundbreaking change.

  The events marked by the Tower card do not necessarily have to be terrible things like disasters or great losses. Change itself is a normal part of life that people must accept. But it can sometimes be frightening because it means we have to let go of the truths we knew before this event. The old ways are no longer useful, and you must find another set of beliefs, values, and processes to replace them.

  On a more positive note, it's time to replace the old foundations of the past with something more genuine and that will serve you better in the future.

  In terms of work, inevitable arguments will arise. You need to control your temper. Avoid saying things that could hurt others. When it comes to your love life, your romantic relationship may be nearing its end. Take this as a warning—if you truly value your relationship, it is time to take damage control measures or communicate to clear up misunderstandings. In your finances, the meaning of the Tower indicates the need to secure your transactions.",
        "reversed_content" => "When you reverse the Tower card, you feel a crisis looming on the horizon, and you are doing everything you can to try to avoid its manifestation. What you don't realize is that these failures might help break your reliance on the wrong things. The Tower is built on a flawed foundation, and it must fall. While destruction will be painful, the resulting humility will bring us peace.

  What you have relied on will no longer exist. Do not see this as a drastic and distressing change; now is the time for you to become more self-reliant.",
        "upright_love" => "The Tower's meaning in love tarot indicates massive fundamental changes. Relationships built on weak or shaky foundations won't last long and may crumble. While initially painful, these clear the way for new experiences. Perhaps your relationship is very important to your identity; you pride yourself on being a good partner or parent, and even if you are unhappy, you can stay. While these times can be tough, know that they will pass. If you are single, it may not be a relationship that is breaking up but your whole view and understanding of what love means to you. What beliefs about love are not serving your highest self? These need to change so you can have an individual understanding of your needs in relationships.",
        "reversed_love" => "Change is never an easy thing to accept, but it will come regardless of how much we resist it. If you see any issues on the horizon in your relationship, now is your chance to address them. Doing so can prevent larger issues down the road. Are your resentments building up? Have you been staying silent because you think it's not worth arguing over? Slowly, these things can turn into big problems, potentially destroying a once-happy relationship. Sometimes, this card can also indicate that you may be ready to leave a relationship that is not working.",
        "upright_career" => "When it comes to your career, there may be a lot of stress right now; the Tower can mean sudden job loss or getting a new position that causes chaos due to a sudden increase in responsibilities. Something from the external environment, such as a new boss or the departure of colleagues, can mean disaster in the workplace. It's important to remember that although things are frustrating at this time, this temporary chaos may bring a better long-term future, such as a job that suits you better or a more peaceful workplace in the long run.",
        "reversed_career" => "Despite the stress at work, you might be able to pull through. For example, if your workplace has gone through rounds of layoffs, you might find yourself among the few lucky ones who managed to keep their job. This can be a relief, or it may prevent you from finding true fulfillment in your career. Sometimes, the Tower is a card we all need to shake us out of our stupor and be motivated to leave a comfortable yet monotonous job. This might be your chance to open your eyes to see what else is out there for you.",
        "upright_finances" => "It is wise to ensure you have some funds saved up right now. The Tower speaks of disaster at its worst, and finances are no exception. There could be unwelcome surprises that might cause a sudden loss of resources.",
        "reversed_finances" => "If you have successfully avoided a financial disaster, take some time to seek relief. However, the Tower suggests it might be best to accept what needs to happen to move forward. For example, if you have avoided bankruptcy by managing to pay off debt this month, it might be easier and healthier in the long run to accept your situation and declare bankruptcy. Or, if you purchased a house you couldn't afford and the mortgage payments are strangling you, it might be wiser to sell. Otherwise, one disaster is avoided only to be reset for the next; you might continue to struggle indefinitely. Consider what can ease your burden now and face the situation with courage.",
        "yes_no" => "The Tower is about unexpected events and the changes about to happen in your life. However, these changes are catastrophic, disastrous, and overall negative. It may relate to some sort of accident, disaster, or damage to other areas of your life. The answer this card provides is no.",
        "past" => "This card highlights the weak foundation of your ambitions. You have tended to expect false rewards. You need to let go of such hopes to make space for new, positive ideas.",
        "present" => "A conflict is about to erupt in your life. Relationships need to be re-evaluated and restructured to last.",
        "future" => "By welcoming the challenges ahead, your future will be bright. View things the way you want them to be to make them that way. Thus, remain calm in the face of unexpected failures, and maintain faith that everything will pass in due time.",
    ],
    17 =>
    [
        "id" => 18,
        "type_id" => 1,
        "number" => 17,
        "name" => "The Star",
        "upright_keyword" => "Hope, Inspiration, Positivity, Faith, Renewal, Healing, Rejuvenation",
        "reversed_keyword" => "Despair, Hopelessness, Negativity, Lack of Faith, Discouragement",
        "astrology" => "Aquarius",
        "element" => "Air Element",
        "image_key" => "17_Star",
        "content" => "The Star card shows a woman kneeling by a small pond. She holds two containers of water. One container pours water onto the dry land as if to nourish it and ensure its fertility. The lush greenery around her seems to say it is working. One foot is in the water, showing the woman's spiritual abilities and inner strength. The other foot is on the ground, showing her practical abilities and strengths. Behind her is a large central star surrounded by seven smaller stars representing the chakras. A bird stands on a tree branch, representing the sacred ibis of thought.",
        "upright_content" => "The Star brings hope, renewed power, and strength to carry on with life. It shows how abundantly blessed you are by the universe, which can be seen in many things around you. It may not be directly evident at the moment, as this card comes after the trauma of the Tower card. Remember that you hold within you all you need for your fulfillment; all you need is the courage. For this, you have all the reasons to rejoice. Seeing this card is a message to have faith, for the universe will bless you and bring forth all that you need.

  Getting the Star in your reading means you have gone through a terrible life challenge. You have managed to go through it without losing hope. While you suffered, you may not have been aware of your own strength, but now you may be recognizing that the loss has helped you discover your resilience and inner power. Only now can you appreciate all that you have.",
        "reversed_content" => "When the Star card is reversed, it means you feel as though everything is against you. The challenges you normally find exciting seem to be overwhelming. You have lost faith in something, whether it is within you or in something you usually hold dear.

  Without hope and faith, we cannot find the motivation to move forward with the challenges we face. Where in your life do you feel despair? In what ways have you already given up? How does this affect your actions? The reversed Star asks us to nurture our sense of hope and positive energy to propel our actions with joy rather than fear.",
        "upright_love" => "The Star card's love meaning suggests a lot of hope in love and romance. Your hope and optimism can be a powerful magnet for you to feel attractive and charismatic. If you are recovering from a breakup, this card indicates that you are on the right path and slowly rebuilding your confidence to move forward. If your relationship has gone through a rough patch, this can also be a time of healing. As long as you both maintain communication and honesty, there is great potential to bring you two closer together.",
        "reversed_love" => "Self-doubt and a loss of confidence may cloud your judgment with the appearance of the reversed Star. Are you plagued with a lack of confidence? Are you overly critical of your own flaws? What makes you feel unworthy of love? Others can sense this from you, which can make you feel worse, reinforcing your negative feelings about yourself. It's important now to remember all the good things about yourself so you can see yourself as a valuable partner.

  Doubts and a loss of faith can apply not only to yourself but also to your overall feelings about love. If you have been single for a while, cynicism might lead you to believe that love only brings pain or is an illusion not worth pursuing, but in reality, it is an attitude that can push others away.",
        "upright_career" => "When it comes to work, believe in your ambitions and that they will come true. This can bring you a great deal of positivity that others will notice, which can lead to the opportunities you are hoping for. If you are looking for a new job or promotion, the Star reminds you to keep hope alive. If you have recently gone through a difficult or stressful period at work, the Star also marks a time of recovery. This should be a quiet and peaceful time during your recuperation.",
        "reversed_career" => "With the reversed Star, your negativity is likely affecting your work. You may no longer feel enthusiastic or creative because you can only see things pessimistically. Have your hopes been dashed? Have you given up believing that things will get better? When we despair, we make bad situations worse, and the willingness to keep going can be stifled. It is likely that while things may be tense right now, they are not as bad as you imagine. A change in your approach, perspective, or attitude may be all that is needed to inspire positive change.",
        "upright_finances" => "When it comes to your finances, the Star indicates that one's faith and positivity should help you achieve your financial goals. As you work towards your financial future, also take the time to appreciate and be grateful for what you already have, as this can motivate you to continue on this path.",
        "reversed_finances" => "If you have been struggling financially, the reversed Star may suggest that not all hope is lost, but you may have given up. There are still things you can do to change your situation now, provided you can muster the positivity, see things from a new perspective, and take action. Opening yourself up to a more positive outlook can also help you see opportunities.",
        "yes_no" => "The Star signifies hope, renewal, and beauty. It suggests a period of spiritual peace, happiness, and positive opportunities. The overall feeling of this card is optimistic and serene. The answer implied by its presence is yes.",
        "past" => "Your strong intuition and improvisational skills have led you to the right place in life. This may also indicate you felt lost when facing unexpected realities.",
        "present" => "Several ideas and thoughts are stirring within you. You desire to make a contribution to humanity through your efforts.",
        "future" => "Do not let your hope fade, for you will find solutions to your problems and emerge successful soon.",
    ],
    18 =>
    [
        "id" => 19,
        "type_id" => 1,
        "number" => 18,
        "name" => "The Moon",
        "upright_keyword" => "Illusion, Intuition, Uncertainty, Confusion, Complexity, Secrets, Unconscious",
        "reversed_keyword" => "Fear, Deception, Anxiety, Misunderstanding, Clarity, Understanding",
        "astrology" => "Pisces",
        "element" => "Water Element",
        "image_key" => "18_Moon",
        "content" => "When we encounter the Moon, we see a path that leads off into the distance. A wolf and a dog stand on either side of the path, representing our animalistic nature, one being tamed and the other wild. A small crayfish crawls out of the pond from where the path originates, symbolizing our early stages of consciousness. The pond symbolizes the unconscious mind. In the distance, we can see two towers flanking the central path, again hinting at the duality visible in this card. Everything in this card seems to echo each other, suggesting two possibilities. As we walk down this path, we tread the fine line between the conscious and unconscious, between the tamed side of the dog and the natural forces represented by the wolf.

  The towers at the ends represent the forces of good and evil, and their similarity in appearance can hint at the difficulty we face in distinguishing between them.",
        "upright_content" => "On one hand, the Moon card can symbolize your imagination playing tricks on you. You walk a path in the darkness of the night, uncertain of what lies ahead because it may be fraught with danger. You are the crayfish venturing onto the card's path. The Moon's light can bring you clarity and understanding, and you should let your intuition guide you through this darkness.

  Whether now or in the future, you need to be mindful of situations causing fear and anxiety in your mind. It reminds you not to let internal disturbances and self-deception take the best of you. These deep memories and fears need to be released, and negative energies must be let go and transformed into something constructive.

  Another interpretation of the Moon card is the presence of illusion. Some hidden truths must be discovered because what you see now may be a mere trick of the light. You must seek out the hidden forces that need to be unraveled.",
        "reversed_content" => "The reversed Moon in the tarot can sometimes suggest that the darker and more negative aspects of the Moon are present in your life. It can represent confusion and unhappiness—you want to make progress, but you are unsure what the right thing to do is. You must deal with your anxieties and fears by overcoming them because they are like shadows in the dark. It is time to trust yourself and move forward.

  The reversed Moon means you are in a period of intuition, or you have recently been struggling with confusion, anxiety, and self-deception. It may be that you have misinterpreted your feelings, but you are starting to improve in this area.

  Another meaning of the reversed Moon is that the powers of the night that have been bringing you confusion are beginning to dissipate. You have started to manage your fears and anxieties. Any negative energy you have faced is slowly dissipating. Discovering the positive side of things provides a sense of liberation.",
        "upright_love" => "In the context of love tarot, the Moon indicates that emotions are likely complex at this time. The environment may be filled with misunderstandings, and not everything is as it seems. You may need to do some work to get to the truth of the matter; make sure you understand not only others' intentions but also your own emotions, desires, and motives. There may be old attitudes, beliefs, or ideas that are clouding your judgment. Many things may be hidden in your subconscious, affecting your ability to accept love. Are past relationships haunting you? Have you lost faith in love? Do you believe you are unworthy of being loved? All these can deeply impact how we handle relationships. Now is the time to examine them and reveal their true nature.",
        "reversed_love" => "The reversed Moon tarot love meaning can suggest that confusion and deception may be in the air. You may not have all the information you need at this time, and you will have to rely on your intuition to guide you to the truth. Are you being honest with your partner? Are they being honest with you? Sometimes deception does not always have malicious motives, but it can be done out of a desire to avoid hurting someone or to avoid confrontation. However, hiding the truth is never a sustainable situation.",
        "upright_career" => "There may be some uncertainty regarding your career path at the moment. You may be unclear about your goals and which direction you should move in. Alternatively, your current workplace might have a tense atmosphere, arising from a lack of clarity and confusion about project goals or everyone's roles. Misunderstandings are common now, so make sure to communicate clearly; it might be best to repeat yourself. For the same reasons, you may find you do not have all the information needed to make sound work decisions right now. Who can help clarify the facts?",
        "reversed_career" => "On one hand, the reversed Moon suggests that the uncertainty and confusion characteristic of your work or workplace are beginning to clear up. Things might become more transparent, and you may have a better understanding of the direction to take. On the other hand, the reversed Moon can also indicate that situations are worsening, with misunderstandings and miscommunications escalating into deception, lies, and sabotage. Your anxieties and fears about your workplace or colleagues might turn into reality, as everyone becomes more defensive, protective, and paranoid.",
        "upright_finances" => "Now may not be the best time to make any major financial decisions, as the Moon indicates that the information available to you is incomplete at the moment. If you are taking financial action, do not be afraid to dig deeper and ask questions so that you can make the best decision possible. Confusion and uncertainty around finances may be an issue right now.",
        "reversed_finances" => "At best, the reversed Moon indicates that your financial situation and goals are becoming clearer. You will have all the information you need to feel satisfied with major decisions or future investments. However, at worst, the reversed Moon can also indicate that there may be deception regarding your financial situation. Trust your intuition; but try to separate your fears from your intuition.",
        "yes_no" => "The Moon is an illusory and confusing card. It suggests that there are risks, secrets, and a degree of mental disarray. It cautions you to be careful with any endeavors you are pursuing in life. The answer you are seeking is no.",
        "past" => "Your understanding of past events may be distorted by your current perception. Reflect on your past and ensure the pieces fit together. By eliminating uncertainty, you will find more peace.",
        "present" => "A challenge is approaching, either in the form of a new creative project or a conflict in a relationship. Your past will reveal the best course of action.",
        "future" => "If you combine imagination with action, your creativity will bring you success. Striving to reach your potential may bring many conflicts in your life, but the outcome will be beautiful.",
    ],
    19 =>
    [
        "id" => 20,
        "type_id" => 1,
        "number" => 19,
        "name" => "The Sun",
        "upright_keyword" => "Happiness, Success, Optimism, Vitality, Joy, Confidence, Fulfillment, Truth",
        "reversed_keyword" => "Blocked Happiness, Overenthusiasm, Pessimism, Unrealistic Expectations, Arrogance",
        "astrology" => "The Sun",
        "element" => "Fire Element",
        "image_key" => "19_Sun",
        "content" => "The Sun card gives a feeling of optimism and fulfillment. This card represents the dawn following the darkest of nights. The Sun is the source of all life on our planet, representing life energy itself. The card depicts a child playing joyfully in the foreground. As a symbol of our innocence, it represents the happiness that comes when you are in alignment with your true self. The child is naked, meaning they have absolutely nothing to hide. This card also depicts the innocence of childhood and absolute purity. This is particularly emphasized by the white horse the child rides. Here, the horse is also a symbol of strength and nobility.",
        "upright_content" => "The Sun card represents success, abundance, and brilliance. Just like the Sun itself, it brings strength and vitality to those who feel its warmth. There is much joy and happiness coming your way.

  Because of your own personal achievements, you also bring inspiration and joy to others. People are drawn to you because they can see the warmth and beautiful energy you bring to their lives. You are also in a position to share your qualities and achievements with others. You radiate love and affection towards those you care about the most.

  This card indicates that you now have a well-deserved sense of confidence. Life is particularly good at the moment, and the Sun is shining upon you as you reach your goals. The Sun is a card in the tarot that provides a sense of good feelings and fulfillment.",
        "reversed_content" => "In the reversed position, the Sun suggests that you may have difficulty finding the positive aspects of certain situations. Clouds may be blocking the warmth and light you need to move forward. This can prevent you from gaining confidence and strength. You may encounter some setbacks that dampen your optimism and enthusiasm.

  On the other hand, the reversed Sun might suggest that you are being unrealistic. It could indicate that you are overly optimistic about certain situations. These are things you need to consider to ensure you are on the right track and that your success continues.",
        "upright_love" => "With the Sun comes light, life, and warmth. The Sun tarot love meaning brings much of the same in your relationship and general romantic life. There is happiness, celebration, and fulfillment in this card. In this light, your relationship can blossom, bringing you two closer together as you enjoy life’s blessings. Harmony is likely now, and you can use this time to create an even closer bond with your loved one. If you are single, now is also the time to go out and let yourself shine. Your positivity and radiance are attractive right now, and can bring you the romance you have dreamed of.",
        "reversed_love" => "The Sun still shines, even when it is temporarily blocked by clouds. If you are in a relationship, you may be feeling bored even though everything is going smoothly. Do you take your relationship for granted? Are you and your partner drifting apart due to daily routines and mundane tasks? It’s likely that the two of you need more fun times to reignite your romance. The Sun is always a positive card, whether upright or reversed; but in reverse, it usually means something is preventing you from seeing the good things you already have. Are you in love with your partner? What can you appreciate in your relationship?",
        "upright_career" => "When it comes to your career, the Sun brings success, optimism, and joy wherever it shines. When it comes to your current job, you may be experiencing a period of great enthusiasm, motivation, and happiness. Your career might feel both spiritually and materially fulfilling. This joy and positivity can now radiate outwards; your happiness can create a wonderful environment for your colleagues and those around you. If you are in the process of searching for a new job or a promotion, your continued positivity can lead you to success in your career goals.",
        "reversed_career" => "Even when the Sun is reversed, it still implies pleasant things; but perhaps overshadowed by one’s inability to appreciate and see what is truly there. If you feel downhearted, frustrated, or pessimistic about your job, the Sun suggests that you may just need to part the clouds and see how much happiness you already have. Feeling burnt out and exhausted? Your work environment may be highly supportive of getting the rest you need. Perhaps you feel underappreciated? Bring the matter to the attention of your superiors for the raise you deserve. Don’t let negativity close the door on taking decisive action and improving your situation. Sometimes, this card can also suggest that you may be overconfident or have unrealistic expectations about your ambitions. Ensure you have a realistic approach to what can be achieved at this time.",
        "upright_finances" => "Your financial situation now may be comfortable and abundant. The Sun suggests a level of appreciation, abundance, and happiness, and this is no different in the context of tarot. The Sun also shines on objects, making them visible outdoors. If there are any hidden factors related to your financial situation, they can now be revealed.",
        "reversed_finances" => "Reversed, the Sun may suggest that your worries about finances may be temporary and not as bad as you think. Alternatively, be mindful that the financial decisions you make now are well researched and based on solid logic. The reversed Sun can suggest being overly optimistic and unrealistic. Temper your expectations, but remain hopeful.",
        "yes_no" => "The Sun, opposite to the Moon, is a card full of life, joy, and energy. It reveals positive achievements, successful endeavors, and overall manifestation of good fortune in your life. Therefore, the answer it provides to your question is yes.",
        "past" => "The successes you have achieved in the past will lay the foundation for future happiness. Continue developing your work or field of study, and the rewards will come.",
        "present" => "There is an opportunity to form a new friendship or relationship that will bring you happiness and fulfillment. Don’t give up, and you will be guided to success.",
        "future" => "You are approaching a moment that has the potential to change your life. Make the most of this time, and you will achieve a future of infinite possibilities.",
    ],
    20 =>
    [
        "id" => 21,
        "type_id" => 1,
        "number" => 20,
        "name" => "Judgement",
        "upright_keyword" => "Self-Evaluation, Awakening, Renewal, Purpose, Reflection, Reckoning",
        "reversed_keyword" => "Self-Doubt, Lack of Self-Awareness, Failure to Learn Lessons, Self-Loathing",
        "astrology" => "Pluto",
        "element" => "Fire Element",
        "image_key" => "20_Judgement",
        "content" => "This card depicts an image of the Last Judgement, which appears in various forms in many mythologies. The imagery on the Judgement card shows women, men, and children rising from their graves to respond to the archangel Gabriel’s horn. Their outstretched arms symbolize their readiness to accept the universe's judgement. They are about to meet their creator, their deeds measured, and learn where they will spend the remainder of eternity: in heaven or in hell. The massive waves in the background signify that judgement is inevitable and that this judgement will be final.

  Judgement is ruled by Pluto, the ruler of the underworld. It suggests that you make decisions based on your intuition and wisdom, as they will bring significant changes in the coming days.",
        "upright_content" => "The traditional meaning of Judgement focuses on the moment when we reflect and evaluate ourselves and our actions. It is through self-reflection that we can gain a clearer and more objective understanding of where we are now and what we need to do to grow as human beings. The appearance of the Judgement card in a tarot reading signifies that you are approaching this significant moment in your life, and you need to start evaluating yourself.

  Seeing this card also indicates that you are in a period of awakening brought on by self-reflection. You now have a clearer understanding of where changes need to be made and how to become your true self and fulfill your needs. This could mean making small changes in your daily life or making significant changes that affect not only you but also those close to you.",
        "reversed_content" => "A reversed Judgement card may indicate that you are overly harsh in doubting and judging yourself. This can lead to missed opportunities waiting for you. Lost motivation can cause you to fall behind in your plans, making it difficult to move forward. It means you should not be cautious but should move forward with pride and confidence.

  Another reading of the reversed Judgement card can be urging you to take time out from your busy daily life to reflect on your current life and what you have learned so far. You likely have not given yourself enough time or space to thoroughly consider issues and learn the lessons needed to elevate your consciousness. You may also be too critical of your past actions, preventing you from forgiving yourself and moving on. The mistakes we make in the past are learning tools that help us advance in life. Over-focusing on these mistakes can cause us to stumble and fall.",
        "upright_love" => "Now is the time to take a good look at your love life and identify what needs to be changed. The Judgement tarot love meaning signifies a time of self-reflection and analysis brought on by an awakening. Issues in your love life that you once ignored may now be clearly seen, and you have the opportunity to make adjustments. Keep open communication with your partner and ensure that both of you understand each other's needs. The small changes you make together can have a significant impact on your relationship. Your past actions and their consequences, whether good or bad, are now catching up to you. If you have made mistakes in the past, use the lessons learned to make changes for the future.",
        "reversed_love" => "Before you criticize, make sure that your current criticism of your partner is fair. You may be unhappy with certain things, but the reversed Judgement tarot love meaning may suggest that some compromise and temperance are needed.

  On the other hand, this card can signal that you need to open your eyes and see your romantic situation more clearly. Have you been in denial about something? Are you happy in your relationship? Is something missing? Are there some attitudes towards love that you’ve ignored but have deeply influenced the way you date? This card calls you to take an honest look at yourself and your relationships. Facing the truth can also set you free.",
        "upright_career" => "On your career path, you may be going through a period of awakening. Perhaps you have found a new purpose or a calling that cannot be ignored. This can sometimes require adjustments in your workplace or position. While this can bring stress, these changes can make you feel rejuvenated at work. If your workplace has been tense, the Judgement card also suggests that you may need to be more aware of how your actions at work affect others. Take some time to evaluate how you are doing and where you can improve. Take responsibility for your actions and your role in any brewing conflicts.",
        "reversed_career" => "Perhaps you have been too hard on yourself recently. If you have made mistakes at work, you may find it hard to let go of those feelings of disappointment in yourself instead of making amends and moving on. Lingering doubts about your abilities may persist. Alternatively, this card may indicate that you are failing to take responsibility for your actions and learn the lessons needed to take the next step in your career. Your lack of awareness in dealing with yourself may be frustrating your colleagues. Have you been doing your best on your work projects? Have you communicated well? Or are you always shifting the blame to others?",
        "upright_finances" => "When it comes to your relationship with money, you may need to go through a period of self-reflection. Sometimes this means evaluating whether your financial habits are hindering your material situation and making the necessary changes to do better. Are you someone who always buys things you can't afford? Or do you always feel lacking, even if your finances have improved? Now can be a time to consider new ways of handling your finances, giving you a chance to make positive improvements.",
        "reversed_finances" => "If you have recently experienced a financial setback, you may be particularly hard on yourself right now. Learning lessons when making responsible choices is important, but being kind to yourself can also help keep you motivated. On the other hand, the reversed Judgement card may indicate that you find yourself stuck in the same patterns with your financial decisions. Be aware of which side of the light you belong to.",
        "yes_no" => "The Judgement card represents a kind of change or transformation that has likely already happened. This can mean there is a spiritual calling and making decisions that will lead you to success. The answer to your question is yes.",
        "past" => "Your past is full of good work, but the process of freeing yourself from these experiences is ongoing. You are opening a new chapter in life.",
        "present" => "The time has come, and the past is relinquishing control over your destiny. This is the best time to change your lifestyle.",
        "future" => "The fruits of your decisions are coming, and you will get what you deserve. The path beneath your feet and where it leads you are clear. You will see your ultimate wishes come true.",
    ],
    21 =>
    [
        "id" => 22,
        "type_id" => 1,
        "number" => 21,
        "name" => "The World",
        "upright_keyword" => "Completion, Achievement, Fulfillment, Sense of Belonging, Wholeness, Harmony",
        "reversed_keyword" => "Lack of Closure, Lack of Achievement, Feeling Incomplete, Emptiness",
        "astrology" => "Saturn",
        "element" => "Earth Element",
        "image_key" => "21_World",
        "content" => "The World card in the tarot shows a dancing figure in the center. The dancer's legs are crossed, holding a wand in each hand. She symbolizes balance and evolution in movement. The fulfillment and unity she represents are not static but constantly changing, dynamic, and eternal.

  The green wreath surrounding the central figure is a symbol of success, and the red ribbons circling it evoke infinity. Each corner of the card has four figures - the same ones that appear on the Wheel of Fortune. These four figures represent Scorpio, Leo, Aquarius, and Taurus, symbolizing the four corners of the universe, the four elements, and the four evangelists. Together, they signify harmony between all energies.",
        "upright_content" => "Encountering the World in your cards is encountering a great unity and wholeness. It signifies the moment of becoming one with your inner and outer worlds, with yourself and others. In some traditions, this state is described as enlightenment or nirvana. One realizes the deep connection between the individual self and all other things, dancing and swaying to the rhythm of life. You not only hear this rhythm but also participate in it - following the lows and highs, joys and sorrows.

  The World card’s meaning is accomplishment, achievement, and completion. It suggests that all your efforts are starting to pay off. It reflects that you have reached an important milestone in your life and have built the resilience to withstand challenges. The World may signify the completion of a long-term project, a course of study, or any other significant event in your life. It can also mean the birth of a child, marriage, graduation, or any other thing you have accomplished.

  The World card indicates your desire to give back to your community in various ways. You have a commitment to making the world a better place because you understand that everything is interconnected.",
        "reversed_content" => "You are approaching something that marks the end of a journey or era. There may be many accomplishments on your path, but when you look back, a strange emptiness fills you, as if you have all the pieces, but they haven't come together. What is missing? Do you feel connected to what you are doing? Do you feel connected to others? What makes you feel incomplete?",
        "upright_love" => "Your relationship now gives you a deep sense of fulfillment and gratitude. The World tarot love meaning symbolizes a sense of wholeness and happiness. Sometimes, this card can even suggest that you are moving into the next step of your relationship, such as marriage or starting a family. As you complete a cycle in your life, you are also looking forward to the next steps. You and your partner may be making plans and even major decisions.

  Even if you are single, there is a sense of fulfillment and happiness here. Before starting a relationship, one must feel like a complete person. While a relationship can be great, you are confident in yourself. This sense of wholeness and self-understanding now gives you a great chance to meet new and exciting people, as well as charm and attractiveness.",
        "reversed_love" => "While other areas of your life may be going well, something seems to be missing in the love department. The reversed World tarot love meaning suggests a feeling of incompleteness; a cycle is ending but not yet fully complete. You are very close to feeling fulfilled and happy, but something is preventing you from seeing it. Are you overlooking all the good things about your partner? Or are past relationships affecting your experience of this one? Is there a lack of closure with past partners? Some things need to be tidied up now so you can feel happy in the present.",
        "upright_career" => "Take pride in yourself, as you have completed what you set out to do in your career. Whether it means finding a job that fulfills you both spiritually and materially, completing a particularly challenging project, or starting your own business, there is much to celebrate now. Take the time to enjoy what you have earned. You may already be considering what will happen next, as this is the normal cycle of things. For now, enjoy the moment.",
        "reversed_career" => "Have you finally completed an important career goal that you’ve longed for, only to find the rewards aren’t as sweet as you imagined? Or have you just shy of what you wanted to accomplish? The reversed World signifies nearing completion but perhaps missing the final part that would make you feel truly fulfilled. Perhaps your goals were defined by what others deem as successful, or your standards were too low that reaching this goal felt unchallenging. Now is the time to reevaluate your goals and adjust them as needed.",
        "upright_finances" => "You may have worked hard to achieve your financial goals, and now it might be time to enjoy the fruits of your labor. Perhaps you have paid off some debts, found security after saving, or made a big purchase you have been saving for. Pat yourself on the back and feel proud of your accomplishments. Now it’s time to consider other long-term goals. Since the World also represents a sense of completeness, take some time to see how your financial situation fits into the bigger picture of your life.",
        "reversed_finances" => "Even if your financial situation is good, you may feel stagnant and unsatisfied with what you have. A reevaluation of your relationship with material things that need adjusting may be in order with the reversed World. If you find yourself not meeting financial goals, now is not the time to wallow in disappointment; you are close to what you want to achieve; stay consistent, and you will find comfort.",
        "yes_no" => "The World card signifies fulfillment and success at the end of a journey. Accomplishment, rewards, certainty, and positive outcomes are all directly related to the presence of this card. The answer is most likely yes.",
        "past" => "The path you’ve taken will ultimately bring you full circle. Realizing this may take some time, but this journey will bring you new responsibilities and perspectives.",
        "present" => "The current moment will bring you the realization of a wish or a long-desired change of scenery. To gain fulfillment, you must accept that the ideas of others are just as valid as your own.",
        "future" => "You must find your purpose to complete it. Dreams are the same; you must first realize them to let them exist. Success is not guaranteed, but the experience you gain will potentially fulfill your desires.",
    ],
    22 =>
    [
        "id" => 23,
        "type_id" => 1,
        "number" => 22,
        "name" => "Ace of Wands",
        "upright_keyword" => "Inspiration, Creative Spark, New Initiative, New Passion, Enthusiasm, Vitality",
        "reversed_keyword" => "Delays, Obstacles, Lack of Passion, Lack of Energy, Hesitation, Creative Block",
        "astrology" => "",
        "element" => "Fire Element",
        "image_key" => "22_Ace_of_Wands",
        "content" => "The Ace of Wands is associated with the element of fire, and it is the core representation of fire in the deck. This card depicts a hand holding a wand emerging from a cloud.

  When we look at this card, we can see the hand offering a growing wand. Some leaves have already sprouted from the wand, symbolizing balance and progress in both spiritual and material realms. In the distance, there is a castle, symbolizing future opportunities.",
        "upright_content" => "The wand symbolizes creativity, and the Ace of Wands is the boldest in the suit. This isn’t the kind of creativity you learn in school or as a hobby. It bravely seeks to find its own voice and creates a place to develop its vision. In other words, it is about willpower and creativity in the cosmic sense.

  When you get the Ace of Wands, it suggests that you should go all out. Seize the opportunity and pursue the ideas in your heart. Take the first step and start a creative project. The Ace of Wands calls you to follow your intuition. If you think the project you’ve been dreaming about is a good idea, go for it.

  The Ace of Wands can also mean that you are waiting for a sign to start a project. Drawing this card prompts you to take immediate action rather than dwelling on research and more planning. Take small steps today and continue to develop your ideas over time. Action is what helps you grow and build momentum. Don’t stay in the abstract.

  Another meaning of the Ace of Wands is that it is a breakthrough moment in your life. This is a time when you are full of motivation and inspiration for a passionate project or idea. You are excited about the opportunities opening up for you in the near future.",
        "reversed_content" => "The reversed Ace of Wands indicates that you will face trials and tribulations in the near future. You may have no direction, which leads to a lack of inspiration or motivation. At this stage of your life, you may not know what you really want to do. You don’t know how to get out of the slump.

  If you already have a goal, you are not excited about achieving it. When you get a reversed Ace of Wands, you should consider taking a break and letting inspiration find you. You feel overwhelmed by current commitments and responsibilities, unable to come up with new ideas or muster the enthusiasm to push your projects forward.

  The reversed Ace of Wands can also indicate delays in your current projects. You want to complete your tasks, but something is blocking you. Or you have an idea but don’t know how to execute it and make it a reality. In this case, you should be patient and wait for the right time.",
        "upright_love" => "The Ace of Wands tarot love meaning signifies excitement and passion; things are heating up for you! At this moment, your relationship may present a very sensual character, and if you are single, potential romances may be equally so. There may be a lot of flirting and attraction, and if desire is accompanied by some kind of spiritual understanding, there’s even room for more lasting relationships. If you are committed and passion has waned, now may be the time for it to be rekindled. This is a great opportunity to reignite the flames and get you two more emotionally connected.",
        "reversed_love" => "When reversed, the Ace of Wands tarot love meaning signals strong passion that may quickly burn out. There may be lots of excitement at the beginning stages, only to fizzle out when commitment is mentioned. This card may not favor long-term romance. If you are in a relationship, this card can hint that your passion for each other may not be very high at the moment. Sometimes it’s just a matter of learning to communicate better or ensuring you make time for one another. Efforts are needed to rekindle the passion.",
        "upright_career" => "If you find the Ace of Wands here, you are likely experiencing a period of rapid career growth. This is your time to be ready to seize opportunities. You may also find your work particularly inspiring right now. You can break through old boundaries and see the potential in all experiences. This is a great time to face issues that have been holding you back in the past because you are now in a better position to deal with them. Your creativity and problem-solving abilities are high. Use this energy to the fullest.",
        "reversed_career" => "The reversed Ace of Wands signifies a lack of inspiration. This defect can manifest in several ways. You may find it challenging to brainstorm now. If your career requires a lot of creativity, you may feel like you’ve run out of ideas. When you sit down to write, even a simple letter or essay, you may find yourself staring at a blank page longer than usual. A lack of creativity makes starting new projects or jobs difficult. This timing is particularly unfortunate because you are also prone to feeling frustrated by the lack of progress now. Try to be patient with your inspiration and your career path. There will be lulls; this is neither uncommon nor inevitable. Be kind to yourself and do something that might inspire you where possible.",
        "upright_finances" => "The upright Ace of Wands can mark the end of financial struggles. Any pressure that existed before is starting to dissipate. This may be because you are about to pay off a debt. Even if you haven’t experienced stress from a specific debt source, your financial situation may still improve in other ways. You might find yourself receiving gifts or bonuses. Whatever you receive is likely to ease your previous worries. This is a good card but not a symbol of immense wealth. Don’t mistake this relief from pressure as an excuse for reckless spending. This decision is never wise. Instead, be thankful that your life’s stress will be a bit lessened.",
        "reversed_finances" => "The reversed Ace of Wands may indicate that your financial situation could be worsening now. If you see the Ace of Wands in this position, start preparing for a downturn in your financial status. Now is not the time to invest in anything or make significant purchases. You are likely to lose whatever you set aside. Be particularly cautious about gambling, buying stocks, or any behavior that promises high potential (and high risk). Instead, rely on the preparations you may have made to withstand economic uncertainty. Try to prepare for the worst.",
        "yes_no" => "Revisit your past goals because you may have limited yourself. If you don’t use it creatively, inspiration will build up inside you, and it will vent its energy destructively.",
        "past" => "A new beginning is on the horizon. It may appear in the form of a new phase of life, a new venture, a new project, or a new source of inspiration.",
        "present" => "You will see positive results in your life in the coming years. But don’t expect it to happen like that without any effort. All you have to do is focus on your goals and shape yourself into a confident person.",
        "future" => "The Ace of Wands is a creative card suggesting a passionate union, a positive new beginning, or the birth of something powerful and inspiring yet to come into your life. It could be a new project or creative endeavor you are about to undertake. The answer to your question is likely yes.",
    ],
    23 =>
    [
        "id" => 24,
        "type_id" => 1,
        "number" => 23,
        "name" => "Two of Wands",
        "upright_keyword" => "Planning, First Steps, Making Decisions, Leaving Comfort, Taking Risks",
        "reversed_keyword" => "Poor Planning, Over-Analysis, Inaction, Cautious, Avoiding Risk",
        "astrology" => "",
        "element" => "Fire Element",
        "image_key" => "23_Two_of_Wands",
        "content" => "The Two of Wands card depicts a man standing on top of what looks like a castle, holding a miniature globe in his right hand. Standing in his position, the man looks out over the vast terrain, with the ocean to his left and land to his right. The man is dressed in an orange tunic and a red hat, symbolizing his passion for life itself and his desire for adventure. The miniature globe in his hand represents the potential to expand his influence to broader experiences in life.",
        "upright_content" => "The Two of Wands is a more mature version of the Ace of Wands, meaning this tarot card is about planning and moving forward—progress. Look at it this way; you have embarked on a particular task, indicating that you have turned an idea into a realistic plan. Such a plan needs to be put into action, so you must move from merely making plans to actually achieving your goals.

  Notice the significance of being seen with the other two wands. This is because it signifies stepping out of the cocoon and exploring new experiences and worlds. Although it may seem daunting and challenging initially, the Two of Wands card encourages you to keep going and push forward.",
        "reversed_content" => "The reversed Two of Wands indicates poor planning, over-analysis, and inaction. You may find that the plans you made for your career path are not going as you intended. You might have missed details and encountered many unforeseen obstacles. These issues are now causing you trouble. Alternatively, you might have made all the plans in the world; perhaps you have drawn out various scenarios and outlined all the risks. But fear might be preventing you from taking the first step. Instead of over-analyzing every detail, take action. One cannot plan for everything; we must trust our abilities.

  In summary, the Two of Wands' meaning revolves around making decisions. In other words, you are either satisfied with your current knowledge or moving forward and taking risks. This means stepping out of our comfort zones and exploring new territories.",
        "upright_love" => "Regarding your current romantic life, what are your goals? The Two of Wands tarot love meaning can indicate that you are considering changes and making plans. If you are in a relationship, you now have the opportunity to make adjustments. If you are thinking about taking your commitment to a new level, this card indicates great hope as long as you work to visualize what you want and put your ideas into action. With your partner, create a path to the future you both desire. The decisions you make together now can have profound capabilities to bring you closer together.",
        "reversed_love" => "Sometimes, no matter how well one plans for the future, things don't fall into place. Now may not be the best time to push forward with romantic goals. Love takes time to happen, and you may need more patience than usual. It's best to use this time to truly consider what you want from your love life and find a clear path to achieving it. The Two of Wands is a card of planning, setting expectations, and charting the course forward; the best plans start with a clear vision. The Two of Wands' love tarot meaning can also indicate some hesitation in romantic interests.",
        "upright_career" => "When upright in the career position, the Two of Wands indicates you are planning for your future career. You might be examining your ambitions and charting the path to achieve that dream. You may consider the ideal company to work for, what your profession might be, or outline your own business plan. This can be an exciting time for you as your dreams take shape. Let these first steps serve as powerful motivation to continue down this path.",
        "reversed_career" => "When the Two of Wands is reversed, it can have two meanings. You might find that the plans you made for your career path are not going as you intended. You might have missed details and encountered many unforeseen obstacles. These issues are now causing you trouble. Alternatively, you might have made all the plans in the world; perhaps you have drawn out various scenarios and outlined all the risks. But fear might be preventing you from taking the first step. Instead of over-analyzing every detail, take action. One cannot plan for everything; we must trust our abilities.",
        "upright_finances" => "Regarding your finances, the Two of Wands represents financial stability. This stability does not necessarily mean an abundance of wealth, but it indicates a comfortable and stable situation. You might be comfortably making plans for your long-term financial future. Now is a good time to make conscious choices without worrying about severe consequences. If you have funds, consider investing them in savings.",
        "reversed_finances" => "The reversed Two of Wands here can indicate financial instability. This does not suggest significant losses or gains but rather general confusion in your bank account. Your plans for your financial future might not be coming to fruition, which can be an economically turbulent time for you. Now is not the time to invest or make significant purchases; instead, carefully review your financial situation and long-term goals. Try to gain more clarity.",
        "yes_no" => "The Two of Wands shows control and reaping the rewards of life on one hand. On the other hand, it brings significant anxiety and the possibility of losing the control you once had. The vitality projected through this card does not provide a definite answer. Perhaps that's what it implies.",
        "past" => "You may have taken a bold move in the past that benefited you. If you lack willpower, try drawing inspiration from your past.",
        "present" => "You are on the right path that will lead you to your goal. However, you may need the help of someone experienced.",
        "future" => "Reflection and self-awareness will lead you to success. Trust your intuition but also be willing to accept help from others.",
    ],
    24 =>
    [
        "id" => 25,
        "type_id" => 1,
        "number" => 24,
        "name" => "Three of Wands",
        "upright_keyword" => "Motivation, Confidence, Expansion, Growth, Vision, Foresight",
        "reversed_keyword" => "Limitations, Restrictions, Lack of Progress, Obstacles, Delays, Frustration",
        "astrology" => "",
        "element" => "Fire Element",
        "image_key" => "24_Three_of_Wands",
        "content" => "The Three of Wands depicts a man standing on the edge of a cliff, overlooking the sea and mountains. From the edge of the cliff, he can see everything in front of him. While two wands stand on either side of the man, the third wand is held in his left hand. This may signify that your plans are in the process of forming, encouraging you to step into new paths more fully, leading to rapid progress. As you seize better opportunities, you will become more enlightened, confident, and cooperative. The card suggests developing flexibility and embracing changes happening in your life. Focus on your vision and work towards achieving it.",
        "upright_content" => "The meaning of the Three of Wands implies that you are planning or will be more determined in planning for the future. This may mean that everything surrounding your plans is going smoothly because you have taken the time to plan your future and are taking steps to turn plans into actions. It suggests that you may be building a stable foundation for yourself.

  The symbolism in the Three of Wands indicates opportunities to broaden your horizons in many areas. It is also a warning to keep an open mind, as better opportunities may open up for you. As you take steps to achieve your goals, you become increasingly aware of the opportunities coming your way, which may take you out of your comfort zone. This sometimes prompts you to embrace change and start thinking long-term.

  The Three of Wands can indicate that you are in control and hold a strong position, just like the figure who overlooks and stands tall. The Three of Wands is one of the main cards of foresight and vision.

  Another meaning of the Three of Wands is travel, seeking what you are looking for. There is a sense of leaving home and embarking on a journey that must be undertaken. Great things do not happen to those who just wait; you must expand. For most readings, this indicates that you may travel across water to new lands, and you may find opportunities during your travels.",
        "reversed_content" => "The reversed Three of Wands indicates that you may have embarked on a personal journey or development but have not achieved the success you had hoped for. This could be due to delays or obstacles. Nevertheless, this card reminds you that all your efforts are not in vain; they help you build personal strength and perseverance.

  The reversed Three of Wands may also mean that you need to take some time to plan your future. This is especially true if you have not started working towards long-term goals or feel overwhelmed by the tasks you are currently facing or about to face. You are merely reacting instead of acting thoughtfully and deliberately.

  However, the most common meaning of the reversed Three of Wands is pushing for planning for future changes and keeping an eye out for better options as they arise. The figure on the Three of Wands knows this and is constantly aware of upcoming changes, which is worth emulating.",
        "upright_love" => "With the Three of Wands, your love life seems to be entering the next phase. If you find yourself in a new relationship, it looks like you need to ensure you are creating a solid foundation for a lasting commitment. If you are in a committed relationship, this may be a good time to set couple goals and work together to achieve them. Talk about what moving in together means; even the communication of the most mundane details can ensure you take this step with as little frustration as possible. Alternatively, this card can also signal travel; take the opportunity to explore the world together—or, if you are single, new places can inspire the love you are looking for.",
        "reversed_love" => "Sometimes you can't say or do the right thing; if this is the case, it may seem easier to bury your head in the sand. This is unwise; you really need to address any issues and sort things out now.
  The course of true love is rarely completely smooth, and any recent relationships may struggle to take off; this doesn't mean they don't have wings, but they need a little patience. Trying to force things forward will be counterproductive. Before establishing a relationship, check if your partner is truly who you think they are.
  In all relationships, we must compromise from time to time, demanding that your partner change to accommodate you can lead to issues. Are you being realistic?",
        "upright_career" => "When upright, the Three of Wands depicts adventure and new experiences in various aspects of life, including the career position. You may encounter new opportunities to explore your career. Additionally, your career can drive you to make bold choices that you might otherwise hesitate to make. Here, it signifies a new opportunity or bold move. This might mean starting to work abroad or traveling for work in situations where you usually wouldn't. This also applies to business. If you own a business and have been discussing going global, now is a good time to do so.",
        "reversed_career" => "The reversed Three of Wands can indicate frustration, stagnation, or refusal to seize the opportunities presented to you. You may want to explore many things but feel tied down or as if you missed opportunities by not taking advantage of them. Perhaps you declined opportunities to look for new jobs elsewhere or expand your business globally. If you haven't made such decisions recently, it could be due to frustration and irritation over the lack of progress or challenges in your workplace.",
        "upright_finances" => "When the Three of Wands is upright, it signifies that you can enjoy the profits from your hard work. Your labor is paying off. Don't be afraid to spend your hard-earned money on things that can broaden your horizons, such as travel or long trips. If you've been discussing courses or travel but delayed due to financial reasons, the card suggests that now is your chance to embrace these desires and expand your mind. Your ideas about financial stability and your relationship with money may also be expanding now.",
        "reversed_finances" => "In this position and direction, the Three of Wands indicates that you may be in a state of financial disarray. It may not be that you lack money, but you cannot achieve your financial goals. If this card appears before you, better assess your inflows and outflows of funds. With a bit more diligence, you might get through this period without incurring financial losses. Pay attention to your finances and take responsibility for them.",
        "yes_no" => "The Three of Wands represents new beginnings, achievements, and positive partnerships. It can signify some form of business expansion or confirm that you are on the right path to success. With an overall positive tone, it gives you a yes answer.",
        "past" => "Your efforts have laid the foundation for your success. Keeping your resourcefulness and efficiency is key to moving forward.",
        "present" => "Offering help may bring new projects or ideas, so don't delay in accepting it. Interacting with people who have more resources than you will bring long-term success.",
        "future" => "The work ahead of you will present intellectual or spiritual challenges. To succeed, you must be able to think creatively or invent a path forward.",
    ],
    25 =>
    [
        "id" => 26,
        "type_id" => 1,
        "number" => 25,
        "name" => "Four of Wands",
        "upright_keyword" => "Community, Family, Celebration, Gathering, Stability, Sense of Belonging",
        "reversed_keyword" => "Lack of Support, Instability, Feeling Unwelcome, Transience, Lack of Roots, Family Conflict",
        "astrology" => "",
        "element" => "Fire Element",
        "image_key" => "25_Four_of_Wands",
        "content" => "The Four of Wands depicts a couple dancing beneath a welcoming wreath tied between four crystal-tipped wands. There is a garland on the card, similar to those specific to traditional Jewish ceremonies. It seems there is a party happening, indicating you are enjoying a period of stability and peace, and a sense of completion, especially after a difficult phase. You are reveling in the glory of your success, celebrating with family and friends.

  If you have set a high goal for yourself, this card suggests you take time to enjoy the lighter moments in life instead of rushing. It also reminds you to acknowledge the significant milestones you have achieved, as such accomplishments are not easy in one's life.",
        "upright_content" => "The overall meaning of the Four of Wands is that it heralds celebrations and a harmonious, happy, and relaxed family environment. In numerology, the number four symbolizes stability and a particularly reliable foundation. These all relate to a period of happiness and balance.

  The symbolism in the Four of Wands suggests that this is the best time to get together with close people, such as friends and family. This may or may not be for any special occasion. Known to reflect a holiday period, this card often comes up when you spend extended time with friends and family. It can also suggest that you invite your closest friends for a lavish and intimate dinner, sharing a few laughs.

  Additionally, if you have been working on a project, this card signifies reaching a particularly important milestone. This will give you a reason to celebrate, which should be considered. You have successfully completed the appropriate and most crucial phase of the project, meaning you have every reason to feel proud and fulfilled, which is one of the general feelings the Four of Wands invokes and reflects.",
        "reversed_content" => "If the upright position of the card reflects balance, stability, and harmony, the reversed position of the Four of Wands means there is a breakdown or complete lack of harmony in your home or family. There is likely a lot of tension between your family or other close loved ones. If you have accomplished something important to you and expected to share it with those closest to you and come home to a welcoming celebration, you might instead find a lack of support. This can leave you feeling quite uncertain about your relationships and what you can and cannot rely on.",
        "upright_love" => "This card is one of family, reunions, and celebrations. The Four of Wands tarot love meaning can bring engagements, marriages, or other gatherings that commemorate you and your love. If your relationship is built on a solid foundation of trust, support, and understanding, your union may be further solidified with the support and witness of family and friends. This love is not just between two individuals but a love that is supported in a larger community context. If you are single, you may find love within these communities and gatherings.",
        "reversed_love" => "Some conflicts may arise concerning family and your romantic life at the moment. The Four of Wands tarot love meaning can indicate incompatibility between your partner and your family, or between how you approach love and romance. Sometimes, as this card is also one of deepening your commitments on a more public level, there may be some fear and hesitation about taking these follow-up steps. Change, especially tying yourself to another person, can be wonderful, rewarding, and also frightening. These feelings can coexist, but only you can know if it comes from a deeper place rather than just cold feet.",
        "upright_career" => "The upright Four of Wands is a card of stable social relations. When upright, it denotes stable and supportive relationships. This sense of community applies to the work environment in this position. You may have made new friends at work, or the atmosphere has been particularly positive recently. In the near future, there might also be some work-related gatherings, such as office parties, aimed at bringing you closer to the people you work with. If so, these events will likely lead to stronger bonds between you and your colleagues.",
        "reversed_career" => "When reversed, the joyful nature of the Four of Wands is overturned. As a result, you may find your relationships at work strained or difficult to form. This difficulty applies to the overall atmosphere of your office; or it could relate to a specific moment or point of tension at work. For instance, there may be upcoming office events, but they might not go as planned. They could have the opposite effect of fostering camaraderie. If there are no specific issues in your work environment, the card might highlight the general state of your office. Perhaps the atmosphere is unpleasant or unfriendly. In any case, expect some rude behavior from those you work with, and be aware of these behaviors in yourself.",
        "upright_finances" => "The Four of Wands here represents not only financial stability but also suggests you can spend this money on your loved ones. You might be buying gifts or taking people you care about out for meals or drinks. These are good financial decisions. They might not increase your financial wealth, but they benefit your social relationships, so you can embrace them. Don't go overboard on anything, but as long as you live within your means, the cards encourage you to treat those around you well.",
        "reversed_finances" => "If you find the Four of Wands here, you might be struggling with poor financial conditions. Your financial problems might be related to your personal relationships. Family expenses may be overwhelming you right now. These unforeseen expenses might make it particularly challenging to make ends meet at this time. Be wary of friends or family asking for money you cannot afford to give. Question whether the money is necessary or just their wish. If it is the latter, consider getting your finances under control before helping them.",
        "yes_no" => "While tarot cards are primarily used for detailed divination, they can also be used for yes/no answers, though many people are unaware of this fact. The Four of Wands answers 'yes' to your question, as it symbolizes positivity, harmony, kindness, and the joy of new beginnings.",
        "past" => "Your perseverance has led to success, and you have reason to feel fulfilled and satisfied with your achievements. The seeds you planted in the past and watered through relentless effort have now grown into blossoming plants of victory. You should analyze your past choices, note what you did right to get to this point, and keep your future ambitions in mind to cultivate good habits that will allow you to achieve similar success in the coming months or years.",
        "present" => "It is most important now that you embrace happiness and make room for it in your heart: spend time with family and friends, and have them by your side during difficult times; likewise, ensure you are there for them when they need you. Everything is falling into place, hard work is paying off, and if you continue as you are now, you will succeed. No matter what the future holds, know that there are people who love you in your life, and you are not alone.",
        "future" => "If you continue on the path you are on, you will achieve your dreams and fulfill your ambitions, but don't get too caught up in future plans: remember to enjoy the present, and the choices you make now will affect what happens later. Contentment, good fortune, and success are all flowing towards you on a river of prosperity.",
    ],
    26 =>
    [
        "id" => 27,
        "type_id" => 1,
        "number" => 26,
        "name" => "Five of Wands",
        "upright_keyword" => "Conflict, Competition, Arguments, Aggression, Tension, Rivals, Inner Conflict",
        "reversed_keyword" => "End of Conflict, Cooperation, Agreement, Truce, Harmony, Peace, Avoiding Conflict",
        "astrology" => "",
        "element" => "Fire Element",
        "image_key" => "26_Five_of_Wands",
        "content" => "The Five of Wands depicts five men each holding their own wands and waving them in the air. Like most of the fives in the tarot, it is about some sort of disagreement the querent is facing. This disagreement can be seen as a sign of conflict among the men, or they may just be enjoying the adrenaline rush this conflict brings, where their competition is a friendly rivalry rather than anger. The casual way they hold their wands gives a sense that this argument might be more of a performance than a fierce dispute.",
        "upright_content" => "From the imagery on the card, the Five of Wands' symbolism suggests that there is conflict in a person's life. This could be an existing conflict or one that is brewing and will eventually erupt in front of them. It may also describe problems in communication, such as in situations where no one is actually listening to each other - meaning there is no agreement or understanding. The five people might signify problems within a group where patience is running thin, and everyone just wants to be heard, without listening to anyone else, causing a lot of arguments all at once.

  Most of the issues could be resolved if the querent takes the first step to try to communicate in a way that suggests everyone should take turns to speak and be heard. By doing this, you will be able to address the problem, and everyone will feel satisfied.

  The Five of Wands can also suggest that you are or will be facing competition in an area you are not used to. This can be at work or school, where you will meet people with the same abilities as you, presenting a significant challenge - leading to feelings of jealousy, greed, and envy. This tarot card encourages you to embrace the competition and use it as a way to improve yourself without holding any malice towards them. It suggests that you should learn how to deal with them in a civilized manner.

  The meaning of the Five of Wands can also be a personal struggle you are dealing with on your own. This could involve several issues affecting you, requiring you to resolve them and find solutions for them. You need to pinpoint where the problems are and come up with solutions to deal with them.",
        "reversed_content" => "The reversed meaning of the Five of Wands could indicate that your natural way of dealing with disagreements is to avoid any form of conflict by leaving the place as quickly as possible. While this can sometimes be seen as a good thing, other times it can lead to many issues brewing inside you that need to be addressed as soon as possible. On the other hand, it could also mean that you have resolved your troubles and have no more issues to worry about.",
        "upright_love" => "When it comes to your love life, you need to take action now. If you are single, you might have many suitors competing against each other. While the attention can be flattering, don't add unnecessary drama; this can push potential partners away rather than bringing them closer. If you are already in a relationship, there might be some minor conflicts. Be aware that what starts as playful teasing can turn into explosive arguments if either of you is under stress. Most likely, the arguments here are not very serious. Nonetheless, they require a light-hearted approach to remember how unimportant they actually are to your happiness. Keep things fun.",
        "reversed_love" => "How you handle conflict can now affect your relationships. If you are in a relationship, ensure you are not suppressing your resentments to avoid conflict, which is what you both need to build a smooth couple's relationship. Ultimately avoiding tough conversations can lead to a weakening of trust. Remember, everyone has the right to have their needs met, and having needs does not make you any less lovable. However, if you have been struggling to express yourself honestly to your partner, you might find misunderstandings dissipating. Once honesty and clarity are achieved, the arguments that once existed might disappear.",
        "upright_career" => "If you find the Five of Wands in this position, the conflict and competitive nature of this card apply to your career. This could be permanent due to the nature of your work. This card is common among workers in industries such as sales, banking, and athletics. If not, and your work does not have a competitive component, it may be a temporary state caused by conflicts over a specific issue. You may be competing with someone for a raise or position. Regardless of the specific conflict you are currently facing, you will need to contend with others' egos. Thanks to the presence of the five figures here in an upright position, it is clear that you can overcome the challenges ahead and dispel anything that tries to block your path. Remember, you can succeed.",
        "reversed_career" => "Reversed, the Five of Wands means that recent conflict and competition in your work life are coming to an end. You might be moving to a less competitive industry, or your surroundings may be becoming more friendly and relaxed. Either way, it is a welcome change. This easing of recent work conflicts allows you to focus your energy on other aspects of life.",
        "upright_finances" => "If you see the Five of Wands here, you might be experiencing financial instability. This is temporary, but you will need to work hard to get out of it. The nature of this battle might involve putting in extra effort at work or otherwise working very hard to get your finances under control. If your current state isn't unbalanced, you may soon be arguing over money. These arguments could be with loved ones or strangers, such as clerks or salespeople. You may find simple tasks like returning items or getting refunds stressful and contentious.",
        "reversed_finances" => "You are finally getting out of financial trouble and making a comeback, heading into a more stable period. Now it is a priority to address any issues related to money and property to make up for previous losses.",
        "yes_no" => "The Five of Wands signifies being challenged in some way and having to protect yourself from others. It brings feelings of struggle, anxiety, and overall unease about upcoming inner battles. The negative foreboding brought by this card gives a negative answer.",
        "past" => "An important consequence or fight may arise due to past events, as old memories cause interference and prevent you from moving forward. Don't waste time finding the cause and focusing on your goals.",
        "present" => "Poor communication or misunderstandings will hinder your progress.",
        "future" => "An opportunity in the future will require you to tame your courage to succeed. No one but you can decide your actions, so rely on your willpower to achieve balanced progress.",
    ],
    27 =>
    [
        "id" => 28,
        "type_id" => 1,
        "number" => 27,
        "name" => "Six of Wands",
        "upright_keyword" => "Success, Victory, Triumph, Reward, Recognition, Praise, Acclaim, Pride",
        "reversed_keyword" => "Failure, Lack of Recognition, No Reward, Lack of Achievement",
        "astrology" => "",
        "element" => "Fire Element",
        "image_key" => "27_Six_of_Wands",
        "content" => "The Six of Wands tarot card depicts a man crowned with a wreath of victory. He is shown riding a horse through a crowd of cheering people. The horse is white, a well-known symbol of strength, purity, and success. The crowd suggests public recognition of the rider's achievements. The man's wand is also decorated with a wreath, further emphasizing his success. This person is not afraid or shy of the attention but rather proud of his accomplishments. The crowd reacts with joy and enthusiasm.",
        "upright_content" => "This particular card signifies gaining recognition, victory, and success. You have not only managed to accomplish all your goals successfully, but you are also receiving public acknowledgment for those goals and the results you have achieved. You might have received an award or some sort of public acclaim.

  This card indicates that you have successfully utilized your inner strengths and talents to bring about particularly successful outcomes in your life. You have managed to overcome the confusion previously brought by the Five of Wands and have successfully reduced interference, allowing you to focus on your goals and achieve them.

  It is also worth noting that aside from the overall positivity brought by the card, there is a slight downside. It can bring arrogance and a sense of conceit, leading you to believe that no one is better than you.",
        "reversed_content" => "When the card is reversed, it suggests that you might find yourself doubting all your abilities and the overall potential to achieve any success. You might feel particularly negative about your entire self, as though you have let others down and they have let you down. This is a sign that you lack the confidence and motivation needed to achieve. You need comprehensive support and recognition from a third party to provide you with some much-needed emotional strength.",
        "upright_love" => "If you are single, the Six of Wands tarot card love meaning suggests that success is coming your way. Others may find you particularly attractive right now. If you have been looking for someone, they might be more receptive to you than usual. All it requires is for you to make your approach. If you are in a relationship and have been working towards something together, such as moving in together after a long-distance relationship or buying a house, these goals are likely to be realized. The future between you two seems bright, bringing you both much happiness.",
        "reversed_love" => "Your confidence may be low right now; the reversed Six of Wands tarot card love meaning suggests that you are not receiving the love you think you deserve. You might feel overlooked while your rivals, who may not be as loving and caring as you, find success. Often, what is needed is a change in attitude; make sure this does not turn into bitterness. Confidence and positivity are attractive, while negativity often repels others. If you are in a relationship, you or your partner might feel unappreciated or neglected.",
        "upright_career" => "The Six of Wands is typically a very positive card symbolizing success and confidence. When appearing in this position, these principles apply to your work life. You are likely to have achieved something in your job that you are particularly proud of. Rewards may also be forthcoming; this could mean an upcoming promotion or raise or one that has recently occurred. If you have recently completed a project, it is likely to have a positive outcome. Whatever battles you have fought recently have been resolved in your favor. Enjoy the satisfaction and confidence of this moment. Do not let your confidence venture into arrogance, but do celebrate the end of previous conflicts and enjoy your current position.",
        "reversed_career" => "When reversed, the success usually associated with the Six of Wands is overturned. In this position, the Six of Wands represents failure and a lack of ambition in your work, rather than indicating victory. You may have been overlooked for a promotion or raise. If there has been conflict or competition at work recently, it may not have or will not resolve in your favor. If there is no specific moment of tension, this six may refer to your general feelings about work. These feelings will manifest as a lack of progress or interest in projects. Due to a lack of motivation, you might feel stuck in your current position. Regardless of the exact background, this is a sign of poor performance.",
        "upright_finances" => "If this card appears here, your financial situation is good. You are currently enjoying a moment of peace and financial stability due to your dedication and perseverance during difficult times. This is a time to appreciate your hard work and value their rewards. Feel free to indulge in moderation but be wary of overconfidence. Reckless spending is never wise.",
        "reversed_finances" => "If the Six of Wands appears in this position, take some time to reassess your financial situation. Your finances may be taking a downturn. This might be due to a single negative event or more broadly representing your economic condition. If it is the former, an investment you made might not be yielding results, or a purchase you made is not what you expected. If no individual investment or purchase is causing your financial assets to decrease, your funds might be slowly dwindling. While this might not be a crisis, you could be going through a tough period. It might be hard to muster the confidence to believe things will get better. Work to make your financial efforts productive and proactive.",
        "yes_no" => "The Six of Wands showcases the victory, triumph, and success of your efforts. It indicates someone feeling exalted for winning and finding the inspiration needed to move forward. The overall feeling this card brings is good news. The answer is yes.",
        "past" => "Your past efforts and inspirations have brought you to your current position. Continue on your path, and you will find rewards.",
        "present" => "Good news is coming. Though it may be conditional, this change will greatly aid you in your pursuit of fulfillment.",
        "future" => "Victory awaits you at the end of your journey. Finding it will require careful navigation and clearing obstacles, but everything you want is achievable.",
    ],
    28 =>
    [
        "id" => 29,
        "type_id" => 1,
        "number" => 28,
        "name" => "Seven of Wands",
        "upright_keyword" => "Defend Yourself, Stand Up for Yourself, Protect Yourself, Protect Territory",
        "reversed_keyword" => "Giving Up, Admitting Defeat, Yielding, Lack of Confidence, Surrender",
        "astrology" => "",
        "element" => "Fire Element",
        "image_key" => "28_Seven_of_Wands",
        "content" => "The Seven of Wands depicts a man standing on top of a hill, challenged by opponents below. He appears to be defending this position and retaliating. Interestingly, in the Rider-Waite depiction of the Seven of Wands, the man wears two different shoes. This relates to the symbolism of being on uneven ground or not having a stable footing in life.",
        "upright_content" => "The meaning of the Seven of Wands is similar to that of the Five of Wands; both cards indicate a struggle after the initial completion and satisfaction of events. However, the Seven of Wands is different because it is about the struggle you need to go through to maintain your position, rather than attaining it. It is about the difficulties you face to continue your success. You should be ready to face the competition to defend your title and prove yourself. This person is the epitome of defense, endurance, and determination. The mismatched shoes refer to unstable foundations in life, with no clear stance. The six wands depict fierceness and challenges.

  The overall meaning of the Seven of Wands is to stand your ground, no matter what challenges you face. You will need to defend this position and oppose those who aim to take your place. There are setbacks during this time, but you need to keep fighting for your beliefs and face those who might threaten or oppose you and your beliefs.",
        "reversed_content" => "The reversed meaning of the Seven of Wands is that you might be overwhelmed by all the responsibilities and challenges you face. This can make it difficult to see the whole picture. You may also feel that you have to compete and compare yourself with others, making you feel vulnerable and inadequate.

  The reversed Seven of Wands can also reflect the feeling of being constantly criticized and judged by others. Your friends and family might be questioning your decisions and choices, and you feel overwhelmed by their judgment.

  Avoiding conflict and backing down is common in the reversed Seven of Wands. This leads to unhappiness, as you evade activities and abandon your goals when challenged by anyone. Remember all the struggles you went through to get here, and carefully consider if you truly believe it is worth giving up now. Another interpretation of the reversed Seven of Wands could be that you are being overly aggressive in protecting yourself and, by doing so, damaging your relationships.",
        "upright_love" => "When this card appears in a love tarot reading, you may have to set boundaries, even if it might cause some uncomfortable situations. If you are with a partner, you might find yourself in a position where you must fight for your relationship. There may be opposition from other parties; family members, other suitors, friends who oppose the two of you being together. Despite many external factors in your environment working against the two of you, you may need to put in a lot of effort to keep the relationship going. Despite all these factors, you might feel confident that this is the right thing to do. Hold on to that feeling, as it will help keep you energized when things get tough.",
        "reversed_love" => "Being overly defensive might be working against you. The reversed Seven of Wands tarot card love meaning can suggest that the relationship you are working so hard to maintain might indeed be on shaky ground. Others around you may clearly see this; people who care about your well-being. Conversely, you might be ignoring these concerns and may be in denial. Love might make it hard for you to see the truth. Or, even if the two of you are together for the right reasons, you might find it increasingly difficult to stay together amidst the outside forces trying to pull you apart.",
        "upright_career" => "Generally, the upright Seven of Wands symbolizes challenges and perseverance. If the Seven of Wands appears here, these ideas apply to your work life. While it sounds daunting, this card doesn't need to be negative. When upright, it indicates that you can tackle (though perhaps caught off guard) the problems you're about to face. Others may attack you or be envious of your job position. Embrace your inner confidence and move forward fearlessly. Challenges to your position or your ethics may be especially common now. Fortunately, you have the strength to overcome any fears or concerns and successfully stand up for yourself and your beliefs.",
        "reversed_career" => "When the Seven of Wands appears in the tarot, your attempts to stand your ground may not be successful. This could be due to a lack of preparation. You might not be ready to defend your past victories, your principles, or your stance. Now, it is crucial to protect your job position or business, but you are unwilling or unprepared to do so. People often envy success, so merely being content with the status quo is not enough. Sometimes, like now, you may need to be on guard against those who try to undermine you. Any recent choices you made have left you vulnerable to others intruding and stealing the opportunities you are trying to create.",
        "upright_finances" => "This position and direction of the Seven of Wands are associated with the success of long-term investments. This could mean that you are benefiting from past efforts and/or future efforts. You might be displaying financial foresight at this time. While your position is currently stable, you are well aware of the fleeting nature of this stability and are taking measures to safeguard your income. This financial planning could be in the form of starting a retirement fund, buying a house, or otherwise beginning to save more. Whatever form your investments take, these choices will serve you in the future (as they have in the past). The Seven of Wands is also associated with others being envious; thus, don't be surprised if people covet your financial success.",
        "reversed_finances" => "If you find the Seven of Wands here, be careful with frivolity. Don't let yourself become overly confident about your financial stability. Regardless of your income, economic downturns are part of life. The Seven of Wands serves as a reminder of this. It warns against wasting your income on useless purchases when you should be saving and considering the future. Even if you tend to and are capable of blind spending, such activities are never recommended, especially now.",
        "yes_no" => "The Seven of Wands represents long-term success due to its strength in overcoming obstacles and taking calculated risks. Standing up for yourself with courage is what this card is all about. The answer you seek is yes.",
        "past" => "Despite slow progress, your determination and continuous efforts will lead you steadily forward. Don't give up!",
        "present" => "A major conflict is approaching, but don't be afraid. With courage, you will overcome this obstacle and experience significant changes in your life.",
        "future" => "Continue to believe in yourself. Things may not be in your favor, but you have the power to defeat them. Fighting and accepting challenges will lead you to a bright future.",
    ],
    29 =>
    [
        "id" => 30,
        "type_id" => 1,
        "number" => 29,
        "name" => "Eight of Wands",
        "upright_keyword" => "Movement, Speed, Progress, Quick Decisions, Sudden Changes, Excitement",
        "reversed_keyword" => "Waiting, Slowdown, Confusion, Delays, Loss of Momentum, Haste, Unpreparedness",
        "astrology" => "",
        "element" => "Fire Element",
        "image_key" => "29_Eight_of_Wands",
        "content" => "The Eight of Wands depicts eight flying wands that appear to be suspended in mid-air. Some may see them as blooming wands moving forward at maximum speed. They traverse a background of clear skies, representing a path to their destination without any obstacles. It showcases a majestic landscape of a river, injecting life into the image. The wands also appear to be about to land, marking the end of a long journey.",
        "upright_content" => "The image depicted by the Eight of Wands suggests that the struggles brought on by the Seven of Wands are finally ending. It symbolizes high energy levels, indicating that different aspects of your life will be pioneering. Perhaps important news will be coming your way, and you may experience sudden and steady positive growth. The meaning of the Eight of Wands can also relate to your work. A decision you have been waiting for is likely to come soon. You need to be patient.

  In terms of love, the meaning of the Eight of Wands is about whether you are ready to commit to a relationship; however, the card advises you not to force the other party to be ready for commitment. Your partner will soon be ready, and forcing things to happen may have a negative impact on the outcome. Financially, now does not seem to be the best time for hasty investments. As with your love life, it is advisable to be patient. Save your funds and wait for the best investment opportunity. Everything you have been striving for is continuously evolving. Where you previously saw no progress, you will soon find that they pave the way for a wave of upcoming actions.",
        "reversed_content" => "Like the upright Eight of Wands, the reversed meaning of the Eight of Wands usually relates to patience. You may feel frustrated about something. You may now see that the actions you initiated previously have caused the obstacles you are now discovering. It is time for you to realize that you cannot change the past. You must forgive yourself and adjust your strategy.

  In terms of work, there may be disagreements in your office. You need to resolve this issue quickly to avoid any major problems from derailing. Breathe, think, and try to relax. Be patient and trust that everything will be fine. The reversed Eight of Wands meaning in love may relate to possible jealousy. The jealousy you feel now is unfounded and will only affect your good relationship with your partner. In terms of health and spirit, you need to improve your focus, cooperation, and determination. If you lose focus, the card's energy will dissipate.",
        "upright_love" => "If you find your love life stagnant, you will be relieved to see vitality and excitement again. If you are single, you will find your romantic life starting up again; a new lover might spark romance, and your love life might even develop at an astonishing pace. Ensure you are ready to harness this sometimes-crazy energy. If you are in an existing relationship, there may be surprises that bring excitement to both of you. These surprises are likely to be welcome, and other cards in the tarot spread will provide more background information.",
        "reversed_love" => "Misunderstandings, the reversed Eight of Wands tarot card love meaning. Whether single or partnered, consider carefully what you say or do. Your relationship with your partner lacks passion and communication. Neither of you is willing to talk about your issues, leading to further misunderstandings. It indicates that the sexual relationship between you has not developed as expected, often due to frequent arguments or letting jealousy undermine the hard-earned trust between you.",
        "upright_career" => "The Eight of Wands represents moving quickly forward. Applied to your career, this principle can mean literal or figurative quick movement. Physically, this card can sometimes indicate that you are about to travel for work. If not, you might feel a broader sense of progress in your work. You may feel that your career is developing rapidly. This is a positive feeling for you now. It's like you're bursting out of your shell, finally able to make the impact you want. This progress is exciting and invigorating. Move forward confidently, and you will continue to exceed expectations.",
        "reversed_career" => "In this position, the Eight of Wands has two meanings that can apply to your career. Either you are not progressing fast enough at work, or you progressed too quickly in the past. Evaluate how you feel. If you feel frustrated by a lack of progress at work, this card may indicate that you missed opportunities by failing to act in time. You are not progressing because you let opportunities slip by. However, if you have recently progressed in your career, you may have moved too fast. This concern manifests as feeling overwhelmed by people's demands on you. If projects seem daunting, discussing how others handle such tasks might be helpful. You will learn to handle new responsibilities, but it takes time and patience.",
        "upright_finances" => "The speed associated with the Eight of Wands applies to your money in this position. It seems that money is disappearing from your hands as quickly as it is coming in. This tendency itself is neither good nor bad. It depends on your ability to remember how much is coming in and how much is going out. While particularly tempting now, if you see this card here, be cautious of impulse spending. Be mindful not to choose high-risk investments.",
        "reversed_finances" => "The Eight of Wands here means you may feel frustrated with the pace of incoming funds. You might feel that funds are insufficient or should be flowing in faster. The card's message is that you should be more patient and remember that everything you do is part of your slow progress. The small investments you make today will eventually pay off (even if they are frustrating now). If your job is not going as well as you would like, it may be that you are still paying your dues. One day you might get the job (and income) you want, but today you need to be patient.",
        "yes_no" => "The Eight of Wands represents a journey or travel of some kind. It implies events that will unfold rapidly and opportunities that will arrive unpredictably. While overcoming obstacles, it indicates and ends some kind of delay or blockage in your life. The answer to your question is most likely yes.",
        "past" => "Past goals will not push you forward. Think of a change that will bring you the greatest happiness. The struggle that has occupied you will pass, followed by a brief peace.",
        "present" => "Exciting news is coming, breaking your current tranquility. With nothing happening in your life, you want to break the routine and quickly do something exciting. It's recommended to engage in something productive rather than wandering.",
        "future" => "A new adventure will bring future success, but you must be prepared to make the right choices in sudden decisions.",
    ],
    30 =>
    [
        "id" => 31,
        "type_id" => 1,
        "number" => 30,
        "name" => "Nine of Wands",
        "upright_keyword" => "Last Stand, Persistence, Perseverance, Resilience, Nearing Success, Fatigue",
        "reversed_keyword" => "Stubbornness, Rigidity, Defensiveness, Refusal to Compromise, Giving Up",
        "astrology" => "",
        "element" => "Fire Element",
        "image_key" => "30_Nine_of_Wands",
        "content" => "The Nine of Wands depicts a man who appears weak and holding a wand, with eight upright wands standing behind him. The man looks injured, but he seems ready to fight again and eager for victory. He is filled with hope and determination, which should help him get through the final battle. This card combines challenges, hope, and victory.",
        "upright_content" => "The Nine of Wands tarot card symbolizes great hope, even in the face of many issues that may unbalance them. The Nine of Wands represents a person who has gone through many trials in life, but through determination and willpower, they have been able to overcome these challenges. The eight upright wands symbolize these victorious battles; however, this person may face more tests. It might be a significant test or challenge they should face to achieve their goals or succeed in their pursuits. This card is a sign of hope and encouragement, urging you to face your trials bravely so you can succeed.

  The Nine of Wands may also indicate that someone has become distrustful due to betrayal. This may be because something has happened many times, making it seem hopeless at first glance. However, there is hope and courage here, believing that this outlook is about to change. Someone or something might enter their life, changing their overall view of past struggles. It encourages people to take this adventurous step as they might be surprised.",
        "reversed_content" => "The reversed Nine of Wands shows that a person might not be an adventurer; they might avoid making long-term moves or commitments because they fear they might not get out of the situation. They are distrustful and therefore build barriers between themselves and others, becoming their personal prison. You might worry that you don't have enough resources to face upcoming challenges, which is why you might avoid or evade them.

  However, this is a situation that needs to change, as it may be self-imposed limits preventing you from reaching new heights necessary for growth. It encourages you to be brave but also careful not to make reckless or hasty decisions that might cost you in the future.

  The Nine of Wands can indicate significant personal fears or mindsets that may affect you. Therefore, it's important to take steps to address it before fear consumes you and prevents you from moving forward.",
        "upright_love" => "You are prepared and strategized, now ready to face the upcoming challenges. The Nine of Wands tarot love meaning signifies that you recognize that the love you desire requires a lot of effort, self-improvement, and sacrifice. This is, in fact, the essence of all love. Many people think love is just a feeling, but it comes from two lovers willing to adapt and solve problems together as a team. It's constant communication and adjustment. This recognition is now coming your way, and you are preparing for it. Regarding your romantic life, you are also likely to take a big step forward. Are you proposing? Or suggesting to your partner that you take the next step together? The Nine of Wands tarot love meaning indicates that if you work hard, you will succeed.",
        "reversed_love" => "All the preparation and work you have done in your romantic life may not yield the expected results. The reversed Nine of Wands tarot love meaning suggests that despite your best efforts, the relationship you have been fighting for has left you exhausted. Disagreements are natural, as you are two different people, but make sure you are not the only one willing to do the work; both parties must be willing to compromise and meet halfway for a successful relationship. If you are single, you may also want to ensure that the boundaries you set for yourself are not preventing others from coming in.",
        "upright_career" => "Here, as in every position, the Nine of Wands signifies mid-battle. You haven't finished these struggles yet, but they will soon end. Currently, you may feel exhausted. The battle is ongoing, but you might feel too tired to continue much longer. Let this card remind you that any troubles you are encountering in your career are temporary. Perhaps your recent workload has been particularly heavy, but it will lighten. Whenever your troubles ease, you will see that you have the strength to fight to the end. You can persist, but the battle is not yet won.",
        "reversed_career" => "If you find the reversed Nine of Wands here, you might feel exhausted and burned out at work. Whatever battles you have recently fought at work have left you drained. Remember, work is only part of your life. Try to recharge the energy you can gather at work or other areas of life. Additionally, be aware of your failure to compromise, as this might be the root of your exhaustion. Fighting against your morals is particularly tiring, so be mindful when engaging in such work struggles. Whether you are fighting against your morals is an external conflict, it might be a struggle against an unrelenting tide. Recognize when you are exhausted from a futile fight. Sometimes, changing course is the best way to end the conflict. This is not necessarily a failure. Change is part of growth. Self-criticism helps determine whether you are strong or stubborn.",
        "upright_finances" => "The Nine of Wands can foreshadow financial issues. You may not be in financial turmoil, but you are under some pressure. Considering withdrawing funds from your savings or other sources like loans or borrowing from someone might be enough. Instead of depleting your savings or otherwise harming your financial situation, consider finding additional income sources. (If you work in shifts, work overtime or otherwise consider overtime.) This doesn't have to be a permanent change. You will soon get out of this financial pressure. However, until then, you must face your financial situation with determination and motivation.",
        "reversed_finances" => "If you find the reversed Nine of Wands here, it indicates that you need to take responsibility for your financial situation. Avoiding money issues might be particularly tempting now, but don't do it. Escaping reality is tempting but ultimately destructive. Don't let these things sway you, as it will harm your financial future. For example, if you feel pressured by debt, don't waste money on travel. Financial responsibility at this time also means paying particular attention to your valuables. If you don't take care of them now, you may find them missing.",
        "yes_no" => "The Nine of Wands showcases determination and courage under fire. However, it also indicates the need for caution and defensiveness in battles that have yet to come. There is no clear indication of whether these things will have a more positive or negative outcome, so the answer is maybe.",
        "past" => "The struggles you have gone through have given you some stability in the present. By evaluating others' reactions, your progress will be smoother, but this strategy will not lead to sustainable ease.",
        "present" => "Some encouragement from a friend or loved one will help you overcome the challenges you face.",
        "future" => "An inevitable conflict in the future is approaching, but you can overcome it. To succeed, rely on your inner strength and avoid sacrificing your values for short-term gains.",
    ],
    31 =>
    [
        "id" => 32,
        "type_id" => 1,
        "number" => 31,
        "name" => "Ten of Wands",
        "upright_keyword" => "Burden, Responsibility, Obligation, Pressure, Duty, Exhaustion, Struggle",
        "reversed_keyword" => "Unable to Let Go, Taking on Too Much, Collapse",
        "astrology" => "",
        "element" => "Fire Element",
        "image_key" => "31_Ten_of_Wands",
        "content" => "The image on the Ten of Wands depicts a man carrying a heavy load of wooden sticks, bundled together in the form of ten wands, as he approaches a town that is not too far away. The image on the Ten of Wands indicates a person who has struggled and succeeded in life and is now bringing the harvest to his final destination. Although the destination is not near, it suggests that he has completed the hardest part of his life struggle, and he just needs a place to relax and bask in his success.",
        "upright_content" => "This card indicates that you have completed a cycle of struggle. After spending too many resources and a lot of energy seeking success, you have finally overcome the obstacles. The sweat on your forehead is worth it, and your efforts have finally paid off. You may find yourself living in a world of abundance, where there is no poverty or suffering.

  Although it sounds great and satisfying, this card depicts many responsibilities around you. You are now the sole problem solver in your family and friend circle, which can even lead you into another world full of challenges. At this point, you also bear the responsibility of maintaining success. The business you have started is booming and keeps you on your toes. The main issue is that if you lose control, these problems can overwhelm you, requiring you to ensure you know how to prioritize and address relevant issues.

  In the real world, this card expresses how people try to take on responsibilities after achieving initial success. It's like graduating from college, finding a job, and then starting to succeed in the real world. More challenges follow, and you may find yourself taking care of parents, starting a family, while also looking out for others, which can make you feel like you haven't succeeded. It becomes a burden, as at some point you will find that nothing is enough to accomplish all these duties. The general lesson of this card is that one must moderate, prioritize, and understand that not everything can be solved; some things must be let go and given to others to share the burden.",
        "reversed_content" => "When the Ten of Wands is reversed, it indicates that you are truly overwhelmed by unnecessary circumstances in your life. Look around and see what is bothering you, and even if you correct it, it won't have a positive impact on yourself. Let them go and be a free person who can think clearly and act accurately. Anything that does not add value to your life is not worth your time, so let it go.",
        "upright_love" => "The Ten of Wands tarot love meaning suggests that love may feel like a heavy burden. Other aspects of your life, such as work or finances, may have recently stressed you, making it difficult to be romantic. Sometimes, the pressure can make your love life feel like just another burden you must bear rather than something that can help you bear your burdens. If you are in a relationship, don't be afraid to seek help. It can alleviate your lover's worries, ease your worries, and create an opportunity for you two to become closer. If you are single, don't be afraid to spend some time alone; everyone needs to focus on themselves before they can focus on finding a partner. Take good care of yourself.",
        "reversed_love" => "You and your partner are meant to bear the burdens of life together. Not sharing the heavy load can lead to the deterioration of your relationship. One person may hoard all the responsibilities instead of working as a team, perhaps out of good intentions, believing it can protect the other from stress, or worse, not believing the other is capable of providing help. If it's you, trust your partner; give them the opportunity to help you. When someone loves you, they want to see you happy, helping you will not be a burden but a joy.",
        "upright_career" => "The Ten of Wands is a card of burden. This principle can easily be applied to your work life. When upright, the Ten of Wands indicates you feel overworked. It could be that you have too many projects to handle by yourself. See if you can delegate your burden to others or share it with them. Collaboration and delegation will be your greatest help at this time. Don't be afraid to seek help or talk about uneven work distribution. If your current workload isn't particularly heavy, you may find the tasks at hand unusually difficult or exhausting. If you need help, you can still seek it.",
        "reversed_career" => "In this context, the Ten of Wands represents the end of a work burden. This relief from stress can come in two ways. One way to achieve this is through successful delegation of work. Potentially, you realize that it is too much for one person. By better distributing most of your previous concerns to a group, they won't have a severe negative impact on any individual, and you can relax a bit. If you haven't delegated responsibilities when needed, you may collapse under the pressure of too many demands. Either way, you will no longer be overworked, and there will be a quiet time to recover.",
        "upright_finances" => "If you find the Ten of Wands upright regarding finances, you will have financial burdens. This can take many forms. You may be struggling to pay off debts or have other outstanding balances to consider. Large expenses, such as school or business loans, may be particularly pressing now. You may discuss with someone how best to address these issues. Don't do anything reckless or generally undesirable, but know that professionals may have reliable solutions that can help you achieve long-term success.",
        "reversed_finances" => "The Ten of Wands, when reversed here, has two potential meanings. It may be that you are emerging from a period of financial difficulty. If you have taken steps to address the core issues disrupting your finances, this ten may indicate that you can finally gain control of the situation. As a result, your financial situation will soon improve. Alternatively, if you haven't worked to understand what has disturbed your finances, you may be falling into deeper economic distress. This card is closely related to your life, so consider how much control you have over your finances to determine its meaning. Sometimes other cards can help suggest which of the two interpretations is correct. However, more likely, if you can't answer what steps you've taken to control your finances, it's likely you haven't taken decisive enough action.",
        "yes_no" => "The Ten of Wands is a card highly associated with feeling immense pressure and overburdened in some aspect of life. Other possible things this card suggests are feelings of being trapped, oppressed, or unable to control your surroundings. The answer is no.",
        "past" => "The strength you have developed over years of struggle will guide you in solving current problems. The recent letting go of negative emotions will lead you to form a new philosophy.",
        "present" => "Hang in there and see the challenges through. If you have been disconnected from someone close to you, expect an opportunity to reconnect.",
        "future" => "Concentrate your energy in one direction and consolidate your efforts; success will be easier to achieve. You will have the opportunity to realize your desires, but you must first reach your lofty goals.",
    ],
    32 =>
    [
        "id" => 33,
        "type_id" => 1,
        "number" => 32,
        "name" => "Page of Wands",
        "upright_keyword" => "Adventure, Excitement, Fresh Ideas, Cheerful, Energetic, Fearless, Outgoing",
        "reversed_keyword" => "Hasty, Impatient, Lack of Ideas, Tantrums, Lazy, Boredom, Unreliable, Distracted",
        "astrology" => "",
        "element" => "Fire Element",
        "image_key" => "32_Page_of_Wands",
        "content" => "A well-dressed young man stands boldly holding a wand on a barren land. His shirt is made of a salamander pattern, a symbol of turning bad into good. This young man is a passionate advocate, constantly spreading ideas of spiritual and social progress to uplift his fellows. The desert in the background, representing his element fire, also symbolizes that he lives in a world yet to bear fruit. Thus, his ideas are purely hypothetical. However, if he chooses to use them and embarks on his journey, his pure heart can lead him to find better fortune.",
        "upright_content" => "When we see the Page of Wands, we see a young person filled with excitement and curiosity about the world. He knows what to do, he has the passion for success, but due to his lack of experience, and perhaps a bit of fear of the unknown, his ideas remain abstract. He has identified new worlds to explore, new opportunities he can easily exploit, and he even has the 'big picture' vision necessary for success. Even with all of this, he still tends to either remain dormant or get easily distracted by one idea after another. If he doesn't learn to control this, it could be that he wastes opportunities to elevate himself.

          When you get the Page of Wands, it merely means that there is something inside you, something that will trigger you to make discoveries, indulge in investments, or make new advancements in life. You might be about to act on an idea, but conflicting messages in your mind keep discouraging you. This card is akin to the internal battle that stops you from expressing your heroism to the world, letting the world know that you exist for a reason.

          If you are wise enough, this card is usually a trigger for courage. It should encourage you to overcome personal setbacks and move forward bravely, launching your ideas into the real world. Eliminate fear, gather resources, and do something. Let the world know that you are there, moving forward on your chosen path, and you are not joking. Overcome every obstacle, let your ideas shine and be known to the world, as this card indicates a level of success that can only be reached by courageously acting.",
        "reversed_content" => "This indicates that your lack of focus is leading you down the wrong paths, resulting in unexpected failures. Due to your inability to accept this, you continue to make wrong decisions.

          This card suggests that you will not be negatively impacted by losses, obstacles, and criticisms and will start over without losing hope.",
        "upright_love" => "The world is full of possibilities with the Page of Wands tarot love meaning. If you are single, you may find yourself happy to meet new people and explore new realms in love and romance. You may also encounter someone embodying this personality in your love life. As a person, the Page of Wands represents someone adventurous and lively, quick to fall in love but also quick to get bored. Because they live for new experiences, forming a long-term relationship with this person may be challenging, but a short romance could be rewarding. Couples may also find themselves more willing to try new things; you can take classes together, discover new hobbies, or even explore new adventures in the bedroom.",
        "reversed_love" => "If you are single, the reversed Page of Wands tarot love meaning can suggest a person who may not be suited for commitment. They may not know what they want from their life, likely to be drifting and unreliable. Their fiery nature can also get them into trouble. This card can also indicate a period in your love life where you are uncertain about what you are looking for; without clear direction, you might find yourself stuck in dead-end situations. You may need to spend more time deciding what kind of partner you want rather than aimlessly searching for love. If you are in a relationship, this card can signal a period of boredom and lack of motivation. You will need to put in some effort to revitalize your relationship.",
        "upright_career" => "The Page of Wands can be a great sign when it comes to new enterprises. In your career, this can mean you are about to enter a new position or start a new project. Either way, this card is a good omen; it signifies success and fulfillment following your efforts. When the Page appears, it is also an ideal time for adventurous work. Just be careful not to move too quickly. The Page represents a desire for challenges without necessarily being prepared for them. Before taking on new tasks, ask yourself if you are ready. That said, if you are prepared, now is the ideal time to seize opportunities and start new projects.",
        "reversed_career" => "The reversed Page here indicates that you may be experiencing a disconnect between the career you want and the one you currently have. This disharmony could stem from many different causes. You might know where you want to go but are unsure how to get there. This can manifest as stagnation or boredom at work. Alternatively, you might know all the steps needed to achieve your goals but lack the motivation to take them. Whatever the reason, take stock of where you are now, where you want to go, and try to figure out what will help you get there. Nothing is permanent; therefore, do not assume this state of affairs will last forever. However, if you can identify what is holding you back, it will pass more quickly.",
        "upright_finances" => "The Page of Wands suggests you may find some money in the near future. This unexpected income can come in many forms. Someone might give you money as a gift, or you may receive an unexpected bonus from work. While it is always fun to spend such cash, try to save some for the future. Your financial situation may dip, and when it does, you will be thankful for this buffer. Though this is always a wise choice, it is especially important to remember with the Page of Wands, as he tends to be shortsighted in these matters. Do not succumb to the temptation of quick spending, even if it feels like you can afford it.",
        "reversed_finances" => "The Page of Wands can indicate financial instability. Most likely, this instability is the result of a lack of foresight. You may have been too confident financially in the past, and it is now affecting you. Let this serve as a reminder of the cyclical nature of good and bad fortune. The next time you find yourself wealthier than expected, remember this low point and use it as motivation to save. Currently, the best thing you can do is work hard and frugally to weather the storm.",
        "yes_no" => "The Page of Wands is an energetic, lively, and fearless young person with a can-do attitude and a hands-on approach. This card represents adventurous spirit and ambition in starting new projects by overcoming fears and utilizing your skills and courage. The answer you seek is yes.",
        "past" => "A young natured person from your past has positively influenced you. You may be glad to complete a task you have long tried to accomplish.",
        "present" => "Good news is coming. It will bring joy to your life.",
        "future" => "You will soon start a new chapter in life that may be better than your current one.",
    ],
    33 =>
    [
        "id" => 34,
        "type_id" => 1,
        "number" => 33,
        "name" => "Knight of Wands",
        "upright_keyword" => "Brave, Energetic, Charming, Heroic, Rebellious, Hot-Tempered, Free-Spirited",
        "reversed_keyword" => "Arrogant, Reckless, Impatient, Lack of Self-Control, Passive, Unstable, Domineering",
        "astrology" => "",
        "element" => "Fire Element",
        "image_key" => "33_Knight_of_Wands",
        "content" => "The Knight of Wands can be seen riding his horse, which is rearing and ready for action. Judging from the knight’s clothes and armor, as well as his horse, he is prepared for what lies ahead. He wears a shirt with yellow patterns over his metal armor. He also wears a helmet with red feathers. He seems ready for battle, only he carries a large wand instead of a sword. His horse is orange, with a mane that looks like flames. When you look at the face of the Knight of Wands, you see the determination to succeed in his endeavors. Fire is the main element in the symbolism of the Knight of Wands. The tassels hanging from his arms and back, as well as the horse’s mane, are all colored like flames. He also wears a yellow shirt with a fire salamander symbol.",
        "upright_content" => "The symbolism of the Knight of Wands is straightforward. When it appears, it means that it is a great time to get away and travel. The person should feel charged up and full of life. A person is also ready to get things done. He loves adventures and can find fun in any situation. There will never be a dull moment when the Knight of Wands is around. When the Knight of Wands appears in a tarot reading, it seems to suggest that the seeker wants to complete important tasks. A person wants to impress others with his knowledge and skill.

  You may be filled with a lot of energy, but don’t be in too much of a hurry to prove yourself, as this might lead you to lose touch with reality. Therefore, if you don’t want to ruin your chances of success, don’t be hasty and do not criticize others.

  Receiving the Knight of Wands in a tarot reading can also mean that there is an event that you don’t expect to happen soon. If it comes with the Eight of Wands, then you should expect a lot of changes in your life. Most of the time, the Knight of Wands indicates changes in your work, residence, or anything in your life happening quickly.",
        "reversed_content" => "When you receive a reversed Knight of Wands, it represents frustration and delays. You might be feeling angry and incapable of accomplishing anything. The reversed Knight of Wands can be interpreted as a loss of power. You might be trying to compensate for something you have no control over, which can lead to pessimism and loss of self-esteem.",
        "upright_love" => "A vibrant and fearless person may have just entered your love life with the Knight of Wands tarot love meaning. They may be very impulsive, charming, and passionate. But their reckless and unstable nature makes it hard for them to settle down with one person. If this card doesn’t represent a person, it can instead indicate an exciting but also unstable and adventurous period in your love life. You might be more inclined to take risks right now, which can pay off handsomely. Fear of rejection might not be an issue at this moment.",
        "reversed_love" => "You or someone else in your life might now be running from the idea of commitment. The reversed Knight of Wands tarot love meaning signifies impatience, instability, and recklessness. This person might pursue their heart's desires on a whim, only to quickly change their mind once they have it. They might love the thrill of the chase but not the simple, steady love that follows. If you are in a relationship, you might find that things are unstable now, but this could also be due to changes in your environment. Arguments are easily triggered right now.",
        "upright_career" => "The Knight of Wands is a passionate card. This kind of energy is a perfect match for those starting new ventures. You might be enthusiastic about the new projects you are facing at work. You might be eager to take on new responsibilities. However, if you are not starting anything new, you might feel a bit frustrated by this lack of progress. In this case, the Knight of Wands can be a double-edged sword. If you have a passion but are worried it might be wasted, try to find new opportunities on your own. You might have been waiting for things to fall into your lap, but actually, you should be seeking them out. Use your energy to make progress, even if it requires extra effort from you.",
        "reversed_career" => "The reversed Knight of Wands can indicate that your career lacks direction. Unmoored, you might find yourself jumping from job to job without considering what you want and how to get there. While unpredictability is common in many people’s careers, it has become an issue in yours. Routine might seem daunting or boring, but if you have a direction you want to go in, you may have to accept these features in future jobs. This doesn’t mean you need to settle now; it just suggests you start moving vertically in one direction rather than horizontally.",
        "upright_finances" => "This card can sometimes indicate that you might soon receive a substantial sum of money. It could be the perfect time to spend some of this money on travel. Traveling is a great way to use this influx of cash because, while you won't see a return on investment, you will learn and broaden your horizons. Therefore, traveling at this time is not a waste of money. It's a wise, well-rounded choice. Don’t give in to blind spending. Use your money to expand your mind and embark on new adventures. Investing in these types of projects will benefit you in the future, whereas blind spending will waste your good fortune.",
        "reversed_finances" => "There is a tendency to be overly confident when we have money. This is a common impulse, but if you find the Knight of Wands reversed here, you might be particularly susceptible right now. Even if you feel financially secure, now is not the time to waste money or make large purchases. This principle especially applies to your investments. The reversed Knight of Wands can also indicate some sort of loss. In many cases, this will be unavoidable. However, don’t foster this trend by engaging in blind spending or gambling. You are likely to lose more than you currently anticipate. Therefore, it is advisable to be particularly cautious now.",
        "yes_no" => "The Knight of Wands is an ambitious, energetic, and determined leader. While this card brings some challenges, it suggests viewing them as upcoming positive things. Even though the changes are unpredictable, having faith in yourself and courage is best. Your answer is yes.",
        "past" => "Your recent desire for change stems from your curiosity and intuition. The conflicts you encountered at work have influenced the outcome of events around you.",
        "present" => "You will face several challenges that will provide you with the experience of a lifetime. A new journey or project will catch your attention.",
        "future" => "New challenges are approaching based on hasty decisions. These might or might not be your choices, but if overcome, they will lead to a happy and fulfilling life.",
    ],
    34 =>
    [
        "id" => 35,
        "type_id" => 1,
        "number" => 34,
        "name" => "Queen of Wands",
        "upright_keyword" => "Confident, Enthusiastic, Determined, Sociable, Charismatic, Lively, Optimistic",
        "reversed_keyword" => "Demanding, Vengeful, Insecure, Jealous, Selfish, Moody, Bullying",
        "astrology" => "",
        "element" => "Fire Element",
        "image_key" => "34_Queen_of_Wands",
        "content" => "The Queen of Wands depicts a queen proudly sitting on her throne, facing forward, a clear symbol of strength and fire. She holds a sunflower in her left hand, and her throne is decorated with sunflowers, symbolizing happiness, satisfaction, and fertility. In her right hand, she holds her wand, which is beginning to bloom, symbolizing life. On her positive side, the Queen of Wands can be associated with loyalty, dedication, and warmth. The black cat at her feet hints at her hidden side, traditionally a symbol of witchcraft and mysticism, but also indicating her deep intuitive grasp.",
        "upright_content" => "The Queen of Wands often represents a positive, strong, and ambitious woman, and in general implications, this card in the wand suite leans more towards emotions, sentiment, mood, and intuition, using these internal powers to enhance external action. Simply put, one first has a hope, then starts making concrete plans, and once plans are made, action begins—it's a continuous process. Thus, this card can also signify the preparation for success. The appearance of this card usually indicates vitality and positive thinking, with action easily being drawn out. Borrowing a phrase from an advertisement, 'Greatness comes from having dreams.' Therefore, the appearance of this card means that success is very close.",
        "reversed_content" => "Generally, the Queen of Wands in tarot may be portrayed as an intensely focused and passionate person. She is brave and individualistic, though at times she might seem self-centered. They have positive energy; they represent people willing to stand by you and stand up for you.

  In terms of work, the Queen of Wands indicates you are planning to accomplish a lot in a short amount of time. If you are looking for a job, the appearance of this card may suggest that a woman will play an important role in your career development. In general, things look pretty good for your career. The Queen of Wands also conveys positive energy in matters of love. For those seeking love, there is a good chance you will find it soon.

  When it comes to your finances, you may feel overwhelmed by spending a lot of money. It is advised to control your spending, or you may end up regretting it. In terms of health and spirituality, the meaning of the Queen of Wands may relate to spiritual hunger, the pursuit of or the quest for meaning.",
        "upright_love" => "This card represents an independent person who approaches love and relationships with refreshing confidence. She is unlikely to change herself to cater to the desires of others and generally does not care about what others think of her. The Queen of Wands tarot love meaning can encourage you to be open, be proud of your individuality, and engage with the world. You may no longer worry about appearances or how others view you, but instead, just enjoy being around people. Your courage and self-assured nature will draw others to you and inspire them to do the same. If you are in a relationship, you might find success in being more open with your partner than ever before. This honesty and frankness can bring you closer. The Queen of Wands is also a very sensual character.",
        "reversed_love" => "There is a difference between confidence and self-centeredness. The reversed Queen of Wands tarot love meaning can represent someone whose fiery temper can occasionally get out of control, and her changeable and selfish nature may mean she quickly loses interest in you. They may find it hard to meet your needs while demanding their own be met. If this isn’t someone entering your love life, this card can indicate that you or your partner might be quite domineering right now, possibly neglecting each other's needs, or there may be explosive arguments in your relationship. Give yourself time to be gentle, listen, and address any lingering insecurities.",
        "upright_career" => "If you find the Queen of Wands here, it means you have both the energy and the ability to carry out your ideas at work. Whatever you face in your career, you can handle it with determination and enthusiasm. This drive can apply to your work in general, or it could be more specific to your position. You might already be in a leadership role in your career. It could be that you mentor others or are about to start acting as a role model. Whatever the specifics, you are a force to be reckoned with in your field. Now, you have the energy and enthusiasm to lead others in a particularly meaningful and positive way. Use this time to advance your career and support those around you as best you can.",
        "reversed_career" => "When the Queen of Wands is reversed, it shows a lack of passion for your career. You may feel burned out or unwilling to take on new tasks. This negative attitude towards your work can affect how you perceive your work life. While your career is only a part of your life, it is important to feel satisfied with the work you do. If you don’t see the value in your career, your overall demeanor might lack fulfillment. Therefore, you should strive to remember what motivated you to get this job, what you like about it, and any other positive attributes you can assign to it. Consider making a list and reading it aloud each morning (or find other ways to incorporate this positivity into your daily routine). Your perspective on your work might change, but this gloom will pass faster if you make a conscious effort to defeat it.",
        "upright_finances" => "If you find the Queen of Wands here, you are now able to make wise financial decisions. Whatever you choose to do is likely the result of careful planning and consideration. Don’t get distracted or go too far (it’s easy to fall into overspending), but if you stay focused, you can spend some money without severe consequences. This might be a good time to expand your finances since you can calmly assess stocks and other commodities. However, trust your intuition; if it doesn’t feel right, it probably isn’t. Your mind is in an ideal position to evaluate what is a wise choice and what isn’t; trust it.",
        "reversed_finances" => "If you find the Queen of Wands in this position, you might not be managing your funds well. This mismanagement can take two forms: either you are too strict with your spending or not strict enough. You will likely know which applies to you based on your financial situation (rather than the other cards on the table). If it is the former, ask yourself where you can be more generous, remembering that money spent on a good cause often returns in goodwill or good fortune. If it is the latter, try to rein in your spending. Pay attention to each economic decision and ask yourself if it will benefit you in the long run.",
        "yes_no" => "The Queen of Wands is a lively, passionate, independent woman. She suggests a career-oriented and successful person. Honest, considerate, and confident, this card’s presence indicates someone seeking positive self-development, and the answer associated with it is yes.",
        "past" => "Patience is one of your virtues, helping you create a comfortable environment with those around you. You have made wise decisions, and this sound thinking will help you in the future.",
        "present" => "A caring friend will give you helpful advice. This ally might be a woman, but regardless of their identity, remember to be grateful and reciprocate.",
        "future" => "By following the advice of a close female influence, you will achieve success. Your family life will be fulfilling, free of intense conflicts. You and your loved ones will feel content with your environment.",
    ],
    35 =>
    [
        "id" => 36,
        "type_id" => 1,
        "number" => 35,
        "name" => "King of Wands",
        "upright_keyword" => "Leadership, Vision, Big Picture, Control, Bold Decisions, Daring, Optimism",
        "reversed_keyword" => "Domineering, Overbearing, Tyrant, Malicious, Powerless, Ineffective, Weak Leader",
        "astrology" => "",
        "element" => "Fire Element",
        "image_key" => "35_King_of_Wands",
        "content" => "The King of Wands depicts a man holding a blooming wand, representing creativity and passion for life. His throne and cloak are adorned with salamanders and lions, symbols of fire and strength. The salamander biting its tail represents infinity and the drive to overcome all obstacles. His robe is orange-yellow like fire, and his crown resembles flames. Let's delve deeper into the symbolism behind the King of Wands.",
        "upright_content" => "The upright meaning of the King of Wands represents pure energy. However, unlike the other wand cards in the deck, this particular card does not focus on pure creativity. Instead, this king is more likely to take an idea and then decisively implement it himself. The King of Wands is a natural leader of people, and he is also very capable. Once the king sets himself a goal or target, he sticks to it to ensure it becomes a reality.

  The King of Wands looks forward to all sorts of challenges—whether big or small—because he relishes the natural adrenaline that comes with solving problems.",
        "reversed_content" => "As you might guess, the negative aspect of this card relates to feelings of arrogance. He can even be quite aggressive in pursuing his goals, whether or not he realizes it. He won't show restraint or humbly acknowledge when his help is not needed.

  It may mean you are being too harsh and reckless with the people around you, with unscrupulous intentions. You are manipulating everyone to get what you want instead of achieving it properly.

  The King of Wands warns you to stop attacking and set high goals for yourself. Failing to meet these expectations will make you feel like a failure, adding more bitterness to your heart. Stick to realistic goals and achieve them with honest motives.",
        "upright_love" => "There will never be a dull moment with the King of Wands, and in your love tarot reading, he can manifest as an energetic, natural leader who is generous with his time and resources. His fiery nature means he can be quite temperamental, but he will forget his anger as quickly as he stirs it. With such energy, some may find the King of Wands exhausting, but he brings excitement to any situation. If this card does not appear as someone entering your life, it can signify a time of focus and persistence. You may be putting extra effort into your romantic situation, which can yield great rewards. If you are in a relationship, this card is a happy one; the love between you is passionate and deep, even if you sometimes have disputes here and there.",
        "reversed_love" => "The reversed King of Wands tarot love meaning can point to an arrogant, aggressive, and domineering bully. If this card does not appear as a person in your life, you may need to consider your own behavior. Have you been controlling, dominating, or self-centered? If you are facing issues in relationships and romance, this attitude is likely the cause. You may think you are doing the right thing by pushing others to be their best, but even the best intentions can sour under heavy-handed pressure. Everyone has their own way of learning; you might be better off letting your partner explore their own methods of problem-solving rather than forcing them to do things your way.",
        "upright_career" => "In your career tarot reading, the King of Wands can signify success and respect in your field. These ideas are interconnected in the present; you don’t have to choose which one applies to you. If you see the king, it’s likely you hold a high position. You might be a mentor to others. Alternatively, those around you might view you as someone worth admiring, with morals and values. The king also implies thriving business ventures. Your career is currently doing particularly well. This isn’t just a temporary situation. Your success is lasting.",
        "reversed_career" => "The reversed King of Wands here can indicate a lack of leadership and direction. You might be waiting for others to bring things to you instead of chasing opportunities yourself. If you continue to wait for others to define your goals, you may never find something that truly fits your passion. Serendipity is useful and important in many careers. However, it is not a reliable source. Try to define your own needs. If you have a goal or career in mind, your career may not be progressing because of a lack of confidence. Sometimes, it’s important to trust your own intuition rather than others’ advice. Everyone views the world through their own lens; remember that others' biases may influence their view of your needs. Trust your own career path.",
        "upright_finances" => "If you find the King here, you are good at managing money. You may be in a stable state because you can save money when needed but also are willing to spend it when the time is right. This balance allows you to appreciate and protect your income. Continue practicing these principles. Only saving money can be wise, but spending it, especially on others, can be a gesture of appreciation. You are wise enough to maintain this balance. Trust your judgment in investments and purchases. The stability and success you are experiencing now have the potential to be even more lasting. As long as you continue to actively practice, your good habits will endure.",
        "reversed_finances" => "If you see the King of Wands reversed here, take action. Expecting fate to bring you success is unreasonable. Take charge of your finances. Instead of hoping for good luck, proactively seek economic opportunities. You can control your finances in many ways. Ask for a raise. Budget your expenses. Seek more/different work. Any action in your position that makes the most sense is likely the best. Waiting and hoping money falls into your lap is easier but rarely happens. Instead, try to take productive and definitive steps toward your goals. You have the ability to achieve your financial dreams. You just need to work for them.",
        "yes_no" => "The King of Wands is a greedy, determined, and confident authority figure. He represents some sort of expansion, establishing something in your career, or gaining financial benefits with success. He is a positive presence, likely bringing positive outcomes. The answer is yes.",
        "past" => "The new ideas you integrated into your past will open opportunities for you now. These ideas gave you the motivation and drive to inspire others.",
        "present" => "If you have put in great effort in your field of work, you will undoubtedly succeed. Nothing can stop you from achieving your goals unless you give up.",
        "future" => "The future will bring success to your career. Good investments and prudent spending will outweigh the risks you take, and the steadfast determination you demonstrate will bring many opportunities.",
    ],
    36 =>
    [
        "id" => 37,
        "type_id" => 1,
        "number" => 36,
        "name" => "Ace of Pentacles",
        "upright_keyword" => "New opportunities, Resources, Abundance, Prosperity, Security, Stability, Manifestation",
        "reversed_keyword" => "Missed opportunities, Scarcity, Lack, Instability, Miserliness, Poor investment",
        "astrology" => "",
        "element" => "Earth Element",
        "image_key" => "36_Ace_of_Pentacles",
        "content" => "In this card, a mysterious hand emerges from a cloud. It holds something that looks like a gold coin, with a pentagram inscribed on its surface. This pentagram is related to the element of earth, symbolizing wealth and all material and earthly matters. Below the hand is a garden that appears to be lush with flowers and other types of vegetation, emanating an aura of fertility, growth, and prosperity. The mountain represents the ambition needed to drive one to seek the pentacle. The flowing stream seems to predict emotions flowing towards this ambition.",
        "upright_content" => "The Aces in the tarot predict new beginnings. When you draw any of them, it means you are at a point where a new cycle is beginning in your life - you are about to start anew.

  Because the suit of Pentacles is primarily concerned with all things material (not just financial, but also sensory), this reset can manifest as a new career, a new venture, or a focus on taking better care of your health. Wherever this beginning occurs, the Ace of Pentacles promises that what is to come will bring great abundance and opportunity.

  Seeing the Ace of Pentacles indicates that a seed is being planted in the material world, in your sense of security and stability. Like a seed, this opportunity must be nurtured, and sometimes it requires investment of energy, time, or funds. Watering this seed can bring very rewarding results - for anything that grows within this energy is meant to be stable, secure, and give good yield. Prosperity is coming your way.

  One must also ensure that they are mentally prepared for the opportunities appearing. To be able to harvest the gifts of the pentacle, we need to be filled with the calm that stability brings, a form of spiritual prosperity, if you will. This mindset may mean being open to trying new things rather than sticking to old, outdated routines.",
        "reversed_content" => "While the Ace of Pentacles usually predicts some kind of opportunity that brings great benefits, seeing it reversed may mean that this could be a bad investment, requiring far more resources than you originally reserved - or you may be missing your chance.

  When one receives the Ace of Pentacles reversed, it can indicate that they will face tough financial times and many elusive opportunities. Currently, it is advised not to take any huge financial risks and to consider all options when a deal is presented.

  This can also be a good time for the individual to seek advice from others and avoid making hasty decisions, as the timing is not right. This is not a good time to jump into a new job or business opportunity, especially if the primary motive for joining is the pursuit of more financial gain. It may just be an illusion that could lead to your downfall.",
        "upright_love" => "This card indicates a loyal, lasting, and practical love. Pentacles are associated with the element of earth, granting relationships qualities of stability, generosity, and reliability. Couples may find that their relationship gives them a sense of stability and security, whose influence gives them the confidence to take risks and explore. This gives lovers a sense of independence, allowing each person to thrive as an individual while bringing more to the relationship. Relationships may feel prosperous and abundant, and you and your lover may feel lucky and blessed to enjoy life together. If you’re single, make sure to also tend to your practical life, as this will give you the foundation needed to find a love that can flourish.",
        "reversed_love" => "The reversed Ace of Pentacles tarot love meaning can indicate that a relationship that once gave you a sense of stability may now make you feel anxious and vulnerable. Worries about financial matters can seep into the relationship, making both of you feel insecure. Sometimes, this can be alleviated with honest discussions and a game plan moving forward. If you’re not in a relationship, be wary of those who appear selfish, greedy, or willing to take advantage of you. This card can also simply indicate missed romantic opportunities.",
        "upright_career" => "New opportunities are available to you now, which can ensure you obtain a better job or a higher position in your current company. If you seize the opportunity and work hard, you can get rewarded with a promotion, start a new business, or find a job that truly fulfills you. Since it’s the Ace of Pentacles, this card marks beginnings, and these changes can signify a new adventure or a new era for you. Positive energy is heading your way; you should welcome it like a breath of fresh air.",
        "reversed_career" => "Do you feel like you missed out on a promotion or chance to get your dream job? The reversed Ace of Pentacles can have a sense of instability or missed opportunities. You may feel like you are not performing well in your job and may worry about getting fired for poor performance. Some of this might be impostor syndrome, but some concerns may be real. You need to take a realistic look at yourself. You may also feel that you have not spent your time wisely and made some poor decisions on your career path. You have not invested in a career that gives you material and emotional returns. It’s not too late to change now; think more about what you want to do.",
        "upright_finances" => "What investments are you making for your future? The Ace of Pentacles marks a financial opportunity or a new financial journey. Think of this card as a seed; you have the opportunity to take this seed and grow it into something that can sustain you long-term. Try and make the most of it by learning more about your finances, or setting aside some savings for the future. If you’re really lucky, this card can also mean some kind of windfall or financial gift is coming your way.",
        "reversed_finances" => "If you haven’t recently paid attention or checked in on your finances, it might be time to do so. Poor planning can mean you have made some bad financial decisions. This could be a very tight period for you; you’ll have to learn how to pinch pennies to get by. In the worst case, it can indicate a financial emergency; one you may not be prepared for.",
        "yes_no" => "The Ace of Pentacles represents prosperity, financial gain, and successful ventures leading to promotion. It brings good luck and emotional stability. This card highly suggests a positive future and the ability to achieve your goals. The answer is yes.",
        "past" => "Your time has been well spent, and you will eventually achieve the success you desire. The projects you have started will pay off.",
        "present" => "Comforting news will come to you. It may help you realize that you are on the right or appropriate path to gain the recognition and material rewards you deserve.",
        "future" => "You are destined to gain significant rewards. Whether financial, emotional, or personal, spiritual blessings are awaiting you.",
    ],
    37 =>
    [
        "id" => 38,
        "type_id" => 1,
        "number" => 37,
        "name" => "Two of Pentacles",
        "upright_keyword" => "Balancing resources, Adaptability, Resourcefulness, Flexibility, Prioritization, Multitasking, Fun-oriented, Win-win",
        "reversed_keyword" => "Imbalance, Disorganization, Overwhelmed, Messy, Chaos, Overextension",
        "astrology" => "",
        "element" => "Earth Element",
        "image_key" => "37_Two_of_Pentacles",
        "content" => "The Two of Pentacles card depicts a man dancing while juggling two large coins. The coins are surrounded by the infinity symbol, indicating that this person can handle all the issues they encounter and manage their life with grace. In the background, you will notice two ships sailing on high waves, reinforcing the balancing act the man must face - he is in turbulent waters but manages to stay afloat. The two pentacles depict the usual ups and downs in a person's life. Despite the chaos around him, this person lives a very carefree life while dancing and happily handling everything that comes his way.",
        "upright_content" => "When it comes to love, the Two of Pentacles is a message that you cannot provide what is necessary to make your partner happy. Your partnership should be your priority, but due to the craziness of other aspects of your life, you find it hard to focus on the person you love. Regarding finances, you should pay attention to the bottom line. You should have a clear understanding of your financial situation. Plan your finances accordingly, control your spending, and increase your sources of income to lay a solid foundation for your future. In terms of health, this card asks you to find a balance between your well-being and your responsibilities. When you have a lot going on around you, it is easy to make yourself the last priority.",
        "reversed_content" => "When the Two of Pentacles is in a reversed position, it can mean that you are trying to handle too many things in your life. You need to take at least a short break to alleviate the stress. If you feel like you can't handle everything, you need to consider your health and give yourself a moment to breathe. In your job, the reversed Two of Pentacles can be a positive sign. Avoid committing to too many things as it will overwhelm you.

  Financially, you need to learn to live within your means. The reversed Two of Pentacles reminds you to pay attention to your income and expenses, as overspending can become a big problem, especially when you are being pulled in multiple directions.",
        "upright_love" => "This card often appears when you have many responsibilities to handle, and love might be the last thing on your mind. You may feel stressed, dealing with relationships, career, and family issues. Everything requires effort, and if you think your relationship is important, be careful not to neglect your partner. If you are single, you may need to consider whether you are really ready for love right now. You may need to decide what is most important to you and make some choices to prioritize or not prioritize romance.",
        "reversed_love" => "When the reversed Two of Pentacles appears in a love tarot reading, you may find it difficult to maintain balance. With so many conflicts and demands, you may not even realize that your partner feels neglected. It seems that everything is more important than them, and there may be some resentment as they feel taken for granted. If you are single, this card can suggest that you may have to choose between two potential lovers, or you are too busy and overwhelmed to make romance a priority right now. Take your time; come back when you are ready to make space for love in your busy life.",
        "upright_career" => "When the Two of Pentacles appears in your career tarot reading, you may be juggling many projects at work right now. This can be a busier time than usual, with things being thrown at you last minute that are not your responsibility, or you have been taking them on to get a better position. Others may be impressed with your ability to handle things and your resourcefulness. Ideally, this is only a temporary state. Be careful not to take on more than you can handle, or your coworkers and bosses may get used to giving you all the tasks no one else wants to do. If this continues, make sure you are being adequately compensated! Sometimes, this card can also point to balancing your career goals with other aspects of your life.",
        "reversed_career" => "Are you taking on too much right now? When your boss asks you to do something, do you just say 'yes' even if you don't have the time? Deadlines may be looming, and the pressure is mounting. Your work life may be causing you significant stress right now. It's time to stand up for yourself, seek help, renegotiate deadlines, and prioritize your tasks. If you are not careful, things may fall through the cracks, causing you more trouble. You are human, and the sooner your boss or colleagues understand that, the better for everyone.",
        "upright_finances" => "The Two of Pentacles indicates that you are working hard to make sure all bills are paid. You may have to do a juggling act right now, as things may be quite tight. Sometimes, the Two of Pentacles can also indicate the need to make some important choices regarding money. Things feel very uncertain, and you may be in an unstable position right now. Everything seems to be changing so quickly, which means you may be very hesitant to make this choice. Stay adaptable, and you will be able to get through this situation well.",
        "reversed_finances" => "Finances are tight, and no matter what you do, you can't seem to figure out how to pay all your bills. As soon as money comes in, it seems to be spent immediately on rent, groceries, utilities, one after another. Unfortunately, this situation is not uncommon. Take a close look at your budget, and if you don't have one, create one, and see where you can make cuts. Ask for a raise, or find a side project that can bring in a little income. If possible, getting help from a professional to make a plan may benefit you.",
        "yes_no" => "The Two of Pentacles showcases movement, balance, and growth through change. It suggests the possibility of fluctuating wealth, which may require some juggling, bringing ups and downs. The workload will be heavy, and the presence of this card does not give a clear answer.",
        "past" => "It reminds you of the need to accept life's changes. Perhaps in the past few years, you had to choose between two things in your life. Regardless of the outcome, you have learned lessons.",
        "present" => "The current situation indicates that you are balancing between two main aspects of life, such as work and family. The journey may not always be smooth, but you will feel comfortable and secure. However, it is sometimes good to be selfish and emphasize your personal needs.",
        "future" => "Identifying your most valuable assets can help you create opportunities for yourself. If you want to find it, there is a way to get out of your indecisiveness.",
    ],
    38 =>
    [
        "id" => 39,
        "type_id" => 1,
        "number" => 38,
        "name" => "Three of Pentacles",
        "upright_keyword" => "Teamwork, Shared goals, Collaboration, Apprenticeship, Hard work, Focus",
        "reversed_keyword" => "Lack of cohesion, Lack of teamwork, Indifference, Lack of motivation, Conflict, Self-interest, Competition",
        "astrology" => "",
        "element" => "Earth Element",
        "image_key" => "38_Three_of_Pentacles",
        "content" => "The Three of Pentacles shows a young apprentice working on a cathedral. In front of him are two other people, a priest and a nobleman, who are holding the plans of the cathedral on a piece of parchment. From the way the apprentice is looking up, you can tell he is discussing the progress of building the cathedral. The other two are listening attentively to him to better understand what is needed and how they can provide guidance. Despite the apprentice’s lack of experience, the other two still listen to him because they know his ideas and experience are the foundation for the successful completion of the building. Therefore, the Three of Pentacles represents different kinds of knowledge coming together to build something together.",
        "upright_content" => "The Three of Pentacles in the tarot represents the successful completion of a goal - it takes the energy of the Ace and Two of Pentacles and adds a foundational element, usually involving some kind of group. In this context, the upright Three of Pentacles signifies the successful implementation of all requirements to start a business, deal, venture, or any other type of endeavor. Successful projects typically require different kinds of expertise, and at this point, the Three of Pentacles means that all the necessary skills have come together. In short, you enjoy working as part of a team and the preliminary success of this larger project.

  The Three of Pentacles shows the successful start of a goal, a sign of encouragement that you should continue working and not give up. By yourself, it might be difficult to achieve your goals, but the Three of Pentacles also teaches you not to disregard the talents of others around you. You need to work with others with different viewpoints, experiences, and expertise to accomplish something you dream of.",
        "reversed_content" => "The reversed meaning of the Three of Pentacles indicates a lack of teamwork; it shows people working against each other and undermining the project in the process. There seems to be too much competition among them, with everyone trying to show their superiority. This leads to scarce resources, and too many people viewing their project partners as competitors.

  When you are in such a team, it is best to ensure you try to foster camaraderie as much as possible. Projects with reversed Three of Pentacles are hard to complete in this constant bickering. You may find people not listening to others and everyone working individually. This difference in motivation and ambition will lead to complications. If you can be the first to extend a hand, give everyone a chance to be heard and considered, perhaps this project has a chance to move forward.",
        "upright_love" => "Love and teamwork can be combined with the Three of Pentacles tarot love meaning. If you are in a relationship, you may find that working on things together with your lover is particularly enjoyable; couples can get to know one another more and deepen their trust by making future plans, working on their home, or collaborating on creative projects. By coming together as a team, you two can also feel supported as partners, with each of you having unique talents and weaknesses, creating a harmonious balance. If you are single, you may find that love comes from cooperation at work or your hobbies.",
        "reversed_love" => "The reversed Three of Pentacles tarot love meaning can point to a couple that is struggling with practical matters. While emotions may be present, they aren’t translating into effort or action. All love requires work, as well as desire. Being together as a couple often means being able to trust that your partner is your teammate, as well as your co-pilot on the long journey of life. How do you two share chores? How do you allocate finances? What about emotional labor? One person in the relationship may be giving their all, while the other person thinks everything is a given. Make sure both people in your relationship play their part as teammates.",
        "upright_career" => "The Three of Pentacles suggests that you bring your experiences and skills together with a larger team to accomplish a common goal. Collaboration may be very important for your success now, and your work may need cohesion between people with different skills, experiences, ideas, and processes. You must work hard to ensure these different views are all focused on achievement. Keep in mind the larger goal; this will help everyone come together rather than argue. Support your teammates and trust their expertise while sharing your unique perspective.

  This card can also indicate a period of learning and building your qualifications. You are likely to cope well with your new challenges.",
        "reversed_career" => "Conflicts between your colleagues and yourself can cause stress and frustration at work. Those who should be your partners in collaboration are creating more trouble for you rather than helping you. Instead of working towards the greater good, coworkers or collaborators may be more concerned with their self-interests. Different teams may try to undermine each other instead of genuinely listening to each other's needs. Miscommunication is also common. The reversed Three of Pentacles can also indicate that your learning progress is not going smoothly; there may be a lack of effort or motivation to accomplish your goals. Are you really challenging yourself?",
        "upright_finances" => "In terms of finances, you may find that working with someone who has financial experience can be helpful to you right now. Others may help you create a budget and get on track towards your material goals. If this doesn't apply to you, the Three of Pentacles could simply indicate learning more about how to consolidate your finances. This learning period will be very beneficial for you in the long run.",
        "reversed_finances" => "People may be unwilling to learn about financial issues through the reversed Three of Pentacles. Instead of directly looking at your financial situation and seeing what you can do, anything related to money or resources might scare or exhaust you, so you avoid it altogether. You need to put in the effort to learn about savings, bank accounts, credit cards, and other financial products before you start using them.",
        "yes_no" => "The Three of Pentacles is a card representing excellence and success. These things can be achieved through productive teamwork or diligent effort. It is directly related to becoming a master in the field and great career accomplishments. The answer to your question is yes.",
        "past" => "If you look back on your past life, you will realize that somewhere lacking guidance must have led you here. But, if you did the opposite, then all obstacles were overcome and success was achieved.",
        "present" => "In your current life, you may feel like you are on the right track, but something may be missing. To find the answer, study and understand the subject you have chosen to gain more knowledge. In this way, you can become a role model and inspire everyone around you.",
        "future" => "You have already achieved success in numerous creative endeavors and are working harder than ever to secure a guaranteed future. Try to gather more qualities and make improvements to see a better version of yourself in the coming years.",
    ],
    39 =>
    [
        "id" => 40,
        "type_id" => 1,
        "number" => 39,
        "name" => "Four of Pentacles",
        "upright_keyword" => "Possessiveness, Insecurity, Hoarding, Stinginess, Stability, Security, Savings, Materialism, Wealth, Frugality, Boundaries, Guarding",
        "reversed_keyword" => "Generosity, Giving, Spending, Openness, Financial insecurity, Reckless spending",
        "astrology" => "",
        "element" => "Earth Element",
        "image_key" => "39_Four_of_Pentacles",
        "content" => "This card depicts a man sitting on a stool, clutching two pentacles in a very defensive and tight posture. It almost seems like he is hoarding them out of fear of losing them. One pentacle is balanced on his head, another is held tightly in his hands, and two more are placed securely under his feet. He is ensuring that absolutely no one touches his coins. At the same time, he cannot move because he is so firmly holding onto them. In other words, he is immobilized by his tight grip on his possessions. For some people, money does not always bring freedom.",
        "upright_content" => "The Four of Pentacles can generate both negative and positive perceptions. On one hand, this card signifies that you have successfully achieved most of your goals and have amassed significant material wealth in the process. On the other hand, there is a high possibility that you have started evaluating things solely based on their material value. It is only natural that you want to ensure your stability after working hard to get to where you are. But this also has the potential to turn you into someone who is overly possessive or greedy, wanting to ensure that no one can take away your wealth.

  The Four of Pentacles is also a card that suggests you are in a position of financial stability and investment security. Because of your newfound wealth, you are particularly conservative with your money and absolutely not inclined to gamble when it comes to any financial matters. You protect what you have accumulated and hope to steadily increase your overall net worth.

  Be aware that without risk, there is no reward, and if you spend too much time trying to preserve, you might become a prisoner of your material wealth. Wealth is also a form of energy, and we create what we express.",
        "reversed_content" => "When reversed, the Four of Pentacles sharply leans towards the card’s negative implications. Instead of being protective, you succumb to being miserly. You are plagued by certain fears of poverty that force you to become materialistic. You are extremely self-protective and defensive about material things, refusing to open up and trust others out of fear they might take them away.

  On the other hand, you might actually be spending too much money, and you need to start properly managing your actual financial resources. In any case, this card can invoke both positive and negative associations, and if you get the Four of Pentacles in a reading, you need to be very responsible and considerate.",
        "upright_love" => "Your relationship might feel clingy, even suffocating, with the Four of Pentacles representing love. Relationships with this card might be filled with jealousy and possessiveness, which can slowly erode even the happiest love. There may be issues with insecurity or fear that lovers need to address before driving their partners away. If you’re single, it’s likely you’re still holding onto something from past relationships; whether it be grudges, resentment, or hopes of an ex returning to your life. These things need to be resolved before you can truly open your heart to another lover again.",
        "reversed_love" => "Past insecurities may now be healing, making you or your lover less jealous and possessive. Thus, the reversed Four of Pentacles love meaning can suggest that relationships can move forward without being hindered by past traumas. If you are single, you may be ready to welcome new love and have let go of something that has been preventing your romantic life from flourishing.",
        "upright_career" => "You might have finally found some stability in your career right now. If you have been struggling to find this stability in the past, or if this job is new to you, you might still be a little insecure about your role. This can make you guarded, anxious, or even paranoid. If you let it go too far, this can do more harm than good for you. You might find it hard to collaborate and work in a team, feeling like your ideas are guarded and worrying that others might take credit that belongs to you. These things do happen, address them, but don’t let them consume you.

  Sometimes, this card can also mean that you stay in a job that doesn’t fulfill you just for the paycheck. The job may be stable, but you may truly hate it.",
        "reversed_career" => "The reversed Four of Pentacles can be a bit difficult to interpret. Your passion and generous nature at work can be a powerful asset. You are always available to help others and give credit when it is due. Alternatively, you might make risky decisions without regard for consequences. Avoid immediately trying to take on the most dazzling projects or striving for the most ambitious, unreasonable goals, as this can get you into trouble rather than help you.",
        "upright_finances" => "You may have recently found some material stability, allowing you to accumulate a bit of wealth. If you are used to being frugal, you might spend a lot of time thinking about your finances, doing everything you can to protect this small fortune. You can be quite thrifty and conservative with your money, even if it brings you a lot of extra work or pain. Alternatively, the Four of Pentacles could simply indicate that you are saving up for something big, like a car or a new house, your children’s future, or your own retirement fund.",
        "reversed_finances" => "Sometimes, the reversed Four of Pentacles can indicate that you are slowly learning how to open up your wallet. You might generally be very frugal, but you are learning that giving to others or using your money in useful ways can feel good. You might be donating or sharing your resources with family or friends, or buying things based on quality rather than price. However, at other times, you might be careless with your money. This can make you an easy target for thieves or dubious financial schemes. Stay alert.",
        "yes_no" => "The Four of Pentacles represents security, stability, and the presence of balance in elements of life. It suggests being smart and frugal with what you have, sticking to a strict budget, but with the safety of only positive outcomes. Moving forward may require tenacity. Your answer is yes.",
        "past" => "Your ability to work hard and your dedication will bring you material success. Recent deals, proposals, or business ventures are adding a deeper layer of meaning to your life.",
        "present" => "You will receive financial rewards for the effort you have shown. You will be victorious, but this victory will be hollow if it is considered only in terms of monetary gain.",
        "future" => "Although the future promises material security and growth in wealth, one can only imagine that people can feel happy about materialism. You should act normally with your emotions and behaviors.",
    ],
    40 =>
    [
        "id" => 41,
        "type_id" => 1,
        "number" => 40,
        "name" => "Five of Pentacles",
        "upright_keyword" => "Hardship, Loss, Isolation, Feeling Abandoned, Adversity, Struggle, Unemployment, Estrangement, Shame",
        "reversed_keyword" => "Positive change, Recovery from loss, Overcoming adversity, Forgiveness, Feeling welcomed",
        "astrology" => "",
        "element" => "Earth Element",
        "image_key" => "40_Five_of_Pentacles",
        "content" => "Like the other fives in the tarot, the Five of Pentacles symbolizes adversity. It shows two people walking outside in the snow. They are not only cold but also sick, poor, tired, and hungry. They seem to lack basic necessities. Many people can relate to these two figures in more ways than one.

  One person in the card uses crutches, while the other has a shawl covering her head. She walks barefoot in the snow. In the background, there is a black wall with a stained-glass window depicting five pentacles, suggesting some sort of church.

  Generally, the Five of Pentacles is a bad omen. However, do not worry, as its meaning changes depending on its position in the reading.",
        "upright_content" => "Whenever the Five of Pentacles appears in a tarot reading, it signifies a time of hardship and insecurity. The meaning of this card can include deep loneliness, illness, poverty, or loss. Your state might worsen in the near future. You might lose something significant, whether it is financial wealth or something important to you. The deterioration of your health might have been ongoing or very sudden.

  The person using crutches has a lot of symbolic meaning. This person might feel cursed – their bad luck is something they cannot easily escape. The symbolism of the Five of Pentacles can also be old debt, high credit card balances, or unpaid loans. It serves as a reminder to consider organizing your finances. Mistakes made in the past might also haunt you.

  When it comes to matters related to love, the Five of Pentacles is not a good sign. It can indicate that the person you love feels differently. Like the figures in the card, you might feel left out in the cold.",
        "reversed_content" => "Unlike the upright version, the reversed Five of Pentacles can indicate good things. The snow is now on top, symbolizing light entering your life. The stained-glass window now represents a passage, with the Five of Pentacles acting as a light at the end of the tunnel. The reversed Five of Pentacles means that change is coming.

  Drawing this card might mean that the worst is over, but do not expect change to happen overnight. It will take some time to recover and find your strength again. It signifies that you will be able to regain stability in property, health, relationships, business, or finances.

  Slow recovery from illness can also be indicated by the reversed Five of Pentacles. You will find a treatment that can lead to recovery. If you are caring for someone, it might mean that help will be provided, whether in the form of financial or practical assistance.",
        "upright_love" => "At this moment, it might feel like you will never find the love you are looking for, according to the Five of Pentacles tarot love meaning. Singles may be in a period of despair, ready to give up on the long search for a suitable partner and succumb to loneliness. Unfortunately, this attitude can be a self-fulfilling prophecy. Feelings of isolation or lack might also appear in existing relationships, either coming from within the partnership or from external sources. Lovers may find it hard to communicate honestly or emotionally connect, creating a wall between them. Depression may also be an issue. Sometimes this card can indicate a lack of financial security, putting strain on your romantic relationships. This might be a tough period, but it is more important than ever to unite rather than separate.",
        "reversed_love" => "A period of isolation, rejection, and despair might be ending. The reversed Five of Pentacles tarot love meaning can indicate that your relationship or your dating prospects are improving again as you work through tough situations. As the struggle eases, you can make steady progress in reigniting a relationship or opening yourself up to new friends.",
        "upright_career" => "The Five of Pentacles appearing in a career or work setting can bring trouble. You might experience a difficult period at work, perhaps due to job loss or feeling isolated and abandoned by colleagues or bosses. Others might treat you like an outcast, and you might struggle with office politics and socializing. If you are a business owner, you may also face difficulties. All these problems can severely impact your mental health and might create a downward spiral. If you believe the situation won't change, you might want to start looking for another job.",
        "reversed_career" => "If your career or business has been facing issues, the reversed Five of Pentacles might suggest that there is light at the end of the tunnel. Things are likely to return to normal. The difficult situation can now heal, or you might have found another job that values your work. Keep an eye out for any opportunities.",
        "upright_finances" => "The Five of Pentacles signifies financial difficulties. You need to tighten your belt now, as money feels tight. Sometimes, in the worst case, this card can hint at material loss, meaning you might be dealing with debt, bankruptcy, or eviction. Therefore, expect funds to be tight when they come in. Regardless of the situation, do not let your pride prevent you from seeking help. Look into food kitchens and charities if necessary; there is no shame in this, as we all go through financially difficult periods. If you can, you might want to start building an emergency fund.",
        "reversed_finances" => "Slowly, you might be recovering from financial loss. You might be paying off debt or rebuilding an emergency fund after suffering significant losses. Keep working at it, and you might find yourself in a financially stable situation once again. The worst is over.",
        "yes_no" => "The Five of Pentacles foretells of financial or emotional troubles or a period of bad luck ahead. Worries, poverty, and setbacks are all associated with this card. These things might be due to a lack of faith or a loss of faith. The overall tone of this card is negative. The answer to your question is no.",
        "past" => "Recent emotional or financial loss has weighed heavily on you. Do not let your pride keep you away from the help of others.",
        "present" => "The difficulties you are facing will be overcome, so do not succumb to the inadequacies or insecurities it brings you.",
        "future" => "Necessary changes will bring you happiness and security in your future. This change might be in direction or motivation, but it will tell you that all difficulties can be overcome.",
    ],
    41 =>
    [
        "id" => 42,
        "type_id" => 1,
        "number" => 41,
        "name" => "Six of Pentacles",
        "upright_keyword" => "Generosity, Charity, Community, Material Help, Support, Sharing, Giving and Receiving, Gratitude",
        "reversed_keyword" => "Power Dynamics, Abuse of Generosity, Selfishness, Inequality, Extortion",
        "astrology" => "",
        "element" => "Earth Element",
        "image_key" => "41_Six_of_Pentacles",
        "content" => "In the image of the Six of Pentacles, there is a man dressed in a purple robe. The purple symbolizes this person's status and wealth. He holds a balanced scale, representing equality and fairness. It reminds us of the Justice tarot card, which hints at karma and cause and effect, suggesting we receive what we give. His other hand is giving coins to two beggars kneeling at his feet. The Six of Pentacles indicates that you are in a secure enough position to give to others without affecting your own well-being.",
        "upright_content" => "The Six of Pentacles signifies that you are in a good relationship with your income. Like the main character in the card, the money you bring in and your expenses are well balanced, and you are fortunate not to have any stress. You are also grateful for everything you have and are happy to share your wealth with others. From the imagery on the card, the Six of Pentacles can be associated with charity. You could be the person donating money to those in need, or you could be the beggar gratefully receiving what you need from a wealthy benefactor.

  If the card shows you as the giver, you have accumulated wealth, and now you can help others through financial aid. You might have lived in the dark side of the pentacles long enough to see the light. You are considering donating to charity or helping those who need your support and are in the same position you were in before. The Six of Pentacles is not necessarily about material gifts or money; it can also mean your time and presence.

  If the card shows you as one of the beggars, you might be receiving charity from others. This can help you recover, so accept the help – you can repay the kindness in the future. You may also find ways to become self-sufficient in the future. Despite this situation, you should be careful not to become desperate or submissive during this period.",
        "reversed_content" => "The reversed Six of Pentacles can indicate that charity can be one-sided. If you have lent money to someone, you should not expect your money to be repaid, or your kindness to be returned in the future. You should be cautious about whom you lend money to, especially if your finances are unstable. You might also encounter problems with spending and donating more than you can afford.

  The reversed Six of Pentacles can also warn you about debts you owe. It might mean that you have gone overboard, and it will come back as a major issue in the future. During this period, you should also be cautious about business dealings, as you might end up with huge losses instead of returns on investment.

  The reversed Six of Pentacles suggests selfishness related to giving and charity. It could mean that you are willing to give to others in a way that benefits yourself rather than them. Be careful that you are not being charitable just to prove your generosity to others. The source of charity should be selfless, not selfish.",
        "upright_love" => "The Six of Pentacles in love represents kindness and generosity in your relationship. Your partner may be emotionally and financially supportive as you pursue your goals. You might be going to school or starting a new job and worrying about the risks it might bring to your partnership. However, you might be pleasantly surprised by your partner's willingness to help you achieve that goal. Remember to keep the relationship balanced. Give back to your partner in other ways to show your appreciation for them. This way, your relationship will flourish. If you are single, you might find that generosity in energy, time, or resources, whether from you or others, can bring about love.",
        "reversed_love" => "Power dynamics and imbalance can create major issues in your relationship, as indicated by the reversed Six of Pentacles tarot love meaning. If one partner is always giving while the other is always taking, one person might feel used and resentful, while the other feels trapped and dependent. Maintaining a level of independence and self-sufficiency in relationships is always important. The dynamics here need to be corrected for the relationship to be healthy. Singles might need to be wary of partners who create this power imbalance; avoid being overly generous or overly dependent on your romantic relationships.",
        "upright_career" => "If you draw the Six of Pentacles in a career tarot reading, someone senior in your workplace might be ready to help you achieve your career goals. This mentor can be very generous with their time and energy, helping you gain more skills and a higher status in your career path. The Six of Pentacles can also indicate that your contributions are highly valued in your workplace. If you are looking for a new job, this card can suggest that these changes will be more favorable than you anticipated. If you own a business, this card can recommend investors or people willing to help you grow your business.",
        "reversed_career" => "Beware of seemingly helpful and generous people in your workplace who might have ulterior motives. Someone might misuse their position of power or offer help to create a sense of indebtedness. They might ask you to do something at the cost of your honor. If you are in a position of power, remember to offer help without expecting anything in return; recall what it was like when you were younger. If you are receiving help, ensure not to abuse it. Are you attracting people with positions or status to help you? This might be more obvious to others than you think. Avoid this temptation and remain honest with yourself and others.",
        "upright_finances" => "Currently, you might find a lot of generous people in your community. If you have a dream of starting a project or business, you might find many people willing to help you achieve this dream. Go out and ask, pitch your ideas, and tell people what you want to build. Your enthusiasm will likely inspire others to help as much as they can. On the other hand, you might find yourself in a position to provide material support to others. You might be in a comfortable position now where you can afford to help others.",
        "reversed_finances" => "If you have been seeking financial help, the situation might seem bleak now. It seems that no one can offer you what you need. If you do find someone willing to help, proceed with caution. Check if the terms of your loan are fair or if the gifts come with strings attached. Otherwise, you might find yourself in more trouble than you are currently in. If you can give, avoid feelings of resentment or using your financial comfort for leverage. Alternatively, you might be the one being taken advantage of; ensure that your financial aid goes directly to the person you intend. Watch out for scams preying on your kindness.",
        "yes_no" => "The Six of Pentacles represents success, prosperity, and generosity. It suggests financially helping others, donations, and selfless charity. There is a sense of positive favors and overall good luck, with happy returns in the future. The answer you seek is most likely yes.",
        "past" => "Your fair consideration of others in the past will guide you to success in the present.",
        "present" => "Your passion for life and confidence in your talents will be revived. The joy of helping those in need will illuminate the bigger picture.",
        "future" => "Remember, the kindness of others is beyond your control, but you are entirely capable of giving others favors. If you seek help, it is best to give freely to others.",
    ],
    42 =>
    [
        "id" => 43,
        "type_id" => 1,
        "number" => 42,
        "name" => "Seven of Pentacles",
        "upright_keyword" => "Harvest, Rewards, Results, Growth, Progress, Perseverance, Patience, Planning",
        "reversed_keyword" => "Unfinished Work, Procrastination, Low Effort, Wasted Resources, Lack of Growth, Frustration, Impatience, Lack of Reward",
        "astrology" => "",
        "element" => "Earth Element",
        "image_key" => "42_Seven_of_Pentacles",
        "content" => "The Seven of Pentacles depicts a young man who seems to be taking a break from his hard work to admire the fruits and flowers in his garden. He leans on his shovel, admiring the seven pentacles hanging from the lush green vegetation. The way he rests his head on his hand suggests a sense of fatigue; he has worked hard to ensure this year's harvest is good. Since he focuses on long-term goals, he cannot reap the benefits immediately, but he has kept one pentacle for himself. Through his efforts, he hopes to achieve a long-term, stable harvest.",
        "upright_content" => "The meaning of the Seven of Pentacles is related to investment and effort. Following the Six of Pentacles, it refers to the end of financial or material hardship. If you have been putting in time and effort at work, it indicates that your efforts are paying off and will continue to do so in the future.

  If you are considering investing, the Seven of Pentacles indicates that you are ready to put in a lot of effort, time, and work to achieve your desired goals. It reinforces your long-term vision and helps indicate that you are not limited to seeing results in the short term. It shows how much you value your investments due to the effort you are willing to put in.

  The Seven of Pentacles is also related to the fear of failure. You don't know if you will reap the fruits of your labor. When delays occur, it can also indicate frustration. You may have put in a lot of effort into your project, but now it seems that nothing is coming to fruition. The good news is that it means you are learning from your failures and mistakes. It may not seem like it at first, but mistakes allow you to study how to better invest your time to make the most of your future risks.",
        "reversed_content" => "Reversed, the Seven of Pentacles means your returns may now be scattered. It can also mean that the returns on your labor are not as significant as you imagined. The benefit of this is that it shows you know when to stop investing time, money, or energy into a particular project. Therefore, you need to reassess your choices and figure out where you should place your resources. The reversed meaning of the Seven of Pentacles can also be applied to relationships and the effort and emotions you put into them.

  The symbolism of the Seven of Pentacles often involves business risks and investments. However, it also crosses into relationships, which are also seen as investments. The efforts put into these investments can be time, money, and hard work.",
        "upright_love" => "The Seven of Pentacles in love indicates that love can develop slowly. For singles, long-term friendships can slowly turn into romantic love. The friendships you are building now can also become seeds for something more. Love can be exhausting at times, but the rewards that come with it are priceless. If you are in a relationship, life together might seem tedious or grueling now. Perhaps your relationship might need to create long-term plans or make compromises in daily life or finances to stay together. But this card also reminds us that love isn't always about passionate romance and emotional highs; it's about partners working hard every day to stay together in a constantly changing world. Over time, all the mundane moments, all the hard work, will become something worth cherishing.",
        "reversed_love" => "When the Seven of Pentacles appears reversed in a love tarot reading, you might be ready to give up. You may have worked hard for love and romance, putting in so much effort with little return. It can suggest a degree of impatience when one cannot force love to magically appear. Some loves come suddenly, while others need time; we can only patiently wait for the right moment. Whether reversed or upright, the Seven of Pentacles in tarot love meanings indicates slow and steady progress, so much so that you might not even notice it. But keep nurturing this love, and one day you might find it has had a profound impact on your life.",
        "upright_career" => "Whether or not you see the results, the Seven of Pentacles suggests progress is being made. It may be slow, but each day your work is paying off. Now, it would be helpful to take a close look at your accomplishments and see what works and what doesn’t. This can help you understand where to focus your energy and what strategies you can take. If you own your business or are self-employed, taking the time now to evaluate your work will be helpful and can lay a solid foundation for future growth.",
        "reversed_career" => "Are you putting too much effort into your work? Or are you not putting in enough? When it comes to your career, the reversed Seven of Pentacles may indicate some imbalance. It seems that no matter the answer, what you do or don’t do seems to make no difference. Results are minimal. Spending too much time on work can sometimes be counterproductive, like overwatering a plant; focusing too much on something can kill it. On the other hand, you might be too distracted to focus on a specific successful strategy. As your efforts are diluted, they might not amount to much. You need to focus on one approach and do research to ensure it is effective.",
        "upright_finances" => "You may now be reaping the fruits of your labor. What you have been steadily investing your energy and time into can finally show progress. Before you know it, you might find that you will be able to enjoy these rewards.",
        "reversed_finances" => "In financial matters, the reversed Seven of Pentacles symbolizes investments of time, energy, and resources that have not paid off. You may even suffer losses. Despite working hard for your dreams, you might not get the returns you were hoping for. Negotiate your worth.",
        "yes_no" => "The Seven of Pentacles represents perseverance in your career or business. It is associated with success but requires slow, steady growth. It indicates that you will have to wait a long time to receive rewards, and you may not fully realize your potential. There is no definite answer here.",
        "past" => "Delays in your matters have been affecting you, but don’t lose hope. Your perseverance will lead you to success.",
        "present" => "Your current long-term hard work will bring you a lot of personal growth and achievement.",
        "future" => "Your path will be long, but if you can continue without losing determination or energy, the rewards will be immense.",
    ],
    43 =>
    [
        "id" => 44,
        "type_id" => 1,
        "number" => 43,
        "name" => "Eight of Pentacles",
        "upright_keyword" => "Skills, Talent, Craftsmanship, Quality, High Standards, Expertise, Mastery, Commitment, Dedication, Achievement",
        "reversed_keyword" => "Lack of Quality, Hasty Work, Poor Reputation, Lack of Motivation, Mediocrity, Laziness, Low Skills, Dead End",
        "astrology" => "",
        "element" => "Earth Element",
        "image_key" => "43_Eight_of_Pentacles",
        "content" => "The Eight of Pentacles card depicts a young man etching a pentacle shape onto eight gold coins. This card symbolizes someone who is completely focused on what they are doing. The distant town signifies that he has successfully isolated himself from distractions, allowing him to fully concentrate on his task. The Eight of Pentacles refers to moments in your life when you focus on completing a specific task. You are completely immersed in it and are dedicated to producing the best work possible.",
        "upright_content" => "This card indicates a time when you must work hard and focus entirely on your task. This does not necessarily mean a negative situation, but it does mean you have to truly put in the effort to do your best. The task you need to complete can be personal or professional. Whatever the type of task, don't be afraid to ask for help when things become overwhelming. The Eight of Pentacles is about the effort you put into what you do. It’s possible that you have many things to address. Hard work is essential, but you still need to find a balance.

  In terms of work, job seekers should expect their work to be demanding. The Eight of Pentacles also indicates that you need to have confidence in yourself and your ability to complete the job. For those currently employed, you will be responsible for more tasks and responsibilities. Do not hesitate to ask your colleagues for help. In terms of love, your work may impact your relationships. No matter how demanding your job is, you need to make time to establish emotional connections with others.

  In financial matters, the Eight of Pentacles can indicate that the financial assistance you have been hoping for is coming. Be careful how you spend this money, remembering that it is the result of your hard work, not luck. When it comes to health, the Eight of Pentacles may mean it's time to work hard to improve your health, and you must be vigilant about exercise and diet.",
        "reversed_content" => "Reversed, the Eight of Pentacles signifies a task that may be more arduous. This means that if you want to feel happy and successful with the outcome, you need to act quickly and carefully. In terms of work, the reversed Eight of Pentacles emphasizes the importance of impressing your employer with your diligence, dedication, and wisdom. Never shy away from any tasks or responsibilities at work—otherwise, this could damage your reputation. In love, the Eight of Pentacles can indicate that neither of you may be ready to take on the responsibilities needed to make your relationship work.

  Concerning finances, you may have illusions about your current financial status. Perhaps you are relying purely on luck to achieve your goals. While dreaming is not wrong, you should understand that to improve your situation, you must be patient and ready to work hard. In terms of health, the reversed Eight of Pentacles may indicate concerns but not knowing how to address them. Never be afraid to seek help from medical professionals to understand and improve your condition.",
        "upright_love" => "Think carefully; loving someone is like honing a skill. It requires growing empathy, compassion, patience, curiosity, and a desire for self-improvement. Be proud of your achievements and the lessons you've learned. If you are in a relationship, you may find that your lover still surprises you, even after all the time you have spent together. If you work hard enough, you will discover new aspects of them every day. Perhaps you fell in love with them for their sweetness and kindness, only to see their passion flare up when faced with danger or something against their principles. Learning to appreciate their new facets can deepen your love for each other.",
        "reversed_love" => "In love, there are no shortcuts, and no easy paths to take. The reversed Eight of Pentacles tarot love meaning reminds us that the effort we put into our relationships and love lives is important. We either put our all into it, watching it grow under our care, or take it for granted, letting it eventually wither. This means your relationship or romantic life may now demand a lot from you. Perhaps your partner needs you to step up; have you been doing your part of the chores? Have you expressed your love? Have you given love as much as you have received it? Try to ensure that both of your needs are met.",
        "upright_career" => "In work, your dedication and commitment to improving your skills may be paying off. Career goals can be achieved now, and you may reach a new level of skill and expertise. Others may appreciate your growth and see you as a leader in your field. Sometimes, this card can also signify promotions. If you are running a business, your craftsmanship and care for your work will bring great success and profit. Keep your skills sharp and stay curious. If you are currently in a learning phase, your talents might now impress others.",
        "reversed_career" => "You might now be stuck in a monotonous job that you hate. A lack of passion may affect the effort you put into your work, and your work is likely to suffer. However, you may not feel an urgency to make any changes. The work you do feels bland, and you no longer care about improving your skills. Instead, you might drag your feet, waiting for the clock to run out and collect your paycheck. Employers might now see you as lacking the experience needed for a new position. If you have a business, quality standards might drop, and your reputation could suffer as a result.",
        "upright_finances" => "You may be financially rewarded for your dedication and commitment to your field. Sometimes this can indicate promotions, and if you are self-employed, it can mean more business. If you have been careful with your finances, you might slowly become more financially independent. As you enjoy your success, you might reflect on past struggles. Pat yourself on the back and let these thoughts motivate you.",
        "reversed_finances" => "You may be a bit careless with your finances, leading to overspending, or you might be entirely ignorant of your financial status. When you need money, you might find yourself in a bind. It’s best to face these issues and take care of them before they get worse.",
        "yes_no" => "The Eight of Pentacles is a card that suggests skill and diligence improvement. It indicates favorable career opportunities and gaining new skills as long as you act prudently and take a balanced approach. The outlook of this card is positive. Yes, this is your answer.",
        "past" => "The skills you have mastered will lead you to success. Continue to develop, and you will reach moments of enlightenment.",
        "present" => "By developing your talents, you will find success in your endeavors. Investing in yourself now will bring greater rewards later.",
        "future" => "The future brings you success in your career or spiritual endeavors. The amount of praise you receive depends on the time you spend identifying and mastering skills.",
    ],
    44 =>
    [
        "id" => 45,
        "type_id" => 1,
        "number" => 44,
        "name" => "Nine of Pentacles",
        "upright_keyword" => "Rewarding Efforts, Success, Achievement, Independence, Leisure, Material Security, Self-Sufficiency",
        "reversed_keyword" => "Guarded, Overspending, Material Instability, Recklessness, Superficiality",
        "astrology" => "",
        "element" => "Earth Element",
        "image_key" => "44_Nine_of_Pentacles",
        "content" => "The Nine of Pentacles depicts a woman in the middle of a vineyard. The lady is wearing a luxurious robe decorated with sunflowers. She seems to be part of a grand estate, as we see a castle in the distant background. A falcon sits calmly and playfully on her left hand. The vineyard behind her is lush and full of grapes and golden coins, indicating that her efforts have been successful and have borne abundant fruit.",
        "upright_content" => "The Nine of Pentacles suggests that the querent has reached a stage in their life where they are confident, independent, and self-sufficient. Through hard work, this person is now ready to enjoy the money, leisure, and material comfort.

  The difficulties faced earlier in the journey of the Pentacles seem to be over. The Nine of Pentacles not only conveys happiness but also a sense of security and freedom that material wealth can bring. In retrospect, the querent can now celebrate the hardships, struggles, and hard work of their path. The challenges they faced before have given them a broader perspective necessary to understand the spiritual value of success. Knowing how difficult it was to get here, she intends to enjoy every day given to her.

  Like other Nines in the tarot deck, this card sometimes suggests that the querent's journey is not yet complete. There is something missing here—the element of community and relationships. The gifts of the suit are meant to be shared, and this woman is far from home.

  The Nine of Pentacles can also refer to a specific time in a person’s life. This time is about restraint and grace. Diplomacy and grace will lead to the expected outcome.",
        "reversed_content" => "The reversed Nine of Pentacles can indicate financial troubles. It might suggest a false display of security and stability. There may be a desire to keep up appearances—to have all the finer things in life even when we cannot afford them. Where does this come from?

  There may be a desire to keep up appearances—to have all the finer things in life even when we cannot afford them.

  Use this as an opportunity to figure out what is most important. The reversed Nine of Pentacles indicates that a person may truly see, perhaps for the first time, that we cannot rely solely on material wealth to bring happiness.

  Other meanings of this card can vary depending on the context—you might find yourself in a period of your life where you should be able to rest and relax after years of hard work, but find you are unable to do so. In such a case, rejuvenation is the ultimate advice of the reversed Nine of Pentacles. You need to take a step back, allow yourself to rest, and regain strength.",
        "upright_love" => "Your life is going well; you might be experiencing a luxurious period, or at least, you have everything you need. Even if you don't have a partner now, romance might not seem particularly urgent to you. You might just want to savor what you have. This quality can make you more attractive to others; any lover you find now needs to ensure they contribute to this happiness rather than take it away. Those already in a relationship may find that everyone has their own achievements, careers, hobbies, interests, and social lives; there is a healthy mix of independence and love between you two. Sometimes, this card can also point to working together with your lover at home, creating a space that truly belongs to you.",
        "reversed_love" => "Although it seems you have everything you want now, that might not be the case. The reversed Nine of Pentacles tarot love meaning can indicate a feeling that, despite having everything, something is still missing in your life. Single people may be acutely aware of this; you might have a good career, stable finances, great friendships, and family relationships, but love still eludes you. Sometimes, this can be unconscious; you might worry about giving up your independence, or fear sharing your life with someone who won’t love you but love what you have. You may not even realize you’re pushing people away. If you’re in a relationship, despite your best efforts and wanting to spend your life with this person, you may still feel guarded. The reversed Nine of Pentacles asks you to let go a little.",
        "upright_career" => "This card indicates you have achieved great accomplishments in your career, and you will be duly rewarded; abundance, success, and financial rewards are well-deserved. All your hard work and professional attitude have paid off, and now you can take the time to sit back and enjoy your success. Your business might be flourishing, and profits might allow you to live comfortably. Sometimes, this card also symbolizes retirement or taking a break after a period of continuous work and labor.",
        "reversed_career" => "If you've recently failed to handle things properly, it might be because you haven't put in much effort. The Nine of Pentacles indicates that you desire success but might not be ready to actually work for it. On the other hand, this card can indicate that you might be working too hard, to the point where everything else has been put on hold. Time flies quickly, and before you know it, everything could change. If you have a business, take some time to check your finances. You need to make sure that the people you work with are trustworthy. It's also safe to take some time to check your legal documents.",
        "upright_finances" => "The Nine of Pentacles represents prosperity, stability, and material security. If you have invested time or resources into something, it might be time to enjoy the rewards. Your social status might rise due to this newfound comfort. Since this card is also associated with land, you might be purchasing some property.",
        "reversed_finances" => "You might be overspending right now, and you might have to deal with some severe financial recklessness issues. Impulse buying and spending beyond your means can lead to regret. You might also be financially dependent on others. This card is also a warning to avoid shady business deals or get-rich-quick schemes. These usually lead to financial troubles.",
        "yes_no" => "The Nine of Pentacles represents wealth and financial security. It might indicate that you will finally be rewarded for all the efforts you have put into a significant project in your business or life. The presence of this card may indicate financial and/or personal independence. The answer you seek is likely yes.",
        "past" => "The joys you have experienced are the rewards for your achievements. Though the rewards of a recent project are not yet apparent, you will be richly compensated for your work.",
        "present" => "The solution you have been seeking will come, relieving you of the stress associated with the problem.",
        "future" => "Indicating positive outcomes, this card signifies achieved goals. You will be in a more blissful state, having more free time to enjoy nature.",
    ],
    45 =>
    [
        "id" => 46,
        "type_id" => 1,
        "number" => 45,
        "name" => "Ten of Pentacles",
        "upright_keyword" => "Inheritance, Roots, Family, Ancestry, Legacy, Windfall, Foundation, Privilege, Affluence, Stability, Tradition",
        "reversed_keyword" => "Family Disputes, Bankruptcy, Debt, Fleeting Success, Financial Conflict, Instability, Breaking Tradition",
        "astrology" => "",
        "element" => "Earth Element",
        "image_key" => "45_Ten_of_Pentacles",
        "content" => "In the Ten of Pentacles card, an elderly man sits beneath an archway leading to a vast estate. He appears to be the head of a family, surrounded by younger relatives. He wears a robe adorned with crescents and grapevines—symbols of the merging of the spiritual and material. He is with his family and dogs. In front of him is a happy couple, presumably his children, and behind the couple is a playful child, his grandchild. The child reaches out playfully to pet the dog.",
        "upright_content" => "The Ten of Pentacles is associated with lasting success and satisfaction. This card indicates that all the hard work you’ve put in will pay off in the future. It signifies that everything will ultimately work out well because you have always looked at the long term and have not chosen shortcuts. Your legacy will certainly stand the test of time for many years to come. This is a relief, as the journey to get here was filled with setbacks and challenges, making this point in the journey all the sweeter.

  In the card, the elderly man can sit back and relax while observing the lives of his descendants. The satisfaction he gains from his achievements is intertwined with the happiness of his children. The Ten of Pentacles also touches on the happiness you experience because you have sown many happy seeds and shared them with others, especially family and relatives. It points out the importance of these people in your life.

  This card suggests that family is prioritized above all else, no matter what goals you have set for yourself. You must reach out to the elders in your family and make them feel comfortable and secure.",
        "reversed_content" => "The reversed Ten of Pentacles may be a warning about your future financial status. It can point to big or small issues later in life, even if they may not be a problem now. It also shows the erroneous nature of investments in which you have invested a lot of time and effort. Generally, this reversed card seems to suggest that you are placing too much stake on short-term success while undermining your long-term potential. Take a step back and assess if your current decisions might cause greater harm in the future.

  Generally, this reversed card seems to suggest that you are placing too much stake on short-term success while undermining your long-term potential.

  The reversed Ten of Pentacles meaning can also deal with relationships. It may indicate that a marriage that has lasted many years could suddenly end. It may also indicate that you have encountered issues but still have hope for things to get back on track. For singles, it may suggest that some of your relationships are suitable for short-term affairs but lack the substance needed for lifelong commitments.",
        "upright_love" => "If you are in a relationship, the Ten of Pentacles love meaning can symbolize abundance, family, and luck for the couple. Both of you are in a strong position emotionally and materially. If you choose to have one, you have likely already laid down a solid foundation for a family. This thought may indeed be on your mind; you may be moving in together, buying a house, or starting a family.

  If you are single, your family’s approval may have a large impact on who you choose as a partner. Your extended family might be very important to you, and creating harmony between them and your romantic interest is crucial for you. You are looking for something long-term, and you recognize that marriage is sometimes not just about love, but also about joining two families together.",
        "reversed_love" => "Are you placing too much emphasis on what your family or others think of your partner? In your quest to find love, you might also be seeking external validation instead of focusing on the emotional connection between the two of you. On the other hand, there may be conflicts between your lover and your family or friends. They may find your partner 'unsuitable'; they may not have a good enough job, come from a different background, or not be the prince charming your family needs to boast about how well their child is doing. Current conflicts can greatly impact your relationship, and you may need to stand your ground and set boundaries instead of taking their opinions without consideration for yourself.",
        "upright_career" => "If you have a business, you are building something lasting. The Ten of Pentacles can also imply something about a family business. If you are not a business owner, don’t worry—the Ten of Pentacles also suggests that your work and career path are very secure and will provide you with long-term financial stability. This reliable job may be in a large, traditional company with a long history.",
        "reversed_career" => "If you own your own business, things might not be going well for you. In the worst-case scenario, it might mean the dissolution of the company, debt, or bankruptcy. It might be time to reevaluate your business decisions and see what can be salvaged. When it comes to careers, the Ten of Pentacles indicates that your job may not be stable, especially in the long term. You might find better prospects elsewhere.",
        "upright_finances" => "The Ten of Pentacles can bring about a sudden windfall. Since this card is associated with family, it is likely to come from a relative. The card can also mean that you are establishing your own financial future. You might be planning your retirement, building your savings, or even creating a will. Generally, this card symbolizes wealth and money coming from the family.",
        "reversed_finances" => "Beware of any debts you are accumulating now. The reversed Ten of Pentacles represents significant financial losses. Sometimes, this card can also suggest inheritance disputes, family quarrels, or general financial conflicts. You may need to be especially cautious now.",
        "yes_no" => "The Ten of Pentacles indicates stability, prosperity, and overall good fortune. This is likely all due to having positive, close relationships or a tight-knit family as a foundation. An inheritance or discovery of treasure might be waiting for you, and your answer is yes.",
        "past" => "Through your ability to wisely spend money, you have become wealthy and established a secure foundation.",
        "present" => "You will receive a reward due to your efforts and your standing within the family. Carefully evaluate your merits accordingly.",
        "future" => "Unexpected solutions to solve financial difficulties will arise. The projects and ideas you are working on now will benefit future generations.",
    ],
    46 =>
    [
        "id" => 47,
        "type_id" => 1,
        "number" => 46,
        "name" => "Page of Pentacles",
        "upright_keyword" => "Ambitious, Diligent, Goal-oriented, Planner, Consistent, Star Student, Studious, Grounded, Loyal, Faithful, Dependable",
        "reversed_keyword" => "Foolish, Immature, Irresponsible, Lazy, Poor Grades, Procrastination, Missed Opportunities, Bad Prospects",
        "astrology" => "",
        "element" => "Earth Element",
        "image_key" => "46_Page_of_Pentacles",
        "content" => "The Page of Pentacles depicts a young person standing alone in a vast field blooming with flowers. In the background, you can also notice lush trees and a plowed field. The young person seems to walk slowly and appears unaware of his surroundings as his attention is entirely absorbed by the coin he holds and everything it represents: ambition, security, wealth, nature, and sensuality. The Page of Pentacles symbolizes someone who is grounded, loyal, and diligent.",
        "upright_content" => "When we encounter the Page of Pentacles, we immediately see a person who is ambitious and focused. She is protected and nurtured by the suit she is named after. Under its guidance, she is deeply connected to the earth, nature, and all its gifts. She cherishes the body as it is also a manifestation of her element. Her diligence, ambition, and loyalty drive her to quickly plan for the future, as her focus is right there.

  Under the guidance of the pentacle, she is deeply connected to the earth, nature, and all its gifts. She cherishes the body as it is also a manifestation of her element.

  When you meet her, she may convey news related to all worldly and material things. When you hear her message, be inspired like her and lay the foundation for achieving your ambitions.

  Typically, the Page of Pentacles refers to all the energy required to complete a task. It can indicate determination, focus, and the ability to persist on a particular task, no matter how tedious it may seem. In work, the Page of Pentacles may mean that you have many tasks you are responsible for but too little time to complete them. Now is not the time to feel pressured and overwhelmed. Assistance will be there for you; you just need to ask for it.

  In financial matters, the Page of Pentacles can refer to the rewards of your hard work. For those who invest their hard-earned money, now is not the best time to take risks. Invest your money in safe and traditional ways—diligence will pay off. If you are currently experiencing health issues, this problem may be the result of ongoing neglect. Let a professional ensure this is not the case.",
        "reversed_content" => "When the Page of Pentacles card appears reversed, it can indicate that you are unfocused. You may be distracted by many things. Try to emulate the Page's talent and focus your attention before moving on to the next step.

  The Page of Pentacles can indicate that you are unfocused.

  This can also indicate that you need to take a break to rejuvenate. In terms of work, the reversed Page of Pentacles can mean you currently feel overwhelmed by the heavy demands of your workplace. Remember, it is always better to seek help and get the work done than to try to do everything yourself and ultimately fail. In love, you may be in a stable and steady relationship, but perhaps someone has recently caught your interest.

  When it comes to your finances, the reversed Page of Pentacles may refer to a tendency to play and gamble. Be sure to stay responsible and control your actions. In terms of health, try to stay away from dangerous activities.",
        "upright_love" => "The person symbolized by the Page of Pentacles is ambitious, loyal, and practical; they are often seen as diligent students, but once you get to know them well, they can be quite fun. Their ambition and focus mean they work hard. They are likely to be as focused on their goals as they are on their lover. Compared to others who may be more outgoing, their quiet demeanor might make them difficult to notice at first.

  If this doesn't represent someone entering your love life, the Page of Pentacles tarot love meaning can simply indicate this Page's dedication and loyalty in your relationship. While sometimes this relationship may lack passion and feel a bit dull, love is there; you may just need to go out and figure out how to inject some fun and excitement into your romance. Try not to always put practicality before passion in your relationship, and you should be fine.",
        "reversed_love" => "The reversed Page of Pentacles tarot love meaning can indicate a lack of commitment and dedication when it comes to matters of the heart. You may find yourself easily distracted by every passing stranger instead of focusing on long-term companionship. There's nothing wrong with this, but make sure to set clear expectations instead of leading potential lovers on. Other times, this card can point to ambivalence about dating. If you are in a relationship, this Page can indicate a romance that has become stagnant and monotonous. This boredom can lead to frustration. You and your partner need to work hard to stay together and remember why you fell in love with each other in the first place.",
        "upright_career" => "You may now be laying a solid foundation for future success. You are likely setting goals, planning strategies, and putting these plans into action. You are not afraid to put yourself out there to achieve your wildest dreams. There are likely many opportunities available to you, so keep up the hard work! Sometimes, this card can also suggest that you are taking or wish to begin a higher education course. Study hard; if you do the work, you are likely to do an amazing job.",
        "reversed_career" => "When the Page of Pentacles is reversed, bad news may be coming. You may now be neglecting your work or studies, meaning the foundation for your success feels quite shaky. You may dream of success, but when it comes to putting in the work, you may become lazy and unmotivated. Sometimes, this stems from unrealistic ideals of success. We often see the results but not the hard work needed to achieve those goals. Be realistic about what you want to achieve and whether you are willing to make the sacrifices necessary to achieve them. If you are currently in school, you may be performing poorly or not putting in your best effort.",
        "upright_finances" => "Good news regarding your finances is on its way. The Page of Pentacles promises rewards as long as you take steps to plan your future. Do your research, stick to a budget, and you will find that your efforts greatly impact your material situation.",
        "reversed_finances" => "The reversed Page of Pentacles can bring bad financial news or sometimes material insecurity. When it comes to finances, you may feel anxious and worried. Sometimes this card can also indicate being irresponsible with your money. While this can be scary, it’s important to get a clear picture of what money is coming in and out of your bank account. Don’t avoid the situation; make sure you live within your means. Savings for emergencies can be helpful.",
        "yes_no" => "The Page of Pentacles represents a young person who is skilled, focused, and studious, being both disciplined and enthusiastic. He may indicate some kind of promotion or a new, enjoyable hobby in the near future. The overall mood of this card is positive, suggesting that the answer is yes.",
        "past" => "Your past ambitions and idealism will gain success from your latest ideas. You are cultivating new hobbies or careers.",
        "present" => "News is coming, heralding the arrival of change. Though not immediate, be prepared to weigh the risks and rewards of new ventures.",
        "future" => "The future may bring some daunting challenges that will force you to give in. However, if you stand your ground, you can overcome them and achieve success.",
    ],
    47 =>
    [
        "id" => 48,
        "type_id" => 1,
        "number" => 47,
        "name" => "Knight of Pentacles",
        "upright_keyword" => "Practical, Reliable, Efficient, Steadfast, Slow but Steady, Diligent, Loyal, Patient, Conservative",
        "reversed_keyword" => "Workaholic, Lazy, Dull, Boring, No Initiative, Cheap, Irresponsible, Gambler, Risky Investments",
        "astrology" => "",
        "element" => "Earth Element",
        "image_key" => "47_Knight_of_Pentacles",
        "content" => "The Knight of Pentacles revolves around work, effort, and general responsibility. The Knight of Pentacles sits on a black horse in a field. Unlike other knights who are always off on adventures, this knight decides to stay home and focus on plowing the fields. He prepares for the next harvest—he believes he can do the most on this land. In his hand, he holds only one coin. He gazes at it, and in his eyes, we see a kind of careful consideration. Perhaps he is dreaming about what it can bring him. Other knights might find him a bit boring, but this knight is more concerned with the long-term future of his kingdom.",
        "upright_content" => "The Knight of Pentacles is about daily tasks and the responsibility one must gain through a specific project. This knight has the patience to complete all his duties and is seen by others as reliable and committed to his work. Seeing this card suggests the need to be trustworthy and dependable.

  This knight has the patience to complete all his duties and is seen by others as reliable and committed to his work.

  You are fully committed to your tasks and ensure that you complete your work efficiently. You are absolutely loyal and do everything you can to ensure things go smoothly. While your sense of responsibility is admirable, be mindful that it does not turn into perfectionism—it can manifest in all aspects of your life.

  The Knight of Pentacles can also represent routines or the kind of general hard work you go through daily. The meaning of the Knight of Pentacles also suggests that the querent should continue doing what they are doing. Stick to tried and tested methods, and he will accomplish all he has set out to do. Sometimes, sticking to what has been done is not necessarily a bad thing.",
        "reversed_content" => "When the Knight of Pentacles appears reversed in a tarot reading, the once positive characteristics in the upright position are now taken to the extreme. You may feel stuck in your daily life and bored with everything around you. You might wish for a change of pace to avoid this tedious repetition. The reversed Knight of Pentacles can also indicate that you have completely neglected many serious aspects of your life. When this card appears reversed, financial or personal issues are often ignored in favor of work.

  You may be an ambitious and driven person who works hard to shoulder your responsibilities—to the point of sacrificing your social life. Perhaps you could try taking more risks or spending more time with friends and family. The reversed Knight of Pentacles is a strong indication that you need to change this lifestyle before you risk burnout and exhaustion.",
        "upright_love" => "The Knight of Pentacles is diligent and hardworking. He is patient, reliable, and stable, but sometimes deeply focused on his work. They are reluctant to take risks in love and other aspects of life. It can be hard to change this person’s mind; this means they can be stubborn but are also very dependable and committed partners. The Knight of Pentacles tarot love meaning can also hint at a deep and reliable relationship, though not very exciting. If you are looking for commitment, stability, and security in your love life, this card will be a welcome sight. It suggests a partnership where both of you will work together towards long-term goals.",
        "reversed_love" => "Your love life may have recently become quite dull and stale. You might feel like a homebody, preferring to stay alone rather than take any emotional risks and face potential rejection from others. If you are in a relationship, you might feel a bit desperate for change. Perhaps one of you is spending too much time at work, or all their energy is focused on practical, financial, or career matters that they haven't prioritized the relationship. Make sure both of you take the time out of your busy lives to be with each other or try spontaneous activities to bring much-needed freshness to your partnership.",
        "upright_career" => "When it comes to work, the Knight of Pentacles suggests ambition, drive, and focus. You are deeply committed to your goals, no matter how far into the future they might be. It’s likely you’ll do anything you can to achieve them, so you’re prepared to put in the hard work, sweat, and tears. You have a slow and steady approach and believe that hard work will pay off. If you are looking for a job, you need to prove your reliability and dedication to potential employers.",
        "reversed_career" => "Are you lacking ambition? Do you find yourself unmotivated when it comes to your work? One possible meaning of the reversed Knight of Pentacles is that you are not working hard enough to achieve your career dreams. Alternatively, you might be so obsessed with your career goals that you sacrifice everything else to achieve them. Your love life might be a mess, you might hardly meet friends, and you might have almost forgotten your close family. Do you remember how to have fun? It might be better to balance your work and life better in the long run. Don’t work yourself to death.",
        "upright_finances" => "The Knight of Pentacles slowly but steadily builds his financial future. He avoids risks and prefers things that are as safe and reliable as he is. You might be budgeting for long-term goals and slowly saving up. Some frugality now can be helpful.",
        "reversed_finances" => "Wasting resources can be signaled by the meaning of the reversed Knight of Pentacles tarot card. You might be careless, or you might be very impulsive with purchases, only to find out later that what you bought wasn’t what you hoped or needed. Try to be more cautious. Do all your research before buying big-ticket items.",
        "yes_no" => "The Knight of Pentacles is reliable, respectable, and trustworthy. He possesses undeniable common sense, incredible determination, and various skills, including patience and supporting others. The presence of this card suggests positive things for those who remain loyal. The answer you are seeking is yes.",
        "past" => "Your past challenges have laid the foundation for a hopeful future. Your reliability and responsible attitude have put your best effort at the forefront of completing your work.",
        "present" => "You will receive encouragement from a young person. The security you need to pursue your ambitions will come.",
        "future" => "Follow your routines to produce the best results. Through patience and consistent focus, you can achieve your loftiest ambitions.",
    ],
    48 =>
    [
        "id" => 49,
        "type_id" => 1,
        "number" => 48,
        "name" => "Queen of Pentacles",
        "upright_keyword" => "Generous, Caring, Nurturing, Homely, Good Business Sense, Practical, Comfort, Warmth, Sensible, Luxury",
        "reversed_keyword" => "Selfish, Untidy, Jealous, Insecure, Greedy, Materialistic, Gold Digger, Intolerant, Self-centered, Envious",
        "astrology" => "",
        "element" => "Earth Element",
        "image_key" => "48_Queen_of_Pentacles",
        "content" => "The Queen of Pentacles depicts a beautiful woman sitting on a beautifully decorated throne, holding a coin in her hand. She is surrounded by beautiful blossoming trees and lush green gardens. Her throne is adorned with various beasts of the earth, closely connecting her with nature and abundance. On the bottom right of the card, a rabbit is leaping into the frame, symbolizing her high energy and fertility. Thus, the Queen of Pentacles depicts a degree of success and prosperity. But the rabbit at the bottom warns us to be careful of our leaps when pursuing success.",
        "upright_content" => "The Queen of Pentacles represents a grounded woman who plays many roles to ensure her family’s happiness. She knows how and when to show love, keep a home orderly, cook, and take care of the children. But don't mistake her for just a homemaker; in addition to all these maternal attributes, she can also plan business ventures and execute her plans successfully. It is through her innate business sense that she enjoys such a luxurious life. She is quiet and does not like to publicly display her financial accounts, fearing it would complicate her life, which she prefers to keep simple. She might have a secret bank account that no one knows about because she might choose to be cautious, vigilant, and self-sufficient.

  Therefore, the Queen of Pentacles represents a maternal figure who wishes to help you navigate your way and achieve your goals with her common sense. She will not only show you love but also point you in the right direction when you seem stuck and confused. By her advice, she will ensure you don’t make dangerous financial decisions. She offers you precautions, principles, and support, as well as all the lessons she has learned in her personal life. Because she is a self-made woman, she wants you to be independent and wise so you can also nurture others and be responsible for them.",
        "reversed_content" => "When the Queen of Pentacles is out of sync with her suit’s energy, she can become entirely self-absorbed. The generosity of the upright position has vanished, and she may become selfish or even jealous when others' success seems greater than hers. While upright, her home is usually a haven for her guests, but when reversed, it can become slovenly, and she loses the ability to take care of herself and her surroundings. Her focus on materialism can have a negative impact, making her greedy but lacking a sense of responsibility and competence. How can she get back on her feet and re-enter her natural relationship with the earth and all its creatures?

  The reversed Queen of Pentacles can also indicate that your priorities are misplaced, which can ultimately jeopardize your future. You may find yourself upset and unable to focus on work and long-term goals. You might also be working on projects without taking the time to consult experienced people who can guide you to avoid mistakes.

  This card can also suggest that someone you care for is now ready to take responsibility for their own life. You must learn to let go and let them become independent—it's the most valuable role for a caregiver when their loved one grows enough to make their own decisions.",
        "upright_love" => "The Queen of Pentacles is a worldly, practical, generous, diligent, and warm person who has both business acumen and a love for comfort and luxury. She enjoys making her home welcoming and is always happy to have guests. Singles should be in a good position now to choose a partner who truly brings something to their life. You might have high standards and seek someone as dedicated, committed, and ambitious as you are. If you are already in a relationship, you may find that both of you are enjoying a time of stability, productivity, and prosperity in your life together. You certainly can indulge and treat yourselves.",
        "reversed_love" => "This person can be very self-centered, shallow, and easily envious of what others have. Their insecurities make them frequently jealous and possessive, which can extend to their lovers and relationships, treating their partners as trophies rather than having genuine feelings or love for them. If you are single, the reversed Queen of Pentacles tarot love meaning can indicate that you may need to spend some time nurturing your confidence and healing any insecurities before establishing a relationship with another person. Avoid forming relationships for the wrong reasons; whether for status, money, or simply because you don’t want to be alone. If you are in a relationship, avoid treating your lover as something to possess.",
        "upright_career" => "When it comes to all career-oriented things, the Queen of Pentacles tarot card can bring great success. She is a talented businesswoman, practical, organized, and highly capable in anything she sets her mind to. In your life, she can manifest as a successful person who could be a great mentor, colleague, or business partner. If you choose to work with her, you will find her wealth of skills valuable for your career or professional project. If she offers advice, listen; she cares about you and will help you achieve your goals.",
        "reversed_career" => "Your career may be somewhat chaotic right now, meaning you might find it hard to gain stable income. Don’t be afraid to do as the Queen of Pentacles does and get your hands dirty. Let her confidence in her abilities inspire you. As a person, she might represent a colleague or business partner, but one who might be lazy or bad at managing her tasks. Be cautious, as she might create more problems for you than you need to solve.

  Sometimes, this card can also represent someone who is jealous of your position at work and might secretly cause trouble for you. Be wary of gossip or envy.",
        "upright_finances" => "The Queen of Pentacles brings abundance, success, and material security. You might find that after a period of hard work, you have everything you need to feel comfortable. This card represents a responsible person who knows how to balance enjoying life’s pleasures with practicality, thrift, and taste. She will always look for a good bargain but never compromise on quality.",
        "reversed_finances" => "The reversed Queen of Pentacles can have her finances in disarray, making her easy to mismanage her money. This card can suggest a time when you are too materialistic or superficial. Avoid hoarding cash or items as a way to soothe insecurities.",
        "yes_no" => "The Queen of Pentacles is a practical, organized, and reliable multitasker. She brings abundance and wealth but also needs the ability to love herself and not fear future changes or journeys to achieve your goals. This card certainly points to yes.",
        "past" => "You will have the opportunity to create a secure environment with the talents you have been developing. The help you give and continue to give to those in need will be an important source of achievement.",
        "present" => "Influence from a female in your life will provide you with some practical advice. This advice will help you create abundant prosperity.",
        "future" => "Effective use of your talents will lead to financial success. Remember your practical nature, and prosperity will find you.",
    ],
    49 =>
    [
        "id" => 50,
        "type_id" => 1,
        "number" => 49,
        "name" => "King of Pentacles",
        "upright_keyword" => "Abundance, Prosperity, Security, Ambitious, Safe, Kind, Patriarchal, Protective, Merchant, Provider, Sensual, Reliable",
        "reversed_keyword" => "Greedy, Materialistic, Wasteful, Chauvinistic, Poor Financial Decisions, Gambler, Exploitative, Possessive",
        "astrology" => "",
        "element" => "Earth Element",
        "image_key" => "49_King_of_Pentacles",
        "content" => "The King of Pentacles represents a person who is ambitious, materially satisfied, and worldly successful. The King of Pentacles sits on a throne adorned with vines and bull carvings, and his robe is embroidered with numerous grapevine patterns. He appears experienced and majestic. He is also surrounded by various types of plants, vines, and flowers, illustrating the material success of this king. He holds a scepter in his right hand and a coin engraved with a pentacle in his left hand. In the background, you can see a castle, symbolizing his determination and effort.",
        "upright_content" => "When we meet the King of Pentacles, we instantly feel his regal and generous presence. He is a provider and protector, as under his care is a thriving kingdom where citizens prosper and are encouraged. He is naturally responsible and reliable, having almost built everything from scratch through the wisdom granted by the suit. Seeing him in the card foretells success earned through diligent work.

  Generally, this card reminds us to maintain control over our energy and resources in pursuit of greater goals. In terms of work, the King of Pentacles can refer to a more mature person who will play an important role in your career. This person can be very smart and rational but also may be harsh in judgment. He can be your biggest supporter, but be prepared for unsolicited harsh criticism. In love, this can indicate that the person you’ve been waiting for will appear and will love you for who you are.

  In financial matters, the King of Pentacles is one of the best cards to receive. It can mean that your financial situation is stable due to wise investments and hard work. If you are gambling, be sure to initiate a planned action.",
        "reversed_content" => "When reversed, the King of Pentacles falls from his throne. The once prosperous king has either been dethroned or lost everything. Disconnected from the suit’s energy, he may become impatient, overly indulgent, gamble too much, overwork, or seek shortcuts that lead to his downfall. He may become overly focused on materialism, understanding the cost of things but not their value.

  The reversed King of Pentacles can also mean that your definition of success and happiness is determined solely by appearances rather than the true value that security and stability can bring you. It’s time to cultivate a more holistic attitude towards the material world to find true happiness. In love, this card may mean that the person you love is currently facing career-related problems.

  In financial matters, the reversed King of Pentacles tells you to focus on long-term goals. You may be facing financial issues, but don’t see yourself as a failure. Stay positive and understand that this is just a phase in your life. When opportunities come again, don’t make decisions based solely on short-term situations.

  Seeing the King of Pentacles in a reading can indicate some material loss or loss of reputation—be careful not to repeat past mistakes.",
        "upright_love" => "Successful, generous, reliable, and protective, the person represented by the King of Pentacles is a great partner, parent, and provider. He shows his love through actions rather than words and wants to create a stable and loving home for his family. If you meet this person, they may be slow to commit, but that's only because they take love very seriously and need to truly know you before taking any next steps. If not representing a person, the King of Pentacles can suggest a time of security and stability in your relationship. You both will be comfortable, emotionally and materially. You may have worked very hard in the past to enjoy your current level of comfort, and now you can relax a bit.",
        "reversed_love" => "The reversed King of Pentacles can be stubborn, conservative, greedy, and materialistic. They can do almost anything to gain more resources; so beware of characters in your love life who may only be using you. On one hand, this person can be irresponsible and unreliable, choosing to gamble their resources. On the other hand, this person can use their material means to control their partner and family. If this doesn’t signal someone in your love life right now, the reversed King of Pentacles tarot love meaning may suggest a period of emotional or financial insecurity, jealousy, manipulation, or coercion.",
        "upright_career" => "In a professional context, the King of Pentacles can be an outstanding indicator of successful business ventures. When it comes to your job and career, this King has achieved his highest ambitions and is highly respected among colleagues. This card can also indicate that a more experienced person will guide and encourage you in your chosen field. This person will have a wealth of experience and can provide you with much-needed support, sometimes even recommending new jobs or promotions.",
        "reversed_career" => "In terms of work, the reversed King of Pentacles can indicate unsuccessful work projects or, at worst, business closures or unemployment. There can be a lot of instability regarding work. You may be tired of your job, and as your motivation declines, this can greatly affect the quality of your work. Sometimes, this card can also indicate a cold-hearted person at work who may discourage you or try to undermine you. It's important to ignore his negativity and focus on what you need to do. Engaging with such selfish, greedy, and manipulative individuals will only drag you down. Instead, focus on your career and do your best. If you have been looking for a promotion or a raise, the King of Pentacles can sometimes point out that you need more experience.",
        "upright_finances" => "Financially, the King of Pentacles represents the achievement of financial milestones. Perhaps you have reached a level of security that comes from diligent and wise savings and investments. Since this King is also generous, you might also use your newfound wealth to support loved ones while enjoying luxuries you may have missed while saving. Indulge a little; you deserve it.",
        "reversed_finances" => "In monetary matters, the reversed King of Pentacles can signify financial losses, or worse, bankruptcy and debt. Financial resources may be very tight right now. You may have gambled away your savings or made poor financial decisions. Alternatively, the reversed King of Pentacles can indicate you might be hoarding your resources, and your stinginess could cause others to view you negatively.",
        "yes_no" => "The King of Pentacles is a reliable, confident, and self-sufficient individual. He signifies success, wealth, and endless personal growth. Achieving your goals may require some self-exploration and firm commitment, but the outcome looks positive. Your answer is yes.",
        "past" => "The careful progress you have made is leading you towards success. The advice you received recently will help you achieve your goals.",
        "present" => "Your idealism has made you confident and reliable, but focusing on your financial security for a while may be better. Consulting a professional or elder will help safeguard your efforts.",
        "future" => "You possess an inherent ability in the areas of financial gain and material acquisition, even if you are unaware of it. The money you earn through your own efforts will bring rewards that go beyond material benefits.",
    ],
    50 =>
    [
        "id" => 51,
        "type_id" => 1,
        "number" => 50,
        "name" => "Ace of Cups",
        "upright_keyword" => "Love, New Feelings, Emotional Awakening, Creativity, Spirituality, Intuition",
        "reversed_keyword" => "Apathy, Emptiness, Emotional Loss, Blocked Creativity, Feeling Unloved, Melancholy",
        "astrology" => "",
        "element" => "Water Element",
        "image_key" => "50_Ace_of_Cups",
        "content" => "On the Ace of Cups card, a hand emerges from a cloud, holding a cup as if offering it to the querent. The cup is overflowing with sparkling water, symbolizing pure and pristine emotions. Accepting this offer and drinking from the cup will undoubtedly bring emotional and spiritual fulfillment.

  The cup has five streams of water flowing out of it, representing the power of intuition and the importance of listening to one's inner voice. To achieve the kind of emotional or spiritual satisfaction depicted in the Ace of Cups card, the querent needs to follow this inner voice and stay true to it, no matter the circumstances. This will require emotional discipline, but the rewards suggested by the card are overflowing joy and happiness.",
        "upright_content" => "The upright Ace of Cups indicates that it's time to let go of any emotional baggage and start living a fulfilling life. Like all other Aces, this card represents a new beginning—a chance to start afresh. It might be in the form of allowing yourself to embrace the possibility of new relationships, whether romantic or otherwise, that can emotionally satisfy you.

  The release indicated by this card can be spiritual or emotional, depending on what you are experiencing. The Ace of Cups can appear after a long period of solitude or enduring something that deeply hurt you emotionally, signaling a new chapter.

  For an individual, it is important to open up to more friendships, love, and spiritual learning opportunities. You now have the chance to leave your past behind, as you are gifted the cup.

  Whether you drink from the cup to your fullest content is up to you.",
        "reversed_content" => "When the Ace of Cups is reversed, the image is most clear—the water spills out of the cup, leaving it empty, and the blessings of water are wasted. Seeing the Ace of Cups reversed in a Tarot reading means you have been enduring emotional instability or pain for some time. It suggests a sense of loss, perhaps something significant to you no longer brings you the joy it once did.

  Since the cup also governs creativity, you may also encounter various creative blocks where the inspiration once flowed, but now it is dried up.

  In all these situations, you must examine who or what controls the cup, who is allowing it to spill? What can you do to turn it upright again?",
        "upright_love" => "As one of the happiest cards in a love Tarot reading, the Ace of Cups suggests a new emotional awakening. If you are single, you might find yourself developing a new romantic relationship or a friendship that means a lot to you. If you are already in a relationship, you and your partner could reach a new level of intimacy, compassion, and understanding. The Ace of Cups Tarot love meaning implies that you now have the opportunity to grow emotionally, spiritually, and creatively if you drink from the cup. Decisions made based on feelings and intuition are favorable at this time; learn to trust your gut and avoid overanalyzing situations.",
        "reversed_love" => "Some sadness and emotional upset can be indicated by the reversed Ace of Cups Tarot love meaning. This may stem from arguments or even breakups, leaving you feeling lonely and vulnerable. The card can also simply mean feeling a bit gloomy about your current relationship or experiencing a temporary loss of faith. Something is hindering you from experiencing, giving, and receiving true love. You may not be meeting your partner or others with an open heart. Insecurity likely plays a significant role; we all must love ourselves before we can truly love another. Try to look within and give yourself the love you seek before finding it in someone else.",
        "upright_career" => "The upright Ace of Cups is a sign of new emotional beginnings and friendly intentions. In your career, these principles can manifest in various ways. If you are looking for a job, this card can signify a new beginning in your work. It doesn't always mean a new job but can indicate pleasant relationships with your colleagues or an emotional awakening regarding how you view your work. New projects can become sources of creativity. This is a good time to start new challenges and tasks, as you can harness this surge of inspiration. If you have been afraid of taking on more responsibilities, now is the time to overcome those fears, especially if you work in a creative field.",
        "reversed_career" => "When reversed, the good news and camaraderie of the Ace of Cups are overturned. For those seeking a new job, you may feel disappointment. There might be some negative emotions in your work. You may face frustration and obstacles at work, along with a sense of emptiness. Whatever the reason, you may now feel uninspired and unmotivated in your job. Sometimes, since the cup also governs relationships, you may find colleagues less friendly and helpful at this time. Do your best to get through this period and seek motivation where possible. If all else fails, try to remember that work is only one aspect of your life and not its entirety.",
        "upright_finances" => "The Ace of Cups' friendly and sociable qualities can also affect your financial situation. As people become more accepting of you, they are more likely to offer you the financial support you ask for. This support typically comes in the form of approved loans or mortgages, but it can also come from the backing of family and friends. This card is particularly reassuring for those who have been seeking help. Sometimes, this card can also indicate a new wave of creativity when it comes to making money. If this doesn't apply to you, the card usually symbolizes financial stability and the emotional satisfaction that comes with it.",
        "reversed_finances" => "With the Ace of Cups reversed, you may receive some financial news that you weren't hoping to hear. If you applied for a loan or grant, you might be disappointed. Seeking help from family or friends may also not yield any results. If none of these situations apply to you, you might just be dealing with some conflicting emotions or frustrations when handling your financial situation. Allow yourself to feel these emotions but don't let them consume you.",
        "yes_no" => "The Ace of Cups represents overall satisfaction in all different areas of your life. It predicts success and abundance by using good intuition and creativity. New relationships or possible fertility or pregnancy may be related to these positive prospects. The answer is yes.",
        "past" => "There have been numerous times in your life when you have utilized your creative talents and abilities and achieved success in your endeavors. By being passionate and highly focused, you can increase productivity.",
        "present" => "Good news will bring joy and great satisfaction to your life.",
        "future" => "The difficulties you face in the future will affect your emotions but will ultimately bring abundant joy. Remembering this natural balance will bring you rich rewards.",
    ],
    51 =>
    [
        "id" => 52,
        "type_id" => 1,
        "number" => 51,
        "name" => "Two of Cups",
        "upright_keyword" => "Unity, Partnership, Attraction, Connection, Close Bonds, Unified Effort, Mutual Respect",
        "reversed_keyword" => "Separation, Rejection, Division, Imbalance, Tension, Poor Communication, Withdrawal",
        "astrology" => "",
        "element" => "Water Element",
        "image_key" => "51_Two_of_Cups",
        "content" => "This card depicts the image of a man and a woman exchanging cups in a ritual. In the middle is the symbol of the caduceus of Hermes, often associated with negotiation, trade, cosmic energy, protection, proper conduct, and duality. The Two of Cups signifies something very positive as it is one of the most auspicious cards in the Tarot deck for relationships, whether romantic, business, or otherwise. It indicates that a new partnership is brewing, which will be based on balance, respect, and honor. Above the caduceus is a chimera, symbolizing the fire and passion that also governs this partnership.",
        "upright_content" => "Seeing the Two of Cups indicates a partnership built on the union of forces, strong connections, and balanced, equal partnerships. The exchange of cups suggests that each party's emotions are intertwined with the other's, each one's emotions having a profound impact on the other. This signifies a strong pair, the joy of two becoming one.

  When it comes to work, you may notice that people around you will start to appreciate you more. There is mutual respect here, which means you will also feel more comfortable in your workplace. If you are looking for new job opportunities, this card can be a good sign. In love, this card represents commitment, a balanced relationship, and love. But it doesn't just mean you won't need to cultivate your love to make it last. This card merely indicates the presence of true love and affection.

  In your financial situation, the Two of Cups is associated with fairness and balance. This means you are currently financially capable, and you have enough funds to fulfill your obligations. Related to your health, those currently facing health issues need to find a practitioner they are willing to work with and trust. Spiritually, it calls for you to be more loving and kind to others. You are receiving positive energy from the universe, and you need to share this energy.",
        "reversed_content" => "When reversed, the Two of Cups can mean that the balance that once was has been broken. This balance is a crucial component of maintaining individual unity, and breaking it leads to disconnect and disharmony. There is a presence of negative energy between two forces, seeming to repel rather than join or attract.

  You may find that certain small details, which previously did not matter, start to play a role, indicating that one party may hold resentment. A channel of communication that allows you and the other party to discuss differences openly is cut off, only amplifying the cycle of resentment and imbalance.

  Being the first to open up, you might find that the issue is easier to resolve than you thought.",
        "upright_love" => "Attraction and coming together is the essence of the Two of Cups Tarot love meaning. This card encourages the start of any relationship, and the harmony generated when two people unite. It also implies a mutually beneficial relationship where partners encourage each other and bring out the best in each other. If you are in a relationship, you might find that this period brings better communication, balance, and friendliness. You may work better together at this time. Try to understand your partner’s talents as well as your own; give each other the trust to do what you are good at. The Two of Cups is about building each person up in the partnership while being together.",
        "reversed_love" => "When the reversed Two of Cups appears in a love Tarot reading, things may not be going well. Either you and your partner have become overly dependent on each other to the detriment of each person’s individuality, or the balance between the couple has been broken due to unequal power dynamics. If you are in a relationship, always ensure you nurture both your and your partner’s individuality; you two are different people with different interests and needs. Being yourself will bring more to the relationship than trying to be exactly like your partner. Sometimes, this card can also point to pursuing love at all costs.",
        "upright_career" => "Upright, the Two of Cups is closely related to positive relationships, meaning you may find your relationships with colleagues or business partners particularly strong in your career. You may find support and harmony among those around you. For those discussing establishing business partnerships, this should be particularly reassuring. This card signifies that this new partnership will be fruitful, and you will work well together. Generally, the Two of Cups is associated with romantic relationships, but this rarely applies to the professional environment. However, if you have recently been interested in someone you met through work, it can also indicate happiness in that relationship. Be mindful of the risks of mixing pleasure with work.",
        "reversed_career" => "While the upright Two of Cups signifies strong positive relationships, the reversed Two of Cups is the opposite. If you are in a business partnership, you may deal with differing interests, conflicts, or lack of respect. If you haven't established a partnership but are hoping to, this is a warning to be cautious. The other person may not value you or agree with your goals. If you are not in or trying to establish a business partnership, those you work with may become hostile now. If you are a leader or your colleagues are generally tense and aloof, you may find insubordination.",
        "upright_finances" => "The Two of Cups can indicate a stable financial situation; it does not wholly represent wealth, but it suggests a period of financial security. It is unwise to view this card as a sign of financial windfalls, as more importantly, it represents reliability. Since the Two always indicates balance, you likely have enough money to cover your expenses. However, it is still advised to use your funds wisely to ensure this stable period lasts. If you go beyond your means or act recklessly in other ways, there is no reason to believe these actions will go unpunished. Instead of spending money, take time to remind yourself that you are not under financial pressure now, which is a reward in itself.",
        "reversed_finances" => "The reversed Two of Cups is not a great card for finances. Instead, it suggests you might not have the balance you think you do. Try to track more of your expenses to see if there is a problem. While this card is not very positive, it is not a terrible card either. Comparing the amount of money coming in with the amount going out is relatively easy. You may need to look closely at the numbers and make some adjustments accordingly. Now is a good time to check how well you stick to a budget and if there are any unexplained expenses.",
        "yes_no" => "The Two of Cups shouts love, positive relationships, and unity. It implies a life full of close connections, good friendships, mutual love, and respect. This card encompasses all the happy, positive, and loving feelings. The answer it offers you is yes.",
        "past" => "You have recently formed friendships or partnerships that will bring you great rewards in the future. This connection will be meaningful in the coming years.",
        "present" => "A union of love or a close partnership will begin soon. With commitment and dedication, this relationship will bring you great rewards, even if they are far away.",
        "future" => "Look for partners who can help you achieve your goals. It should be someone who can understand your ambitions and priorities like you do.",
    ],
    52 =>
    [
        "id" => 53,
        "type_id" => 1,
        "number" => 52,
        "name" => "Three of Cups",
        "upright_keyword" => "Friendship, Community, Gatherings, Celebrations, Group Activities, Social Events",
        "reversed_keyword" => "Gossip, Scandal, Excess, Isolation, Loneliness, Imbalanced Social Life",
        "astrology" => "",
        "element" => "Water Element",
        "image_key" => "52_Three_of_Cups",
        "content" => "When you look at the Three of Cups, you see three women raising their cups in the air to celebrate. The air is filled with good times, as the three ladies wear wreaths made of flowers in their hair. Wreaths are often associated with success and victory, so their happiness is well-deserved. The women are also seen standing on top of a field of flowers and fruit, further emphasizing the feeling of joy in this card. There is a sense of beauty, growth, compassion, and happiness between the women.

  Interestingly, in the Rider-Waite Tarot deck, the woman in the middle has her back turned to the reader, hiding her face from view. However, the other two maidens are smiling.",
        "upright_content" => "The meaning behind the Three of Cups represents a happy time. You will be able to forget the troubles of daily life and enjoy a good time with family and friends.

  Seeing the Three of Cups can indicate the happiness of reuniting with long-lost friends, relatives, or loved ones. It can also mean celebrations, whether it’s your own or that of someone you love. The events could be birthdays, weddings, or any other joyful occasion. In general, it’s about having a great time with those you cherish in your life.

  The three maidens represent your circle of friends, and you turn to them for love, compassion, and support when you need them most. It could be old friends from college, colleagues at work, or people you have developed a special bond with over the years.

  If you have had problems in your social life, this card can signify the end of those difficulties. You will be able to resolve differences and learn how to handle problems.",
        "reversed_content" => "When the Three of Cups is reversed, it indicates that you may not have time to socialize or go out with friends. You may be busy with school or work, leaving you with no time for fun. The reversed Three of Cups can also mean losing touch with some of your friends. As time goes by, you may find yourselves drifting apart. As we grow older, we need to work to ensure our friendships are not neglected.

  Alternatively, the reversed Three of Cups can mean a lack of balance and harmony within your social circle. Gossip and scandals may rear their ugly heads. Perhaps jealousy is lurking within the circle, making you feel isolated.",
        "upright_love" => "The Three of Cups in a love tarot reading signifies celebration, friendship, and gatherings. If you are single, you may find love in your social life. Close friendships may also turn into romance. If you are in a relationship, social gatherings can bring you two closer. As you step into the world as a couple, it may become more apparent how well you two get along. Being with friends and family can strongly impact both of you, reminding you why you chose each other. Your love can now feel deep and satisfying.",
        "reversed_love" => "If you are single, the reversed Three of Cups love meaning suggests that your romantic life may be fun and exciting, but it may also be fleeting. Relationships that begin at this time may quickly fail once you get to know each other better. If you are in a relationship, be wary of any third parties trying to disrupt your relationship. Sometimes, this can manifest as unpleasant gossip, or there may be someone attempting to insert themselves between you two.",
        "upright_career" => "The Three of Cups symbolizes celebrations in all areas of your life. If it appears concerning your career, some work-related events are likely to occur soon. These gatherings will be joyous occasions. They can take many forms, such as celebrating a graduation, a position change, or a promotion. If you are launching a business and planning a release, these events could be particularly successful. Aside from these events, your office environment may be very positive now. You may find past teamwork and collaboration easier. Now is a good time to enjoy these celebrations and supportive relationships.",
        "reversed_career" => "The events and celebrations that the upright Three of Cups typically represent may not go as planned when reversed. If you are planning a release or other events, it may happen but not bring the success and outcomes you wanted. Sometimes, this card can mean that these events will be delayed or canceled. If none of these apply to you, your work environment may be particularly toxic now. There may be gossip and other forms of undermining that are destroying camaraderie. Conflict could be rampant; some may be directed at you, but you may also have to deal with being caught in the crossfire. Try not to become a part of this negativity. Don’t fuel the fire, as it will only burn you in the long run.",
        "upright_finances" => "If you find the Three of Cups in a financial tarot reading, it can indicate that you may have much to celebrate financially. All of this can be very exciting, but it is important not to get too carried away. You may find that your social life is more important than ever during this period, and while you may be generous, make sure your good fortune lasts. Be happy, but also be responsible.",
        "reversed_finances" => "The reversed Three of Cups can indicate financial strain, often in a social context. If you have been spending a lot of money on your social life or some event or party, you may need to control your budget. For example, if you are planning a wedding or birthday party, be aware of the financial strain it may cause. There may be more expenses than you anticipated. While the upright Three of Cups also hints at this concern, the reversed card makes the warning more serious. Be wary of spending and giving beyond your means. Celebrations can easily get out of hand, but forgetting your financial progress in this way is not good for you in the long term.",
        "yes_no" => "The Three of Cups brings an abundance of love and joy. It suggests happy gatherings or celebrations and success in all aspects of your life. It is associated with celebrating love and intimate relationships, meaning the answer you seek is yes.",
        "past" => "Talents that have long lain dormant are beginning to influence your life, and the work you have done is starting to impact your future. By exploring more experiences than you previously have, you may find richer rewards.",
        "present" => "An abundance of energy surrounds this moment, indicating that you are approaching a new phase in life.",
        "future" => "The desire to help others will significantly influence your considerations, and you will find greater joy when you play a significant role in your community. A complete life lies ahead, celebrated by those who love you.",
    ],
    53 =>
    [
        "id" => 54,
        "type_id" => 1,
        "number" => 53,
        "name" => "Four of Cups",
        "upright_keyword" => "Apathy, Contemplation, Feeling Disconnected, Melancholy, Boredom, Indifference, Discontent",
        "reversed_keyword" => "Clarity, Awareness, Acceptance, Choosing Happiness, Depression, Negativity",
        "astrology" => "",
        "element" => "Water Element",
        "image_key" => "53_Four_of_Cups",
        "content" => "The Four of Cups depicts a young man sitting under a tree on top of a hill, away from others. He appears to be deep in contemplation and meditation. In front of him, three cups lie on the grass, and a hand is offering him another cup from the air. The man has his arms and legs crossed, looking down at the three cups, ignoring the cup being offered to him.

  The Four of Cups represents our tendency to take what we have for granted, making it difficult to see the treasures the universe offers us. We often have the answers to our problems around us, but we tend to focus on what we don't have.",
        "upright_content" => "The Four of Cups often appears when you feel discouraged and unmotivated. You may feel that there is no solution or path forward in your situation. Life has stagnated, and nothing seems to make you happy or passionate. You feel indifferent, and it doesn't matter what happens—whether the day is good or bad, it is irrelevant to you. The Four of Cups calls for self-evaluation of your attitude so that you can break free from this routine. The solution is likely right in front of you, with the hand offering you a way out, but you must free yourself from your spiritual stubbornness and deploy a new approach.

  You must seek out your motivations, instincts, and ideas to find your passion again. The Four of Cups revolves around finding your true interests and striving to achieve them. Our lives are short and sometimes monotonous, but we must create meaning for ourselves. Our personal calling not only requires us to seek but also to decide and imagine.",
        "reversed_content" => "When the Four of Cups is reversed, it indicates that you may have been feeling apathetic and ignoring opportunities offered by the universe, but now you are longing for a fresh start.

  You may now suddenly recognize the fleeting beauty of life, something you were too disconnected from yourself to see before. You are gradually understanding that while life isn't perfect, there is beauty in it, and happiness comes from choosing to see that beauty.

  Embrace new ideas, new people, and new places; you never know where these adventures may lead you. Many people may miss these opportunities because they are too stuck in their own beliefs and ambitions.",
        "upright_love" => "If you are single, the Four of Cups in a love tarot reading suggests you may feel bored or indifferent about your love life. Sometimes this naturally happens after a breakup, but ensure this isn't coming from an unconscious attempt to protect yourself from the pain and torment that love brought you in the past. Opportunities will come when you are willing to see them, but right now, you are not bothered. If you are in a relationship, your relationship may lack interest and be plagued by boredom. The excitement has faded, and you may feel more like roommates than lovers. Sometimes this just requires a willingness to explore and try new things. Without effort from both sides, the relationship may be nearing its end.",
        "reversed_love" => "The reversed Four of Cups in a love tarot reading represents the end of a period of withdrawal and contemplation. You may become more active in your romantic life again, this time with a better understanding and appreciation of what it brings you. If you are recovering from a breakup, you may be starting to let go of past hurts, and the future may seem hopeful. Feel excited about what the future holds. With a better understanding of what you want and who you are, potential love interests you meet now can feel refreshing.",
        "upright_career" => "If you see the Four of Cups in a tarot reading regarding your career, you may feel distracted and disengaged at work. It might be hard to focus on tasks at hand or feel excited about projects. This boredom can also negatively affect your mood. You may feel disappointed in yourself, making it harder to be productive. The overwhelming stagnation you feel isn't helping either. This stagnation may be the root of the problem. If you feel like there's nowhere to go, it’s hard to concentrate. Taking some time to address this issue may help; look inward and understand what is making you so unhappy and do something about it to make better changes.",
        "reversed_career" => "When reversed, the Four of Cups can mark the end of the stagnation you recently faced at work. This change can be sudden, like some sort of revelation, or as if the fog has lifted. You might find your creativity suddenly returning. Therefore, you will use this newfound inspiration and creativity to push your work projects forward. If your new understanding of your career tells you that a change is needed, now is the time to do it. While the change may be quick, don't mistake it for luck. You still need to use your newfound energy. The universe won't give you anything unless you act, but opportunities you hadn't considered or noticed before may suddenly come to the forefront of your career.",
        "upright_finances" => "When it comes to your finances, the Four of Cups can indicate that you may be distracted. Are you too busy being jealous of what others have to see what’s in front of you? You might continually compare your situation to others, but this jealousy prevents you from appreciating what you already have. Being more grateful can help you find better ways to improve your finances and feel more at ease when taking significant risks. If you are so fixated on what you don't have, you might never notice opportunities to actually achieve the goals you envy. Sometimes this card can also manifest as general disillusionment with money, capitalism, and the financial system.",
        "reversed_finances" => "The reversed Four of Cups can mark a journey toward financial improvement and security. This is not only a result of your ability to control your finances but also a reflection of your efforts to appreciate what you already have. While you may have previously envied others' financial security, you might be taking steps to take a more positive approach to your finances. As you focus on better financial habits, the universe will reward you. Save and spend as needed, and don't let others' thoughts or ideas distract you. Be prepared to work for the rewards this card signifies.",
        "yes_no" => "The Four of Cups is a card of apathy, displaying feelings of indifference, boredom, and even disappointment. This may mean you need to reevaluate some areas of your life, or you may just be content with the status quo and missing opportunities. There is no clear answer here.",
        "past" => "You have been dissatisfied, and no change can affect this. Your desire for change will be the most powerful drive to change the world around you. Take new approaches to change your environment.",
        "present" => "Do not be afraid to move forward. Instead, be afraid of becoming too complacent. Seek new paths so that you can progress to new levels.",
        "future" => "There will be a long delay before you achieve your goals. Do not lose faith, and keep your eyes facing forward. Make your plans and do not neglect the exciting rewards you desire.",
    ],
    54 =>
    [
        "id" => 55,
        "type_id" => 1,
        "number" => 54,
        "name" => "Five of Cups",
        "upright_keyword" => "Loss, Grief, Disappointment, Sadness, Mourning, Dissatisfaction, Regret",
        "reversed_keyword" => "Acceptance, Moving On, Finding Peace, Contentment, Seeing the Positive",
        "astrology" => "",
        "element" => "Water Element",
        "image_key" => "54_Five_of_Cups",
        "content" => "Certain tarot card images immediately evoke negative emotions, and the Five of Cups carries such significant meaning. This card symbolizes loss and the difficult challenge brought about by that specific loss.

  The card depicts a figure wearing a black cloak. This person appears to be hiding his face in despair. On the ground, five cups are shown, three of which have fallen, while the other two remain standing. However, this person seems to notice only the fallen cups, as he is busy mourning them. A powerful river flows between him and a house or castle in the distance, indicating that the emotional flood separates him from home.",
        "upright_content" => "The Five of Cups symbolizes disappointment and the feelings that arise when things do not go as you had expected. You are unhappy that a certain situation has not turned out the way you hoped. This card does not move towards a more positive outlook but rather indicates that you are wallowing in the past, invoking feelings of self-pity and regret. The water spilling from the cups signifies that you may have missed an opportunity. It also suggests that the problem is primarily emotional rather than material or financial.

  The meaning of the Five of Cups indicates that you may have issues letting go of the past. More importantly, it also shows a reluctance to learn from the mistakes you have made. This card typically reflects someone who is so focused on their past that they cannot move forward. This means they are likely to miss out on new joys the future may bring.
  ",
        "reversed_content" => "When the card is reversed, the Five of Cups shows a significant recovery from regret and proper acceptance of your past. You are beginning to understand all the implications of your actions, and you are finally starting to appreciate the lessons that can be learned from that experience.

  You may even begin to recognize the overall value of your painful experiences on a broader scale. You see that the suffering and grief you have endured have given you strength and resilience. You are ready to pick up the two remaining full cups and move on with your life.",
        "upright_love" => "You might be going through a period of mourning; there may be many things to grieve over. You could be experiencing some form of breakup, or if not that, then a period of tension and arguments with your partner. However, it is helpful to understand that not everything is lost. The Five of Cups love meaning in tarot suggests emotional loss but also indicates that you might be overlooking what can still be salvaged and what remains. Often, these carry the seeds of hope. Did the arguments reveal certain things about your relationship? Did it foster communication that might have otherwise remained silent? Did the breakup free you to explore individuality beyond your past relationship? While there are many things to mourn, the Five of Cups love meaning in tarot also hints at things to look forward to.",
        "reversed_love" => "It's time to stop living in the past when the Five of Cups appears reversed in a love tarot reading. This card truly signifies moving on and letting go of past sadness and pain. If you've recently gone through a breakup, this card may be a welcome sight to help motivate you to accept what has happened and make peace with it. As this chapter in your life closes, you are making room for new love to emerge, one that truly lives in the present, rather than comparing current potential romance to your past. If you are still healing, that’s natural. Give yourself time and be gentle; you will find happiness again. If you are in a relationship, you may have just gone through a period of tension. Hopefully, you and your partner have had all the necessary discussions so that you feel understood and heard. Try not to dwell on past hurts and resentments; look forward to what you two can change together, rather than what you cannot change.",
        "upright_career" => "The Five of Cups symbolizes loss and grief. In your career, this could come in the form of losing a job, business, dream project, or partnership. Perhaps you have been forced to take a step back in your career. Alternatively, someone you work with might abandon a shared project, or you might choose to leave. This could be a time of sadness and transition. These changes are difficult but offer a learning opportunity. There may be more to salvage than you initially thought. Try to maintain positive relationships with old colleagues outside the office. Stay connected to the best elements of what you’ve lost.",
        "reversed_career" => "The reversed Five of Cups is a sign of recovery. When it comes to your career, if you have recently faced setbacks such as unemployment, layoffs, or business troubles, the reversed Five of Cups suggests that you have what it takes to move past these difficult times. You can now make up for some of the losses. Healing is on the way; you may realize that although you went through a lot, these losses allowed you to find a position that suits you better. The stress and pain you endured due to these troubles may also begin to lessen your burden.",
        "upright_finances" => "In a financial tarot reading, the Five of Cups can indicate a lack of resources. You might be suffering from significant financial loss. There could be a lot of pressure right now, and you may need to ensure that you are not wasting money in order to rebuild financial security. Now, more than ever, it is important to maintain a positive attitude toward your situation. Fortunately, this card usually suggests that there is still much to salvage in this situation, so look at what you already have and your skills to see what you can use to make up for the loss.",
        "reversed_finances" => "If you have recently experienced some financial loss or turmoil, the reversed Five of Cups can indicate relief and the end of this period. By overcoming the losses you’ve faced, you might be finding new ways to financial stability. Perhaps you are investing the remaining resources into something valuable, such as a business or part-time job, to help build a financial cushion. Be proud of what you’ve overcome.",
        "yes_no" => "The Five of Cups is a card filled with regret, grief, and disappointment. It may suggest that you are not appreciating what you have in life or are avoiding something that has yet to come. The disappointment and dissatisfaction associated with this card provide a negative answer to your question.",
        "past" => "The urge to try something new was a result of the disappointments or dissatisfaction you experienced. Your current sadness is a manifestation of these failed expectations.",
        "present" => "Explore any alternative paths you discover. But if you shy away from the truth, it will be difficult to create any lasting contentment.",
        "future" => "Your mistakes will lead you to a place of regret. Be prepared to repair the damage you have caused, and more importantly, forgive yourself.",
    ],
    55 =>
    [
        "id" => 56,
        "type_id" => 1,
        "number" => 55,
        "name" => "Six of Cups",
        "upright_keyword" => "Nostalgia, Memories, Familiarity, Healing, Comfort, Sentimentality, Pleasure",
        "reversed_keyword" => "Stuck in the Past, Moving Forward, Leaving Home, Independence",
        "astrology" => "",
        "element" => "Water Element",
        "image_key" => "55_Six_of_Cups",
        "content" => "The Six of Cups symbolizes the joy of nostalgia, the comfort of home, and the innocence of childhood. On the card itself, there are six cups filled with white flowers. In the foreground, two children are depicted, one handing a cup to the other. The boy gives flowers to the girl, indicating traditional giving and the joy of reunion. The children appear to be in some sort of castle, which we can imagine gives them a sense of safety and comfort.",
        "upright_content" => "The Six of Cups upright generally represents generosity, innocent happiness, and childhood. It can represent your desire to return to a happier time, whether it was when you were a child, a teenager, or a young adult. Often, these memories are things of the past, reflecting aspects of ourselves that have faded away. You might feel that reminiscing about these times is the only way to feel happy. The appearance of the Six of Cups in a tarot reading seems to suggest that while we can look at the past with fondness, we must avoid living in it.

  The Six of Cups may also mean that you will be returning to a familiar place. This could be your hometown, an old friend's house, a school, or any place that holds significant meaning for you. You are seeking to reconnect with people from your past. Bringing back old memories reminds us of our childhood, a time when things were simpler.

  Following the Five of Cups, this card can also suggest that you may have experienced some loss or disappointment, and you are finding your way back home. You are looking to the past to find answers to the crisis or challenge you are currently facing. You might be seeking comfort and warmth from those who love you unconditionally, gathering strength to face the trials ahead.",
        "reversed_content" => "The reversed Six of Cups can mean that you are clinging to the past. You should explore your memories, but you should not allow yourself to stay there. While you may find comfort in the safety of home, you must also learn to carve your own path. The past should be used as a guide for the future. Learn to focus on the present and be truly aware.

  Another interpretation of the reversed Six of Cups is that you might feel disconnected from your childhood self and the dreams of that child, which sometimes may be unrealistic. Not reaching these goals can be painful, but sometimes reality opens a path you must follow, and you should not blame yourself for your choices. Take some time to think about who you want to be now and how to achieve your goals instead of just dreaming about them.",
        "upright_love" => "The past becomes active again with the Six of Cups love meaning in tarot. This card can signify a revival of the past and the accompanying nostalgia; you may be exploring happy memories, you may appreciate the familiarity of your partner more, or an ex may even reappear in your life. The Six of Cups can also represent a time of healing wounds, where comfort may be important to you. If you and your partner have had a stressful period in your relationship, looking back at the good times you've spent together and perhaps reliving them can bring you great comfort. But be careful not to live only in the past. Let the past nourish your future; they are lessons showing you what you want to keep in your life and what you don't.",
        "reversed_love" => "You might be living in the past rather than the present when the reversed Six of Cups appears in a love tarot reading. Past relationships are likely holding you back from opening your heart to love and making space for someone else. You might believe you will never meet anyone like your ex, or the love you once had was legendary. This can be quite unfair for a current or potential partner to live with someone like this. You might only see the happy memories and not the tumultuous ones. Let the past be the past. Otherwise, you may block all possibilities of love again, and you may never know if the love you would have had was greater than what you lost.",
        "upright_career" => "The Six of Cups often represents childhood, memories, and healing. When it comes to your career, now might be a good time to look back at the path that got you to where you are today. This card can be a signal that your past work can provide important lessons needed to build your future. Reflect on what you did right and ensure you don't repeat past mistakes. Alternatively, this card might suggest that you are reconsidering your career path and might return to a position you once left.",
        "reversed_career" => "The reversed Six of Cups can indicate that your work has become outdated, and your career may be stagnant. You may feel so frustrated by this stifling atmosphere that you are looking for a more exciting position or field of employment. You may wish to leave the safety and comfort of your current position. Alternatively, you might choose to stay in your comfortable current position to avoid seeking risks elsewhere. Overall, when this card is reversed, there is an important lesson to be learned. Be cautious of repeating any negative patterns from your past workplaces that may follow you; if not addressed, your own behaviors can often create the same problems again wherever you go.",
        "upright_finances" => "The goodwill of the Six of Cups can relate to your finances in various ways. Sometimes, this card can indicate gifts or donations, or simply sharing resources. This card is also connected to childhood and family, indicating that this sharing might come from a family member. You might return to your parents' home, allowing you to save more of your funds while enjoying the comfort of being with loved ones. Alternatively, you might be on the other side, welcoming family members back into your home while sharing resources.",
        "reversed_finances" => "Upright, this card is a sign of childhood and past memories. When reversed, the Six of Cups suggests that you are ready to set out on your own. This card is common for those living at home but ready to move out. It symbolizes becoming financially mature. If you have been living with your parents or others, you have better learned how to save and manage your funds, and now you have the discipline to make a living for yourself. These changes can be scary but are necessary; enjoy the freedom it brings!",
        "yes_no" => "The Six of Cups speaks of reconciliation and letting go of the past. This can mean some sort of apology or unlocking skeletons from the closet. There is a sense of relief and moving forward with its presence, and the answer you seek is most likely yes.",
        "past" => "The past has brought you many loving and successful experiences. Do not dwell too long on past events and move towards your achievements.",
        "present" => "The results of your past actions are now coming to fruition. Through making new friends or strengthening relationships, you will find much common ground.",
        "future" => "To improve your future, you must build upon the virtues of your past. It is not enough to be successful in the past; you must increase your abilities. Deep-rooted desires will need some evolution to be realized.",
    ],
    56 =>
    [
        "id" => 57,
        "type_id" => 1,
        "number" => 56,
        "name" => "Seven of Cups",
        "upright_keyword" => "Choices, Searching for Purpose, Illusion, Fantasy, Daydreaming, Wishful Thinking, Indecision",
        "reversed_keyword" => "Lack of Purpose, Confusion, Chaos, Diversion, Distraction, Clarity, Making a Choice",
        "astrology" => "",
        "element" => "Water Element",
        "image_key" => "56_Seven_of_Cups",
        "content" => "The Seven of Cups symbolizes imagination, choices, wishful thinking, illusions, and fantasy. The card shows a person facing away from us, contemplating seven images coming out of cups, all floating in the clouds. The clouds represent dreams, illusions, thoughts, and imagination. The numerous fantasies emerging from the cups symbolize the many visions people see while dreaming. The Seven of Cups may imply that you have many options.",
        "upright_content" => "When the Seven of Cups appears in a tarot reading, you need to clearly see the shadows and illusions in your imagination, not only in your dreams but also in the real world. You should be careful of wishful thinking and be mindful of the choices you make. In a sense, the Seven of Cups suggests you are a dreamer, excited yet afraid of what you see in your subconscious. On the other hand, the Seven of Cups reminds us that while having dreams and desires is good, taking action to realize those dreams is better. At some point in life, you will need to stop fantasizing and face the reality of life.

  If you are unable to make a decision due to having too many options, you should evaluate the pros and cons of each choice to make the best one. Be cautious when making decisions, as the card itself seems to suggest that you have access to wonders and treasures, but also monsters and shadows.

  In some cases, the Seven of Cups may indicate that your lifestyle is not necessarily based on real life - your actions are being guided by illusions you feed yourself. Your ideas might be so clouded, developed solely by your imagination. Therefore, you need to distinguish what is real and what is not, so you can make better choices.

  The Seven of Cups is also related to temptation. This applies to the upright meaning as well as the reversed meaning of the Seven of Cups.",
        "reversed_content" => "The reversed Seven of Cups is somewhat similar to the upright one, as both indicate dreams, illusions, and temptations, but it seems to emphasize more of the card's negative qualities. Your perspective might lean towards fantasy rather than being based on reality. This could mean that you are unclear about what you are looking for.

  The reversed Seven of Cups might suggest an unwillingness to face reality, seeking escape through imagination and daydreams.

  On the other hand, the reversed Seven of Cups might indicate the end of confusion, clearing away illusions, and moving forward with clarity.",
        "upright_love" => "With the appearance of the Seven of Cups in a love tarot reading, several decisions lie before you. If you are single, you may have to decide between different lovers, or between love and family, or love and career. The Seven of Cups tarot love meaning can also indicate that all choices now seem tempting, but despite their glitter, they may be illusions. Take your time and consider things carefully; only diligent communication and evaluation will get you what you desire. With love, we may be eager to dive in, letting desire and infatuation lead us into something that may not last in the long run. It's important to consider all options and look for any red flags or intuitive feelings you may have about the relationship. Trust your intuition.",
        "reversed_love" => "Your lack of clarity about what you want in love can make your love life more chaotic and confusing than it needs to be. There may be wasted time, missed opportunities, emotional turmoil, all because of the inability to make a choice. Your dating life may be full of dead ends, broken hearts, and mixed messages. It is important to always focus on what you want instead of letting the world make choices for you. Alternatively, if you are gradually gaining clarity about what is important to you, acting on these decisions will be rewarding. You can now take steps to make things happen.",
        "upright_career" => "The Seven of Cups depicts a person faced with many different choices. If this card is related to your career, you may be seeing many different ways to advance in your job. This variety of options is generally a good thing, but it is important to note how much time you are spending dreaming instead of taking steps to make it happen. Remember, a potential path depends on the steps you are willing to take. You have many ways to advance in your career, and they can all serve you well. But if you don't choose a path and stick to it, none will get you what you want. Whatever you ultimately decide, it will benefit you; so take decisive and confident action.",
        "reversed_career" => "While the upright Seven of Cups represents many choices, the reversed Seven of Cups may indicate the opposite. It often appears to those who feel trapped in their jobs without opportunities for advancement. It is also common for those who feel they missed the perfect position by not taking action in time. Whether one (or both) of these applies to you, try not to be overwhelmed by these negative feelings. This card also represents a clear vision of your career goals. Use these skills to honestly evaluate your position and where you may be falling short. Ask yourself what you can do to more actively progress in your career.",
        "upright_finances" => "The Seven of Cups indicates that you have multiple ways to improve your financial situation. Take some time to consider your options. While this card generally gives you many opportunities, that doesn't mean everything is decided for you. To turn these opportunities into reality, you need to be proactive. Weigh each option and consider it critically. Things that sound too good to be true usually are. Follow your intuition and keep your eyes open for any red flags.",
        "reversed_finances" => "When it comes to your financial situation, the reversed Seven of Cups can have several conflicting meanings. You need to look at your situation carefully to see which applies to you. It can indicate clarity when making financial choices, giving you the willpower to focus on achieving your goals. You are not easily distracted, thus able to concentrate on what you need. This vision will serve you well, as it can prevent unnecessary spending. You may find you are particularly good at budgeting or other structured plans now. Alternatively, this card can also mean confusion and delusion, or the inability to turn daydreams into reality. When it comes to opportunities presented to you, make sure you are not being deceived. Ensure you understand all the facts of any deal presented to you.",
        "yes_no" => "The Seven of Cups represents confusing decisions, wishful thinking, and temptations caused by a lack of morality. Delusional ambitions and poor choices are associated with this card. It brings a certain pessimism and negativity. The answer is no.",
        "past" => "You have spent too much time chasing many conflicting interests in life. Do not be misled by daydreams and fantasies; choose one practical goal and start working towards it.",
        "present" => "You will receive an amazing reward from the usual mental and creative activities.",
        "future" => "Indecision will slow your progress. Being open to change will be helpful, but continually striving to discern what is real will keep you moving forward. Do not deceive yourself.",
    ],
    57 =>
    [
        "id" => 58,
        "type_id" => 1,
        "number" => 57,
        "name" => "Eight of Cups",
        "upright_keyword" => "Abandonment, Walking Away, Letting Go, Seeking Truth, Leaving",
        "reversed_keyword" => "Stagnation, Monotony, Accepting Less, Avoidance, Fear of Change, Stuck in a Bad Situation",
        "astrology" => "",
        "element" => "Water Element",
        "image_key" => "57_Eight_of_Cups",
        "content" => "In the Eight of Cups, we face a moment of transformation. We see a cloaked figure flying over a barren land, leaving behind eight golden cups. He is tired of the cups he spent so much time collecting and is now seeking higher goals. This may result from boredom or unhappiness, realizing that what they have been searching for in life is not as pleasing or fulfilling as they once thought.

  The journey undertaken by this person may also mean seeking excitement in the unknown. The mountainous and barren land he sets out for may also symbolize facing new challenges. Their bare emptiness seems to indicate that they are waiting for someone to come and shape them. The journey taken can be done under the guise of trying new things that could help a person grow spiritually and mentally.

  It also indicates a willingness to separate oneself from others to focus on self-improvement, self-understanding, and growth.",
        "upright_content" => "The Eight of Cups symbolizes a time of change or transition, by walking away from something. Just as a caterpillar must die before becoming a beautiful butterfly, we all need to change ourselves from time to time in life. This is especially true after becoming bored with living day-to-day life and embarking on a journey that helps people gain a deeper understanding of life.

  Receiving this card in the upright position indicates that you are dissatisfied with your life and need to experience higher goals. You may have been exploring your options, going from one to another, tasting the wine in each cup to clarify what you truly want in life. You are now experiencing a sense of fatigue and beginning to realize that you must walk away from familiar things. This is both a choice and an acknowledgment that true happiness will not be found in what you have already created.

  Usually, receiving the Eight of Cups signifies that a person is tired of mundane things and is about to embark on a more spiritual journey. If so, rejoice, for change happens when we need it most.",
        "reversed_content" => "Receiving the Eight of Cups reversed can indicate confusion about the path you should take. The confusion often stems from not knowing what is best for you, ultimately resulting in drifting in an ocean of uncertainty.

  People may find themselves aimless, without a clear life goal. In the end, they almost always follow where the waves of life take them.

  On the other hand, you might know what you need to do. There are things in your life that haven't brought you joy or happiness for a long time, and although your soul longs to walk away from them, you find yourself still there. The idea of leaving the security you have built fills you with fear—you are afraid of change, afraid of losing what has brought you great comfort.

  Most people usually find themselves stuck because they are torn between two important decisions. For example, a person may want to change and better themselves, but at the same time, they may be unable to make the necessary sacrifices to achieve their goals. We must have the courage to believe we deserve better, knowing that more joyful things await us if we embark on this journey.",
        "upright_love" => "Take some time to ask yourself if your relationship is satisfying you. The Eight of Cups tarot love meaning indicates that some reflection is needed to determine if your partnership truly fulfills you. Can you see yourself spending the rest of your life with this person? Do they encourage you to be your best self? Do they support your growth? Or are you with them out of fear of being alone or returning to the dating scene? This is unfair to both you and your partner. It takes great courage to honestly examine your heart, answer these questions, and leave behind the life you two have built together.",
        "reversed_love" => "In the reversed Eight of Cups tarot love meaning, your intuition might be telling you that you need to leave your partnership, but something is holding you back. It is important to engage with and question this fear. Leaving behind what you have built, the time, emotions, and energy invested in another person is very difficult, but sometimes one must be wise enough to leave something that is truly not working. You must figure out if the desire to leave comes from a relationship that has truly reached its end or if it can still be salvaged. Give yourself some time to be clear about what you need to do and address whatever is holding you back from moving on.",
        "upright_career" => "In a career tarot reading, the Eight of Cups can mean a few things. Given the card's general meaning of leaving and walking away from something, it could be as simple as taking a break or as stressful as leaving a job that feels unfulfilling. If work has been particularly dull lately, a bit of an escape might leave you feeling rejuvenated. If you're trying to decide whether to leave your job, remember that sometimes you need to know when to cut your losses and move on. Knowing how to make the best of any situation and making responsible decisions will provide you with an exit from a bad situation in favor of a better one.",
        "reversed_career" => "When the Eight of Cups is reversed, you might find it hard, or even outright refuse to leave out of fear. You might feel unfulfilled in your career and have the capability to change it. You can choose to accept a role that doesn't give you emotional rewards, creative outlets, or growth opportunities, or make the necessary changes to look elsewhere. Don't be afraid to leave something behind if it no longer serves you. This task also applies to those who own their own business. If you are clinging to your business or job out of a sense of responsibility or fear, now is the time to let go.",
        "upright_finances" => "Sometimes, to make the right choices for us, we need to leave behind what we have built. The Eight of Cups might indicate that you may need to leave some financial security to build the life that is right for you. Take this opportunity to get your finances in order before making major decisions. Pay attention to how much you spend and what you spend it on. Be cautious about significant expenditures at the current moment. You might find that you don't have as much money as you thought to spend on them. This card could be a warning to plan ahead.",
        "reversed_finances" => "The reversed Eight of Cups indicates that you might find it difficult to let go of some financial security in pursuit of something better. You might be holding on to a job that does not serve you out of fear that you won't find another job that pays as well elsewhere. These worries are valid, but sometimes bold decisions and risks are necessary. You need to consider how much your happiness is worth. Spend some time each day looking for job openings that can meet your financial needs while also fulfilling you emotionally.",
        "yes_no" => "The Eight of Cups shows a certain level of lifestyle change. It brings feelings of frustration, indifference, and avoidance. It might indicate that you need to abandon, leave, or walk away from certain things in your current life. The melancholic feelings associated with this card suggest a no.",
        "past" => "Your ability to make money through determination and hard work will be necessary for the future. Your direction has always been uncertain, but your heart tells you to keep searching. The change you seek can take any form.",
        "present" => "You will experience something entirely new, whether in thought or location. Great changes are coming.",
        "future" => "Keep an open mind, and each of your journeys will result in life-changing results. Personal success and achieving your goals will bring you the greatest joy.",
    ],
    58 =>
    [
        "id" => 59,
        "type_id" => 1,
        "number" => 58,
        "name" => "Nine of Cups",
        "upright_keyword" => "Wishes Come True, Satisfaction, Fulfillment, Success, Achievement, Recognition, Happiness",
        "reversed_keyword" => "Unhappiness, Lack of Fulfillment, Disappointment, Poor Performance, Arrogance, Snobbery",
        "astrology" => "",
        "element" => "Water Element",
        "image_key" => "58_Nine_of_Cups",
        "content" => "In this card, a middle-aged man sits on a wooden bench with his arms crossed, displaying a significant degree of satisfaction on his face. He is dressed elegantly and has a look of true contentment. The red headpiece he wears depicts his active mind. In the background, you will notice nine golden cups neatly arranged. The Nine of Cups symbolizes both spiritual and material achievements and success. This man displays an aura of accomplishment after achieving his innermost desires.",
        "upright_content" => "After a long journey, the Nine of Cups symbolizes finding self-satisfaction. After experiencing the turbulent ups and downs in the earlier numbers of this suit, the emotional journey of the cups is nearing its end. You have struggled to find purpose and happiness after loss, you have tasted the different offerings of life, and you have left comforts to find greater heights. Here, you have found them, and you are indulging yourself as you celebrate this new phase of your life.

  When we look at the Nine of Cups, it initially appears to be one of the most pleasant cards to appear in a reading. It is also known as the wish card, meaning that the things you desire, or your most perfect dreams, will undoubtedly happen. The Nine of Cups is usually associated with extreme happiness and satisfaction.

  Regarding your work, there is a good change, and something wonderful will happen at your workplace. It is time to push forward your stalled projects, or if you have something you desire greatly, you are likely to achieve it finally. In love, it also has positive significance. Your romantic relationship with someone is destined to reach a new level. If you are still single, it is time to engage with new friends.

  In terms of finances, the Nine of Cups is also a positive messenger. It may mean that the financial state you have been hoping for will soon come true. In terms of your health, the tests you need to take will lead to positive results. The good energy you are receiving now should be used to improve your health habits.",
        "reversed_content" => "When the Nine of Cups is reversed, you need to think more carefully about what you truly want in your life. The reversed Nine of Cups can indicate that you are searching for a more genuine form of satisfaction.

  Your path has been a difficult one, and you have reached a period that seems fulfilling, but something else is still missing. This can manifest as smugness on the surface, and it can indicate that you want recognition and acknowledgment for your achievements. But you still feel personally dissatisfied with yourself—as if your desires are never-ending, a black hole. Where does this come from? What aspects of yourself are you lacking confidence in?

  The reversed Nine of Cups indicates that it is time for you to stop valuing all your blessings and focus on the quality of your life. True wealth lies in your relationships with family, friends, and community.",
        "upright_love" => "When the Nine of Cups appears in a love tarot reading, cherish what you have. Wishes here are about to come true, and it is best to look to the future with gratitude. There is much to celebrate, and if you are single, you might find love at parties and other joyful gatherings. Enjoy it; now is not the time for calculating or goal-setting but just for having fun. Easygoing joy can attract others to you. If you are in a relationship, you will find your love life becoming more pleasurable and sweet. This can be a great time to get closer to your partner.",
        "reversed_love" => "In the reversed Nine of Cups tarot love meaning, you might find that your relationship checks all the boxes, looks great on paper, but still feels like something is missing. Maybe you and your partner are not as close as you hoped; perhaps there is a lack of deeper connection. There is no need to worry, as this can be addressed through sincere and intimate conversations. On the other hand, you might be so engrossed in a relationship that you have not noticed the personal growth you need. Sometimes, we get caught up in romance to distract ourselves from the inner work we must do for happiness. Without doing that inner work, no matter how wonderful a romance we find, that dissatisfaction will always remain.",
        "upright_career" => "When it comes to your career, the Nine of Cups means you can find respect and recognition in your field. Any projects you start now are likely to be completed easily, and the skill you display in completing them can earn you much praise. If you are looking to advance in your career, this could be a great time to ask for a raise or promotion. People may be more receptive to these requests now than in the past or future. Take advantage of this moment. Overconfidence is never wise, but don't be shy or modest now. You have worked hard for this recognition.",
        "reversed_career" => "The reversed Nine of Cups can be a frustrating card in your career. Since the upright card is considered the 'wish card' in tarot, in reverse, it can indicate that the things you have been dreaming of will not soon happen as you imagined. You might hope that everything will be better by starting a business or taking this new job, but reality differs greatly from your imagination. You might find the job harder, more boring, or just too difficult to handle. There might also be a lack of reward, and your efforts might go unrecognized. You might not feel thrilled about the new career path and instead feel disillusioned and disappointed. You may need to return to the drawing board and make some changes.",
        "upright_finances" => "The Nine of Cups symbolizes wishes coming true, and when it comes to your finances, this card can suggest that you have everything you need. This card symbolizes wealth, emotional, and financial security. If you have been working hard, you will find that you can be well-rewarded. Take time to enjoy this moment, you have earned it.",
        "reversed_finances" => "When it comes to your finances, the reversed Nine of Cups can indicate that your expectations are not being met. Sometimes, this can mean that the money you invested has not brought the expected returns. If you have made any large purchases, investments, or helped family with this money, the results are not as you imagined. Alternatively, the reversed Nine of Cups can suggest that your hopes for financial stability have not yet been realized. Be patient. Remember, you will have to earn these dreams. Focus on what you have and how to achieve your goals better.",
        "yes_no" => "The Nine of Cups signifies joy, satisfaction, pleasure, and overall contentment. Its presence heralds a bright future filled with good times, happiness, and the realization of your wishes. The answer you seek is yes.",
        "past" => "The source of true happiness is the balance your soul has attained with peace. The effort you have put in will bring rewards. Stay strong and keep working.",
        "present" => "Your emotional and material well-being is within reach. Seek advice and support from your friends, but recognize that you will find fulfillment.",
        "future" => "The goals you have set for yourself are on their way. Stay true to your desires, and you will reach the destination you seek. Balance your mind and spirit to find a true calling.",
    ],
    59 =>
    [
        "id" => 60,
        "type_id" => 1,
        "number" => 59,
        "name" => "Ten of Cups",
        "upright_keyword" => "Happiness, Homecoming, Fulfillment, Emotional Stability, Security, Family Harmony",
        "reversed_keyword" => "Unhappy Home, Separation, Family Conflict, Disharmony, Isolation",
        "astrology" => "",
        "element" => "Water Element",
        "image_key" => "59_Ten_of_Cups",
        "content" => "In the Ten of Cups, a couple is depicted holding hands, facing a beautiful house and green garden. Beside them, two children are playing joyfully. The couple appears to be in a loving embrace, full of affection and romance, while the children play freely. This couple seems to have a stable relationship, a comfortable home, and beautiful children. The green land symbolizes fertility, and the river shows how freely the couple's emotions flow, indicating a very peaceful relationship. Ten cups are seen in the sky, forming an arc, signifying blessings from above. The rainbow behind them foretells the end of suffering and sadness, indicating a new happy life for the family. The Ten of Cups portrays having it all.",
        "upright_content" => "From its joyous depiction, we can assume the Ten of Cups embodies happiness, joy, contentment, and emotional fulfillment in your family, relationships, or partnerships. It represents an idyllic comfort, harmony, peace, and love, making you feel like you are in paradise. Here, all your dreams, desires, needs, and wishes are fulfilled, and you feel a complete sense of satisfaction. Take some time to breathe, look around, and give thanks for all your blessings. This card symbolizes what many of us are searching for.

  Seeing the Ten of Cups means true emotional fulfillment, sharing the solitary self-satisfaction of the Nine of Cups with others to create a true sense of community and family. It is the crystallization of the innocent will of the Ace of Cups. After learning how to love yourself, the Nine of Cups becomes the Ten of Cups, which at its core is about how true happiness comes from forming genuine bonds and connections with others. This card is most related to the feeling of 'happily ever after'—family, lasting harmony, and peace.

  It symbolizes family harmony, as this card shows that you live in perfect peace. No more adjustments or shifts are needed; you are right where you should be, so just relax and enjoy your moment. In a love reading, this card indicates it is romantic, true, and sincere—with strong potential for long-term development. It is worth all your efforts to make it come true.",
        "reversed_content" => "When the Ten of Cups is reversed, the strong bonds established with family and community are broken or distorted. The Ten of Cups is indeed the 'happiest' card, but somehow this ideal image of family peace and comfort has been shattered or was unrealistic all along. You may find distance instead of connection. You may be separated rather than coming together.

  Your hopes for happy times and special moments seem not to align with your expectations. You should learn to be kind to each other, love each other, and care for each other. This is the best way to ensure you maintain a harmonious life.",
        "upright_love" => "Love is calm and sweet, aligning with the Ten of Cups tarot love meaning. Spending time with family is particularly meaningful now. You might introduce your partner to your family or take the next step in commitment together. The Ten of Cups tarot love meaning also suggests long-term stability, peace, and comfort. If you are single and meet someone at this time, the relationship is likely to be enduring.",
        "reversed_love" => "Conflict between family and love can be suggested by the Ten of Cups tarot love meaning. External issues may create chaos in your romantic life, including interference from relatives who believe you should not be together. It is more important than ever to face family criticism; protect each other and avoid public arguments. Ensure your partner feels loved even during this tumultuous time.",
        "upright_career" => "Although the Ten of Cups is often more linked with family ties than work, this card can also bring some happiness to your career. This card can indicate a sense of comfort and belonging in your current position. There are ample growth and creativity opportunities, and you need not worry about these aspects of your career. There might also be a sense of cohesion and happiness among you and your colleagues, with an office culture that feels welcoming and supportive. You may find this job also allows a comfortable work-life balance, enabling you to spend ample time with your family. This card can also indicate retirement or leaving a job to take care of the family.",
        "reversed_career" => "When the Ten of Cups appears reversed in a career tarot reading, you may be dealing with feelings of tension, isolation, and frustration at work. The atmosphere may be more hostile than usual, and your colleagues may not be supportive now. You may feel you do not fit well in this position, shaking your basic sense of stability and security. Sometimes, this card can also signal a disruption in your work-life balance. You might be working longer hours than expected, impacting your family life.",
        "upright_finances" => "Since the Ten of Cups symbolizes domestic stability and harmony, you may find that you and your loved ones have all you need to feel happy and comfortable. This does not always translate to wealth but rather knowing there is enough stability and security. If you have previously argued with family members over financial issues, these problems may dissipate now.",
        "reversed_finances" => "When it comes to your finances, the reversed Ten of Cups can indicate domestic disharmony over money matters. You may face disputes at home about how much money should be spent or how much you have compared to others. There might be a fundamental sense of financial instability at home, exacerbating this tension. Your financial situation and emotions are likely closely related now, and resolving issues in one area or the other may help clear up the entire mess.",
        "yes_no" => "The Ten of Cups represents perfect harmony, abundance, and happiness. It can signify personal or familial dreams coming true, as well as overall contentment and security in life. Positive achievements and emotional stability lie ahead, so the answer you seek is yes.",
        "past" => "By being confident in your direction and following your deepest beliefs, you have been progressing. This commitment and your comfort with authority have provided space for recognition and success in your life.",
        "present" => "A new venture is about to start serving you. This task, event, or journey will initiate a lasting friendship. Do not miss this opportunity.",
        "future" => "The potential for financial success may manifest in some aspects of property ownership. Either find familial happiness or gain prestige in public work. Although challenging, balancing both is possible.",
    ],
    60 =>
    [
        "id" => 61,
        "type_id" => 1,
        "number" => 60,
        "name" => "Page of Cups",
        "upright_keyword" => "Idealistic, Sensitive, Dreamer, Naive, Innocent, Inner Child, Head in the Clouds",
        "reversed_keyword" => "Emotional Vulnerability, Immaturity, Ignoring Inner Child, Escapism, Insecurity",
        "astrology" => "",
        "element" => "Water Element",
        "image_key" => "60_Page_of_Cups",
        "content" => "The Page of Cups represents unexpected inspiration from the unconscious, perhaps in ways we may not fully understand. In this card, a young person by the sea is wearing a blue tunic with floral prints, holding a golden cup. She also wears a bohemian beret and a long flowing scarf. She is surprised to see a fish popping out of the cup, seemingly greeting her like a fairy tale character. She can neither drink from the cup nor toast with it as the fish stares at her, trying to communicate.",
        "upright_content" => "One of the most important meanings of the Page of Cups is that you should be open to new ideas, especially those coming from intuitive inspiration. This card suggests accepting such inspirations, even if they come unexpectedly. They can lead you on an adventure and open many doors. If it’s a creative calling, such as entering the fields of music or art, this card strongly pushes for it.

  When facing dilemmas and giving up on dreams, the Page of Cups seems to tell you to solve the problem from a completely different perspective. It symbolizes perseverance as this is the only way to achieve your dreams. Listen to your intuition, follow your calling, and believe that everything is possible.

  For those afraid to express their emotions, the Page of Cups may signify that it is time to release and show these emotions. Your creativity and feelings should be expressed, no matter how trivial they may seem. In most cases, some people cannot express themselves because they want to protect their ego. The Page of Cups heralds new beginnings, welcoming the true you.",
        "reversed_content" => "The reversed Page of Cups means that your creativity is being blocked. There are things or projects you find interesting, but you seem to pursue them for reasons other than enjoyment. You might be doing these things for money, fame, or other purposes. The reversed Page of Cups suggests you remember the joy your projects initially brought you to rekindle your imagination.

  Another meaning of the reversed Page of Cups is that it can symbolize a troubled person. Someone who fears reality, whether emotional, financial, health-related, or otherwise. They find these issues hard to face and may resort to alcohol or drugs to escape. It might represent you or someone struggling to accept themselves.

  The Page of Cups may indicate someone lacking inspiration, struggling with low self-esteem, and easily discouraged. What can you do to help inspire them to be their best self?",
        "upright_love" => "The Page of Cups tarot love meaning represents a person who is intuitive, creative, and emotional. Regardless of their actual age, they often have an innocent quality. If this card doesn’t point to someone in your life, you might encounter a pleasant surprise. If you’re in a relationship, you may start to see it with fresh eyes, wonder, and awe, developing a new appreciation for parts of your partner you hadn’t noticed before. If you’re single, your approach to love might be playful and childlike. Everything about romance and potential partners will feel novel and delightful.",
        "reversed_love" => "Shy, hesitant, perhaps a bit awkward, the Page of Cups tarot love meaning can point to someone in your romantic life with these characteristics. They might respond well to some much-needed kindness and slowly open up to you if they feel safe. However, sometimes this person may also be a bit emotionally immature; there might be mood swings, insecurity, and lots of drama. If this card doesn’t represent a person, consider your traits. Are your insecurities getting the best of you? How do they affect your romantic life?",
        "upright_career" => "The Page of Cups is an imaginative, sensitive, and creative person, often representing someone focused on creative fields such as art, fashion, poetry, and music, or any area where they can use their talents to create something. The Page of Cups often finds it hard to express their feelings in words, so their creative outlets are where they can express themselves. However, they tend to be directionless, so ensure you’re not just daydreaming about career goals but actively working and taking steps to make them a reality. Follow your dreams, but first, ensure they are well-grounded in reality.",
        "reversed_career" => "Are you having trouble dealing with your feelings at work? The Page of Cups may suggest unprofessionalism or letting your emotions get the better of you. Often, when we are in new environments, we may face feelings we don’t know how to turn into positive things. If your job is in a creative field, the reversed Page of Cups may also indicate difficulties dealing with creative blocks. This too shall pass if you can remember why you initially fell in love with what you do. Seek inspiration.",
        "upright_finances" => "Regarding finances, the Page of Cups may suggest daydreaming and perhaps unrealistic financial goals. For your long-term future, focusing on achievable things and tackling one goal at a time might be better rather than hoping that the lottery or another risky venture will give you what you want.",
        "reversed_finances" => "If you have been dealing with any financial setbacks, ensure your emotions are in check. Avoid making any rash decisions driven by overconfidence. If you’ve been in denial about your financial situation, now is the time to face it rather than escape it. Many valuable lessons can be learned; denial will only delay the inevitable.",
        "yes_no" => "The Page of Cups is a gentle, artistic, dreamer-type messenger. He brings good news and messages of new, calm beginnings. All dealings with this card are positive, and the answer it represents is yes.",
        "past" => "You have had an idea that, if further developed, can bring better results. Your awareness of obstacles will guide you to the best ways to get around them.",
        "present" => "Good news will arrive, reminding you of the importance of reevaluating life. See the humor in life and remember the healing power of laughter.",
        "future" => "Be prepared for upcoming opportunities. If you’re not ready to grasp it, it will easily slip away. The emotional struggles you have gone through will teach you how to love more deeply and intimately.",
    ],
    61 =>
    [
        "id" => 62,
        "type_id" => 1,
        "number" => 61,
        "name" => "Knight of Cups",
        "upright_keyword" => "Idealist, Charming, Artistic, Graceful, Tactful, Diplomatic, Mediator, Negotiator",
        "reversed_keyword" => "Disappointment, Temper Tantrums, Moody, Confusion, Avoiding Conflict, Vanity",
        "astrology" => "",
        "element" => "Water Element",
        "image_key" => "61_Knight_of_Cups",
        "content" => "The Knight of Cups is a card that depicts a young knight proudly riding a white horse while holding a cup, as if he is some sort of messenger. Unlike the Knight of Wands or Knight of Swords, this particular knight is not charging along with his horse. Instead, he moves slowly forward, providing an overall impression of peace and calm. Horses are known to represent a person's drive, energy, and power. The horse's color is white, which is a well-known symbol of spirituality, light, and purity.",
        "upright_content" => "In fact, among all the knights in the tarot, the Knight of Cups is the most feminine. It is important to note that this does not imply he is an unworthy knight. It means he is in proper touch with his emotions and intuition, and he uses them for his well-being and in many of his romantic and seductive quests. Regardless of gender, he is usually very attractive to others.

  When faced with practical decisions, the Knight of Cups listens to his heart, whether or not it is the logical choice. He can manifest as an event or a person in your life, or a part of yourself. He appears as a messenger, carrying with him an invitation or the arrival of something or someone that will benefit you emotionally. As a knight, he is also responsible for accepting gifts and bringing them into the world. Therefore, he can also represent the undertaking of certain projects that are of emotional or creative value to you.",
        "reversed_content" => "Now that you understand the meaning of the upright Knight of Cups, let's look at what this card means when reversed. Conversely, the Knight of Cups means you are letting your emotions control your life, which you should not be doing. You might be overly jealous, emotional, or moody. In fact, this can lead to a degree where no actual action is taken, which should definitely be avoided. Jumping to conclusions is characteristic of the Knight of Cups, and making judgments without the necessary information is common.

  This card indicates a situation that might initially seem appealing but will soon turn very different. Holding such high expectations, everyone will walk away disappointed.",
        "upright_love" => "Romance is coming your way with the Knight of Cups tarot love meaning. This person loves the idea of love and spares no effort to show it. However, sometimes this person can go overboard in their pursuit of true love; holding unrealistic expectations of the perfect partner and perfect relationship. Without a gentle dose of reality, they can move from one lover to another, leaving a trail of broken hearts as everyone eventually shows their human flaws. Be mindful of taking this attitude toward your romance. Try to enjoy things as they are and keep a grounded perspective while pursuing love.",
        "reversed_love" => "When the Knight of Cups is reversed, he can be passively aggressive and full of empty talk. As a great romantic, many of his stories and love declarations may be exaggerated. If this doesn’t sound like someone in your love life right now, it might indicate you feeling overwhelmed by the emotional ups and downs in your romantic life. Feelings can run hot and cold, and perfect facades can quickly shatter. Be cautious of whispering lovers and ensure that they are truthful.",
        "upright_career" => "The Knight of Cups represents your ability to handle work situations with tact and grace. You are particularly diplomatic right now. Conflicts around you will be easier to manage at this time. You can solve problems with creative solutions, emotional connections, and awareness of others. You can see solutions that might be overlooked. This creativity can apply to you and your general career ambitions. If you have been considering entering a creative industry, this card also represents your success in that field.",
        "reversed_career" => "When it comes to your career, the reversed Knight of Cups can have various interpretations depending on context and other cards in the spread. Your work environment might now be full of disagreements, with everyone on edge. You might also consider how you are handling your emotions at work; is your moodiness affecting the environment? Alternatively, your desire to maintain peace might become self-destructive. You might go to great lengths to avoid conflicts rather than address your issues, even if expressing frustrations would help. Try to balance being diplomatic in dealing with others’ problems and lashing out inappropriately.",
        "upright_finances" => "Regarding your finances, your empathy, compassion, and skills in mediating tough conversations might now come in handy. As long as you can use this gift to maintain peace, arguments about money may be alleviated. If your financial situation has been tense, this card might also suggest that you need to get creative in solving your problems. However, once you can think outside the box, you are likely to successfully turn the situation around.",
        "reversed_finances" => "The reversed Knight of Cups can be a passive observer in their own life; in financial matters, you might not be taking decisive action. Sometimes, this card can also indicate that things you hoped for didn’t go as planned. You might have quickly put all your eggs in one basket, only to be disappointed by the results. Ensure you do your research before making any big purchases or investments.",
        "yes_no" => "The Knight of Cups is a romantic and compassionate dreamer who brings new opportunities or some positive invitation. He represents self-acceptance and finding the right path that fits your life. The answer you are seeking is yes.",
        "past" => "Your strengths lie in your intellect and self-determined willpower. Being caught off guard by new directions and ideas from others is natural for your unique perspective.",
        "present" => "An important offer or invitation will arrive suddenly and unexpectedly.",
        "future" => "Staying focused and following your most passionate beliefs will lead to progress towards your goals. You will find peace in deep and meaningful connections with others.",
    ],
    62 =>
    [
        "id" => 63,
        "type_id" => 1,
        "number" => 62,
        "name" => "Queen of Cups",
        "upright_keyword" => "Compassion, Warmth, Kindness, Intuition, Healer, Counselor, Support",
        "reversed_keyword" => "Insecurity, Overgiving, Overly Sensitive, Needy, Vulnerable, Dependent, Martyrdom",
        "astrology" => "",
        "element" => "Water Element",
        "image_key" => "62_Queen_of_Cups",
        "content" => "The Queen of Cups rules over the realm of emotions. Her throne is right at the edge of the sea, and water typically symbolizes the unconscious and feelings. Her position at the shore suggests she is between land and sea, a place where feelings and thoughts exist. She holds a cup with angel-shaped handles. This cup is closed, which is why the Queen of Cups symbolizes our subconscious thoughts. The queen sits alone, allowing her to reflect. The calmness of the sea and sky symbolizes the queen's inner tranquility. Her feet do not touch the water, representing her ability to view her thoughts and feelings from the outside.",
        "upright_content" => "We can understand the meaning of the Queen of Cups by closely observing the woman in the image. She is seen as compassionate, caring, sensitive, and nurturing. She connects with people on an emotional level, making her beloved for her honesty and fairness. The appearance of the Queen of Cups in a reading can guide you to seek help from others. Most of the time, like other queens, this is a female figure who will enter your life.

  The Queen of Cups possesses a very strong intuition, second only to the High Priestess. The Queen of Cups is like a mirror, reflecting the depths of others, allowing them to see themselves in a new light. Often, the Queen of Cups can also represent the trustworthy voice within you. She seems to be saying that you should take time to focus on your emotional health before trying to help others. Self-love breeds compassion.

  The Queen of Cups can also reflect your relationship with others. You might be the emotional rock and anchor for others. You may use your intuition instead of logic to help teach and support others.

  The Queen of Cups often thinks with her heart rather than her head. She might lack reason and common sense, but she can also be intuitive, dreamy, and almost psychic. When logical approaches fail, the Queen of Cups might be the answer to your problem.",
        "reversed_content" => "The reversed Queen of Cups means you are out of sync with your emotions. You may also feel restricted in expressing your true feelings. Most of the time, suppressing your emotions can be very harmful and will lead to a boiling point in the near future. You might be under immense pressure that you can no longer bear.

  The reversed Queen of Cups can also reflect that your thoughts are wandering too far, and you let your imagination run away with you. While you still mean well, you should stop and see if your emotions are trustworthy, as you are allowing them to control you. You need to take some time to reflect on whether these dreams can become reality. During this time, you should try to remain emotionally stable so you know when emotions will be at their best.",
        "upright_love" => "With her wise, supportive, and kind nature, the Queen of Cups likely has many admirers. Her compassion makes her a natural listener for anyone needing a shoulder to cry on. If no one with these characteristics has entered your life, you might find yourself playing this role. You might attract many people in this way but be cautious of becoming too attached or overly dependent on you. Setting boundaries is important now, as emotional support is also emotional labor. Don't exhaust yourself. Let your intuition guide you. Those in relationships can enjoy deeper love at this time.",
        "reversed_love" => "Do you find yourself always playing the caregiver and supporter in your relationship? The reversed Queen of Cups tarot love meaning can indicate that you are putting more effort into the relationship than your partner. You might even feel like a parent rather than a lover at times. The balance between you two needs to be corrected. Alternatively, you might find the emotional environment quite volatile and ever-changing. You or your partner might feel like you are walking on eggshells, not knowing when the next argument will occur.",
        "upright_career" => "The Queen of Cups is a particularly loving and compassionate card. Therefore, if her appearance relates to your career, you can consider multiple meanings. This queen can remind you that whatever you do should make you feel emotionally fulfilled, not just financially. When it comes to your work environment, this card can point to someone who plays a caring and empathetic role among your colleagues. Sometimes, this card can indicate that you are taking on this role. Along this line, the queen also suggests that mentoring from such a person in your field can benefit you.",
        "reversed_career" => "When the Queen of Cups is reversed and appears in your career, you might be dealing with some emotional issues at work. You might find that the projects you are working on or the environment you are in are now emotionally draining. Sometimes, the fatigue we feel comes from our own needs not being met. Because the Queen of Cups can be so focused on the needs of others, she might struggle to put her needs first. Are you too focused on making your colleagues, clients, or your boss happy, neglecting to do what makes you happy? Take some time to care for your emotional health now.",
        "upright_finances" => "You might be using your financial resources to care for others at this time. The Queen of Cups can signal that your heart moves you to contribute to causes, family, or friends in need. Many times, the queen appears here to remind you that money isn’t everything. You should not focus on it at the expense of other considerations in your life.",
        "reversed_finances" => "When it comes to your finances, the reversed Queen of Cups can be a card to look at your emotional health and its relationship to your financial security. If you have been spending compulsively or indulging in some retail therapy, it might help in the short term, as long as you also address the root cause of your unhappiness. Also, be careful not to overextend yourself; your thoughtful and caring nature means you can easily take care of others, even if you lack resources.",
        "yes_no" => "The Queen of Cups is a sensitive, quiet, and virtuous woman who represents seeking and guiding inner transformation. She suggests finding a good listener and loving advisor. Like her counterpart, the King of Cups, her presence is neither a yes nor a no; she provides an unclear answer to your question.",
        "past" => "Your childhood was a happy time filled with love and affection, so your past is not related to current failures. Your relationships have all the right ingredients to make them last longer.",
        "present" => "The influence of a powerful woman will reveal possibilities in your life. She may challenge or inspire you, but whatever she does will lead to valuable insights.",
        "future" => "Seek help or advice from your loved ones, especially noting the wisdom of the women around you. Whether your career is successful or not, your journey will be determined by your emotional considerations.",
    ],
    63 =>
    [
        "id" => 64,
        "type_id" => 1,
        "number" => 63,
        "name" => "King of Cups",
        "upright_keyword" => "Wise, Diplomatic, Balance between mind and heart, Loyal, Advisor, Counselor",
        "reversed_keyword" => "Overwhelmed, Anxious, Apathetic, Repressed, Isolated, Controlling, Selfish",
        "astrology" => "",
        "element" => "Water Element",
        "image_key" => "63_King_of_Cups",
        "content" => "The King of Cups is a card in the tarot that depicts generosity, control, and emotional balance. The card itself shows a king seated on a throne, with an amulet shaped like a fish. The fish on his necklace represents his creativity and spirit thriving in the calm waters around him. We can see from the background that there is a stable balance between the conscious and the unconscious.

  Behind the king, to the right, a fish jumps out of the sea, and to the left, there is a ship, representing the emotional and material worlds respectively. The King of Cups indicates that you do not suppress your impulses but have learned to manage them in a balanced way.",
        "upright_content" => "The King of Cups is one of the most influential cards in the suit of Cups. He represents creativity, emotion, and the unconscious. This card shows the ability to restrain one's emotions and fully control one's feelings and impulses. Therefore, the King of Cups represents a balance between reason and emotion. He points to a strong relationship between understanding and feeling.

  When you have balanced your emotions and can control them, it means you have a deeper understanding and awareness of yourself. When you face challenges that would normally throw you off balance, the King of Cups reminds you to act as he does - don't fly off the handle or immediately throw yourself into despair! You first need to reconcile your emotional state so you can move forward in reality. Learn to assess yourself to determine how to gain a stronger awareness of your inner state.

  In some cases, the King of Cups can symbolize an older male figure in your life. This is a mature man willing to take responsibility for his actions and has mastered self-awareness.

  The King of Cups tends to be political and diplomatic, allowing him to balance the needs of others and enhance harmony between parties. The King of Cups suggests that as a leader, you are sensitive and carefully responsive to the emotional needs of others. The King of Cups implies you should maintain maturity when dealing with negative energies.",
        "reversed_content" => "At his worst, the reversed King of Cups signals volatility, emotional manipulation, and moodiness.

  When the King of Cups stumbles, his ability to handle situations with compassion and wisdom is turned upside down. He cannot balance the needs of all those seeking his guidance; while he is kind to some, he can be cold to others. His talent for navigating others' emotions might be used for questionable purposes, manipulating the environment to meet his needs.

  The reversed King of Cups indicates a character in your life, whether a part of yourself or someone else. While he is usually accessible and in control of his emotions, he has recently become manipulative and controlling. His actions will be used for revenge and retaliation, usually controlling impulses that he normally restrains, ultimately aiming to serve as a form of punishment.",
        "upright_love" => "The balance between heart and mind is represented by the King of Cups tarot love meaning. This person is emotionally mature and values family. When emotions run high, their calm and composed response is exactly what everyone needs to maintain peace. When this card does not represent a person in your life, it may be an advisory to use both logic and intuition in your approach to love. Approach romance pragmatically, but also with wisdom, compassion, and understanding. Together, the love you find is sure to be deep and fulfilling.",
        "reversed_love" => "The reversed King of Cups lacks consistency, compassion, or morality. In love, he may be quite manipulative and selfish, using his emotional intelligence to fulfill his desires. If this does not represent a person, you may have to deal with a lover who guides you or uses you. Alternatively, the King of Cups tarot love meaning can simply imply a kind of selfishness in your romantic life. You or your partner may not be putting effort into the relationship, content to let the other do most of the work.",
        "upright_career" => "Sometimes, the King of Cups can signify a more experienced, caring, and empathetic counselor or mentor who can help you develop an emotionally fulfilling career. This card is also about balancing one's emotional needs with practical and logical demands. Your wisdom and ability to balance mind and heart can earn you the respect and admiration of those around you and make you particularly valuable in resolving conflicts between office factions.",
        "reversed_career" => "The reversed King of Cups can indicate dealing with a boss or manager who has become tyrannical. While the upright version of this card is empathetic and emotionally aware of others' situations, this reversed King of Cups may be selfish and oblivious to everyone's needs except his own. Insecurity and lack of emotional control may be significant factors in how this person handles the work environment. Sometimes, this person can also be you. Sometimes, this card can indicate that you are in your position just for the money, and you might feel unfulfilled. Even if you started this position with excitement and passion, it might slowly fade away. Try to see if you can reconnect with what you first loved about the job.",
        "upright_finances" => "On one hand, the King of Cups marks a degree of financial stability. This stability results from your wise nature when making decisions. If you find yourself making some major purchases or investments, this card can remind you to be cautious and logical while also meeting emotional needs.",
        "reversed_finances" => "While the upright King of Cups is a sign of good judgment, the reversed King of Cups is the opposite. You might find it difficult to control spending or make logical, wise decisions. You might let unchecked emotions make financial choices for you, which, if left unchecked, could lead to problems.",
        "yes_no" => "The King of Cups is the rational voice of compassion, warmth, and gentleness. He is an authority figure with strong intuition and rich spiritual knowledge. This card represents the ability to make decisions through guided experience and provide good/useful advice. Essentially, neither positive nor negative, the answer is unclear.",
        "past" => "Your past concerns will revisit you. Seeking professional guidance might be a good idea if you need help.",
        "present" => "A person very capable of helping you will appear in your life. Accept their advice and seek support without hesitation.",
        "future" => "To bring about a state of calm, seek advice. You will not find balance by yourself, so seek a strong ally to guide you.",
    ],
    64 =>
    [
        "id" => 65,
        "type_id" => 1,
        "number" => 64,
        "name" => "Ace of Swords",
        "upright_keyword" => "Clarity, Breakthrough, New ideas, Focus, Vision, Strength, Focus, Truth",
        "reversed_keyword" => "Confusion, Poor communication, Hostility, Arguments, Destruction, Brutality",
        "astrology" => "",
        "element" => "Air Element",
        "image_key" => "64_Ace_of_Swords",
        "content" => "The Ace of Swords shows a hand emerging from the clouds, wielding a double-edged sword. The double-edged sword carries a golden crown, surrounded by a wreath. For a long time, the wreath has been associated with victory, success, and great achievements.

  The crown is a symbol of royalty as well as royal authority.

  In the background, the sword floats in different settings, with mountains and seas used as symbols of the vast and distant lands the sword can be used to conquer, as well as symbols of ambition.",
        "upright_content" => "Like all Aces, the Ace of Swords indicates a breakthrough moment that a person is about to experience. The sharp blade of the sword represents the power of intellect, with the ability to cut through deception and uncover the truth. In layman's terms, this card represents a moment when a person can see the world from a new perspective, as a place full of new possibilities. Therefore, now is the best time to achieve goals, as the Ace of Swords gives a green light and signals opportunities and new beginnings.

  This may also be a good time for you to seek justice and truth in all things, as your conscience is awake, and your mind is sharp. If you stand up, your sharp thinking and clarity will be rewarded.

  When we take a closer look at the sword and see its double edges, we are also reminded that this sword can be used for noble deeds or for destruction. It all depends on the holder, which is also a warning that excessive power has the potential for corruption. If you stick to your principles, the sword will serve you well.",
        "reversed_content" => "Receiving the Ace of Swords reversed may indicate confusion, uncertainty, and a state of great disarray. Now is not a good time to make any decisions, as you are unclear about what you should do, which means the chances of failure may be very high.

  At this time, it is best to be prepared and take small steps, working methodically and slowly toward your goals. This would be a good time to relax and think rationally about each stage, rather than acting impulsively, as everything seems blurry at the moment. It may also be a good time to seek advice, as things may not be as they seem.",
        "upright_love" => "You will find the Ace of Swords tarot love meaning particularly attractive for engaging in intellectual discussions. Communicating and discussing important issues with your partner will be beneficial for you. Pay special attention to addressing issues or obstacles in your relationship with clarity and honesty. You may find that facing these issues head-on can bring more harmony and understanding between you two. While discussions may sometimes become heated, it's more important to talk about them rather than sweeping them under the rug. In the long run, learning these communication skills will make your relationship stronger.

  If your relationship has been chaotic, or you are recovering from a breakup, the Ace of Swords tarot love meaning can also encourage you to cut out harmful people or attitudes from your love life.",
        "reversed_love" => "Currently, confusion and lack of clarity may be affecting your relationship. The reversed Ace of Swords tarot love meaning suggests there may be misunderstandings and assumptions, and sometimes your partner may have a completely different perspective from yours. You need to work hard to get back on the same page. This card can also sometimes hint at hurtful words; make sure your communication with your partner is not too harsh. Emotions may be particularly sensitive now, and without goodwill, confrontations can quickly turn into fights.",
        "upright_career" => "Since Aces always represent new beginnings, the Ace of Swords can signify a new job, position, or career that can bring you a lot of intellectual stimulation. You may find your new environment challenging and highly encouraging for developing your mind and skills. You may be with colleagues who enjoy discussing new ideas, and communication will be very smooth. Having a clear vision of what you want to do and being able to articulate that vision will be very helpful to you now.",
        "reversed_career" => "In work, the reversed Ace of Swords indicates that there may be some poor communication at work right now, which could cause trouble for you and your colleagues. This can also indicate that the ideas you are coming up with now may be a bit unrealistic and may lead to failure. Make sure you are very realistic about what you can achieve and don't keep your head in the clouds. Be careful with your words and make sure you can express yourself clearly. Sometimes, this card can also suggest boredom at work. Your job may have become monotonous and no longer enough to keep you engaged.",
        "upright_finances" => "In financial tarot, you need to think very rationally with the Ace of Swords. When it comes to money, your heart and your head may say very different things. In these situations, this card tells you to trust your brain and avoid making emotional decisions. If friends or family ask you for money or seek a loan, handle the situation with your head first. Do you have enough for yourself? Will you be repaid? How will the money affect your relationship with that person? A rational approach might feel less good initially, but it could save you a lot of trouble in the long run.",
        "reversed_finances" => "Be careful with your finances! The reversed Ace of Swords can suggest mistakes and unclear situations regarding your finances. Carefully check your bank statements, contracts, loan agreements, or any legal documents to ensure everything is in order. If there's something you don't understand, be sure to ask and not assume everything is fine. It doesn't hurt to ask, and it's better to be safe than sorry.",
        "yes_no" => "The Ace of Swords represents victory achieved through mental strength and achievement. Justice, clarity, and creative thinking are all associated with this card. A brilliant idea might be just around the corner, or it could be some divine inspiration for creativity. The answer is most likely yes.",
        "past" => "You have fought for good causes, channeling strong energy into idealistic pursuits. Recent events have set in motion an irreversible chain of events.",
        "present" => "You are entering a new phase of your life, and everything will change. The causes and outcomes of this change are yet to be determined, but this period will reveal a lot to you.",
        "future" => "Putting your ideas into action may require some courage, but if you are willing, you will be able to overcome the greatest difficulties.",
    ],
    65 =>
    [
        "id" => 66,
        "type_id" => 1,
        "number" => 65,
        "name" => "Two of Swords",
        "upright_keyword" => "Stalemate, Difficult choices, Caught in the middle, Denial, Hidden information",
        "reversed_keyword" => "Indecision, Hesitation, Anxiety, Information overload, No right choice, Truth revealed",
        "astrology" => "",
        "element" => "Air Element",
        "image_key" => "65_Two_of_Swords",
        "content" => "The Two of Swords symbolizes the confusion we face when forced to make difficult choices. In the Two of Swords card, there is a seated woman who is blindfolded, holding a sword in each hand. In the background, there is a sea surrounded by rocky islands, acting as obstacles that hinder forward movement and action. The blindfolded woman in the card represents a situation that prevents her from seeing the problem and the solution clearly.

  The swords in each hand show two opposing choices that are mutually exclusive. It can also depict a stalemate, suggesting that problems should be solved with logical and rational thinking. The moon on the card's right side symbolizes the role that illusions and deception play in the difficulties of the woman's choice.",
        "upright_content" => "When we see the Two of Swords in a tarot reading, we encounter a stalemate. Two opposing forces are at a standstill, and neither seems to be able to win. When you stumble upon this path, it is not by your choice; you find yourself caught in the middle. If nothing is done or no one intervenes, it can go on indefinitely. We find ourselves in a situation where a choice must be made, either to stand on one side of the situation or the other. Neither seems particularly appealing, making the decision even more difficult. However, it is impossible to make further progress until we get past this stalemate.

  The Two of Swords is often associated with balance and partnerships. It signifies the need to keep your relationships in balance. Whether it be in business, friendships, or romantic relationships, you may find it challenging to maintain the status quo, feeling caught in the middle. Regarding your work, you may currently be in a deadlock, possibly waiting for a decision from another party. Be patient and avoid forcing people into making hasty decisions.

  The meaning of the Two of Swords can also depict a warning to be cautious. Like the woman on the card, you may be choosing to wear a blindfold, hoping that the problem will go away. You should avoid evading any issues you are facing, as this will not solve your problems.",
        "reversed_content" => "The situation we see in the reversed Two of Swords is a legendary stalemate, with two forces clashing. This battle can represent internal or external issues, and you are forced to stand in the middle and become the decision-maker. However, since neither side seems pleasant, you may find yourself confused and too stressed to make a decision.

  When you make a decision, it will be choosing between two poor outcomes. Don't rush; the more important thing here is to make a choice, from which point you can deal with any consequences.",
        "upright_love" => "If you are single, you may find it challenging to make progress in your love life. The Two of Swords tarot love meaning signifies being stuck between decisions. Are you trying to choose between two lovers? Or love and another aspect of your life? It seems that your choices are equally appealing, and you may try to avoid choosing entirely rather than actively engaging in your life choices. Be careful that the world does not make the choice for you. If you are in a relationship, something may be preventing you and your partner from resolving your issues. The Two of Swords tarot love meaning also symbolizes various stalemates. Now is not the time to ignore problems but to carefully discuss them to seek compromise.",
        "reversed_love" => "Sometimes, there is no right choice, as suggested by the reversed Two of Swords tarot love meaning. If you are single and trying to choose between two potential lovers, it may seem that neither is particularly suitable for you. If you are in a relationship, you may find yourself choosing between your lover and other aspects of your life. You may feel more indecisive and confused than ever. This card suggests making a painful decision, regardless of your stage in your romantic life. However, the longer you wait to make a choice, the more anxiety you will create, leading to more problems. Sometimes, you may be forced to make a decision before you are ready. Making a choice now and dealing with the consequences can release your burden. Trust your intuition.",
        "upright_career" => "You may find yourself caught in a work conflict. This can manifest as having to side with one colleague over another, and all you want to do is stay neutral. Choosing one person over another can create tension and rifts, and you may worry about damaging your relationships with them. Sometimes, this card can indicate that you are trying to choose between two jobs or career paths. The Two of Swords can sometimes suggest that you do not yet have all the information needed to make a choice. If you have time, use it to research and get the answers you need.",
        "reversed_career" => "The conflicts you encounter at work seem to be escalating and causing you a lot of stress. If you are caught between two quarreling colleagues, it may seem like no matter what you choose, you will be in trouble, with no right choice. Alternatively, you may find yourself responsible for a significant decision at work; you could be leading a project or choosing between two careers. There is a lot of anxiety behind these decisions as they seem irreversible. You may have done extensive research, but you are now dealing with information overload rather than providing help, and things may seem more unclear than ever.",
        "upright_finances" => "Are you avoiding dealing with financial matters right now? This card suggests that you may be in denial about your financial situation and might find it easier to avoid looking at it altogether. If you make an effort to see clearly, you may find that you have to make some tough choices. Perhaps you want that new designer dress and a new laptop, but a clearer look at your bank account might show you that you can only afford one right now. Whatever the case, make sure you look at it clearly and rationally.",
        "reversed_finances" => "No matter how tense the situation is, you have finally learned to face your finances. Once you see the reality, making the right decision becomes easier. Alternatively, this card can indicate that you haven't fully absorbed any financial information you are trying to learn. Instead of helping you, it may feel overwhelming. Rather than letting this feeling push you away, take it slow. Learn one thing at a time and focus on one topic each week. You will get it soon.",
        "yes_no" => "The Two of Swords symbolizes conflict resolution and decisions that must be made. However, the conclusion is likely to be reached by seeking inner peace and compromise. While this card suggests overall peace, it does not lean towards either yes or no. Therefore, maybe is the answer.",
        "past" => "Honestly recounting your past will help you make difficult choices. The conflicts you encounter will be resolved through new approaches.",
        "present" => "There is a conflict that will take up your energy to resolve. By overcoming indecision, you will take well-thought-out actions to determine the solution.",
        "future" => "The difficult situation ahead of you must be overcome immediately, so do not delay or hesitate. Act honestly and with honorable intentions to achieve the best outcome.",
    ],
    66 =>
    [
        "id" => 67,
        "type_id" => 1,
        "number" => 66,
        "name" => "Three of Swords",
        "upright_keyword" => "Heartbreak, Separation, Grief, Sorrow, Sadness, Distress, Loss, Trauma, Tears",
        "reversed_keyword" => "Healing, Forgiveness, Recovery, Reconciliation, Repressed emotions",
        "astrology" => "",
        "element" => "Air Element",
        "image_key" => "66_Three_of_Swords",
        "content" => "One of the most iconic images in the tarot, the Three of Swords depicts a floating heart pierced by three swords. Above it, there are thick clouds. There is also a torrential downpour in the background. The symbolism is quite opaque, and the emotional impact it has is immediate. The heart represents warmth, emotion, and spirit, and the three swords represent forces that are causing harm, pain, and creating distress to what they pierce. This is an image of grief, loss, and heartbreak. The clouds and rain depict the grimness of the surrounding situation. All these symbols point to the Three of Swords showing a low point in life.",
        "upright_content" => "The Three of Swords delivers a message of rejection, betrayal, hurt, and discouragement. In such times, our minds serve us well. If you can think about it logically and be prepared for the experience, the impact of this painful influence can be minimized.

  But also remember, pain and grief are normal parts of life, for they make us appreciate what happiness and joy we have and teach us. It is through pain that we learn to avoid mistakes that might lead us into danger and grief. Thus, it is a necessity in the journey of life. Hence, the Three of Swords is a depiction of suffering meant to make us stronger, more cautious, and more alert.

  Sometimes life leaves us with no choice—we are struck down. But what determines one's future is the choice to continue being struck down or to rise again. Every bit of pain you encounter is a stepping stone towards finding deeper meaning in this world. This card appears when you need to prepare yourself for the next stage in life. While sorrow can be deeply painful, it enables you to forget the past and focus on the future, knowing that you have control over the actions you take afterward. Don’t dwell too much on what troubles you but focus on what is to come, as you are the one who decides your fate.",
        "reversed_content" => "The reversed Three of Swords indicates that you have recently faced loss, separation, or a moment of grief. You may still be in recovery, and your emotions have not yet fully settled, making it hard to move forward. While you may still be reminiscing about the past pain, this card can signal that it is time to let go and look forward to life ahead, as there is much to enjoy.

  Many people do not see this and end up dwelling on their pain for too long, delaying their recovery process. Do not focus too much on what happened; renew your emotions and gather your courage. The reversed Three of Swords card is here to let you know that all tough times pass, they don’t stay there, and when we fall, we can also rise again.",
        "upright_love" => "The imagery of this card is straightforward; the Three of Swords tarot love meaning signifies heartbreak. This is likely a time filled with tears, sadness, and heartache in your life. If you are in a relationship, this can sometimes indicate a breakup, conflict, or some form of separation. In the worst-case scenario, since this card is a three, it can also point to a third party causing trouble in your relationship. You and your partner may have to face difficult issues to stay together. Without clear and respectful discussions and a willingness to work together, this relationship will end. If you are single, it could be that past sorrow and pain affect your ability to date. Past wounds have not yet healed, and it is important to give yourself some time before trying to find true love again.",
        "reversed_love" => "With the reversed Three of Swords tarot love meaning, lovers may find themselves resolving their conflicts and forgiving each other. Here, there is a desire to heal, to move past old wounds, and look toward the future. For singles, this often means finally overcoming heartbreak to fully present yourself in your dating life again. However, this card can sometimes also suggest the opposite. Wounds may not heal but rather be repressed, leading to festering and resentment. Partners may find it hard to forgive each other for past hurts. Sometimes, in these situations, it may be better for both to move on.",
        "upright_career" => "Right now, work may be a significant source of stress, frustration, and sadness. In the worst-case scenario, it can mean a sudden job loss or the closing of a company. More commonly, it may indicate some form of conflict at work, whether with clients or colleagues. If you are dealing with this, ensure that you have honest and open conversations with your colleagues while maintaining respect. There may be much you can learn from each other. If you are job hunting or have just lost your job, the search can be discouraging right now. Do not lose hope; if you can afford it, take some time to recover from this pain. It can give you a more positive mindset for your job search.",
        "reversed_career" => "Things are starting to look up again at work. Stressful conflicts are beginning to resolve, and your outlook and overall well-being are improving. Your colleagues may have moved past their conflicts, or the person causing frustration has left. Conversely, everyone at work might be focused on forgiving past mistakes and working together for the future. Communication has improved, and new processes may be in place to avoid past errors. But sometimes, this card can point to situations getting worse; they don’t leave the problems behind but hold grudges and maintain negative attitudes. Other cards will provide more context.",
        "upright_finances" => "You may now be dealing with material loss or at least something in your financial life that is causing you great stress. Breakups have both emotional and financial impacts; you might no longer afford your apartment alone, or you may have to split your assets during a divorce. All these things can be overwhelming right now. Be gentle with yourself, but also remember not to avoid taking care of these matters. Seek support; you can get through it.",
        "reversed_finances" => "If you have been suffering financial setbacks, the reversed Three of Swords can indicate an improvement is on the way. You may be rebuilding your savings or finding yourself in a better and more stable financial situation than before. Alternatively, this card can also suggest that the emotional grief from financial loss is worsening. If you have experienced a significant loss, you may find it hard to adjust your spending habits or let go of your previous standard of living. Not accepting the truth of your position often makes difficult situations even harder.",
        "yes_no" => "The Three of Swords expresses pain and suffering through emotional loss, the end of significant relationships, or heartbreak due to separation. The emotional blocks and mental anguish accompanying this card portray a negative answer to your question.",
        "past" => "You are still maintaining significant emotional or physical pain. Letting go of responsibility may give you the chance to create something new as something you loved has recently been destroyed.",
        "present" => "You will soon experience intense emotional upheaval. This period of sorrow will lead you to a better future.",
        "future" => "The path ahead of you is being cleared to make way for something new. It’s up to you to take advantage of the opportunities in store.",
    ],
    67 =>
    [
        "id" => 68,
        "type_id" => 1,
        "number" => 67,
        "name" => "Four of Swords",
        "upright_keyword" => "Rest, Relaxation, Peace, Sanctuary, Recuperation, Self-protection, Rejuvenation",
        "reversed_keyword" => "Recovery, Awakening, Re-entering the world, Breaking isolation, Restlessness, Burnout",
        "astrology" => "",
        "element" => "Air Element",
        "image_key" => "67_Four_of_Swords",
        "content" => "The Four of Swords exudes a quiet stillness, a peaceful calm that contrasts deeply with the pain of the Three of Swords. Here, in a church, there is a carved effigy of a knight lying on a tomb, with three swords hanging above him and the fourth sword placed below him. The three swords remind him of the pain endured in the previous card. The position of the fourth sword seems to signal that the battle has ended. The stained glass window behind the statue depicts a child and a woman, giving the scene a sense of warmth and welcome after the retreat. The knight’s hands are in a prayer position.",
        "upright_content" => "After the chaos, anger, and pain depicted in the Three of Swords, the Four of Swords signals a retreat. The Four of Swords is a moment of rest. It is unclear whether this is due to a choice to withdraw or pure exhaustion. We still feel tender from the wounds we have suffered, and the weapons of battle still hang over us as stark reminders of what has been lost. To continue and reappear in your daily life, you must now take time to breathe. There is always a faint fear that more will happen again, suggesting you seize every chance to rest.

You need to gain strength and clarity in a quiet environment away from your current circumstances. Now is the time to re-evaluate, organize, and understand your priorities. This helps rejuvenate one's spirit, and you will emerge stronger than before.

The Four of Swords indicates that it is time to consolidate new strengths and prepare for new challenges. You have gone through a crisis after crisis, leaving you exhausted. Only by stepping away and embracing a new atmosphere can you face new challenges.

Take time to nurture yourself and re-enter life. Within us, there is a flicker of hope, lying quietly, waiting to reveal itself once we are healed again.",
        "reversed_content" => "While the Four of Swords in tarot can mean it is time for healing, the reversed card can mean restlessness. Your heart desires rest, but this is not what your mind wants. You feel too dependent on your belongings. This is not advisable, as it may impact your health.

You can continue to fight, but sometimes that is ineffective, and you must recognize your strength to decide when to withdraw. Resting and retreating are acts of self-love, and while you may try to push forward, it will only become harder in the long run.",
        "upright_love" => "With the Four of Swords tarot love meaning, taking a break is necessary. If you are single, the excitement of your love life may be exhausting you. You might be trying too hard to impress someone or going on dates every day to find the right person. You may feel worn out, and it is important to listen to your intuition and body, giving it time to rest. If you are in a relationship, both of you can benefit from taking a break. Sometimes, this card can also predict that you two need some time alone; this does not mean the end of the relationship, but everyone, especially introverts, needs some private time.",
        "reversed_love" => "If you haven't heeded the warning to rest, the reversed Four of Swords tarot love meaning can suggest you will have no choice. If you have been relentlessly pursuing a potential lover, you may find your advances now unwelcome. You might benefit from giving this person time and space to make their own choices. Pressuring someone usually has the opposite effect of what you want. Alternatively, this card can also indicate coming out of a period of rest. You may feel more energized than ever! Couples who feel their relationship has become a bit too routine may find their passion reignited.",
        "upright_career" => "Recently, work may have been very busy or frustrating. You may have put in long hours, and chronic stress may be taking a toll on your physical or mental health. Listen to your body and allow yourself to take a break. If possible, take a mental health day and use it to take care of yourself or catch up on sleep. We are not machines, and without some much-needed rest, the effects on our health can be lasting. Afterward, you can return feeling refreshed.",
        "reversed_career" => "You may have given yourself a much-needed break from work, but you might now be ready to return. Ideally, you used this time to relieve stress and do some much-needed self-care. With time passing and feeling refreshed, you may find situations that once made you feel stressed and frustrated are easier to handle. From now on, try to be more aware of your stress levels. However, sometimes, despite needing rest, this card can indicate continuing to work. If this is your situation, you might need to reconsider. Our bodies often force us to take breaks. If things do not seem to be improving, you might also need to consider changing jobs.",
        "upright_finances" => "Are you worrying about what’s in your bank? If you are accustomed to dealing with financial stress, it may be second nature for you to think (or rather worry) about your finances. Try to give your mind a break. Often, letting a thought run in circles does not solve anything, and the best thing we can do for our minds is to think about something else. Avoid letting obsessive and negative thoughts consume you.",
        "reversed_finances" => "Your financial situation may be improving, and you might be recovering from a period of great stress. Perhaps bills are being paid, debts are being settled, or expenses are decreasing. Alternatively, stress may be increasing, and you may start feeling overwhelmed by bills. Seek support; someone may be able to help you at this time. Sometimes, this card can also suggest that despite having it, you may not be accepting financial support.",
        "yes_no" => "The Four of Swords points to some sort of illness or retreat. However, it also brings rest, healing, and order. Other interpretations might simply be a need to take a break or call a truce. This card is quite mild in position but overall positive. The answer is most likely yes.",
        "past" => "The plans you have already made may not guide you correctly through the coming changes. The shadow you feel looming over you will soon pass, and the warmth of your life will return.",
        "present" => "You want to withdraw from your social circles to focus on your welfare. The card also suggests the same to gain some peace of mind.",
        "future" => "Take some time to plan your future. There is no need to rush decisions about what is best for you and those you care about.",
    ],
    68 =>
    [
        "id" => 69,
        "type_id" => 1,
        "number" => 68,
        "name" => "Five of Swords",
        "upright_keyword" => "Arguments, Disputes, Aggression, Bullying, Intimidation, Conflict, Hostility, Stress",
        "reversed_keyword" => "Reconciliation, Resolution, Compromise, Retaliation, Regret, Remorse, Reducing Losses",
        "astrology" => "",
        "element" => "Air Element",
        "image_key" => "68_Five_of_Swords",
        "content" => "The Five of Swords card depicts a young man with a look of disdain on his face. He is watching the enemies he has conquered. He possesses five swords—taken from the other fighters on the card. Two other figures walk away slowly, with a sense of loss and sadness. Above them, the sky is cloudy, indicating that while the battle is over, all is not well.",
        "upright_content" => "This card indicates that you are embroiled in some form of conflict. It may also suggest disagreements with others, leading to hostility and tension. Although you think you have won, in the grand scheme, you may still lose because you have alienated or hurt those you argued with, leading you down a path of isolation. At this moment, you might believe being right is more important than understanding the other person's perspective.

It is crucial to try and pick up the pieces now. You still have the opportunity to act before the conflict escalates. You may feel like everyone and everything is against you. You might also lose some friends in the process. This is why you need to make significant decisions about your stance. What is more important to you? Mutual progress or mutual destruction? This may require you to bravely face your inner conflicts.

This card represents ambition in a rather negative way. Too much ambition without considering consequences or the people you affect is never good. The misplaced ambition depicted by this card can make you a frustrated loser or a callous winner—both quite negative. This card instead asks us to be more considerate of those around us and to let go of our ego.",
        "reversed_content" => "In its upright position, the Five of Swords is a card of tension, conflict, and disagreements. The reversed meaning of the Five of Swords tells you that all you want is for this particular period to be over so you can forget and forgive. Because you are starting to realize that winning isn’t everything, you will be able to focus your energy on more constructive and positive activities.

Alternatively, another interpretation of this card in reverse is that the conflict you are experiencing will become even more unsettling when you realize that there are no winners. These are the terms you need to come to grips with.",
        "upright_love" => "Unexpected changes and restless energy can be indicated by the Five of Swords tarot love meaning. There may be a sense of anxiety and harshness in the air, making arguments and fights easy to start. You and your partner may be feeling irritable, and conflicts can start easily if you’re not careful. If you find yourself in one of these, you should carefully consider your reasons in the fight and ensure that you’re not arguing just to be right. Ego can push you and your loved one into conflict without any real reason. Sometimes, this can create passion when needed, but if it continues, it can be destructive.",
        "reversed_love" => "With the reversed Five of Swords tarot love meaning, reconciliation after intense tensions is possible. There is a desire between you and your lover to put down your swords and seek compromise. Even if both parties choose to let go, the wounds are likely still painful. Sometimes, if reconciliation is not possible, this card can indicate walking away from a lover or potential relationship. While it is painful, it may be the better option if intense arguments happen frequently. Sometimes, in the long run, it is better to cut losses and leave before more damage is done.",
        "upright_career" => "Conflict at work is erupting, and there is a considerable amount of hostility in the air. Arguments can be easily provoked now. This can come from misunderstandings, lack of communication, or poor leadership. The Five of Swords can also indicate bullying and intimidation. Whether it is you or someone else, you may be required to stand up for yourself or others. While it is tempting, make sure you handle this professionally and don’t be afraid to pull in HR if needed. Often, processes are in place to handle these situations. However, this card can also point to self-sabotage, meaning your perception of the situation may first be causing these conflicts. Defensive behavior often creates a cycle of attacks.",
        "reversed_career" => "A previously stressful and hostile work environment may be getting better. It seems now there can be resolutions as everyone is ready to put down their swords. Compromises can be made, and open communication is possible again. If this does not apply to you, this card can also suggest that hostility is escalating. If you have been dealing with workplace bullies, they may retaliate, sometimes even trying to get you fired. Don’t be afraid to bring this up with your manager or HR; it is their job to handle these conflicts. However, once you do, make sure your behavior does not draw attention either. As long as you handle things calmly and professionally, you will get through it.",
        "upright_finances" => "You might be facing financial conflicts right now; whether it is with your partner, your family, or your friends. You need to be extra careful with your finances, especially when it comes to trusting others. There may be some who are trying to take more from you than they are owed or take advantage of you. Sometimes this card can also indicate financial strain; you may need to cut some luxury expenses from your budget.",
        "reversed_finances" => "If you have been dealing with financial tension or even fighting over money, you may now see these start to dissipate and relax. If you have been dealing with people trying to take advantage of you financially, you may see them distancing themselves from you or even being held accountable for their actions.",
        "yes_no" => "The Five of Swords suggests conflict, discord, and impending trouble. In the near future, there could be losses, failures, or painful separations accompanied by feelings of brokenness and low self-esteem. Nothing associated with this card is positive, therefore, your answer is no.",
        "past" => "The losses you have experienced are a result of your overestimation and inabilities. To succeed, you must be honest with yourself.",
        "present" => "Unrealistic attitudes may lead you to experience failure. Your mistakes will result in suffering. Keep your expectations realistic to assess and overcome conflicts.",
        "future" => "Endure your losses gracefully and do not surrender to despair; you can create victories from any results of failure.",
    ],
    69 =>
    [
        "id" => 70,
        "type_id" => 1,
        "number" => 69,
        "name" => "Six of Swords",
        "upright_keyword" => "Moving on, Leaving behind, Transition, Distance, Learning from the past",
        "reversed_keyword" => "Stuck in the past, Repeating mistakes, Avoiding issues, Feeling trapped",
        "astrology" => "",
        "element" => "Air Element",
        "image_key" => "69_Six_of_Swords",
        "content" => "The image on the Six of Swords depicts a woman and a child being rowed across a body of water toward a distant land. From the image, we can see that the woman and child are facing away from us, leaving something behind. The woman is cloaked, which might suggest she is in hiding, leaving in a situation where her true identity must remain unknown. We can assume that, because of this, she is experiencing a great loss or sadness. The symbolism in the Six of Swords is about loss or change, and moving toward a future that looks more promising than the one left behind. The six swords placed beside the boat symbolize the power of a rational mind compared to intuition and the heart.",
        "upright_content" => "The meaning of the Six of Swords is that you are going through a transition that is not entirely happy but necessary. This transition is likely the result of decisions you made in the past, now forcing you to leave something behind to move forward. While you may feel sad, you need to remember that moving on is the best choice for your future.

Life is filled with moments where you will have to let go of things you have grown attached to. This will be challenging. The Six of Swords shows the sadness you may be feeling, but you must remember that pain does not last forever, so you should look to the future for strength.

In life, sometimes the only way to solve a problem is to leave it behind and start anew. You might feel that this is the coward's way out, but when you have tried all other methods, running away is the only option. The important part is to plan your new path, guiding you toward happiness. In this case, the Six of Swords is using your logic, clarity, and objectivity to plan where you are now, where you have been, and where you want to go. Intuition can help, but you need logical thinking to ensure success.",
        "reversed_content" => "The reversed Six of Swords can indicate that you have been trying to move on and make necessary transitions. However, you might be encountering challenges that make these a reality. You may keep going back to the past, either due to unresolved issues or because you are second-guessing your decisions.

Another reversed Six of Swords meaning is that you have been resisting the transitions that life is giving you. You may feel like you are being forced to move before you are ready, or you do not want to move at all. In this case, you should consider the benefits of these movements rather than the drawbacks. Like Orpheus in the underworld, you must look forward and not back, for looking back may risk collapse.",
        "upright_love" => "When the Six of Swords appears in a love tarot reading, it means that struggles are coming to an end. Sometimes, this can take the form of ending a relationship or moving past a painful chapter in your relationship and finding reconciliation. Either way, it suggests leaving the past behind and moving towards an unknown but brighter future. If you are single, you may be ready to leave a part of yourself behind, perhaps the part that hindered you from accepting love. If you have old wounds you have been nursing, the Six of Swords tarot love meaning can be a welcome sight. You may finally be ready to leave them behind.",
        "reversed_love" => "What is it that you find difficult to let go of? The reversed Six of Swords tarot love meaning indicates that despite your attempts to leave it behind, the past still has a firm hold on you. On one hand, you may know that leaving the past is the healthiest thing for you, but you may be compulsively drawn back. You may choose to stay in a relationship devoid of love, remembering its happy moments, unable to let go of a toxic ex, or past insecurities may prevent you from fully enjoying your love life. Examine what is binding you and consider what potential happy futures you are willing to sacrifice for it.",
        "upright_career" => "You may be leaving behind a stressful job. As you move towards a more tranquil phase of work, you may feel relief and peace. You should be making steady progress on your projects. Compared to past experiences, these times may be a welcome improvement. Sometimes, this card can indicate a recent change in role or position, becoming something that better suits you.",
        "reversed_career" => "It seems like no matter what you do, you cannot escape your troubles at work. Your workplace may be full of stress, arguments, and conflict, which drain your energy and affect your mental health. Even though you may want to leave, it seems like you are stuck in this job and cannot find anything better at the moment. Sometimes, this card can also suggest that you may be the one causing trouble; instead of letting things go, you may be returning to the same issues repeatedly, holding grudges while the other party is willing to move on. You may want to examine your own attitude and defensiveness to see if it contributes to your stress levels. What can you let go of? If you do manage to leave this job, be mindful of the same issues reappearing. We can escape environments, people; but not ourselves.",
        "upright_finances" => "When moving on from the past, the Six of Swords can indicate you are emerging from financial difficulties. Things will be more comfortable for you financially, and you may not be under so much stress. As you find material stability, let past experiences remind you to keep an eye on your bank account. Often, we cannot escape our money problems, and it is best to remain responsible so that issues do not reappear time and time again.",
        "reversed_finances" => "Are you trying to escape your financial problems right now? When it comes to money issues, usually avoidance does not work. The only thing you can do is face them and deal with them honestly and calmly. Once you do the work of actually accepting your situation, those seemingly insurmountable things may look easier to face. Seek out professionals who can help you if you need it.",
        "yes_no" => "The Six of Swords signifies a journey or an escape to a state of clarity. It suggests a better, positive future, or perhaps a period of calm. Moving forward may require you to use your logic or natural wisdom, but the end result is positive. The answer is yes.",
        "past" => "You have overcome a major hurdle while staying true to yourself. The understanding and objectivity you have cultivated will lead you to a better future.",
        "present" => "There will be a change for the better in your life. The burden or challenge you face will create a new path.",
        "future" => "The challenges you face will eventually be overcome. Struggles are necessary and can provide you with the growth needed to find a path to a better future.",
    ],
    70 =>
    [
        "id" => 71,
        "type_id" => 1,
        "number" => 70,
        "name" => "Seven of Swords",
        "upright_keyword" => "Deception, Trickery, Tactics, Strategy, Resourcefulness, Stealth, Cunning",
        "reversed_keyword" => "Confession, Conscience, Regret, Malice, Truth Revealed",
        "astrology" => "",
        "element" => "Air Element",
        "image_key" => "70_Seven_of_Swords",
        "content" => "In the Seven of Swords card, a man is seen sneaking away from some sort of camp, holding five swords in his hands. Behind him, two other swords are standing upright on the ground. From this image, we can deduce that the Seven of Swords is about stealth, evasion, deception, or betrayal.

The man's expression shows a hint of confidence, as if he is sure that his mission to steal the swords will be successful. Unfortunately for him, there seems to be a group of soldiers on the left who have noticed the theft, with one soldier raising a flag or weapon as if to signal pursuit.",
        "upright_content" => "Generally, the Seven of Swords is about betrayal and deception. When you draw this card, it can mean that you or someone in your life is trying to get away with something. Sometimes, we are forced to be sneaky, hoping we won’t get caught. When we are discovered, we must face the consequences—whether it’s embarrassment, punishment, or worse. This occurs when you need to stand up and do something clever and out of character. Now, there is a danger that secrets might be exposed.

You might want to sneak away from somewhere, indicating that the situation is no longer working as expected. Instead of dealing with it, you choose to sneak away and hope that it goes unnoticed. Perhaps you hope the issue will resolve itself over time, but ignoring it only makes it worse.

The biggest question when looking at the Seven of Swords is whether evasion will solve the problem you are facing. While you may think you’ve escaped, you may find the situation has backed you into a corner, and you are discovered while trying to flee.

In some cases, the Seven of Swords can indicate a desire to go it alone. You might want to explore and discover some things on your own. If you wish to maintain your independence and circumvent collective agreements, this can be an effective approach. The symbolism of the Seven of Swords might encourage you to go down this path; sometimes, innovation comes from rogue geniuses.",
        "reversed_content" => "Depending on the messages from the other cards in the tarot spread, the reversed Seven of Swords can have multiple meanings. It can first indicate the need to change your approach; the strategies you’ve been using aren’t working. While upright, this card can represent cunning victories gained through deceit and trickery, its reversal can represent the more extreme versions of such behavior. Alternatively, it can signify a renewal of conscience. You or someone in your circle may decide to lift the burden of guilt and confess to some manipulation they were involved in. Trust has been broken, but through confession, you may be repairing it. There is a desire here to try things differently, to collaborate rather than act independently.",
        "upright_love" => "Lies and trickery may be filling the Seven of Swords tarot love meaning. It may be important for you to stay cautious now, especially if you have met new friends. Someone in your romantic life may not be honest right now, and at worst, may even be unfaithful. If your intuition is telling you that you’re being deceived, you may need to face this and have an honest discussion. If this is you, consider the long-term consequences of your actions. Even the most well-intentioned lies can lead to significant problems if the root cause is not addressed. If you’re single, you may need to evaluate whether you’re being too suspicious or untrusting of potential lovers, or on the other hand, whether you’re misleading them or exaggerating about yourself.",
        "reversed_love" => "The reversed Seven of Swords tarot love meaning can indicate the end of lies and deceit. Dishonesty always eventually comes to light, and this card suggests that the truth is surfacing. If you have been deceitful, it is more important in the long run to admit and own up to any wrongdoing. Carrying the burden of dishonesty is not easy; it usually comes with the constant anxiety of being discovered. Those seeking love may be more willing to let go of any vanity or stop playing games. In the long run, this can bring you more fulfillment than constantly altering yourself for love.",
        "upright_career" => "There may be some shady characters in your workplace. Lies and deceit can shock you. You might be dealing with colleagues trying to sabotage you with gossip, bad-mouthing you to the boss, or taking credit for your work. In such cases, be cautious of whom you trust; it might come from the least expected sources. Sometimes, this card can also indicate that you need a degree of strategy to complete your projects. You might be the underdog here, while others have more resources or established positions. Tactical work can now be an advantage for you.",
        "reversed_career" => "The truth comes to light now, and if others have been dishonest, their lies may be exposed. Whether you are a victim of this deceit or the one being unfair, guilt and shame may prompt the perpetrator to confess and potentially reconcile. As long as you make amends and face the consequences, forgiveness is possible. Alternatively, situations at work may escalate; sometimes, those at fault are not publicly held accountable. Remember, no matter how disappointing, one’s character will determine their future fate. Sometimes, the Seven of Swords is a simple statement that the strategies and methods you’re using at work aren’t working, and you must change your approach to handling projects.",
        "upright_finances" => "Be careful with your finances now, as there may be some kind of trickery, scams, or theft of your resources. This might be beyond your control, but if you’re trying any get-rich-quick schemes or gambling on improper deals, you might invite these situations. Stay away from things that seem dubious or too good to be true.",
        "reversed_finances" => "Have you been completely honest in your financial dealings? Now might be a good time to pay your taxes and get things in order before you get into deeper trouble. Or, have you been a victim of theft, scams, or fraud? The truth comes to light now, and those who haven’t taken the honorable path may face consequences.",
        "yes_no" => "The Seven of Swords brings a sense of failure and clear pessimism. It suggests the potential for being robbed or not reaching your full potential due to unknown opponents or perhaps your mental procrastination. The answer you are looking for is no.",
        "past" => "It may be time to put some of your projects aside to focus more on pressing issues. The plans you made did not go as smoothly as you hoped.",
        "present" => "The best way to resolve recent conflicts is through diplomacy and wit. Avoid open confrontation.",
        "future" => "Your future success depends on your ability to overcome opposition. The strategy you choose will determine whether you suffer losses or stay ahead. Assessing the opposition will make your actions wiser.",
    ],
    71 =>
    [
        "id" => 72,
        "type_id" => 1,
        "number" => 71,
        "name" => "Eight of Swords",
        "upright_keyword" => "Trapped, Restricted, Victimized, Paralyzed, Helpless, Powerless, Imprisoned",
        "reversed_keyword" => "Freedom, Release, Control, Survivor, Facing Fears, Empowerment, Surrender",
        "astrology" => "",
        "element" => "Air Element",
        "image_key" => "71_Eight_of_Swords",
        "content" => "The Eight of Swords features a woman who is bound and blindfolded. Eight swords are strategically placed around her, restricting her movement as if she is in some sort of trap or prison. However, the builder of this trap seems to have been somewhat lazy or hasty, leaving some open spaces for her to escape. But since the woman is blindfolded and cannot see, she has no way to escape this trap. The barren land around her might signify a lack of creativity, while the gray sky in the background might indicate despair, as she feels there is no hope of getting out of the situation she is facing. If she could remove the blindfold, she would see that she could simply walk away from this situation.",
        "upright_content" => "The general meaning of the Eight of Swords is a feeling of being trapped and victimized. You might feel powerless because, in your mind, you believe changing the situation is beyond your abilities. This feeling of helplessness you have, this sense of not having any agency in your life, is the main factor that is worsening your situation.

By handing over your power to an unknown entity, whether it is fate, God, the government, or something else, you are relinquishing your personal responsibility to influence change. In the journey of your life, you have willingly given up the driver’s seat, and this has not been working out well for you. It is advisable to avoid making any major decisions at this time because your judgment is likely clouded.

The good news is that since these traps are of our own making, we can also leave them if we put our minds to it. It’s just a matter of removing the blindfold, getting beyond the limited perspective we have created for ourselves, seeing the possibilities, and realizing you have your inner power.",
        "reversed_content" => "Getting the Eight of Swords reversed is a good sign, as it indicates growth and self-acceptance, as well as recognition of one’s power and responsibilities—especially after a long struggle with doubt. It means that one is able to make conscious decisions because they are confident in their identity and their ability to influence change within themselves and the world. It is time to free oneself from the past, metaphorically clean out their closet, and make room for new things and new experiences.",
        "upright_love" => "When the Eight of Swords appears in a love tarot reading, you might feel trapped; are you feeling suffocated in a relationship, or are you stuck in a stale partnership that you can’t leave? You might feel like you have no options, but this is often not the case when you look at the bigger picture. We deny ourselves possibilities when we are too afraid to do the hard work of communicating our boundaries or standing up for ourselves. To make a change, you must be the one to take action and take control. Freedom does not come with passivity. If you are single, this card can also indicate that you are too passive in your love life. You may be unwilling to take risks to meet others, hoping that the solution to your romantic life is a person who will lift you up. This rarely yields results.",
        "reversed_love" => "When you take off the blindfold, take a good look at your romantic life. The Eight of Swords tarot love meaning suggests that your perspective is shifting as you gain a clearer and more objective understanding of your relationship. Anxiety can be lifted, and you can now see clearly what needs to be done to feel happier in your romantic life. If you are single, you may find yourself more willing to take your love life into your own hands. The fears and anxieties that prevented you from truly pursuing romance can be lifted.",
        "upright_career" => "Your career is not what you imagined it to be. However, because your work is so tied to your lifestyle, you feel you cannot leave right now. You may feel that you currently have no backup plan or other available positions, jobs, or career paths. If you want to change career paths, it may require some education, but this can be difficult without a stable income. While you may feel like you have no choice, you might just need to think outside the box. Anxiety can make you feel like you have fewer options than you actually do. Seek help, check your budget, turn a hobby into a career, and find a reputable place to get student loans; there may be many options, and you don’t have to continue suffering.",
        "reversed_career" => "It may have taken some time, but you are finally breaking free from the anxiety about your career. Now that things are a bit easier, your vision is no longer blurred by stress or fear. Sometimes, this card can suggest that you get a new job or position that allows you to reach your full potential. However, the reversed Eight of Swords can sometimes indicate the opposite. Instead, you might have lost all hope and accepted the idea that no matter what you do, this is your only path. Each day may feel like a struggle. Remember, you do have the power to change things as long as you open your eyes to all the possibilities and do not let fear get the upper hand. No one will save you but yourself.",
        "upright_finances" => "When it comes to your financial situation, you may feel like things are closing in on you. Anxiety about the state of your bank account can distort your perception of reality. If you want to earn more cash, you may have more tools than you think. Do you have any talents that others would be willing to pay for? Are you a talented writer? A blogger? Start taking action now. There are many ways to improve your situation; you just need a little more creativity.",
        "reversed_finances" => "The reversed Eight of Swords indicates that your anxiety about money has either lessened or intensified. You may finally learn to see all the possibilities available, or your fears and anxieties will continue to worsen. You need to address these fears before they continue to damage your mental health.",
        "yes_no" => "The Eight of Swords is a card that shows obstacles and difficult barriers. It shows fear of failure as well as pure bad luck. The overwhelming tone of frustration and restriction this card carries points to a negative answer to your question.",
        "past" => "Your desire to avoid confrontation stems from your aversion to causing pain to others. This is an admirable trait, but it can prevent you from acting in your own best interests.",
        "present" => "Only your courage and patience can overcome the obstacles before you. The demands of others are locking you in and limiting your growth.",
        "future" => "Do not be afraid to use your own judgment to determine your path. If you ignore your feelings and trust others more than yourself, you will miss important opportunities to change your life.",
    ],
    72 =>
    [
        "id" => 73,
        "type_id" => 1,
        "number" => 72,
        "name" => "Nine of Swords",
        "upright_keyword" => "Fear, Anxiety, Negativity, Breakdown, Despair, Nightmares, Isolation",
        "reversed_keyword" => "Recovery, Coping, Facing Life, Seeking Help, Shame, Guilt, Mental Health Issues",
        "astrology" => "",
        "element" => "Air Element",
        "image_key" => "72_Nine_of_Swords",
        "content" => "The Nine of Swords depicts a woman sitting up in bed with her head in her hands. It seems as though this woman has just woken up from a very bad nightmare. She looks distraught, anxious, and fearful. Nine swords hang on the wall behind her, and her bed is carved with a scene of a person being defeated by another. The blanket is decorated with various astrological symbols and roses. Here, we see the same woman we saw in the Eight of Swords, perhaps now finally released, but still haunted by the nightmares of the pain she endured while she was abandoned and left behind.",
        "upright_content" => "The Nine of Swords is often associated with fear and anxiety, worrying about all the things that trouble you and keep you up at night. Sometimes this card can be linked to trauma, something that you might feel ashamed to talk about with others, and all the psychological responses that come from experiencing that trauma.

When we can never get out of the entrapment depicted in the Eight of Swords, we escalate to the Nine of Swords, where we are tormented by nightmares. A suit of swords, which deals with the mind, logic, intelligence, and communication, somehow gets stuck on the destructive end of the mind, turning inward on itself, breeding and festering. The problems plague you, and you find yourself reciting all the possibilities and all the things that could happen to you. You are haunted by what might be.

There is a sense of repetition in this card, events that previously troubled you, events you managed to suppress or run away from, coming back again. Sharing your grief can at least provide an outlet for your pain and can help you unburden yourself from carrying this alone. Is there someone who can make you feel comfortable?

If this is more about general anxiety rather than trauma, analyze yourself and think about whether this feeling is within your control or if there are other factors contributing to your anxiety. Focus on things you can control and learn to seek help.",
        "reversed_content" => "Encountering the Nine of Swords reversed still signals nightmares, anxiety, and stress similar to its upright version. Some of your past traumas are resurfacing, and you find the grief of unresolved issues overwhelming.

However, here we also see hope, at least the desire to leave this nightmare behind. You must understand that this pain will not stop unless you make an effort to get out of it yourself. You have to work a lot to drag yourself toward release. But just as you have a way out, you must also realize that you might fall deeper into despair. Your task is to avoid this outcome, and if you push forward, you might find yourself out of it, but if you don’t, you may find yourself sinking deeper.",
        "upright_love" => "Anxiety and fear escalate with the Nine of Swords tarot love meaning. Some nightmarish situation may keep you up at night. Often, this card indicates that the fears are not as bad as they are in your mind. You may be struggling with guilt, self-blame, insecurities, trust issues with your partner, or mental health problems. You need to understand for yourself if these feelings are genuinely warranted. Anxiety can lead you to avoid looking at issues and facing them, but if you work to open your eyes, you may find that you can resolve these problems. If you are single, past relationships may be the source of remorse, sadness, and regret that you need to overcome before entering another relationship.",
        "reversed_love" => "You may now be ready to face the truth honestly with the reversed Nine of Swords tarot love meaning. If you have been suffering silently, being honest with your partner can give you the release you need. The stress of bearing anxiety alone is not easy, and if your partner is supportive, they can be there to give you the assurance you need. Through discussion, you may find that what keeps you up at night isn’t as bad as you imagined. If you are single, you may be working on yourself so that you can enter healthy and loving relationships again. The time is approaching, and you may be ready to find love again.",
        "upright_career" => "Stress and anxiety are the biggest features of your current work situation. Sometimes this card can also point to paranoia, as things may not be as bad as you imagine, which can be good news. Regardless of the situation, your job right now may feel incredibly overwhelming, and you may feel burned out if you continue without making any changes. If your stress is caused by external factors, you may need to take concrete action, such as looking for a job elsewhere or changing your career path. If your stress is primarily due to anxiety and mental health issues, you may need to learn how to think more positively. An internal shift may be necessary, and you might benefit from the help of a professional or a trusted friend to get a more objective perspective on everything.",
        "reversed_career" => "The issues you face in the workplace are either starting to teach you lessons or are getting worse. Ideally, you have found that your work situation isn’t as bad as it seemed, and you only needed some changes in your attitude, perspective, or behavior to resolve the issues you’ve been dealing with. Your negativity about work is slowly fading toward better days. Alternatively, your situation may truly be falling apart and worsening. You may be truly exhausted and unable to go to work due to stress. Look at the other cards in the tarot reading to get the whole picture.",
        "upright_finances" => "Financially, you may be under a lot of stress and strain right now. The pain you feel is real, but the Nine of Swords often points to anxiety and worry because of an exaggerated view of the situation rather than looking at it realistically. If this is the case, your panic may stem from your own negative thoughts. Getting advice from someone who can offer you an outsider's perspective on what can be done might be helpful.",
        "reversed_finances" => "Sometimes the reversed Nine of Swords can indicate that your financial stress is either getting better or worse. The other cards in the tarot reading will tell you which one. Either you have learned to see your money situation more realistically, or things are getting worse, and your fears may now be coming true. Seek help, as others can offer useful support now.",
        "yes_no" => "The Nine of Swords symbolizes worry, sadness, and anxiety. This could mean a period of mental anguish, some kind of horrible accident, or many sleepless nights to come. The situation may worsen, and you should be wary of depression and self-harm thoughts. No is the answer provided here.",
        "past" => "You may feel unfulfilled and suffer from feelings of repression and stifled creativity. Do not miss out on the present because of your stubborn resistance to the past.",
        "present" => "The difficulties you are bearing will soon be lifted from you. Your feelings of depression and mental anguish must be dealt with.",
        "future" => "The standards you set for yourself may be unrealistic and lead you toward self-loathing and disappointment. You must be able to forgive yourself and others to move past negative emotions.",
    ],
    73 =>
    [
        "id" => 74,
        "type_id" => 1,
        "number" => 73,
        "name" => "Ten of Swords",
        "upright_keyword" => "Destruction, Failure, Pain, Collapse, Exhaustion, Dead End, Victim, Betrayal",
        "reversed_keyword" => "Survival, Improvement, Healing, Lessons Learned, Despair, Relapse",
        "astrology" => "",
        "element" => "Air Element",
        "image_key" => "73_Ten_of_Swords",
        "content" => "One of the most striking and ominous cards, the Ten of Swords shows a man lying flat on the ground, face down. He is covered with a red cloth from his chest to his legs. Ten long swords are stabbed into his back, and he likely did not see this ending coming. There is a terrifying silence in the air: the sky above him is dark and ominous, indicating fear and negativity associated with death. The water in front of him is still, with no ripples, adding to the eerie silence and finality of the card. Looking to the horizon, the sun is rising in the east despite the darkness, and the weather appears calm. The Ten of Swords seems to suggest that this is the lowest point in life, with nothing worse to come. At least, even in this state, the sun is rising.",
        "upright_content" => "The Ten of Swords indicates some kind of major disaster. It suggests that an extreme force has hit your life, something you may not have anticipated. There is a sense of betrayal here, as the character has been stabbed in the back. It seems to remind us that despite our many efforts, we cannot control everything, and some things are beyond our ability to change. Here, the situation is inevitable.

The story of the Suit of Swords is a powerful metaphor that ends in tragedy. Swords represent intellect, wisdom, and logic, yet we find that the final climax of this suit is the utter and complete failure of the mind. We must recognize that swords are weapons with the potential for great destruction or benefit. The story unfolding from the Ace to the Ten is one of an untrained person using this weapon for the wrong reasons—making many mistakes and then spending a lifetime trying to escape the power they misused.

This person believed the swords were part of him, external, and when they inevitably returned, he suffered once again. His pain is not the usual pain but the pain of fear, anxiety, and the inability to control his environment. After the despair of the Nine of Swords, what can possibly happen next? Are you suffocated by stress? Or did you pick up the last sword and surrender yourself?

The Ten of Swords describes a \"woe is me\" mentality, where you feel helpless. Pause and remember, just like the Death card, the end of something means new beginnings. Let go of what you have lost and focus on the new path ahead, as that is your life's goal. A good example is breaking up with your partner; while it can be very painful, it can also be the start of a new sense of independence.",
        "reversed_content" => "Seeing any version of the Ten of Swords is powerful. Whether reversed or upright, this card marks the end of a failure. There is no way to avoid this tragedy—it has occurred over a long series of events.

However, with the reversal, recognize that you have hit rock bottom, and there is nothing more to give you. What follows is that things can only get better, and the cycle can start anew. But like the Eight and Nine of Swords, this release must be initiated by yourself. Here lies an opportunity to correct what has harmed you, but you must work to climb out. What happened was terrible, but everyone has a responsibility.",
        "upright_love" => "Unfortunately, the Ten of Swords tarot love meaning can indicate the end of a relationship or a period filled with hardship, sadness, and pain. It is likely that the relationship is heading towards some kind of failure, and you may have seen it coming. Sometimes, this card can also suggest betrayal, indicating infidelity. While this period may be extremely difficult, you need to accept it and come to terms with the inevitable end. For singles, you may be dealing with similar lingering feelings from past relationships. Only through acceptance can you truly heal and move on. The worst has already happened, and no matter how it looks, it can only get better from here.",
        "reversed_love" => "You may have many scars left from past romantic trauma, but the reversed Ten of Swords tarot love meaning suggests that you may be on the road to recovery. If you are in a relationship, bonds that previously seemed permanently severed between you and your lover may be healing. In other cases, the relationship may have ended, but you have managed to cope. There may still be feelings of anger and despair, but there is also an acknowledgment of the lessons this heartbreak has taught you. You may be stronger than ever as you recover from this situation.",
        "upright_career" => "In the worst-case scenario, you may now be nearing the end of your current job, as the Ten of Swords signifies endings and severing ties. Sometimes, this card can also suggest that you may be dealing with office politics that are setting you up for failure; perhaps colleagues have been spreading gossip. Alternatively, you may have been pushing yourself too hard, forcing yourself to collapse and take a break. All these may be necessary for your growth; as you move forward and heal from this ordeal, consider what you have learned and know that you will survive.",
        "reversed_career" => "You are starting the path to recovering from past stress. You may have recently changed jobs or left one that made you feel frustrated, angry, and resentful. Whatever happened, the worst is now over. You can breathe a sigh of relief, as what comes next will be easier to handle. However, this card instead might suggest that this stressful moment is getting more severe, and unless you take steps to distance yourself from it, you are on the verge of collapse. You need to weigh whether your mental health is worth the suffering you are going through.",
        "upright_finances" => "Your financial situation might be grim. You may have put money into something that hasn’t panned out, and you may be dealing with the loss now. Ensure that you cut any expenses related to this failed effort and be prudent with your resources. Risk-averse behavior may benefit you now.",
        "reversed_finances" => "You might have been on the brink of financial failure, but you may narrowly miss it. You could also be recovering from a loss of resources, such as bankruptcy or divorce, and you may eventually rebuild a stable foundation again.",
        "yes_no" => "The Ten of Swords shows a sudden end or negative outcome for some effort in your life. It can mean failure, destruction, or death, accompanied by feelings of dejection and being overwhelmed by the weight of the world. Harsh and negative, this card says no.",
        "past" => "By accepting the sometimes painful reality, you will learn that moving forward is the most crucial aspect of recovery.",
        "present" => "Something important is about to end, so be prepared to cope with the aftermath. Nothing in life is permanent.",
        "future" => "Evaluate the direction in which you are heading. Be wary of listening to others' opinions, as they may make you aware of your own truths. Viewing the world with a pragmatic eye will balance your optimism.",
    ],
    74 =>
    [
        "id" => 75,
        "type_id" => 1,
        "number" => 74,
        "name" => "Page of Swords",
        "upright_keyword" => "Curious, Witty, Talkative, Sociable, Inspired, Vigilant, Alert, Quick-thinking",
        "reversed_keyword" => "Scattered, Cynical, Sarcastic, Gossip, Insults, Rude, Lack of Planning",
        "astrology" => "",
        "element" => "Air Element",
        "image_key" => "74_Page_of_Swords",
        "content" => "The Page of Swords card represents a person who exhibits abundant energy in life. The wind blows through the trees, the clouds are scattered, and the youth stands defiantly on a cliff edge. This energetic young person holds a sword in her hand. Her expression is one of determination, perhaps with a hint of disdain, as if ready to pounce at the slightest word.",
        "upright_content" => "Bright and alert, the Page of Swords is someone who seems never to run out of ideas. She is very curious, always asking questions, and has a naturally sharp tongue and wit. Her gift for language also makes her an incredible communicator, and because of her love for ideas, you may find her constantly engaged in some intense debate.

She seems to thrive on a nearly nervous energy, as if she has too much to say and the wheels in her mind are constantly turning. As a bringer of news, she may come bearing news related to lawsuits, gossip, legal matters, or agreements. Alternatively, you may find yourself needing to use her energy to stay alert, keep your eyes open, and remain sharp and vigilant.

This card may indicate that you are very eager to execute ideas you’ve had for a while or a project you’ve recently started planning. You are passionate about it and can't wait to share your progress with others. Time seems to stand still compared to your burning heart. It’s time to speak up. When the Page of Swords appears in a tarot reading, it signifies communication and sharing ideas. Whether it’s your ideas or those of others, as long as they are constructive, it’s time to open up and talk about them.",
        "reversed_content" => "When the Page of Swords is reversed, all her negative traits are exposed, and she can become almost dangerous. Her natural sharp and alert mind may be used for deceit and manipulation. The sword she wields can be used to create pain, and her natural gift for language turns into a weapon. She may lack the understanding or maturity to realize the pain she causes, feeling an impulse to lash out. On the other hand, this Page of Swords could be someone who talks but has little substance behind their words. Be careful to show strength and action behind your words, as you may damage your reputation.",
        "upright_love" => "As a person, the Page of Swords tarot love meaning reflects a curious intellectual whose playful, nervous energy can border on anxiety. However, in relationships, they may fear emotional confrontation, possibly avoiding it altogether if faced with it. As an emotional state or quality, the Page of Swords tarot love meaning can signify a more intellectual relationship where lovers enjoy exciting discussions but may be cautious about emotional intimacy. A partner may feel their emotional needs are not being met. Sometimes, it can also indicate small arguments with your partner, which, if not handled properly, can escalate into larger conflicts.",
        "reversed_love" => "The person represented by the reversed Page of Swords tarot love meaning may lack empathy, sensitivity, or depth and may enjoy arguing or being defensive. They may take pleasure in being 'right' but at the expense of harmony and concern for others' feelings. This card can also indicate communication failures between partners, potentially even paranoia due to misunderstandings. For your relationship to thrive, partners must learn to tolerate differing viewpoints, be flexible, and seek cooperation instead of creating conflict.",
        "upright_career" => "In terms of your career, you might be a clever, innovative, and ambitious person. You probably have a lot of energy and many ideas to contribute to your career. Since this card is the Page of Swords, it does point to some kind of apprenticeship or new experience, indicating that you might be in training, school, or starting a new job or career path. With ambition comes many goals, and you may be taking extra education or gaining experience to achieve these goals.",
        "reversed_career" => "You have a lot of energy and curiosity, but right now, it's not focused on anything. Without an outlet, you seem unable to decide what you truly want to do for your future. When you feel bored, you might jump from one job to the next, thinking it isn't right for you. Usually, to gain the full depth and experience of working somewhere, you need to invest a lot of time. Sometimes, this card can also indicate many great ideas but zero follow-through. Without action, there will never be results. Get to work! This card can also point to office gossip or a rude person who hurts others with words.",
        "upright_finances" => "You might have great ideas about how to expand your finances or make more money, but whatever ideas you have may be in the very early stages. If possible, try to learn from someone more experienced. You might also be very curious about finances at this time; it’s a complex world, and the more you know about it, the better you can maximize your earnings. Spend some time researching retirement fund options, stocks, bonds, and other financial products, or find a financial planner who can help guide you.",
        "reversed_finances" => "Your ideas about making the most of your money may be unrealistic, or they might all be talk without plans for action. It could also be that all the research you've done to improve your financial situation hasn’t really been effective. You might be overwhelmed by what to do next instead of just doing something. What are you overanalyzing?",
        "yes_no" => "The Page of Swords is an intelligent, logical, and vigilant youth who brings some sort of official change news. While these changes may prove challenging, this card showcases mental clarity and inner demons settling and being driven out of your life. The most likely answer here is yes.",
        "past" => "The abilities lurking inside you are being brought to the surface. Past events are leading you to take positive action, and the time to carve your own path is near.",
        "present" => "Unexpected news is on the way. To benefit from the upcoming changes, you must rely on your intelligence and adaptability.",
        "future" => "A strong desire for change is making you restless and agitated. Seeking true independence of mind will give you a clearer understanding of your and others' motives.",
    ],
    75 =>
    [
        "id" => 76,
        "type_id" => 1,
        "number" => 75,
        "name" => "Knight of Swords",
        "upright_keyword" => "Confident, Direct, Impatient, Intelligent, Bold, Focused, Perfectionist, Ambitious",
        "reversed_keyword" => "Rude, Tactless, Harsh, Bullying, Aggressive, Malicious, Ruthless, Arrogant",
        "astrology" => "",
        "element" => "Air Element",
        "image_key" => "75_Knight_of_Swords",
        "content" => "We see this knight is truly in a hurry! The Knight of Swords card depicts a young man in armor riding a strong white horse into battle. The horse's white color references the overall purity and intellectual energy that motivates this young rider. The sky behind him is cloudy, and the trees are being blown wildly by the wind. The horse's harness is also decorated with images of birds and butterflies. The knight's cloak is also adorned with the same birds.",
        "upright_content" => "When we are entirely consumed by a particular idea and have a strong desire to manifest it, we are often blinded by the actual desire to realize it, so much so that we do not notice the difficulties we might encounter or the consequences of our actions. The Knight of Swords is a powerful figure, full of life and energy. This needs to be balanced with compassion and responsibility to achieve proper and practical realization.

Once the knight sets out towards his goal, absolutely nothing can stop him. He sees neither obstacles nor cares about any upcoming challenges. He is full of ambition, strength, and determination to succeed no matter what. However, this determination can also cause him to overlook the potential consequences of his actions on others on his path to success. He may rush into dangerous territory without preparation or foresight, which could put him at great risk.",
        "reversed_content" => "The reversed Knight of Swords suggests incredible impatience and impulsiveness, filled with energy but without direction. This knight is full of vigor but lacks focus, which often leads to hasty decisions and dragging others down with them.

Their thoughts are often scattered, lacking any practical organization or logic. They are likely disorganized and unprepared for what they truly want to achieve. The reversed Knight of Swords indicates you have a long way to go to gain valuable life experience and overcome adversity along the way. These are things to consider.",
        "upright_love" => "The Knight of Swords finds establishing romantic relationships particularly difficult. This person needs a lot of intellectual stimulation and quickly gets bored without it. This person may also struggle with becoming too emotionally close to another. If this does not represent someone in your love life, the Knight of Swords tarot love meaning can point to a situation where you need to muster up the courage to make a quick decision and take action. This can appear as committing to a pursuer, making a romantic proposal, or even winning back a lover about to leave the relationship.",
        "reversed_love" => "In tarot love readings, beware of the reversed Knight of Swords, as this person can be aggressive, controlling, or even a bully. Certain they are right, they force their way on others regardless of the harm it causes. They may lack empathy or understanding and enjoy arguments, sometimes not just for debate but to intimidate and pressure others. If this does not represent a person, the reversed Knight of Swords love tarot meaning can simply indicate intense arguments, conflicts, and disagreements. If these quarrels become routine, it may be best for both of you to part ways.",
        "upright_career" => "When you combine great ambition with determination and almost singular focus, you are sure to get what you want. Regarding your work, nothing scares you. You are likely very good at what you do, and you will complete your projects with almost ruthless efficiency. Sometimes this may scare others, but this may not be a big issue for you. If this does not represent you now, you may be asked to harness this knight's energy to pursue what you want in your career. If your goal is a promotion, a new job, or an exciting project, go for it! Make a bold move to get noticed. Be decisive and courageous like the Knight of Swords, and you will find success.",
        "reversed_career" => "The upright Knight of Swords’ ambition and drive are admirable, but reversed, the knight can be cold or malicious. Be careful not to hurt others while achieving your career goals; otherwise, you may become known for being ruthless, uncaring about who gets hurt as long as you get what you want. Sometimes, others may also find you arrogant, aggressive about your ideas. Do you always need things to go your way? Do you dismiss or reject others' ideas without explanation? While your approach may yield results, consider what will happen in the long run when no one supports you. Try to be more mindful of your words and how you communicate.",
        "upright_finances" => "You may be very focused on your finances right now. Perhaps you are concerned with saving for something big, or you want to optimize what you are saving. You may put a lot of energy into this. With enough focus and determination, you will be able to achieve your goals.",
        "reversed_finances" => "Are you so focused on money that you sometimes cross the line of acceptable behavior? The reversed Knight of Swords is a determined person who will go to any lengths to make money. This can sometimes point to actions that may be illegal. If this does not represent you, someone in your life might be playing this role, so be careful who you let into your circle.",
        "yes_no" => "The Knight of Swords is domineering and destructive. He represents controlling a project or situation in a ruthless manner. This card foretells unexpected loss, conflict, and the need to establish your ideas and beliefs. The negative tone of this card suggests the answer is no.",
        "past" => "Your inner desire for change has been growing stronger. Plan your future goals, but keep them to yourself.",
        "present" => "You have caught the attention of a young upstart. Issues will be resolved with the help you receive, but be prepared to deal with new problems.",
        "future" => "The compass of your life may suddenly be realigned by a sharp change in perspective. Seek encouragement from your friends and loved ones.",
    ],
    76 =>
    [
        "id" => 77,
        "type_id" => 1,
        "number" => 76,
        "name" => "Queen of Swords",
        "upright_keyword" => "Honest, Independent, Principled, Fair, Constructive Criticism, Objective, Insightful",
        "reversed_keyword" => "Pessimistic, Malicious, Manipulative, Harsh, Bitter, Spiteful, Cruel, Deceptive, Unforgiving",
        "astrology" => "",
        "element" => "Air Element",
        "image_key" => "76_Queen_of_Swords",
        "content" => "The Queen of Swords sits on her throne with a stern look on her face—gazing into the distance. As the queen of the element of air represented by the swords, her position in the clouds signifies that no one can deceive or fool her. The sword in her right hand points to the sky, while her left hand reaches out as if in offering. The Queen of Swords gives us the gift of judging everyday decisions and adeptly gathering knowledge from others.",
        "upright_content" => "The Queen of Swords embodies the archetype of an older, wiser female figure of intellect. She can be seen as the most masculine of all the queens and may appear very stern and aloof. This card signifies the importance of making judgments without relying on emotion. The Queen of Swords calls you to look at all the facts before making a decision. She indeed has compassion, which is why her hand is extended in offering, but she wants to connect with people through a rational understanding.

This card also implies that you need to be independent in your judgment. You must rely on impartial intelligence, which allows you to consider other viewpoints and weigh your decisions carefully. In these situations, compassion and empathy can distract you from the task, so you need to work to maintain a strong objective perspective while avoiding getting entangled in emotions.

It can also relate to how we communicate with others. This queen has the ability to tell people exactly how it is. This enables her to express her views clearly and avoids any confusion about what she says. Above all, truth is important to her, so she feels no need to soften her comments, thoughts, or opinions. She expects others to be honest with her as well, which means you need to be clear about what you say, even if it might hurt.",
        "reversed_content" => "The reversed Queen of Swords indicates that you may be thinking with your heart too much and are overly emotional about the current situation. You need to start thinking more objectively, as your emotions may be leading you astray. Take time to observe the situation with various facts and see it clearly with your mind to understand what is actually happening. Only then can you decide what to do next.

When reversed, the Queen of Swords can also be very bitter, cold, or resentful. You may have started isolating yourself for various reasons, but the outside world might view this the wrong way. You may need to offer some explanations, especially if your relationships have become strained due to your desire for solitude.",
        "upright_love" => "The Queen of Swords can represent a person who is solitary; she is very selective about the people around her. Her wisdom is sharp and keen, and her determination can be quite intimidating to those who do not know her. However, beneath her shell, she can be loving and loyal, though she may still prefer to avoid grand displays of romance. If this is someone you want to win over, you need patience, as this queen does not let her guard down easily. If this card does not represent a person, the Queen of Swords tarot love meaning can suggest a time when you seek independence and self-sufficiency while looking for a partner. This queen values her space and identity. You may need to make some adjustments to create clarity and boundaries in your relationships.",
        "reversed_love" => "The reversed Queen of Swords represents a bitter, controlling, overly critical, and possibly downright cruel person. This person could represent you, your partner, or someone outside the relationship trying to interfere. Sometimes, this bitterness could be a result of trauma, so if your partner exhibits these traits, it might be unresolved trauma surfacing. If you are single, you might have just gone through a breakup, leaving you feeling vengeful and unforgiving. These beliefs can be toxic; learn to use your experience to overcome them rather than let them consume you.",
        "upright_career" => "The Queen of Swords can point to a senior person or yourself in a career tarot reading. This person is intelligent, honest, and can be a source of constructive criticism. They can provide great advice on how to proceed with your career. If this card represents you, you might be in a period of life where you gain respect from colleagues. You can effectively communicate your sharp ideas and combine them with strong empathy. Because of your integrity and fairness, you might have a high reputation.",
        "reversed_career" => "Is there someone at work who holds a grudge against you? The reversed Queen of Swords can indicate an overly critical person who uses their words and intelligence to cause pain. She might express herself harshly and sometimes downright cruelly. If this is you, you might need to learn how to communicate better. Can you be honest while also considering others' feelings? Can you address your concerns about a project without blaming others? This can actually benefit you by helping others digest your ideas better. Avoid being overly negative.",
        "upright_finances" => "When dealing with financial matters, you need to act thoughtfully, logically, and wisely now. There is a clear balance between the heart and the mind. If you are asked to help with someone's finances, consider things fairly from your and their perspectives. This usually means being able to help but with boundaries. Set up contracts or payment plans; establish some rules. Stay sharp and pay attention to all the details. Make sure you understand your financial situation clearly.",
        "reversed_finances" => "If your communication regarding finances has been poor, you might now be dealing with the consequences. Not being clear about your financial status might be the culprit. Perhaps you lent money to a friend or family member who hasn't paid it back, or you have given or spent more than you can actually afford. You need to be more explicit about your boundaries and limits next time.",
        "yes_no" => "The Queen of Swords is an analytical, independent problem-solver. She brings mental clarity or ends some trouble in your life, but not without painful loss or separation. She is resilient and shrewd, but she does not indicate a positive or negative outcome. Maybe is the answer here.",
        "past" => "Your strict idealization of perfection may have caused you stress or pain. Continuing to hold onto this ideal, you will find it unattainable.",
        "present" => "Expect advice from a witty, wise elder, possibly a woman. It is possible to accept help from friends while maintaining independence.",
        "future" => "Don't focus too much on your goals, as this might limit your ability to achieve them. Rely on your powerful intellect to illuminate the bigger picture.",
    ],
    77 =>
    [
        "id" => 78,
        "type_id" => 1,
        "number" => 77,
        "name" => "King of Swords",
        "upright_keyword" => "Rational, Authoritative, Disciplined, Integrity, Moral, Serious, High Standards, Strict",
        "reversed_keyword" => "Irrational, Dictatorial, Oppressive, Inhumane, Controlling, Ruthless, Unforgiving, Dishonest",
        "astrology" => "",
        "element" => "Air Element",
        "image_key" => "77_King_of_Swords",
        "content" => "The King of Swords tarot card depicts a king seated on his throne, holding an upward-pointing double-edged sword in his right hand. The King of Swords exudes the power of intellect, clear thinking, truth, and authority. He understands that power carries great responsibility.

The blue tunic the king wears symbolizes his spiritual understanding. The butterflies on the back of his throne signify transformation.",
        "upright_content" => "The appearance of the King of Swords in a tarot reading suggests that you should remain objective in your current situation; you must stick to the facts to establish the truth. The King of Swords and his intellect mean you need to use your intelligence to articulate your ideas and achieve your goals. Besides your experience and education, you should be sharp and observant, delving into the issues you face.

The meaning of the King of Swords also implies that you need to maintain seriousness in your role while ensuring you keep a clear mind at all times. When judging a situation, you need to consider all possible consequences to make a proper judgment. You need to exclude your emotions from your decisions to stay rational. The King of Swords suggests you should take the time to reason with others and be straightforward with your observations.

In your personal life, the King of Swords urges you to navigate the road ahead using your intellect and logic. You will need to confront the issues before you and make clear-headed decisions. The King of Swords implies you should be able to view any situation with complete impartiality and make decisions accordingly. He can also be an indicator of high moral standards, as demonstrated by the King of Swords.",
        "reversed_content" => "The reversed King of Swords indicates a tendency towards authoritarian, abusive, and manipulative habits. It can signify the misuse of one’s mental power, motivation, and authority. This is an example of persuasion and manipulation to achieve selfish desires. The reversed King of Swords may also imply that you are showing off your intellectual level with big words when discussing ordinary topics. Another interpretation is that you could be a loose cannon, especially with outbursts of anger and impulsiveness.",
        "upright_love" => "The King of Swords is a calm, controlled, and ambitious individual. While they do have emotions, they can be very restrained. Instead, they rely on their intellect and logic. In romance, they treat their relationships in a moral and respectful manner. They may not be very romantic and are likely to express themselves very directly. If this card does not represent a person, the King of Swords tarot love meaning can simply indicate high standards for a romantic partner, especially intellectually. You and your partner may also be full of challenges at this time, pushing each other to be the best you can be.",
        "reversed_love" => "The reversed King of Swords can use their sharp intellect for selfish means. The wisdom and morals that guide their actions with integrity are gone, replaced by terrible selfishness and even abuse. This person also lets their emotions run uncontrolled, quickly switching from cold detachment to rage. As a characteristic or quality, the reversed King of Swords tarot love meaning can indicate that you may be exhibiting these qualities in your relationships. You may need to show more restraint and forgiveness towards your partner, or you may risk losing them. When it comes to potential relationships, this card can also suggest low standards; try not to be swept away by emotions but use some logic to evaluate if someone is right for you.",
        "upright_career" => "The King of Swords is a person with high standards, which they reflect in their work. While they may appear strict, this person does so to ensure you achieve your career goals. They challenge you to be your best while staying true to your principles. If you choose to heed their advice, you can make significant progress in your career. Alternatively, this person may represent you or a point in your career path. Set high standards for yourself and others, and push yourself to be your best. Some routines and processes can also be beneficial to your work now.",
        "reversed_career" => "Your workplace might not be a very pleasant place right now. The reversed King of Swords suggests that someone in your work environment is authoritative, aggressive, and power-hungry. They may be in a position of power and misuse that power for all the wrong reasons. If this doesn’t represent someone in your workplace, you might need to take a hard look at your own behavior. You may find it easier to lose your temper and not act as ethically or logically as you usually would. You might also lack self-discipline; not only losing your temper but also losing motivation and energy.",
        "upright_finances" => "The King of Swords will urge you to challenge yourself and be very disciplined with your finances. Are you really doing your best to save for that nice car you want in the future? All good things come with sacrifice, and your financial goals are no exception. Look at your finances logically; do your research before making any significant financial decisions.",
        "reversed_finances" => "You may not have been very disciplined with your finances recently, overspending, buying many useless things, or investing in things that won’t bring you returns. This may leave you feeling a bit desperate, but make sure you don’t try to make up for losses through lazy or devious means.",
        "yes_no" => "The King of Swords is a confident, professional decision-maker with high intelligence and leadership skills. He represents a significant decision on the horizon that requires control and boundary setting while making a firm commitment to your goals. This card does not provide a clear answer, and maybe is the best at most.",
        "past" => "Your strength lies in your wisdom. Looking ahead and considering authority will guide you to turn the good ideas you have gathered into reality.",
        "present" => "An authoritative figure may help you make plans.",
        "future" => "With your confidence, determination, and integrity, a successful life can be achieved.",
    ],
];
